#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:632
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Tip: The season of the year changes every time you finish a battle. "
#| "Winter battles will have longer nights and shorter days, often with more "
#| "snow and ice. Summer battles are the opposite.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Right now it’s winter. You can see the current season in the top-right-"
#| "hand corner."
msgid ""
"Tip: The season of the year changes every time you finish a battle. Winter "
"battles will have longer nights and shorter days, often with more snow and "
"ice. Summer battles are the opposite."
msgstr ""
"Consello: A estación do ano cambia cada vez que rematas unha batalla. As "
"batallas de inverno terán noites máis longas e días máis curtos, a miúdo con "
"máis neve e xeo. As batallas de verán son o contrario. Agora mesmo é "
"inverno. Podes ver a estación actual na esquina superior dereita."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:634
msgid ""
"Right now it’s winter. You can see the current season in the top-right-hand "
"corner."
msgstr ""
"Agora mesmo é inverno. Podes ver a estación actual na esquina superior "
"dereita."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:647
msgid ""
"Tip: Konrad only has time to fight a limited number of scenarios before the "
"final battle. If you want to (non-canonically) remove that limit, there’s a "
"secret in the Great Ocean that can help."
msgstr ""
"Consello: Konrad só ten tempo para loitar nun número limitado de escenarios "
"antes da batalla final. Se queres eliminar (non canonicamente) ese límite, "
"hai un segredo no Gran Océano que pode axudar."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:660
msgid ""
"Tip: Konrad will start most battle scenarios with 75 gold, plus any "
"carryover from your last battle."
msgstr ""
"Consello: Konrad comezará a maioría dos escenarios de batalla con 75 ouro, "
"máis calquera sobrantre do teu último combate."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:673
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Tip: This campaign’s difficulty setting affects both the strength of your "
#| "enemies and the number of scenarios you can play before the final "
#| "battle.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "However, if you adjust the difficulty mid-campaign, the number of "
#| "scenarios won’t change (or else you might end up stuck in an unplayable "
#| "area)."
msgid ""
"Tip: This campaign’s difficulty setting affects both the strength of your "
"enemies and the number of scenarios you can play before the final battle."
msgstr ""
"Consello: A configuración de dificultade desta campaña afecta tanto á forza "
"dos teus inimigos como ao número de escenarios que podes xogar antes da "
"batalla final. Con todo, se axustas a dificultade a medio da campaña, o "
"número de escenarios non cambiará (senón poderías quedar atrapado nunha zona "
"inxugable)."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:675
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Tip: This campaign’s difficulty setting affects both the strength of your "
#| "enemies and the number of scenarios you can play before the final "
#| "battle.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "However, if you adjust the difficulty mid-campaign, the number of "
#| "scenarios won’t change (or else you might end up stuck in an unplayable "
#| "area)."
msgid ""
"However, if you adjust the difficulty mid-campaign, the number of scenarios "
"won’t change (or else you might end up stuck in an unplayable area)."
msgstr ""
"Consello: A configuración de dificultade desta campaña afecta tanto á forza "
"dos teus inimigos como ao número de escenarios que podes xogar antes da "
"batalla final. Con todo, se axustas a dificultade a medio da campaña, o "
"número de escenarios non cambiará (senón poderías quedar atrapado nunha zona "
"inxugable)."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:688
msgid ""
"Tip: This campaign has many secrets and special interactions. Some are "
"hinted at in the achievements list (viewable on the Wesnoth main menu)."
msgstr ""
"Consello: Esta campaña ten moitos segredos e interaccións especiais. Algúns "
"deles están insinuados na lista de logros (visible no menú principal de "
"Wesnoth)."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:701
msgid ""
"Tip: Most of Konrad’s optional companions (Moremirmu, Haldiel, etc) have "
"special events on the overworld or in certain scenarios, ranging from easter "
"eggs to major power-ups. Companion dialogue and backstories may hint as to "
"where these events can be found."
msgstr ""
"onsello: A maioría dos compañeiros opcionais de Konrad (Moremirmu, Haldiel, "
"etc.) teñen eventos especiais no mapa do mundo ou en certos escenarios, que "
"van desde curiosidades ata grandes melloras de poder. Os diálogos e "
"historias dos compañeiros poden dar pistas sobre onde atopalos."

#. [then]
#. [else]
#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:738
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:807
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:856
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:964
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1318
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:230
msgid "Familiar"
msgstr "Familiar"

#. [message]: speaker=familiar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:745
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:863
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1324
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:237
msgid "Kraa! Kraa! Kraa!"
msgstr "Kraa! Kraa! Kraa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:749
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I’m afraid so, young prince. Blackwing brings ill tidings, for my "
#| "suspicions have been confirmed — Asheviere lays siege to Elensefar, "
#| "breaking the century-old treaty between Wesnoth and the Elense city-state."
msgid ""
"What’s this? Blackwing brings ill tidings — men of the Crown lay siege to "
"Elensefar! Asheviere has broken the century-old treaty between Wesnoth and "
"the Elense city-state."
msgstr ""
"Temo que si, mozo príncipe. Ás Negras trae malas novas, porque as miñas "
"sospeitas foron confirmadas: Asheviere asedia Elensefar, rompendo o tratado "
"centenario entre Wesnoth e a cidade-estado de Elense."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:753
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Lord Maddock may not be the most reliable ally, but he and his army have "
#| "been instrumental in maintaining the relative freedom of the western "
#| "reaches. If Elensefar should fall, we would lose a great ally in our "
#| "quest for a victory against Asheviere. I must depart at once to aid in "
#| "the defense!"
msgid ""
"Lord Maddock may not be the most reliable ally, but he and his coin have "
"been instrumental in maintaining the relative freedom of the western "
"reaches. If Elensefar should fall, we would lose a great ally in our quest "
"against Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Pode que Lord Maddock non sexa o aliado máis fiable, pero el e o seu "
"exército foron fundamentais para manter a relativa liberdade dos confins "
"occidentais. Se Elensefar caese, perderíamos un gran aliado na nosa procura "
"da vitoria contra Asheviere. Debo partir de inmediato para axudar na defensa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:757
msgid "Then we must go to his aid at once!"
msgstr "Entón debemos ir na súa axuda de inmediato!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:761
msgid ""
"No, young prince. That battle would be far too dangerous for you. I could "
"aid Elensefar, but to do so would mean leaving you to face the Continent "
"alone..."
msgstr ""
"Non, novo príncipe. Esa batalla sería demasiado perigosa para ti. Podería "
"axudar a Elensefar, pero facelo significaría deixarte afrontar o Continente "
"só..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. Konrad has something to day, and Delfador is promting him.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:769
msgid "What is it, Konrad?"
msgstr "Que ocorre, Konrad?"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:782
msgid "Ask Delfador to stay with Konrad for one more battle"
msgstr "Pedir a Delfador que quede con Konrad unha batalla máis"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:786
msgid ""
"Yes, you’re quite right. We shall fight one more battle together, and secure "
"allies for you before I depart."
msgstr ""
"Si, tes toda a razón. Loitaremos unha batalla máis xuntos e aseguraremos "
"aliados para ti antes de que marche."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:798
msgid "Ask Delfador to leave (gain Delfador’s raven as a loyal companion)"
msgstr ""
"Pedir a Delfador que marche (gaña o corvo de Delfador como compañeiro leal)"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:802
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Not alone, Konrad. Though I am loathe to see us part ways so soon, I can "
#| "at least leave with you my familiar — the venerable Blackwing. Care for "
#| "him well."
msgid ""
"Very well. You will have to do without my elementals, but I can at least "
"leave with you my familiar — the venerable Blackwing. Care for him well."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Aínda que me sinto desgustado por vernos separar tan pronto, "
"polo menos podo deixarche o meu familiar: o venerable Á Negra. Cóidao ben."

#. [message]: speaker=familiar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:814
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:931
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:970
msgid "Cooo..."
msgstr "Couu..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:842
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Well done, Konrad! I couldn’t be prouder of your wisdom in battle; you’re "
#| "truly well on your way to becoming the prince you were always meant to be."
msgid ""
"Well done, Konrad! I couldn’t be more proud of your wisdom in battle; you’re "
"truly well on your way to becoming the prince you were always meant to be."
msgstr ""
"Ben feito, Konrad! Non podería estar máis orgulloso da túa sabedoría en "
"combate; estás realmente no bo camiño para converterte no príncipe que "
"sempre estabas destinado a ser."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:853
msgid ""
"I had a good teacher! And now that we’ve helped the people here, all kinds "
"of new places are suddenly open to us. Where shall we go to next?"
msgstr ""
"Tiven un bo mestre! E agora que axudamos á xente de aquí, de súpeto ábrense "
"para nós todo tipo de lugares novos. Onde iremos a continuación?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:867
msgid "What’s going on, Delfador? Is something the matter?"
msgstr "Que pasa, Delfador? Tes algún problema?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:871
msgid ""
"I’m afraid so, young prince. Blackwing brings ill tidings, for my suspicions "
"have been confirmed — Asheviere lays siege to Elensefar, breaking the "
"century-old treaty between Wesnoth and the Elense city-state."
msgstr ""
"Temo que si, mozo príncipe. Ás Negras trae malas novas, porque as miñas "
"sospeitas foron confirmadas: Asheviere asedia Elensefar, rompendo o tratado "
"centenario entre Wesnoth e a cidade-estado de Elense."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:875
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Lord Maddock may not be the most reliable ally, but he and his army have "
#| "been instrumental in maintaining the relative freedom of the western "
#| "reaches. If Elensefar should fall, we would lose a great ally in our "
#| "quest for a victory against Asheviere. I must depart at once to aid in "
#| "the defense!"
msgid ""
"Lord Maddock may not be the most reliable ally, but he and his coin have "
"been instrumental in maintaining the relative freedom of the western "
"reaches. If Elensefar should fall, we would lose a great ally in our quest "
"against Asheviere. I must depart at once to aid in the defense!"
msgstr ""
"Pode que Lord Maddock non sexa o aliado máis fiable, pero el e o seu "
"exército foron fundamentais para manter a relativa liberdade dos confins "
"occidentais. Se Elensefar caese, perderíamos un gran aliado na nosa procura "
"da vitoria contra Asheviere. Debo partir de inmediato para axudar na defensa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:879
msgid ""
"Then I am to journey on alone? I fear my quest will be difficult without "
"your guidance and magic... but what must be must be."
msgstr ""
"Entón teño que viaxar só? Temo que a miña procura será difícil sen a túa "
"guía e a túa maxia... pero o que ten que ser, ten que ser."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:890
msgid ""
"Not alone, Konrad. Already you have found new allies — the gentle elves of "
"the Aethenwood — and you will doubtless find many more among the other "
"denizens of the Great Continent."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Xa atopaches novos aliados (os xentís elfos do Bosque de "
"Aethen) e sen dúbida atoparás moitos máis entre os outros habitantes do Gran "
"Continente."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:898
msgid ""
"Not alone, Konrad. Already you have found new allies — the royal knights of "
"Blackwater Port — and you will doubtless find many more among the other "
"denizens of the Great Continent."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Xa atopaches novos aliados (os cabaleiros reais de Porto de "
"Augas Negras) e sen dúbida atoparás moitos máis entre os outros habitantes "
"do Gran Continente."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:907
msgid ""
"Not alone, Konrad. Already you have found new allies — the noble Bay of "
"Pearls merfolk — and you will doubtless find many more among the other "
"denizens of the Great Continent."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Xa atopaches novos aliados (os nobres sirénidos da Baía das "
"Pérolas) e sen dúbida atoparás moitos máis entre os outros habitantes do "
"Gran Continente."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:914
msgid ""
"Not alone, Konrad. Already you have gained new allies, and you will "
"doubtless find many more among the other denizens of the Great Continent."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Xa gañaches novos aliados e, sen dúbida, atoparás moitos "
"máis entre os outros habitantes do Gran Continente."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:922
msgid ""
"I am afraid so. I had rather hoped we would have already gained new allies "
"for you to recruit — perhaps elves, horsemen, or merfolk — but it was not to "
"be."
msgstr ""
"Temo que así é. Tiña a esperanza de que xa conseguiramos novos aliados para "
"que puideses recrutar — quizais elfos, xinetes ou sirenios — pero non puido "
"ser."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:926
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Not alone, Konrad. Though I am loathe to see us part ways so soon, I can "
#| "at least leave with you my familiar — the venerable Blackwing. Care for "
#| "him well."
msgid ""
"You will have to do without my elementals, but I can at least leave with you "
"my familiar — the venerable Blackwing. Care for him well."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Aínda que me sinto desgustado por vernos separar tan pronto, "
"polo menos podo deixarche o meu familiar: o venerable Á Negra. Cóidao ben."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:947
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I had a good teacher! And now that we’ve helped the people here, all "
#| "kinds of new places are suddenly open to us. Where shall we go to next?"
msgid ""
"I had a good teacher! And now that I’ve gained new allies, you are free to "
"travel to Elensefar and aid in its defense."
msgstr ""
"Tiven un bo mestre! E agora que axudamos á xente de aquí, de súpeto ábrense "
"para nós todo tipo de lugares novos. Onde iremos a continuación?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:951
msgid ""
"As we agreed. I am loathe to leave you without my magic, but right now Lord "
"Maddock needs it more."
msgstr ""
"Como acordamos. Dóeme deixarte sen a miña maxia, pero agora mesmo o señor "
"Maddock necesítaa máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:957
msgid ""
"I had a good teacher! But although we’ve fought a battle, I still have no "
"allies for me to recruit. Must you still leave?"
msgstr ""
"Tiven un bo mestre! Pero, aínda que loitamos unha batalla, sigo sen ter "
"aliados que poida recrutar. Debes marchar igualmente?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:961
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Not alone, Konrad. Though I am loathe to see us part ways so soon, I can "
#| "at least leave with you my familiar — the venerable Blackwing. Care for "
#| "him well."
msgid ""
"I am afraid so. You will have to do without my elementals, but I can at "
"least leave with you my familiar — the venerable Blackwing. Care for him "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Non só, Konrad. Aínda que me sinto desgustado por vernos separar tan pronto, "
"polo menos podo deixarche o meu familiar: o venerable Á Negra. Cóidao ben."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:988
msgid ""
"Without any soldiers to recruit, I must advise selecting an easy battle for "
"your next fight. Perhaps one of the islands will be appropriate."
msgstr ""
"Sen soldados que recrutar, debo recomendarche escoller unha batalla doada "
"para o teu seguinte combate. Quizais unha das illas sexa apropiada."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:994
msgid ""
"And as for my guidance, well... I raised you as best I was able, and did my "
"utmost to prepare you for the difficult quest that lies ahead. You have "
"trusted me, and for that I am grateful."
msgstr ""
"E en canto á miña guía, ben... crieite o mellor que puiden e fixen todo o "
"posible para prepararte para a difícil misión que tes por diante. Confiaches "
"en min e por iso estou agradecido."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:998
msgid ""
"Now the time has come for me to put my trust in you. My trust that you can "
"succeed where I failed; my trust that you shall yet restore the throne of "
"Wesnoth! I know that you will make me proud."
msgstr ""
"Agora chegou o momento de confiar en ti. Confío en que podes ter éxito onde "
"eu fracasei; confío en que restaurarás o trono de Wesnoth! Sei que me farás "
"sentir orgulloso."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1002
msgid "Farewell, my young friend. Until we meet again."
msgstr "Adeus, meu mozo amigo. Ata que nos volvamos ver."

#. [event]
#. [then]
#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [unit]: id=Delfador, type=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1013
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1220
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1269
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:225
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:247
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/unified_characters.cfg:467
msgid "Delfador"
msgstr "Delfador"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1038
msgid "It’s up to me then. I won’t let Wesnoth down."
msgstr "Entón depende de min. Non defraudarei a Wesnoth."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1081
msgid "Well?"
msgstr "Ben?"

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1085
msgid ""
"Battle plan approved, Your Highness. And your mother adds — remember what "
"happened to Eldred."
msgstr ""
"Plan de batalla aprobado, Alteza. E a súa nai engade: lembre o que lle "
"aconteceu a Eldred."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1089
msgid ""
"I know the risks, but Elensefar has dragged on for far too long already. "
"Wizard or no, we have to finish things before we overextend."
msgstr ""
"Coñezo os riscos, pero Elensefar xa leva demasiado tempo alongado. Mago ou "
"non, temos que rematar as cousas antes de esgotarnos."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1119
msgid "Well done, Konrad. We must now consider how to proceed."
msgstr "Ben feito, Konrad. Agora debemos considerar como proceder."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1123
msgid ""
"Our victory at Elensefar has been a great blow to Asheviere, but her thumb "
"firmly remains upon the core cities of central Wesnoth. We have not the "
"strength to challenge her in her domain. Even if we did, such a war would "
"kill untold numbers."
msgstr ""
"A nosa vitoria en Elensefar foi un gran golpe para Asheviere, pero o seu "
"polgar segue firmemente sobre as cidades principais do centro de Wesnoth. "
"Non temos a forza para desafiala no seu dominio. Mesmo se a tivésemos, unha "
"guerra así mataría a un número incalculable de persoas."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1127
msgid "This is a crucial moment. We must be sure to act rightly..."
msgstr ""
"Este é un momento crucial. Debemos asegurarnos de actuar correctamente..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1141
msgid "Look there! A boat approaches!"
msgstr "Mira alí! Un barco se achega!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1153
msgid "Look there! Someone comes!"
msgstr "Mira alí! Alguén vén!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1170
msgid ""
"Not just someone! Konrad, this is Kalenz, High Lord of all elves and a close "
"ally and friend."
msgstr ""
"Non só alguén! Konrad, este é Kalenz, Gran Señor de todos os elfos e un "
"aliado e amigo próximo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1174
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1245
msgid "Kalenz! Delfador has told me so much about you!"
msgstr "Kalenz! Delfador faloume tanto de ti!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1178
msgid ""
"Thank you for offering us asylum — even the elves of the Aethenwood "
"recognize your authority. It’s a high honor to finally meet you in person."
msgstr ""
"Grazas por ofrecernos asilo; mesmo os elfos do Bosque de Aethen recoñecen a "
"túa autoridade. É unha gran honra coñecerte por fin en persoa."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1182
msgid ""
"And you as well, friend Konrad. I have not seen you since you were very "
"young, shortly after the deaths... of your brothers. From what I hear of "
"your actions, Delfador would be proud of the king you are becoming."
msgstr ""
"E a ti tamén, amigo Konrad. Non te vin dende que eras moi novo, pouco "
"despois da morte... dos teus irmáns. Polo que oín das túas accións, Delfador "
"estaría orgulloso do rei no que te estás convertendo."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1186
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But this is no idle visit of reminiscence, for I bring word from the "
#| "Ka’lian. Your mentor called upon the advice of the elvish council some "
#| "weeks ago, Konrad."
msgid ""
"But this is no idle visit of reminiscence, for I bring word from Lintanir "
"Forest. Your mentor called upon the advice of the elvish sages some weeks "
"ago, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"Pero esta non é unha visita ociosa de reminiscencias, xa que traio novas dos "
"Ka'lian. O teu mentor pediu consello ao consello élfico hai unhas semanas, "
"Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1190
msgid ""
"Delfador, the strands of prophecy are moving — you know she of whom I speak. "
"May we take a moment in private?"
msgstr ""
"Delfador, os fíos da profecía están a moverse... sabes da quen falo. Podemos "
"tomar un momento en privado?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1205
msgid "Then it shall be done. I depart for the Heart Mountains at once."
msgstr "Entón farase. Parto de inmediato cara ás Montañas do Corazón."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1209
msgid ""
"You’re leaving just like that? We’ve hardly had a moment of peace together "
"since the Aethenwood!"
msgstr ""
"¿Vas marchar así, sen máis? Case non tivemos un momento de paz xuntos desde "
"Aethenwood!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1213
msgid ""
"I am afraid so, Konrad. An urgent matter has come up that demands my "
"attention. It is something you need not concern yourself with just yet."
msgstr ""
"Temo que si, Konrad. Xurdiu un asunto urxente que require a miña atención. É "
"algo do que non te preocupes aínda."

#. [message]: speaker={KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1227
msgid "Gone! And with hardly a word. What’s this quest about, Kalenz?"
msgstr ""
"Desaparecidos! E sen apenas dicir unha palabra. De que vai esta misión, "
"Kalenz?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1237
msgid ""
"Who are you, stranger? Your ears are forked, but I don’t recognize you from "
"the Aethenwood — even your clothes look foreign. Friend or foe?"
msgstr ""
"Quen es ti, forasteiro? As túas orellas son bifurcadas, pero non che "
"recoñezo do Aethenwood — ata a túa roupa semella allea. Amigo ou inimigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1241
msgid ""
"Friend, Konrad. I am Kalenz, eldest in the Lintanir and High Lord of all "
"elves. Greetings."
msgstr ""
"Amigo, Konrad. Son Kalenz, o máis vello de Lintanir e Alto Señor de todos os "
"elfos. Saúdos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1249
msgid ""
"Thank you for offering us asylum — even the elves of the Aethenwood "
"recognize your authority. I am sorry for the price they paid. It’s a high "
"honor to finally meet you in person."
msgstr ""
"Grazas por ofrecernos asilo; mesmo os elfos do Bosque de Aethen recoñecen a "
"túa autoridade. Síntoo polo prezo que pagaron. É unha gran honra coñecerte "
"por fin en persoa."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1253
msgid ""
"And you as well, friend Konrad. I have not seen you since you were very "
"young, shortly after the deaths of your brothers. From what I hear of your "
"actions, you should be proud of the king you are becoming."
msgstr ""
"E a ti tamén, amigo Konrad. Non te vin dende que eras moi novo, pouco "
"despois da morte dos teus irmáns. Polo que oín das túas accións, deberías "
"estar orgulloso do rei no que te estás convertendo."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1257
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But this is no idle visit of reminiscence, for I bring grim news. The "
#| "city of Elensefar — that which was defended so staunchly by your mentor "
#| "Delfador and the lord Maddock — has been conquered."
msgid ""
"But this is no idle visit of reminiscence, for I bring grim news. The city "
"of Elensefar — that which was defended so staunchly by your mentor Delfador "
"and Lord Maddock — has been conquered."
msgstr ""
"Pero esta non é unha visita ociosa de reminiscencias, xa que traio novas "
"sombrías. A cidade de Elensefar, aquela que foi defendida tan firmemente "
"polo voso mentor Delfador e o señor Maddock, foi conquistada."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1261
msgid ""
"No! Has Delfador been taken prisoner? Is he hurt? We must march at once to "
"his aid!"
msgstr ""
"Non! Delfador foi feito prisioneiro? Está ferido? Debemos marchar de "
"inmediato na súa axuda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1265
msgid ""
"Your mentor is alive and well, Konrad. He could not rejoin you here today, "
"but he left you a brief message. Ahem..."
msgstr ""
"O teu mentor está vivo e ben, Konrad. Non puido reunirse contigo aquí hoxe, "
"pero deixouche unha breve mensaxe. Ehm..."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1271
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>I depart for the Heart Mountains at once, Konrad. An urgent matter has "
#| "come up that demands my attention. It is something you need not concern "
#| "yourself with just yet.</i>"
msgid ""
"I depart for the Heart Mountains at once, Konrad. An urgent matter has come "
"up that demands my attention. It is something you need not concern yourself "
"with just yet."
msgstr ""
"<i>Parto para as Montañas do Corazón de inmediato, Konrad. Surxiu un asunto "
"urxente que require a miña atención. É algo do que non te preocupes aínda.</"
"i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1276
msgid ""
"That’s it? We’ve hardly had a moment of peace together since the Aethenwood, "
"and this is all he has to say. Kalenz, what is this quest about?"
msgstr ""
"Iso é todo? Case non tivemos un momento de paz xuntos desde o Bosque de "
"Aethen, e isto é todo o que ten que dicir. Kalenz, de que trata esta misión?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1284
msgid ""
"Delfador is your guardian, and I shall respect his wish for silence on the "
"matter. But in his absence, I shall be glad to accompany you on your travels."
msgstr ""
"Delfador é o teu gardián e respectarei o seu desexo de gardar silencio sobre "
"o asunto. Pero na súa ausencia, estarei encantado de acompañarte nas túas "
"viaxes."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1288
msgid ""
"Together we must continue the work that you and he already began — "
"brightening hearts, kindling hope, and freeing still more of your kind from "
"their oppressive queen."
msgstr ""
"Xuntos debemos continuar o traballo que ti e el xa comezastes: iluminando "
"corazóns, avivando a esperanza e liberando aínda máis da vosa especie da súa "
"raíña opresora."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1311
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:216
msgid "Messenger"
msgstr "Mensaxeiro"

#. [message]: speaker=familiar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1315
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:222
msgid "Fsss... crackle crackle hiss!"
msgstr "Fsss... chispa chispa ase!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1339
msgid "A message from Delfador. He has found the Sceptre of Fire!"
msgstr "Unha mensaxe de Delfador. Atopou o Cetro de Lume!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1345
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We must go at once! Once we hold the sceptre of my fathers; the symbol of "
#| "the king of Wesnoth, surely Asheviere can no longer hope to oppose us."
msgid ""
"We must go at once! Once we hold the sceptre of my fathers; the symbol of "
"the kings of Wesnoth, surely Asheviere can no longer hope to oppose us."
msgstr ""
"¡Debemos marchar de inmediato! Unha vez que sostengamos o cetro dos meus "
"antepasados; o símbolo do rei de Wesnoth, surely Asheviere xa non poderá "
"esperar opoñerse a nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1349
msgid "Indeed. Let us make haste, before some misfortune befalls it..."
msgstr ""
"De verdade. Apresurémonos, antes de que lle aconteza algunha desgraza..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1354
msgid ""
"The Sceptre of Fire? I thought that was just a myth! This is the quest he’s "
"been off doing so secretly?"
msgstr ""
"O Cetro de Fogo? Pensaba que iso era só un mito! Esta é a misión que estivo "
"a facer tan en segredo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1358
msgid ""
"Indeed. Delfador will explain more once we three reunite. He is deep in the "
"Heart Mountains to the northeast — you must go to him at once, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"Si. Delfador darache máis explicacións unha vez que nos volvamos reunir "
"tres. Está nas profundidades das Montañas do Corazón, ao nordés. Debes ir "
"con el de inmediato, Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1369
msgid "A message from Delfador! He has found the Sceptre of Fire!"
msgstr "Unha mensaxe de Delfador! Atopou o Cetro de Lume!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1373
msgid ""
"We must go at once! Once we hold the sceptre of my fathers; the symbol of "
"the king of Wesnoth, surely Asheviere can no longer hope to oppose us."
msgstr ""
"¡Debemos marchar de inmediato! Unha vez que sostengamos o cetro dos meus "
"antepasados; o símbolo do rei de Wesnoth, surely Asheviere xa non poderá "
"esperar opoñerse a nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1378
msgid ""
"A message from Delfador! He has found... the Sceptre of Fire?! I thought the "
"Sceptre was just a myth! This is the quest he’s been off doing so secretly?"
msgstr ""
"Unha mensaxe de Delfador! Atopou... o Cetro de Lume?! Pensei que o Cetro era "
"só un mito! É esta a misión na que estivo a facer en segredo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1382
msgid ""
"I suppose Delfador will explain more once we reunite. The message says he is "
"deep in the Heart Mountains to the northeast — I must go to him at once."
msgstr ""
"Supoño que Delfador darache máis explicacións unha vez que nos volvamos "
"atopar. A mensaxe di que está nas profundidades das Montañas do Corazón, ao "
"nordés. Teño que ir con el de inmediato."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1403
msgid "You already been paid for by da wizzard. Go on thru, softskin."
msgstr "Xa che pagou o meigo. Segue adiante, pelamolle."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1428
msgid ""
"Any other time I would have insisted on stopping to help these poor people! "
"But I’ve been instructed to meet with Delfador at once."
msgstr ""
"En calquera outro momento tería insistido en parar para axudar a esta pobre "
"xente! Pero déronme instrucións para reunirme con Delfador de inmediato."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1432
msgid ""
"Delfador is just north of here. With so many orcs nearby, the Doors are "
"closed to us. But I can still loop around to the west, north, then east, "
"through the Caverns of Chaincolt."
msgstr ""
"Delfador está xusto ao norte de aquí. Con tantos orcos preto, as Portas "
"están pechadas para nós. Pero aínda podo dar unha volta cara ao oeste, ao "
"norte e despois ao leste, a través das Cavernas de Chaincolt."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1450
msgid ""
"There is no time to stop and fight — I must meet with Delfador and claim the "
"Sceptre. He is deep within the Heart Mountains, somewhere to the northeast."
msgstr ""
"Non hai tempo para deterse e loitar — debo reunirme con Delfador e reclamar "
"o Cetro. Está nas profundidades das Montañas do Corazón, nalgún lugar ao "
"nordeste."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1492
msgid ""
"Crossin’ through Stoneskin ford? Dat’ll be $ford_cost gold for passage, "
"whelp."
msgstr "Cruzar o vao de Pel de Pedra? Custará ouro pola pasaxe, carallo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1496
msgid ""
"Clan Stoneskin is an ally of the crown. Let me by or face the consequences."
msgstr ""
"O clan Pedrapel é un aliado da coroa. Déixame pasar ou afronta as "
"consecuencias."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1500
msgid ""
"Das right, miss princess. An bein’ our allies, I’m sure you wooden mind "
"donatin’ dem $ford_cost gold pieces."
msgstr ""
"Así é, señorita princesa. Sendo os nosos aliados, estou segura de que lle "
"importaría doar esas moedas de ouro a baixo custo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1533
msgid "Good news or bad news, Mirya. Are we too late?"
msgstr "Boas ou malas novas, Mirya. Chegamos demasiado tarde?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1537
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "They definitely have a lead on the Sceptre — of that I’m certain, your "
#| "highness. But your “cousin” has only just arrived. They can’t yet have "
#| "reached it."
msgid ""
"They definitely have a lead on the Sceptre — of that I’m certain, Your "
"Highness. But your “cousin” has only just arrived. They can’t yet have "
"reached it."
msgstr ""
"Sen dúbida teñen unha pista sobre o Sceptre — diso estou certo, alteza. Pero "
"o seu \"primo\" acaba de chegar. Aínda non poden telo alcanzado."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1541
msgid "Then there’s still a chance. Double-quick, men!"
msgstr "Entón aínda hai unha oportunidade. A paso redoblado, homes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1567
msgid ""
"It is good that you have chosen to help us, Li’sar. But as we approach "
"Weldyn, will your decision hold? You would do well to learn the lesson on "
"loyalty that your mother did not."
msgstr ""
"É bo que decidises axudarnos, Li’sar. Pero, a medida que nos achegamos a "
"Weldyn, manterase a túa decisión? Farías ben en aprender a lección sobre a "
"lealdade que a túa nai non aprendeu."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1571
msgid ""
"I am not a fool. I fought you because I believed it was best for Wesnoth. "
"Now I fight my mother for the same reason."
msgstr ""
"Non son parvo. Loitei contra ti porque cría que era o mellor para Wesnoth. "
"Agora loito contra a miña nai pola mesma razón."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1575
msgid "Indeed..."
msgstr "De feito..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1579
msgid ""
"Listen, you whose eyes are fair but hide a vacuum, do you think I do not "
"know what power can do to one’s soul? What evils a person is capable of when "
"truth and righteousness are but scrolls that can be rewritten when a queen "
"grows tired of them?"
msgstr ""
"Escoita, ti, cuxos ollos son fermosos pero agochan un baleiro, cres que eu "
"non sei o que o poder pode facerlle á alma a alguén? De que males é capaz "
"unha persoa cando a verdade e a xustiza non son máis que pergamiños que se "
"poden reescribir cando unha raíña se cansa delas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1583
msgid ""
"I spent my entire childhood listening to my mother give orders and command "
"armies around. I hid in the throne room as a little girl as she met with her "
"generals. I now know she was having people killed... entire towns of people "
"killed!"
msgstr ""
"Pasei toda a miña infancia escoitando á miña nai dar ordes e comandar "
"exércitos. De pequena escondíame na sala do trono mentres ela se reunía cos "
"seus xenerais. Agora sei que estaba a mandar matar xente... pobos enteiros "
"de xente!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1587
msgid ""
"You are all lucky. You do not know what Wesnoth has been like these past "
"many years. There is no peace. I have never known peace."
msgstr ""
"Sodes todos afortunados. Non sabedes como foi Wesnoth estes últimos moitos "
"anos. Non hai paz. Eu nunca coñecín a paz."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1591
msgid ""
"I do know the cup of bitterness poured out on Wesnoth by your mother, child. "
"The land has been torn apart. The elves know this. The orcs know this. "
"Undead can feel it. Large armies of men march across the plains hunting each "
"other, and when no men remain, outsiders will claim Wesnoth as their home."
msgstr ""
"Coñezo a copa de amargura que a túa nai derramou sobre Wesnoth, fillo. A "
"terra foi esnaquizada. Os elfos saben isto. Os orcos saben isto. Os mortos "
"viventes poden sentilo. Grandes exércitos de homes marchan polas chairas "
"cazándose uns aos outros, e cando non queden homes, os forasteiros "
"reclamarán Wesnoth como o seu fogar."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1595
msgid ""
"Enough! I can listen to no more of this. Li’sar, you may want to end your "
"mother’s rule, but I will end her life as she ended the life of my father "
"and my brothers. Asheviere’s masterwork of treachery will end, and it will "
"end by my blade!"
msgstr ""
"Abonda! Non podo seguir escoitando. Li’sar, pode que ti pretendas acabar co "
"reinado de túa nai, pero eu o que quero é pórlle fin á súa vida, tal como "
"ela fixo coas vidas de meu pai e dos meus irmáns. A folla da miña espada "
"poralle fin á imperdoábel traizón de Axevier!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1613
msgid "Crier"
msgstr "Pregoeiro da vila"

#. [message]: speaker=crier
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1617
msgid ""
"Hear ye, hear ye! I bring tidings to the Lord Konrad from Her Majesty the "
"Queen!"
msgstr ""
"Escoitade, escoitade! Traio novas para Lord Konrad de parte de Súa Maxestade "
"a Raíña!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1623
msgid ""
"A message from Asheviere? I wonder what new trickery this is. Speak what you "
"have come to say, courier."
msgstr ""
"Unha mensaxe de Asheviere? Pregúntome que novo engano será este. Di o que "
"viñeches dicir, mensaxeiro."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1644
msgid "Kalenz, Lord of the Lintanir."
msgstr "Kalenz, Señor dos Lintanir."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1645
msgid "Ethiliel, Lady of the Aethenwood."
msgstr "Etiliel, Dama do Bosque Eterno."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1646
msgid "Kaylan, Lord of Blackwater."
msgstr "Kaylan, Señor de Blackwater."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1647
msgid "Maddock, Lord of Elensefar."
msgstr "Maddock, Señor de Elensefar."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1648
msgid "Galdrad, Champion of the Aethenwood."
msgstr "Galdrad, Campión do Bosque Eterno."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1649
msgid "Delurin, Three Sisters outlaw."
msgstr "Delurin, forasteiro das Tres Irmás."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1650
msgid "Reglok, Elensefar thieves’ guildmaster."
msgstr "Reglok, mestre da gilda de ladróns de Elensefar."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1651
msgid "Harper, Three Sisters outlaw."
msgstr "Harper, foraxido das Tres Irmás."

#. [message]: speaker=crier
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1657
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Hark! The Lord Konrad and his followers are to be made aware of the "
#| "events to proceed at Weldyn in three weeks’ time, these being the just "
#| "and righeous execution of one thousand twenty-eight condemned partisans "
#| "and rebel sympathizers from the western and northern reaches."
msgid ""
"Hark! The Lord Konrad and his followers are to be made aware of the events "
"to proceed at Weldyn in three weeks’ time, these being the just and "
"righteous execution of the following condemned criminals and rebel "
"sympathizers:"
msgstr ""
"Escoitade! Lord Konrad e os seus seguidores deben ser informados dos "
"acontecementos que terán lugar en Weldyn dentro de tres semanas, que son a "
"xusta e lexítima execución de mil vinte e oito partisanos e simpatizantes "
"rebeldes condenados dos confines occidentais e setentrionais."

#. [message]: speaker=crier
#. $message is a list of names and titles, generated depending on Konrad's actions. For example: "Maddock, Lord of Elensefar. Ethiliel, Lady of the Aethenwood. Delurin, Three Sisters outlaw. "
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1661
msgid ""
"$message|And one thousand twenty-eight other rebel partisans from the "
"western and northern reaches."
msgstr ""
"$message|E mil vinte e oito máis partidarios rebeldes das rexións "
"occidentais e setentrionais."

#. [message]: speaker=crier
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1666
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Hark! The Lord Konrad and his followers are to be made aware of the "
#| "events to proceed at Weldyn in three weeks’ time, these being the just "
#| "and righeous execution of one thousand twenty-eight condemned partisans "
#| "and rebel sympathizers from the western and northern reaches."
msgid ""
"Hark! The Lord Konrad and his followers are to be made aware of the events "
"to proceed at Weldyn in three weeks’ time, these being the just and "
"righteous execution of one thousand twenty-eight condemned partisans and "
"rebel sympathizers from the western and northern reaches."
msgstr ""
"Escoitade! Lord Konrad e os seus seguidores deben ser informados dos "
"acontecementos que terán lugar en Weldyn dentro de tres semanas, que son a "
"xusta e lexítima execución de mil vinte e oito partisanos e simpatizantes "
"rebeldes condenados dos confines occidentais e setentrionais."

#. [message]: speaker=crier
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1672
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The Queen laments such a loss of life as regrettable, but necessary in "
#| "Her Judgement to ensure the continued safety and stability of Her "
#| "Kingdom.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The Lord Konrad is warned to discontinue his campaign of terror and keep "
#| "well away from Weldyn, lest the same tragic fate befall him as well."
msgid ""
"The Queen laments such a loss of life as regrettable, but necessary in Her "
"Judgement to ensure the continued safety and stability of Her Kingdom."
msgstr ""
"A Raíña lamenta esta perda de vidas como lamentable, pero necesaria no seu "
"xuízo para garantir a seguridade e a estabilidade continuas do seu reino. O "
"señor Konrad é advertido de que interrompa a súa campaña de terror e se "
"manteña lonxe de Weldyn, para que non o aconteza o mesmo destino tráxico."

#. [message]: speaker=crier
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1674
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The Queen laments such a loss of life as regrettable, but necessary in "
#| "Her Judgement to ensure the continued safety and stability of Her "
#| "Kingdom.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The Lord Konrad is warned to discontinue his campaign of terror and keep "
#| "well away from Weldyn, lest the same tragic fate befall him as well."
msgid ""
"The Lord Konrad is warned to discontinue his campaign of terror and keep "
"well away from Weldyn, lest the same tragic fate befall him as well."
msgstr ""
"A Raíña lamenta esta perda de vidas como lamentable, pero necesaria no seu "
"xuízo para garantir a seguridade e a estabilidade continuas do seu reino. O "
"señor Konrad é advertido de que interrompa a súa campaña de terror e se "
"manteña lonxe de Weldyn, para que non o aconteza o mesmo destino tráxico."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1685
msgid "A mass execution!? Sweet Haldric, all those people. We have to act!"
msgstr ""
"Unha execución masiva!? Doce Haldric, toda esa xente. Temos que actuar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1689
msgid ""
"... but what did Asheviere hope to gain by telling us? Could she mean to "
"catch us in some trap?"
msgstr ""
"... pero que esperaba gañar Asheviere contándonolo? Podería pretender "
"atraparnos nalgunha trampa?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1693
msgid "How naïve can you be? Of course it's a trap!"
msgstr "Que ingenuo podes ser? Por suposto é unha trampa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1697
msgid ""
"My mother knows how you think. She expects you to rush straight to Weldyn, "
"where she and all her allies will be ready to catch us and crush us. We "
"don’t even know if these people really have been captured."
msgstr ""
"A miña nai sabe como pensas. Agarda que vaias directamente a Weldyn, onde "
"ela e todos os seus aliados estarán listos para atraparnos e esmagarnos. Nin "
"sequera sabemos se esta xente foi realmente capturada."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1701
msgid ""
"We should ignore her taunt. Our wisest course of action would be to do as "
"she says and stay well away, while we continue whittling down her base of "
"power."
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos ignorar a súa mofa. A nosa acción máis sensata sería facer o que "
"ela di e manterse ben afastados, mentres continuamos a reducir a súa base de "
"poder."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1705
msgid ""
"The condemned are my friends and allies; rebels who risked everything to "
"oppose the dark queen. Even ignoring our morals, what message would such an "
"act send? Who would still support us after such a display?"
msgstr ""
"Os condenados son os meus amigos e aliados; rebeldes que arriscaron todo "
"para opoñerse á raíña escura. Mesmo ignorando a nosa moral, que mensaxe "
"enviaría semellante acto? Quen nos seguiría apoiando despois dunha "
"demostración semellante?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1709
msgid ""
"If we are to rule Wesnoth, we must prove ourselves better than Asheviere, "
"not equal. We must defeat her before she can carry out her executions."
msgstr ""
"Se queremos gobernar Wesnoth, debemos demostrar que somos mellores que "
"Asheviere, non iguais. Debemos derrotala antes de que poida levar a cabo as "
"súas execucións."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1713
msgid ""
"Konrad speaks wisdom. Risky though it may be, we should march at once to "
"Weldyn. There is no time to spare."
msgstr ""
"Konrad di sabedoría. Aínda que sexa arriscado, deberiamos marchar de "
"inmediato cara a Weldyn. Non hai tempo que perder."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1717
msgid "Very well. This is it, then."
msgstr "Moi ben. Entón, isto é."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/00_The_Great_Continent.cfg:1741
msgid ""
"Asheviere has left us no time to stop and fight. We must reach Weldyn before "
"she can carry out her executions."
msgstr ""
"Asheviere non nos deixou tempo para parar e loitar. Debemos chegar a Weldyn "
"antes de que poida levar a cabo as súas execucións."

#. [scenario]: id=01_The_Elves_Besieged
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:10
msgid "The Elves Besieged"
msgstr "Os elfos sitiados"

#. [part]
#. notice that appears at the beginning of the scenario if you select Deadly difficulty
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:34
msgid ""
"NOTE: ‘Deadly’ difficulty is intended to be a frighteningly difficult "
"challenge for players who already know many of this campaign’s secrets. If "
"this is your first time playing Heir to the Throne, you may want to try a "
"lower difficulty."
msgstr ""
"NOTA: A dificultade ‘Mortal’ está pensada como un desafío extremadamente "
"difícil para xogadores que xa coñecen moitos dos segredos desta campaña. Se "
"é a túa primeira vez xogando O Herdeiro ao trono, pode que queiras probar "
"unha dificultade máis baixa."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:39
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "In the twenty-eighth year of the reign of Garard II, King of Wesnoth, the "
#| "kingdom was plunged into a bitter war with the Orcs of the North."
msgid ""
"In the twenty-eighth year of the reign of Garard II, King of Wesnoth, the "
"kingdom made bitter war against the Orcs of the North."
msgstr ""
"No vixésimo oitavo ano do reinado de Gárar II, rei do Noroeste, o reino "
"viuse no medio dunha encarnizada guerra cos orcos nórdicos."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:43
msgid ""
"The Northern host encamped at Galcadar, by the Ford of Abez, and the King "
"led his forces to meet them. Years of war brought Wesnoth to the brink of "
"ruin, but at long last victory was won through the actions of Garard’s arch-"
"mage, Delfador."
msgstr ""
"O exército do Norte acampou en Galcadar, xunto ao Vao de Abez, e o Rei "
"liderou as súas forzas para enfrontarse a elas. Anos de guerra levaron a "
"Wesnoth á beira da ruína, pero finalmente a vitoria conseguiuse grazas ás "
"accións do arquimago de Garard, Delfador."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:47
msgid ""
"Garard’s son, the Crown Prince Eldred, joined in the revelry as the King "
"celebrated his victory. Eldred was bright and driven, and might one day have "
"grown into a wise ruler. Unfortunately for Garard, his son was also "
"ambitious... and treacherous."
msgstr ""
"O fillo de Garard, o príncipe herdeiro Eldred, uniuse á festa mentres o rei "
"celebraba a súa vitoria. Eldred era brillante e decidido, e algún día "
"podería converterse nun gobernante sabio. Por desgraza para Garard, o seu "
"fillo tamén era ambicioso... e traizoeiro."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:51
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "At the height of Garard’s triumph, Eldred struck the old King down in "
#| "cold blood. Proclaiming himself heir, the young prince led his father’s "
#| "army south towards Weldyn."
msgid ""
"At the height of Garard’s triumph, Eldred struck the old King down in cold "
"blood. Seizing the crown for himself, the young prince led his father’s army "
"south towards Weldyn."
msgstr ""
"No cumio do triunfo de Garard, Eldred derrotou ao vello rei a sangue frío. "
"Proclamándose herdeiro, o mozo príncipe liderou o exército do seu pai cara "
"ao sur, en dirección a Weldyn."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:55
msgid ""
"Garard’s queen, Asheviere, looked on with glee, having orchestrated much of "
"her son’s treachery. The rule of Eldred would surely satisfy her lust for "
"power far better than her husband’s had."
msgstr ""
"A raíña de Garard, Asheviere, observaba con alegría, xa que orquestraba gran "
"parte da traizón do seu fillo. O reinado de Eldred seguramente satisfaría a "
"súa ansia de poder moito mellor que o do seu marido."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:59
msgid ""
"But Delfador the arch-mage had not fallen alongside his king. Returning from "
"a distant battle, he mustered a force of loyalists to fight the young prince "
"and avenge the King’s death. The loyalist army marched south to meet Eldred."
msgstr ""
"Pero Delfador, o arquimago, non caera xunto ao seu rei. Ao regresar dunha "
"batalla afastada, reuniu unha forza de leais para loitar contra o mozo "
"príncipe e vingar a morte do rei. O exército leal marchou cara ao sur para "
"atoparse con Eldred."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:63
msgid ""
"Eldred made war upon the loyalists with his mother’s advice ringing in his "
"ears: <i>“Fight no one great or small except the old mage, whose head should "
"be severed from his shoulders.”</i>"
msgstr ""
"Eldred declarou a guerra aos leais co consello da súa nai resoando nos seus "
"oídos: <i>«Non loitedes contra ninguén, grande nin pequeno, agás contra o "
"vello mago, ao que lle deben cortar a cabeza dos ombreiros».</i>"

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:67
msgid ""
"And Eldred did indeed meet Delfador face-to-face in battle, along the high "
"road to Weldyn. Sword clashed against staff, as the wise old mage fought the "
"brash young warrior."
msgstr ""
"E Eldred atopouse con Delfador cara a cara na batalla, ao longo do camiño "
"principal cara a Weldyn. Espadas chocaron contra bastóns, mentres o sabio "
"mago vello loitaba contra o descarado mozo guerreiro."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:71
msgid ""
"In the end Delfador’s men were defeated and routed, but Asheviere found her "
"son’s lifeless body, fixed to the ground by the great mage’s staff."
msgstr ""
"Ao final, os homes de Delfador foron derrotados e esnaquizados, pero "
"Asheviere atopou o corpo sen vida do seu fillo, fixo no chan polo bastón do "
"gran mago."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:75
msgid ""
"Asheviere herself then took command of the army and led it back to Weldyn. "
"Knowing that the King’s young nephews were next in line to the throne, she "
"ordered them all killed and declared herself Queen of Wesnoth, striking down "
"any lord bold enough to oppose her."
msgstr ""
"A propia Asheviere tomou entón o mando do exército e levouno de volta a "
"Weldyn. Sabendo que os sobriños novos do rei eran os seguintes na liña de "
"sucesión ao trono, ordenou que fosen asasinados a todos e declarouse raíña "
"de Wesnoth, derrotando a calquera señor o suficientemente ousado como para "
"opoñerse a ela."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:79
msgid ""
"Soon after news of Asheviere’s orders reached Delfador, he secretly entered "
"the palace and stole away Konrad, the youngest of Garard’s nephews, thereby "
"saving him from death."
msgstr ""
"Pouco despois de que a noticia das ordes de Asheviere chegase a Delfador, "
"este entrou en segredo no palacio e roubou a Konrad, o máis novo dos "
"sobriños de Garard, salvándoo así da morte."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:83
msgid ""
"Fleeing to the Aethenwood beyond the south-western border of Wesnoth, "
"Delfador raised the child Konrad under the protection of the elves, watching "
"sadly as Asheviere’s reign of terror over the land began..."
msgstr ""
"Delfador fuxiu ao Bosque do Edén, alén da fronteira suroeste do Noroeste, e "
"deixou o pequeno baixo a protección dos elfos, mentres observaba con "
"tristura como comezaba o reinado de terror de Axevier sobre a terra…"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:147
msgid "10 gold"
msgstr "10 ouro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:147
msgid ""
"A little gold for use in magical experiments. I’m sure it won’t be missed."
msgstr ""
"Un pouco de ouro para usar en experimentos máxicos. Seguro que non se botará "
"de menos."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. this is Delfador trying to wake up a sleeping Konrad, as heard from Konrad's perspective
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:196
msgid "Konrad!"
msgstr "Konrad!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. this is Delfador trying to wake up a sleeping Konrad, as heard from Konrad's perspective
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:202
msgid "Konrad, wake up!"
msgstr "Konrad, esperta!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. the "dream" Konrad refers to is the intro storytext. This is a justification for the artwork (especially Delfador's age) not matching the characters' appearances.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:219
msgid ""
"<i>(yawn)</i> What a vivid dream. Asheviere and Eldred, Delfador and Garard, "
"just like in the histories..."
msgstr ""
"<i>(bostezo)</i> Que soño tan vívido. Asheviere e Eldred, Delfador e Garard, "
"coma nas historias..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Wake up, wake up, wake up! Curse you Konrad, get up and get out here! We’re "
"under attack!"
msgstr ""
"¡Dispierta, dispierta, dispierta! Maldición, Konrad, ¡ergue e sae para aquí! "
"¡Estamos baixo ataque!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. Konrad has heard Delfador calling him but is not concerned. In the past, Delfador has often surprised Konrad with training. In reality, there's a real battle beginning
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:243
msgid ""
"I’m up, I’m up. What’s the “attack” today, Delfador? Orcs in the walls? Magi "
"under my bedsheets?"
msgstr ""
"Estou arriba, estou arriba. Cal é o \"ataque\" de hoxe, Delfador? Orcos nas "
"murallas? Magos debaixo das miñas sabas?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:249
msgid ""
"No, you daft child, nothing like that! Grab your sword and come outside!"
msgstr "Non, neno parvo, nada diso! Colle a túa espada e sae fóra!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. the intent of this is to show that 1) Konrad trains regularly with Delfador and 2) Konrad is living with and on friendly terms with elves, particulary Ethiliel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:295
msgid ""
"Well, I’d better do as he says. Last time I missed battle training, Ethiliel "
"made me spend all week transcribing her poetry. <i>(shudder)</i>"
msgstr ""
"Ben, mellor fago o que di. A última vez que faltéi ao adestramento de "
"combate, Ethiliel obrigoume a pasar toda a semana transcribindo a súa "
"poesía. <i>(tremor)</i>"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:299
msgid "Explore your home"
msgstr "Explora a túa casa"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:303
msgid "Meet Delfador"
msgstr "Coñece a Delfador"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. the player has moved Konrad to his bed
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:334
msgid "No time to rest! Got to train hard if I ever want to be a good king."
msgstr ""
"Non teño tempo para descansar! Teño que adestrar duro se algunha vez quero "
"ser un bo rei."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. the player has moved Konrad near a writing desk. This foreshadows Asheviere's large-scale invasion
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:350
msgid ""
"Looks like Delfador’s written part of a letter. “<i>Sir Kaylan, I hope this "
"missive finds you well. Lord Maddock’s latest report is worrying: the recent "
"mobilization suggests...</i>”"
msgstr ""
"Parece a parte escrita dunha carta de Delfador. « <i>Sir Kaylan, espero que "
"esta misiva o atope ben. O último informe de Lord Maddock é preocupante: a "
"recente mobilización suxire...</i> »"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:354
msgid "The letter trails off there."
msgstr "A carta remata aí."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. Konrad has moved near a bookshelf. These are the names of some of the books
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:371
msgid ""
"“<i>The Young Statesman’s Political Primer</i>”\n"
"“<i>Basics of Swordsmanship, feat. Sergeant Mari</i>”\n"
"“<i>An Abridged History of Wesnoth, by Delfador</i>”"
msgstr ""
"“ <i>Manual político do mozo estadista</i> ” “ <i>Fundamentos da esgrima, "
"con a sarxento Mari</i> ” “ <i>Unha historia abreviada de Wesnoth, por "
"Delfador</i> ”"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:377
msgid ""
"My textbooks, courtesy of the Aethenwood. The shelves get fuller every day."
msgstr ""
"Os meus libros de texto, cortesía de Aethenwood. As estanterías énchense "
"cada día máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#. Konrad is attacking a quintain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:410
msgid "Hi-ya! Take that Eldred! Take that Asheviere!"
msgstr "Ola! Colle ese Eldred! Colle ese Asheviere!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:423
msgid "This is good practice! I’m starting to tire myself out."
msgstr "Isto é boa práctica! Xa estou empezando a cansarme."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:442
msgid ""
"Whew... I’m bruised and exhausted. It’s been good training so far, but if I "
"keep throwing myself at this dummy I’m worried I might faint!"
msgstr ""
"Uf... estou magullado e esgotado. Foi un bo adestramento ata agora, pero se "
"sigo lanzándome contra este maniquí, temo que me desmaie!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. Konrad is leaving home, kicking off the main scenario
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/01_The_Elves_Besieged.cfg:486
msgid "Well, time to see what Delfador’s so excited about."
msgstr "Ben, é hora de ver polo que Delfador está tan emocionado."

