#. [message]: speaker=Dverag-Kukai
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:489
msgid "Are all the fishmen in cages yet?"
msgstr "Están xa todos os homes-peixe nas gaiolas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Managa'Gwin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:493
msgid "Almost."
msgstr "Case."

#. [message]: speaker=Managa'Gwin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:495
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Almost.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "UP, SEA LICE! Drag your slimy hides from the deep! Drop the pearls, then "
#| "scuttle back to your cages!"
msgid ""
"UP, SEA LICE! Drag your slimy hides from the deep! Drop the pearls, then "
"scuttle back to your cages!"
msgstr ""
"Case.\n"
"\n"
"ARRIBA, PIOLLOS DE MARIÑO! Arrastrade as vosas peles viscosas das "
"profundidades! Deixade caer as perlas e logo correde de volta ás vosas "
"gaiolas!"

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:515
msgid "+120 gold"
msgstr "+120 de ouro"

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:515
msgid "+160 gold"
msgstr "+160 de ouro"

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:515
msgid "+40 gold"
msgstr "+40 de ouro"

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:515
msgid "+80 gold"
msgstr "+80 de ouro"

#. [message]: speaker=Gwaba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:532
msgid "Nepba, it’s noon. The orcs are groggy and sleepy. This is our moment!"
msgstr ""
"Nepba, é mediodía. Os orcos están atordados e somnolentos. Este é o noso "
"momento!"

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:536
msgid "Let’s just take a look around for now. We must not act rashly."
msgstr ""
"De momento, botemos unha ollada ao noso redor. Non debemos actuar "
"precipitadamente."

#. [message]: speaker=Gwaba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:540
msgid ""
"I looked this morning and the door to the cave with the Trident of Storms is "
"open! When the others see that we’ve reclaimed it, they’ll rise up and we’ll "
"finally drive out the orcs!"
msgstr ""
"Mirei esta mañá e a porta da cova co Tridente das Tormentas está aberta! "
"Cando os demais vexan que a recuperamos, levantaranse e finalmente "
"expulsaremos os orcos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:544
msgid ""
"I don’t like our odds. Someone could shoot us from the castle while we swim "
"to the entrance."
msgstr ""
"Non me gustan as nosas probabilidades. Alguén podería dispararnos dende o "
"castelo mentres nadamos cara á entrada."

#. [message]: speaker=Gwaba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:548
msgid ""
"Let’s try swimming around the cave. There are cliffs and kelp that are easy "
"to hide in."
msgstr ""
"Intentemos nadar arredor da cova. Hai cantís e algas onde é doado agocharse."

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:554
msgid "Gwaba, wait!"
msgstr "Gwaba, agarda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Bugg
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:577
msgid ""
"Chief, I went to throw some trash in the sea and shot a fishman creeping up "
"on the Trident!"
msgstr ""
"Xefe, fun botar lixo ao mar e disparei a un home-peixe que se achegaba "
"sigilosamente polo Trident!"

#. [message]: speaker=Dverag-Kukai
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:581
msgid ""
"They’re planning an uprising! Drasha, have you managed to harness the power "
"of the Trident yet?"
msgstr ""
"Están a planificar unha insurrección! Drasha, conseguiches xa aproveitar o "
"poder do Tridente?"

#. [message]: speaker=Drasha
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:585
msgid "Not yet, no."
msgstr "Aínda non, non."

#. [message]: speaker=Dverag-Kukai
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:589
msgid ""
"Lock yourself in the cave until you can get the Trident to send a storm that "
"destroys their villages. They need to be punished."
msgstr ""
"Encérrate na cova ata que consigas que o Tridente envíe unha tormenta que "
"destrúa as súas aldeas. Hai que castigalos."

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:649
msgid ""
"Your Highness! Thank you for answering our plea for help. I am Nepba. We are "
"all grateful you have come, but you must hurry!"
msgstr ""
"Vosa Alteza! Grazas por atender o noso clamor de axuda. Son Nepba. Todos "
"estamos agradecidos de que vira, pero debe apurarse!"

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:653
msgid ""
"The orcs have stolen our Trident of Storms and are now trying to harness its "
"power to destroy our villages. They already killed my cousin Gwaba!"
msgstr ""
"Os orcos roubáronnos o Tridente das Tormentas e agora están a tentar "
"aproveitar o seu poder para destruír as nosas aldeas. Xa mataron ao meu "
"primo Gwaba!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:658
msgid "Delfador, can you do anything to stop them?"
msgstr "Delfador, podes facer algo para detelos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:662
msgid ""
"I feel the magic of the Trident... it is old, and powerful. Perhaps my "
"spells could break it, but the power unleashed would do immeasurable damage "
"to this place."
msgstr ""
"Sinto a maxia do Tridente... é antiga e poderosa. Quizais os meus feitizos "
"poidan rompela, pero o poder liberado causaría un dano inconmensurable a "
"este lugar."

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:667
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We can take the Trident back fom the orcs, but it is locked away in a "
#| "cave. They keep the key on land, where my kind cannot easily go."
msgid ""
"We can take the Trident back from the orcs, but it is locked away in a cave. "
"They keep the key on land, where my kind cannot easily go."
msgstr ""
"Podemos recuperar o Tridente dos orcos, pero está pechado nunha cova. Eles "
"gardan a chave na terra, onde a miña xente non pode ir facilmente."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:674
msgid "We’ll help you, Nepba. Let’s get the key and reclaim your Trident."
msgstr "Axudarémosche, Nepba. Imos coller a chave e recuperar o teu tridente."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:683
msgid "Get the key on 32,28; then attack the Orcish Shaman"
msgstr "Colle a chave no 32,28; despois ataca o xamán orco"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:690
msgid "Attack the Orcish Shaman"
msgstr "Ataca ao chaman orco"

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:715
msgid ""
"Konrad, we merfolk are eager to fight for our freedom. My people will join "
"you when you liberate our villages."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, nós, os sirénidos, estamos ansiosos por loitar pola nosa liberdade. "
"O meu pobo unirase a ti cando liberes as nosas aldeas."

#. [message]: speaker=Bugg
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:733
msgid "But chief, why are we only using bats and nagas?"
msgstr "Pero xefe, por que só usamos morcegos e nagas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Dverag-Kukai
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:737
msgid ""
"Because we need to control the seas and the merfolk, and nagas and bats are "
"best for doing that!"
msgstr ""
"Porque precisamos controlar os mares e as sereas, e os nagas e os morcegos "
"son os mellores para facelo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Bugg
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:741
msgid "But orcs are the most powerful race in all of..."
msgstr "Esta é a unidade tecnolóxica da Terra máis poderosa."

#. [message]: speaker=Dverag-Kukai
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:745
msgid "Shut up, worm! I’m the boss!"
msgstr "Cala, verme! Eu son o xefe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Bugg
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:755
msgid "Look at me!"
msgstr "Mírame!"

#. [message]: speaker=Bugg
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:765
msgid "Ha ha ha! Now orcs will rule over land and sea!"
msgstr "Ha ha ha! Agora os orcos gobernarán a terra e o mar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Dverag-Kukai
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:772
msgid "(Sigh) Will someone kill this fool for me, please?"
msgstr "(Suspiro) Alguén matará a este tolo por min, por favor?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:781
msgid "But... but... how can this be happening to me?"
msgstr "Canto tempo vai seguir pasando isto?"

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:791
msgid "That’s for Gwaba!"
msgstr "Iso é para Gwaba!"

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:805
msgid "Who was that fool?"
msgstr "Quen era ese tolo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:822
msgid ""
"We have the key to the cave now! Let’s stop the shaman before it’s too late."
msgstr ""
"Agora temos a chave da cova! Detemos ao xamán antes de que sexa demasiado "
"tarde."

#. [message]: speaker=Drasha
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:849
msgid "Arrgh! No! They broke my concentration — the Trident is out of control!"
msgstr ""
"¡Argh! ¡Non! Romperon a miña concentración. ¡O Tridente está fóra de control!"

#. [message]: race=merman
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:855
msgid "It was never rightfully yours."
msgstr "Nunca foi xustamente teu."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:861
msgid "I am sure the Trident will yield to <i>me</i> much more readily."
msgstr ""
"Estou seguro de que o Tridente cederá ante <i>min</i> moito máis facilmente."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:896
msgid ""
"We’re running out of time. If we cannot reclaim the Trident of Storms soon, "
"the orcs will use it to wreak great destruction upon the merfolk!"
msgstr ""
"Estamos a quedar sen tempo. Se non recuperamos pronto o Tridente das "
"Tempestades, os orcos empregarano para causar gran destrución aos habitantes "
"do mar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Drasha
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:912
msgid "Finally!"
msgstr "Por fin!"

#. [message]: speaker=Drasha
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:914
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Finally!\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The trident has yielded to my power!"
msgid "The trident has yielded to my power!"
msgstr ""
"Por fin!\n"
"\n"
"O tridente cedeu ao meu poder!"

#. [message]: speaker=Nepba
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:920
msgid "No!"
msgstr "Non!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:936
msgid ""
"We were too slow, and the merfolk’s villages have been destroyed! How could "
"I let this happen?"
msgstr ""
"Fomos demasiado lentos, e as aldeas dos habitantes do mar foron destruídas! "
"Como puiden deixar que isto pasase?"

#. [message]: race=merman
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:978
msgid ""
"Your Royal Highness, Prince Konrad, protector of the oppressed! Thank you "
"for saving us from our enemies and helping us to reclaim our sacred Trident!"
msgstr ""
"Vosa Real Altura, príncipe Konrad, protector dos oprimidos! Grazas por "
"salvarnos dos nosos inimigos e por axudarnos a recuperar o noso sagrado "
"tridente!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:982
msgid "From now on, your pearls belong to you and you alone."
msgstr "De agora en diante, as túas perlas pertencen a ti e só a ti."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:984
msgid ""
"Konrad can now recruit Merman Fighters, Hunters, Brawlers, and Initiates!"
msgstr ""
"Konrad agora pode recrutar guerreiros tritóns, cazadores, loitadores e "
"iniciados!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:987
msgid "Can we take the Trident with us? It seems like it could be very useful."
msgstr "Podemos levar o Tridente connosco? Parece que podería ser moi útil."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:992
msgid ""
"No, Konrad. It is set firmly in the rock. And for good reason, too! The "
"Trident of Storms helps maintain the delicate balance of the Bay of Pearls "
"and protects the merfolk from the fierce power of the sea."
msgstr ""
"Non, Konrad. Está firmemente asentado na rocha. E por unha boa razón! O "
"Tridente das Tormentas axuda a manter o delicado equilibrio da Baía das "
"Perlas e protexe as sereas do feroz poder do mar."

#. [message]: race=merman
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:998
msgid ""
"If it were that easy, the orcs would have looted it long ago. But no hand "
"can pry it from the rock in which it is embedded. It is just as well, for "
"its power protects my people from the often terrible power of the sea."
msgstr ""
"Se fose tan doado, os orcos xa o terían saqueado hai moito tempo. Pero "
"ningunha man pode arrincalo da rocha na que está incrustado. É mellor así, "
"porque o seu poder protexe o meu pobo do poder, a miúdo terrible, do mar."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/04_The_Bay_of_Pearls.cfg:1003
msgid "(sigh) I knew it wouldn’t be that easy."
msgstr "(suspiro) Sabía que non ía ser tan doado."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:10
msgid "scenario name^The Isle of Alduin"
msgstr "A Illa de Alduin"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:50
msgid "Yaerby"
msgstr "Aíre"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:191
msgid "Alyra"
msgstr "Alyra"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2lieutenant
#. ship can't be from Weldyn, because Elensefar might still be held by Maddock right now.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:215
msgid ""
"They’re all locked up? Good. The ship from Fort Tahn will be here any day "
"now, and then we can finally get these troublemakers off the Isle."
msgstr ""
"Están todos pechados? Ben. O barco de Fort Tahn chegará aquí calquera día, e "
"entón poderemos finalmente sacar a estes revoltosos da illa."

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:219
msgid ""
"Is all this really necessary? I mean— back in my day... Just a few drunken "
"words... Hardly worth being press-ganged, I don’t think..."
msgstr ""
"É todo isto realmente necesario? Quero dicir... na miña época... Só unhas "
"poucas palabras de borracho... Non creo que mereza a pena ser encarcerado..."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2lieutenant
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:223
msgid ""
"If we let a few apprentices speak ill of the queen, how long until they all "
"do? Don’t forget whose royal endorsement secured you your position, Seimus."
msgstr ""
"Se deixamos que uns poucos aprendices falen mal da raíña, canto tempo "
"tardarán en facelo todos? Non esquezas de quen é o respaldo real que che "
"asegurou o teu posto, Seimus."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:242
msgid ""
"Hail, scholars of Alduin! I’ve heard much about your home! I’ve even heard "
"that there are some of you brave enough to stand up to the dark queen."
msgstr ""
"Saúde, estudosos de Alduin! Xa oín falar moito do voso fogar! Incluso oín "
"que algúns de vós sodes o suficientemente valentes como para enfrontaros á "
"raíña escura."

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:246
msgid ""
"Who’re you to ask, stranger? That kind of talk can be dangerous. Did you see "
"what happened to our locked-up friends?"
msgstr ""
"Quen es ti para preguntar, forasteiro? Ese tipo de falas pode ser perigoso. "
"Viste o que lles pasou aos nosos amigos encarcerados?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:250
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Who am I? I am Konrad, son of the Prince Arand and heir to the throne of "
#| "Wesnoth! I am Asheviere’s sworn enemy, and would welcome to my cause all "
#| "who would oppose her!"
msgid ""
"Who am I? I am Konrad, son of Prince Arand and heir to the throne of "
"Wesnoth! I am Asheviere’s sworn enemy, and would welcome to my cause all who "
"would oppose her!"
msgstr ""
"Quen son eu? Son Konrad, fillo do príncipe Arand e herdeiro do trono de "
"Wesnoth! Son o inimigo xurado de Asheviere e acollería á miña causa a todos "
"os que se opoñan a ela!"

#. [message]: speaker=Alyra
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:254
msgid ""
"Konrad? The one they call “the false prince”! I— I wasn’t even sure you "
"existed!"
msgstr ""
"Konrad? Ao que chaman «o falso príncipe»! Eu... nin sequera estaba seguro de "
"que existiras!"

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:258
msgid ""
"Do you really think you can beat the queen? Is your whole rebel army here?!"
msgstr ""
"De verdade cres que podes vencer á raíña? Está aquí todo o teu exército "
"rebelde?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:262
msgid ""
"Now now, everybody just calm down. We don’t want any trouble. If you really "
"are Konrad then you’d best leave right now, before the queen’s soldiers "
"catch you."
msgstr ""
"Pois tranquilos, todos. Non queremos problemas. Se de verdade sodes Konrad, "
"mellor que marchedes agora mesmo, antes de que os soldados da raíña vos "
"atrapen."

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:266
msgid ""
"Don’t listen to him, Konrad. Soldiers from Wesnoth have locked up our "
"friends. They dared to criticize the throne, and now they’ve been both "
"expelled and imprisoned."
msgstr ""
"Non o escoites, Konrad. Soldados de Wesnoth encerraron os nosos amigos. "
"Atrevéronse a criticar o trono e agora foron expulsados e encarcerados."

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:270
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You have to help us rescue them! Many of the older apprentices here think "
#| "like Seiumus, but my friends and I will fight with you!"
msgid ""
"You have to help us rescue them! Many of the older apprentices here think "
"like Seimus, but my friends and I will fight with you!"
msgstr ""
"Tes que axudarnos a rescatalos! Moitos dos aprendices máis vellos aquí "
"pensan coma Seiumus, pero os meus amigos e eu loitaremos contigo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:274
msgid "You can now advance Mages to Red Mages!"
msgstr "Agora podes ascender os Magos a Magos Vermellos!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:275
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Mages, and advance them to (only) Red Mages!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar Magos e avanzalos a (só) Magos Vermellos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:279
msgid "Of course I will help. To battle!"
msgstr "Por suposto que axudarei. Á batalla!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:287
msgid "Reach the prisoner mages, then move one near Konrad’s keep."
msgstr ""
"Chega aos magos prisioneiros e logo move un preto da fortaleza de Konrad."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:296
msgid "Move any prisoner mage to one of the marked hexes."
msgstr "Move calquera mago prisioneiro a un dos hexágonos marcados."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:306
msgid "(gain a loyal Arch Mage)"
msgstr "(ganar un Arcanomeiro Leal)"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:314
msgid "Death of all prisoner mages"
msgstr "Morte de todas as túas unidades"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:341
msgid ""
"Seimus! My old colleague, what has come over you? There are soldiers "
"occupying the Isle and you do nothing?"
msgstr ""
"Seimus! Meu vello colega, que che ocorre? Hai soldados ocupando a Illa e ti "
"non fas nada?"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:345
msgid ""
"Delfador!? You’re here too? ...well, surely you know that Alduin is in no "
"position to oppose the crown. I mean, we’re not all cut out to be rebels "
"like you."
msgstr ""
"Delfador!? Ti tamén estás aquí? ...ben, seguramente sabes que Alduin non "
"está en posición de opoñerse á coroa. Quero dicir, non todos estamos feitos "
"para ser rebeldes coma ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:349
msgid ""
"And those chained up apprentices really are troublemakers. Really! It’s not "
"that I wouldn’t like to help. I would! But Alduin has a future to think "
"about!"
msgstr ""
"E eses aprendices encadeados son uns verdadeiros alborotadores. De verdade! "
"Non é que non me gustaría axudar. Si que o faría! Pero Alduin ten un futuro "
"no que pensar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:353
msgid ""
"You’ll recall that I was a troublemaker once. How many atrocities will "
"happen because good men like you stay silent?"
msgstr ""
"Lembrarás que eu fun un revoltoso unha vez. Cantas atrocidades sucederán "
"porque homes bos coma ti permanezan en silencio?"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2lieutenant
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:357
msgid "Ignore him, Seimus. Attack, or I will have you charged with treason!"
msgstr "Ignórao, Seimus. Ataca ou faréi que te acusen de traizón!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:361
msgid ""
"The Seimus I knew would never stoop so low! What good is a master who "
"abandons his apprentices!"
msgstr ""
"O Seimus que eu coñecía nunca se rebaixaría tanto! De que serve un mestre "
"que abandona aos seus aprendices!"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:365
msgid "Oh... well..."
msgstr "Oh... ben..."

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:375
msgid ""
"Alright. Okay! Lieutenant, I will not assist you against our own students. "
"If I am to be branded a rebel, so be it."
msgstr ""
"Moi ben. De acordo! Tenente, non o axudarei contra os nosos propios "
"estudantes. Se quero ser tachado de rebelde, que así sexa."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2lieutenant
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:379
msgid "Traitor!"
msgstr "Traidor!"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:383
msgid ""
"Delfador, I cannot fight alongside you now, but neither will I fight against "
"you. I must assemble the faculty and make clear Alduin’s new allegiance."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, non podo loitar ao teu carón agora, pero tampouco loitarei contra "
"ti. Debo reunir o profesorado e deixar clara a nova lealdade de Alduin."

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:387
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And, if you can clear Asheveire’s soldiers off the Isle entirely, I "
#| "promise to personally join your army!"
msgid ""
"And, if you can clear Asheviere’s soldiers off the Isle entirely, I promise "
"to personally join your army!"
msgstr ""
"E, se podes desfacerte por completo dos soldados de Asheveire da Illa, "
"prometo unirme persoalmente ao teu exército!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2lieutenant
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:405
msgid ""
"Seimus, don’t just stand there. There are rebels on the Isle! Put that magic "
"training to good use and throw some fireballs!"
msgstr ""
"Seimus, non te quedes aí parado. Hai rebeldes na Illa! Dalle un bo uso a ese "
"adestramento máxico e lanza algunhas bólas de lume!"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:409
msgid ""
"Rebels? Well... I mean... the worst of the trouble is more or less "
"apprentices, isn’t it? You can hardly expect faculty to fight students!"
msgstr ""
"¿Rebeldes? Ben... quero dicir... o peor dos problemas son máis ou menos os "
"aprendices, non si? É case imposible esperar que o profesorado loite contra "
"os estudantes!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2lieutenant
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:413
msgid ""
"That’s precisely what I expect, provost. There are no students in Konrad’s "
"army — only rebels. Prove your loyalty to the queen."
msgstr ""
"Iso é precisamente o que agardo, preboste. Non hai estudantes no exército de "
"Konrad, só rebeldes. Demostre a súa lealdade á raíña."

#. [message]: id=Elrian,Alyra
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:426
msgid ""
"Academy housing is down this way, Konrad. There’re many other students "
"there, but I think most of them are trying to keep their heads down."
msgstr ""
"As vivendas da academia están por aquí, Konrad. Hai moitos outros estudantes "
"alí, pero creo que a maioría deles están a intentar manter a cabeza baixa."

#. [message]: type=Shackled Mage, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:441
msgid "I hear sounds of fighting outside! Should we do something?"
msgstr "Escoito sons de pelexa fóra! Deberíamos facer algo?"

#. [message]: type=Shackled Mage, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:446
msgid "I would if I could get out of these manacles..."
msgstr "Faríao se puidese librarme destes manilles..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. [message]: speaker=leader3
#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:458
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:268
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:759
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:799
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1810
msgid "Urgh..."
msgstr "Urgh..."

#. [message]: type=Shackled Mage
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:481
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:498
msgid "Who are you! What’s going on?"
msgstr "Quen es ti! Que está a pasar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:485
msgid ""
"I’m a friend. We have to go — there’s no time to cut loose your shackles. "
"Are you willing to help us fight Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Son un amigo. Temos que ir. Non hai tempo para soltar as túas cadeas. Estás "
"disposto a axudarnos a loitar contra Asheviere?"

#. [message]: type=Shackled Mage
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:489
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:506
msgid "Better than rotting in here. Come on, everyone, we’re leaving!"
msgstr "Mellor que podrecerse aquí dentro. Imos todos, que nos imos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:502
msgid ""
"I’m a friend. Come — let us cut loose your shackles. Are you willing to help "
"us fight Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Son un amigo. Ven, imos romper as túas cadeas. Estás disposto a axudarnos a "
"loitar contra Asheviere?"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:541
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "We need more income! Start drawing on our reserves."
msgid "We need more gold! Send in the reserves."
msgstr "Necesitamos máis ingresos! Comeza a retirar das nosas reservas."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. the speaker is a level 1 "Shackled Mage", who's just received an AMLA
#. Shackled Mages are very weak, but when this scenario ends he/she will transform into a regular Mage, keeping the AMLA (including the downside: +20% XP cost)
#. this mechanic is a little silly, but not at all important to winning/losing this scenario, so we lampshade it with this line of dialogue
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:562
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "I would if I could get out of these manacles..."
msgid "I’m going to be so strong if I ever get out of these shackles..."
msgstr "Faríao se puidese librarme destes manilles..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:563
msgid "female^I’m going to be so strong if I ever get out of these shackles..."
msgstr "Vou chegar a ser moi forte se algún día consigo saír destas cadeas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:592
msgid "Wait! Stop! Please don’t kill me!"
msgstr "Espera! Para! Por favor, non me mates!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:596
msgid ""
"I’m not going to kill you, provost. But I can see that you’re a coward. Run. "
"And as long as you live, never forget what would’ve happened to your "
"apprentices had I not been here to help."
msgstr ""
"Non te vou matar, preboste. Pero vexo que es un covarde. Fuxe. E mentres "
"vivas, nunca esquezas o que lles tería pasado aos teus aprendices se eu non "
"estivese aquí para axudar."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:626
msgid "Asheviere’s armies are defeated! We’ve won!"
msgstr "Os exércitos de Asheviere están derrotados! Gañamos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:634
msgid ""
"You... you really did it! Incredible! Alduin is in your debt, Delfador. And "
"Konrad. And you apprentices too!"
msgstr ""
"Ti... de verdade o fixeches! Increíble! Alduin está en débeda contigo, "
"Delfador. E Konrad. E vós, aprendices, tamén!"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:638
msgid ""
"And, well, I made a promise to join you if you wiped those soldiers out. And "
"I intend to keep it. I place myself at your service, young master."
msgstr ""
"E, ben, fixen unha promesa de unirme a vostede se eliminaba a eses soldados. "
"E teño a intención de cumprila. Póñome ao seu servizo, mozo amo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:657
msgid ""
"We’ve done well to defeat Asheviere’s leaders on the isle, but we still need "
"to rescue the prisoners and escape before reinforcements arrive."
msgstr ""
"Fixemos ben en derrotar aos líderes de Asheviere na illa, pero aínda temos "
"que rescatar os prisioneiros e escapar antes de que cheguen reforzos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:673
msgid ""
"We set out to save lives, but we lost many more than we helped. I’m sorry we "
"couldn’t do better, but at least we’ve shown the people here that Asheviere "
"can be beaten."
msgstr ""
"Partimos para salvar vidas, pero perdemos moitas máis das que axudamos. "
"Sinto que non puidésemos facer mellor, pero polo menos demostrámoslles á "
"xente de aquí que Asheviere pode ser derrotado."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:679
msgid "We’ve saved everyone we could! Now it’s time for us to save ourselves."
msgstr ""
"Salvamos a todas as persoas que puidemos! Agora é hora de que nos salvemos "
"nós mesmos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:686
msgid ""
"Live not in fear, Alduin! Once I’m king I will return here to set things "
"right."
msgstr ""
"Non vivas con medo, Alduin! Unha vez que sexa rei volverei aquí para "
"arranxar as cousas."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:692
msgid ""
"Live not in fear, Alduin, for today proves that Asheviere can be beaten! "
"Once I’m king I will return here to set things right."
msgstr ""
"Non vivas con medo, Alduin, porque hoxe demostra que Asheviere pode ser "
"derrotado! Unha vez que sexa rei volverei aquí para arranxar as cousas."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:713
msgid ""
"All of the prisoners we set out to rescue are dead! This has been a "
"disaster..."
msgstr ""
"Todos os prisioneiros que nos propuxemos rescatar están mortos! Isto foi un "
"desastre..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:727
msgid ""
"Asheviere’s soldiers spoke of a royal ship coming to take the imprisoned "
"mages away. If we take too long to finish our work here, that ship will "
"surely arrive with reinforcements and defeat us."
msgstr ""
"Os soldados de Asheviere falaron dun barco real que viña levarse os magos "
"encarcerados. Se tardamos demasiado en rematar o noso traballo aquí, ese "
"barco seguramente chegará con reforzos e nos derrotará."

#. [message]: role=ship
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:736
msgid ""
"Hail, Alduin! We’re here on schedule with a fresh rotation of guards for the "
"garrison. It looks like you need them!"
msgstr ""
"Saúde, Alduin! Chegamos puntualmente cunha nova rotación de gardas para a "
"guarnición. Parece que os necesitas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/06_The_Isle_of_Alduin.cfg:740
msgid ""
"Oh no! Asheviere’s soldiers have been reinforced! We cannot flee while their "
"ship controls the waters, and we cannot afford the time to stop and fight..."
msgstr ""
"Oh, non! Os soldados de Asheviere recibiron reforzos! Non podemos fuxir "
"mentres o seu barco controla as augas, e non podemos permitirnos o tempo "
"para parar e loitar..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:18
msgid "scenario name^Muff Malal’s Peninsula"
msgstr "Península de Muff Malal"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:236
msgid "What’s going on here? Stop attacking that helpless man!"
msgstr "Que está a pasar aquí? Deixa de atacar ese home indefenso!"

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:240
msgid ""
"I warned you not to interrupt! I’m BUSY! And for the record, HE attacked ME, "
"while I was peacefully minding my own business killing innocent townsfolk."
msgstr ""
"Advertínche que non me interrompases! Estou OCUPADO! E para que conste, EL "
"atacoume a MIN, mentres eu estaba tranquilamente ocupado nos meus asuntos "
"matando xente inocente do pobo."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#. vague reference to the events of UtBS
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:245
msgid ""
"For at the end of days, the texts prophesy a great destruction, yea, the sun "
"itself shall rain down from the heavens as sulfur and fire!"
msgstr ""
"Porque ao final dos días, os textos profetizan unha gran destrución, si, o "
"propio sol choverá dos ceos como xofre e lume!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:249
msgid ""
"And lo! The unclean dead shall be smitten down, and lo! There shall be peace "
"eternal for all men. So readeth the texts."
msgstr ""
"E velaquí! Os mortos impuros serán abatidos, e velaquí! Haberá paz eterna "
"para todos os homes. Así lense nos textos."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:253
msgid "Yet until then, it falls to those such as me to do the smiting!"
msgstr "Ata entón, correspóndelle a xente coma min facer o golpe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:258
msgid ""
"Such an annoyance. Just stay out of my way until I’ve dealt with these "
"newcomers, will you? I’ll have plenty of time to finish you off later!"
msgstr ""
"Que molestia. Só non me estorbes ata que remate con estes recén chegados, "
"por favor? Terei tempo de sobra para acabar contigo máis tarde!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:264
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:265
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:269
msgid ""
"We must make haste if we wish to save that warrior, Konrad! I sense magical "
"power in him, but one man alone will not prevail against the hordes of "
"undead that roam this peninsula."
msgstr ""
"Debemos apurarnos se queremos salvar a ese guerreiro, Konrad! Sinto poder "
"máxico nel, pero un home só non prevalecerá fronte ás hordas de mortos "
"viventes que percorren esta península."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:266
msgid ""
"20 against 1 is pretty long odds, Konrad. If we’re goin’ to help that "
"warrior before he’s overwhelmed, we’d better hurry things up."
msgstr ""
"20 contra 1 son probabilidades bastante altas, Konrad. Se imos axudar a ese "
"guerreiro antes de que se sinta abrumado, mellor que nos demos présa."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:267
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We must make haste if we wish to save that warrior, Konrad! I sense "
#| "magical power in him, but one man alone will not prevail against the "
#| "hordes of undead that roam this peninsula."
msgid ""
"We must ride swiftly if we wish to save that warrior, Konrad! He looks to be "
"a skilled fighter, but one man alone will not prevail against the hordes of "
"undead that roam this peninsula."
msgstr ""
"Debemos apurarnos se queremos salvar a ese guerreiro, Konrad! Sinto poder "
"máxico nel, pero un home só non prevalecerá fronte ás hordas de mortos "
"viventes que percorren esta península."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:268
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We must make haste if we wish to save that warrior, Konrad! I sense "
#| "magical power in him, but one man alone will not prevail against the "
#| "hordes of undead that roam this peninsula."
msgid ""
"We should hurry if we’re hoping to save that warrior, Konrad! I sense "
"magical power in him, but one man alone will not prevail against the hordes "
"of undead that roam this peninsula."
msgstr ""
"Debemos apurarnos se queremos salvar a ese guerreiro, Konrad! Sinto poder "
"máxico nel, pero un home só non prevalecerá fronte ás hordas de mortos "
"viventes que percorren esta península."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:270
msgid ""
"20-’gainst-1 fer that warrior, now them’s long odds e’en if he were a dwarf! "
"Tha’ long-staff sixpenny sorcerer’ll be having a change o’ heart — "
"literally! — once we’re through with ’im!"
msgstr ""
"Vinte e un contra un por ese guerreiro, incluso se fose un anano, hai moitas "
"probabilidades! Ese feiticeiro de seis peniques de bastón longo vai cambiar "
"de opinión (literalmente!) unha vez que rematemos con el!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:271
msgid ""
"Oh, oh my. That magical warrior looks rather, err, powerful, doesn’t he? But "
"that’s also a lot, really quite many undead surrounding him. We’d better "
"hurry if we want to save him."
msgstr ""
"Oh, oh meu Deus. Ese guerreiro máxico parece bastante, eh, poderoso, non si? "
"Pero tamén son moitos, en realidade bastantes mortos viventes que o rodean. "
"Mellor que nos deamos présa se queremos salvalo."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:272
msgid ""
"Dat holy man be lookin’ mighty strong, but Dosh is thinking there’s too many "
"o’ dem undead e’en for him. We’d better be helpin’ him out, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"Ese home santo parece moi forte, pero Dosh pensa que hai demasiados deses "
"mortos viventes para el. Será mellor que o axudemos, Konrad."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:273
msgid ""
"We’d better move quickly and help fight! That warrior looks powerful, but "
"the necromancer has the advantage of numbers."
msgstr ""
"Mellor que nos movamos axiña e axudemos a loitar! Ese guerreiro parece "
"poderoso, pero o necromante ten a vantaxe dos números."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:277
msgid "Get ready for battle, everyone!"
msgstr "Preparádevos para a batalla, todos!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:285
msgid "Defeat Muff Malal"
msgstr "Derrota a Muff Malal"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:299
msgid "Moremirmu will join you if you move any unit adjacent to him."
msgstr "Moremirmu unirase a ti se moves calquera unidade adxacente a el."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:314
msgid ""
"I read about this place in Delfador’s books. The peninsula of pearls was "
"once home to several small towns, thriving off of the pearl trade. Farmers, "
"fishers... Muff Malal must have killed them all, while the queen’s armies "
"did nothing to help."
msgstr ""
"Lin sobre este lugar nos libros de Delfador. A península das perlas foi "
"noutro tempo o fogar de varias pequenas vilas, que prosperaban grazas ao "
"comercio de perlas. Agricultores, pescadores... Muff Malal debeu matalos a "
"todos, mentres que os exércitos da raíña non fixeron nada para axudalos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:317
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:318
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:319
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "More of her politicking, I’m afraid. By allowing necromancy to flourish "
#| "in the kingdom’s western regions, Asheviere forces us to devote time and "
#| "resources to protecting the townsfolk — time we can no longer spend "
#| "fighting her directly."
msgid ""
"More of her politicking, I fear. By allowing necromancy to flourish in the "
"kingdom’s western regions, Asheviere forces us to devote time and resources "
"to protecting the townsfolk — time we can no longer spend fighting her "
"directly."
msgstr ""
"Máis das súas políticas, temo. Ao permitir que a necromancia floreza nas "
"rexións occidentais do reino, Asheviere obríganos a dedicar tempo e recursos "
"á protección da xente do pobo; un tempo que xa non podemos empregar en "
"loitar contra ela directamente."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:320
msgid ""
"At Alduin I’ve seen students expelled just for speaking the word "
"“necromancy”. And here Asheviere won’t even act when an entire town is "
"destroyed. She’ll work with anyone she finds useful."
msgstr ""
"En Alduin vin estudantes expulsados só por pronunciar a palabra "
"“necromancia”. E aquí Asheviere nin sequera actúa cando unha vila enteira é "
"destruída. Traballará con calquera que lle resulte útil."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:321
msgid ""
"Hmmph. At Alduin we’ve expelled students just for speaking the word "
"“necromancy”. And here Asheviere won’t even act when an entire town is "
"destroyed. She’ll work with anyone she finds useful."
msgstr ""
"Hmph. En Alduin expulsamos estudantes só por pronunciar a palabra "
"“necromancia”. E aquí Asheviere nin sequera actúa cando unha vila enteira é "
"destruída. Traballará con calquera que lle resulte útil."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:322
msgid ""
"Aye, tha’ human-queen ’o yers is a filthy, white-livered, chicken-hearted "
"skinflint o’ a poltroon, she is! Dinnae you worry son, when we git our hands "
"on her ah’ll tear her queenly flesh t’ shreds!"
msgstr ""
"Si, esa raíña humana de aquí é unha tacaña sucia, de fígado branco e corazón "
"de galiña, unha auténtica canalla! Non te preocupes, fillo, cando a poñamos "
"nas nosas mans enriba faremos anacos coa súa carne de raíña!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:323
msgid ""
"She’s a real piece of work, isn’t she? I’ll bet she let this happen on "
"purpose, to keep all us rebels busy while she be livin’ luxury up in Weldyn. "
"If’n not for Baldras and Relana, one o’ these dead folk could’ve been me..."
msgstr ""
"É unha auténtica xoia, non si? Seguro que deixou que isto sucedese a "
"propósito, para manternos ocupados a todos os rebeldes mentres ela vive no "
"luxo en Weldyn. Se non fose por Baldras e Relana, un destes mortos podería "
"ter sido eu..."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:324
msgid ""
"I’ve visited this place before, to buy supplies from the fishermen... It’s "
"rather terrible to see what’s become of it now."
msgstr ""
"Xa visitei este lugar antes, para mercar provisións aos pescadores... É "
"bastante terrible ver no que foi agora."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:344
msgid ""
"Lo and behold! I stood in need of aid, and so aid has come! What brings you "
"to Muff Malal’s peninsula, pilgrims?"
msgstr ""
"E velaquí! Eu necesitaba axuda, e por iso chegou a axuda! Que vos trae á "
"península de Muff Malal, peregrinos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:348
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am Konard, heir to the throne of Wesnoth, and seeking to reclaim my "
#| "seat from the evil queen Asheviere! Who are you?"
msgid ""
"I am Konrad, heir to the throne of Wesnoth, and seeking to reclaim my seat "
"from the evil queen Asheviere! Who are you?"
msgstr ""
"Son Konard, herdeiro ao trono de Wesnoth, e busco reclamar o meu asento da "
"malvada raíña Asheviere! Quen es ti?"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:352
msgid ""
"Brother Moremirmu, wandering warrior, at your service. Rejoice, for it seems "
"the strands of fate have brought us here together, that we may unite in arms "
"towards the vanquishing of evil!"
msgstr ""
"Irmán Moremirmu, guerreiro errante, ao teu servizo. Alégrate, porque semella "
"que os fíos do destino nos trouxeron aquí xuntos, para que poidamos unirnos "
"en armas para vencer o mal!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:357
msgid ""
"Aid me in my quest against this foul necromancer, and I shall ever-more be "
"your loyal companion in the eternal war against the darkness!"
msgstr ""
"Axúdame na miña misión contra este nefasto necromante, e para sempre serei o "
"teu leal compañeiro na guerra eterna contra a escuridade!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:373
msgid ""
"The Light rebukes you, foul creature of the night! In a blaze of brilliance "
"shall you be purged!"
msgstr ""
"A Luz repréndete, criatura vil da noite! Nun resplandor de brillo serás "
"purificado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:388
msgid "Curse you all! The queen promised I would be left in peace here..."
msgstr ""
"Malditos sexades todos! A raíña prometeu que me deixarían en paz aquí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:404
msgid ""
"Ugh, forget this! I’m not wasting any more time here with you — time for my "
"dashing escape!"
msgstr ""
"Uf, esquece isto! Non vou perder máis tempo aquí contigo — é hora da miña "
"fuxida apurada!"

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:422
msgid ""
"Gah, where did all these piranhas come from? There’s too much rotting meat "
"in the water!"
msgstr ""
"Buf, de onde viñeron todas estas pirañas? Hai demasiada carne podre na auga!"

#. [message]: speaker=Muff Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:429
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "<i>(Gurgle gurgle gurgle...)</i>"
msgid "(Gurgle gurgle gurgle...)"
msgstr "<i>Gorgol gorgol gorgol...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:444
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:452
msgid ""
"The necromancer is defeated, and the countryside is safe once more! Good "
"work, everybody."
msgstr ""
"O necromante foi derrotado e o campo está a salvo unha vez máis! Bo traballo "
"a todos."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:456
msgid ""
"The Light shall always find the Light, and so have I found you! Let us quest "
"on together in opposition to the dark queen!"
msgstr ""
"A Luz sempre atopará a Luz, e eu tamén te atopei a ti! Sigamos xuntos na "
"nosa misión contra a raíña escura!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/07_Muff_Malals_Peninsula.cfg:461
msgid ""
"The necromancer is defeated, and the countryside is safe once more! I am "
"sorry that Moremirmu has perished, but at least he did not die in vain. Now "
"we must continue onwards!"
msgstr ""
"O necromante foi derrotado e o campo está a salvo unha vez máis! Síntoo que "
"Moremirmu morrese, pero polo menos non morreu en balde. Agora debemos "
"continuar!"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:8
msgid "scenario name^Isle of the Damned"
msgstr "Illa dos Condenados"

#. [side]: type=Bone Shooter, id=leader3
#. [side]: type=Necrophage, id=leader4
#. [side]
#. [side]: type=Deathblade, id=leader3
#. [side]: type=Skeleton Archer, id=leader4
#. [side]: type=Revenant, id=leader5
#. [side]: type={TYPE}, id={ID}
#. [side]: type=Death Knight, id=Lionel
#. [side]: type=Death Squire, id=leader2
#. [side]: id=leader2, type=Death Knight
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:51
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:70
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:55
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:73
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:74
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:92
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:109
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:59
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:46
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:35
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:51
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:50
msgid "Undead"
msgstr "Non mortos"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:143
msgid "Hello? Is anybody here?"
msgstr "Ola? Hai alguén aquí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:153
msgid ""
"I’m nearly blind in this fog, but I think I see a hovel off in the distance."
msgstr "Case estou cego nesta néboa, pero creo que vexo unha casucha ao lonxe."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:181
msgid "Freeze! Drop the sword, or we won’t hesitate to run ye through."
msgstr "Conxela! Deixa caer a espada ou non dubidaremos en atravesarte."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:185
msgid "(This keeps getting worse...)"
msgstr "(Isto vai a peor...)"

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:189
msgid "How many of ye are there? How did she find out about us! Speak, vermin!"
msgstr ""
"Cantos de vós sodes? Como descubriu ela a nosa existencia? Falade, bichos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:191
msgid "This is the worst timing... an’ us fighting without Harper too..."
msgstr "Isto é o peor momento... e nós loitando sen Harper tamén..."

#. [message]: type=Thug
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:195
msgid ""
"I dunno, Delurin. They’re a mean lot, but they don’t much look like "
"Asheviere’s. It’s been a long time since we ’ad to put down any of her goons."
msgstr ""
"Non sei, Delurin. Son un grupo malvado, pero non se parecen moito aos de "
"Asheviere. Fai moito tempo que non acabamos con ningún dos seus matóns."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:199
msgid ""
"Peace, friends! I mean you no harm, and I’m no servant of Asheviere’s! My "
"name is Konrad. I’m a prince, nephew of Garard, son of Arand and rightful "
"heir to Wesnoth!"
msgstr ""
"Paz, amigos! Non vos pretendo ningún dano, e non son servo de Asheviere! "
"Chámome Konrad. Son príncipe, sobriño de Garard, fillo de Arand e lexítimo "
"herdeiro de Wesnoth!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:203
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Konrad? I’ve heard of the prince Konrad... You might be he, or you "
#| "mightn’t."
msgid ""
"Konrad? I’ve heard of Prince Konrad... You might be he, or you mightn’t."
msgstr ""
"Konrad? Xa oín falar do príncipe Konrad... Pode que o sexas ou pode que non."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:211
msgid "You say you’re a friend, an’ that’s worth something at least."
msgstr "Dices que es amigo, e iso polo menos vale algo."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:215
msgid ""
"I’ll give you a chance to prove yerself, boy. We’ve been havin’ trouble with "
"some bestial undead on the isle. Our leader is missing, and without ’er "
"we’re struggling to fight back."
msgstr ""
"Dareiche unha oportunidade para demostrar o que vales, rapaz. Temos tido "
"problemas con algúns mortos viventes bestiais na illa. O noso líder "
"desapareceu e, sen el, estamos a ter dificultades para defendernos."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:219
msgid ""
"But the real Konrad’d be a great general; he’d have no trouble beating down "
"the dead. Lead us against the corpses, prince, and we’ll see just how "
"genuine you are. I’ll be watching."
msgstr ""
"Pero o verdadeiro Konrad sería un gran xeneral; non tería ningún problema en "
"derrotar os mortos. Guíanos contra os cadáveres, príncipe, e veremos o "
"xenuíno que es. Estarei vixilando."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:264
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Thugs and Footpads!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar matóns e salteadores!"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:292
msgid "Death of Delurin"
msgstr "Morte de Delurin"

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:319
msgid ""
"Undead in th’ heart o’ town! I’m glad Baldras didn’t live to see this..."
msgstr ""
"Mortos viventes no corazón da cidade! Alégrome de que Baldras non vivise "
"para ver isto..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:335
msgid ""
"This crypt was once grand, but now all has gone to rot. There’s nothing of "
"value here."
msgstr ""
"Esta cripta foi noutro tempo magnífica, pero agora todo está a podrecer. "
"Aquí non hai nada de valor."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:347
msgid "This crypt is shallow and dry, and there’s 20 gold inside!"
msgstr "Esta cripta é pouco profunda e seca, e hai 20 de ouro dentro!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:364
msgid ""
"This crypt is deep, and a foul stench wafts up from below. There’s something "
"near the entrance."
msgstr ""
"Esta cripta é profunda, e un fedor nauseante sobe desde abaixo. Hai algo "
"preto da entrada."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:372
msgid "Gah, undead!"
msgstr "Gah, non morto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#. hint to the player that one crypt contains gold, but another contains undead
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:425
msgid ""
"Watch out around those crypts, Konrad. This whole undead problem only "
"started after our leader went down into one of them looking for treasure."
msgstr ""
"Ten coidado arredor daquelas criptas, Konrad. Todo este problema de mortos "
"viventes só comezou despois de que o noso líder baixase a unha delas en "
"busca de tesouros."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:429
msgid ""
"She’s still down in there, somewhere. But we can’t do much to help now, not "
"till we deal with them that’s up here an’ fightings us."
msgstr ""
"Ela aínda está aí abaixo, nalgún lugar. Pero non podemos facer moito para "
"axudar agora, non ata que nos ocupemos dos que están aquí arriba e loitan "
"contra nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:448
msgid ""
"Not bad, prince. Maybe you is who you says you is after all. But there’s "
"still more of ’em out there to fight."
msgstr ""
"Non está mal, príncipe. Quizais sexas quen dis que es despois de todo. Pero "
"aínda hai máis deles por aí contra os que loitar."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:462
msgid ""
"That’s the last of ’em! The Three Sisters is safe. You done well, kid — I’m "
"sorry we threatened you."
msgstr ""
"Ese é o último deles! As Tres Irmás están a salvo. Fixéchelo ben, rapaz. "
"Síntoo que te ameazamos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:466
msgid ""
"Your threats would have been your end, had you tried to carry them out. But "
"I understand: you’ve been out here so long that you’ve forgotten what a "
"friendly face looks like."
msgstr ""
"As túas ameazas terían sido o teu fin se intentaras levalas a cabo. Pero "
"entendo: levas tanto tempo aquí fóra que esqueciches como é unha cara amable."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:470
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Ain’t that the truth. Been nigh—on—20 years since we fled our homes, "
#| "since that stinker Asheviere warned us to swear fealty or die. We ain’t "
#| "no friends of hers, and we’d be honored to join you on the rest of yer "
#| "journey."
msgid ""
"Ain’t that the truth. Been nigh on 20 years since we fled our homes, since "
"that stinker Asheviere warned us to swear fealty or die. We ain’t no friends "
"of hers, and we’d be honored to join you on the rest of yer journey."
msgstr ""
"Non é iso a verdade? Pasaron case... 20 anos dende que fuximos dos nosos "
"fogares, dende que esa apestosa Asheviere nos advertiu de xurar lealdade ou "
"morrer. Non somos amigos dela, e seríamos unha honra para nós acompañarvos "
"no resto da vosa viaxe."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:488
msgid "Some leader you are. I’m glad Baldras didn’t live to see this..."
msgstr "Que líder es. Alégrome de que Baldras non vivise para ver isto..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:502
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Hurry it up, “prince Konrad”! There’s friends of mine in trouble, and we "
#| "can’t do naught about it until these undead are finished!"
msgid ""
"Hurry it up, “Prince Konrad”! There’s friends of mine in trouble, and we "
"can’t do naught about it until these undead are finished!"
msgstr ""
"¡Date présa, «príncipe Konrad»! Hai amigos meus en apuros, e non podemos "
"facer nada ata que rematemos con estes mortos viventes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delurin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08a_Isle_of_the_Damned_part1.cfg:509
msgid ""
"This is taking too long. ’s what I get for trusting a “prince”; we should’ve "
"dealt with these dead by ourselves from the beginning."
msgstr ""
"Isto está a levar demasiado tempo. Isto é o que me sae por confiar nun "
"\"príncipe\"; deberiamos ter nos ocupados destes mortos nós mesmos desde o "
"principio."

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:98
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:33
msgid "Beasts"
msgstr "Bestas"

#. [scenario]: id=08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:151
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:167
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:183
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:199
msgid "Midnight Queen"
msgstr "Raíña de Medianoite"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:282
msgid ""
"Here we are: the entrance to the island catacombs. The source of the undead "
"must be down here somewhere... and the outlaw leaders, if they’re still "
"alive."
msgstr ""
"Aquí estamos: a entrada ás catacumbas da illa. A fonte dos mortos viventes "
"debe estar aquí abaixo nalgún lugar... e os líderes foraxidos, se é que "
"aínda están vivos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:286
msgid ""
"If Delurin’s guess is correct, this place goes on for miles. We may have to "
"split up if we want to search the whole thing in decent time."
msgstr ""
"Se a adiviña de Delurin é correcta, este lugar esténdese quilómetros. Pode "
"que teñamos que separarnos se queremos rexistralo todo con tempo decente."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:294
msgid "Find and destroy the source of the undead"
msgstr "Atopa e destrúe a fonte dos mortos viventes"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. saying "500 years" is important, as the vampire lady says it takes her 500 years to regenerate after being destroyed. 500 years ago is when Haldric arrived and destroyed her the first time
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:314
msgid ""
"I wonder who built this place, and for what purpose? The handiwork doesn’t "
"look dwarvish, but it’s far too old to have been tunneled by men. Their— "
"err, our kind has barely been on the Great Continent for 500 years!"
msgstr ""
"Pregúntome quen construíu este lugar e con que propósito? A obra non parece "
"anana, pero é demasiado antiga para que fose escavada por homes. A súa... "
"eh, a nosa especie apenas leva 500 anos no Gran Continente!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:317
msgid ""
"Aye, ain’t no dwarf-tunnels, that’s for sure. Jus’ look at them ugly, lumpy "
"walls! Whoever made this place weren’t no troll, neither."
msgstr ""
"Si, non hai túneles de ananos, iso seguro. Mira eses muros feos e "
"irregulares! Quen fixo este lugar non foi ningún trol."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:318
msgid ""
"I have heard stories of this place; the isle of Lilanas. Elves once lived "
"here. But that was long ago, before even my time."
msgstr ""
"Teño oído historias deste lugar; a illa de Lilanas. Os elfos viviron aquí "
"noutro tempo. Pero iso foi hai moito tempo, mesmo antes da miña época."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:319
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:320
msgid ""
"I detect powerful magic down in these tunnels, Konrad, very old magic. But I "
"can’t speak as to its origin."
msgstr ""
"Detecto unha maxia poderosa nestes túneles, Konrad, unha maxia moi antiga. "
"Pero non podo dicir nada sobre a súa orixe."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:321
msgid ""
"There is a dark presence here, Konrad, foul; something that has rejected the "
"Light and hides deep within this place. Beyond that I cannot say."
msgstr ""
"Hai aquí unha presenza escura, Konrad, fétida; algo que rexeitou a Luz e se "
"agocha no máis profundo deste lugar. Máis aló non podo dicir."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:322
msgid ""
"Well, err — the architecture is... ah, old. Mermish? Elvish, perhaps? But "
"these caves are certainly natural. Someone found the caves and took up, err, "
"residence?"
msgstr ""
"Ben, eh... a arquitectura é... ah, antiga. Mermish? Elvish, quizais? Pero "
"estas covas son sen dúbida naturais. Alguén descubriu as covas e instalouse, "
"eh, alí?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:323
msgid ""
"Dis not a troll hole, Konrad. But not a dwarf hole neither. An’ Dosh dunno "
"who else be livin’ in caves."
msgstr ""
"Non é unha cova de trol, Konrad. Pero tampouco unha cova de ananos. E non "
"sei quen máis vive en covas."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:343
msgid ""
"I smell clean fresh air, and spray laced with salt! Nearby lies the ocean; "
"we will find no undead this way."
msgstr ""
"Cheiro o aire fresco e limpo, e salpicaduras de sal! Preto atópase o océano; "
"non atoparemos mortos viventes por aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#. tell the player that they don't need to fight the giant spiders to win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:358
msgid ""
"A nest of giant spiders! I’ve heard terrible stories about the awful danger "
"of these creatures. There’s certainly no undead anywhere inside their lair; "
"perhaps if we keep our distance they will leave us alone."
msgstr ""
"Un niño de arañas xigantes! Xa escoitei historias terribles sobre o perigo "
"que supoñen estas criaturas. Sen dúbida, non hai mortos viventes en ningún "
"lugar do seu covo; quizais, se mantemos a distancia, nos deixen en paz."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:370
msgid ""
"A revenant! That thing is a capable fighter, but such a mindless creature "
"could not have cast the spells needed to raise his fellows. There must be a "
"necromancer or lich somewhere else within these caverns."
msgstr ""
"Un resucitado! Esa cousa é unha loitadora capaz, pero unha criatura tan sen "
"mente non podería lanzar os feitizos necesarios para criar os seus "
"compañeiros. Debe haber un necromante ou un lich noutro lugar dentro destas "
"cavernas."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:378
msgid ""
"Well done, everyone! We’ve beaten one group of undead, but the source behind "
"this dark magic is still at large."
msgstr ""
"Ben feito, a todos! Derrotamos un grupo de mortos viventes, pero a fonte "
"detrás desta maxia escura aínda está en liberdade."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:391
msgid ""
"That’s the last of the spider! A difficult fight, but we’ve gained valuable "
"experience."
msgstr ""
"Iso é o último da araña! Unha loita difícil, pero gañamos unha valiosa "
"experiencia."

#. [message]: speaker=Vampire
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:410
msgid ""
"Welcome, strangers, to the boudoir of the midnight queen. It’s been so many "
"years since I’ve had such handsome visitors."
msgstr ""
"Benvidos, estranxeiros, ao boudoir da raíña da medianoite. Fai tantos anos "
"que non tiven visitantes tan apuestos."

#. [message]: speaker=Vampire
#. exactly what she says to Haldric in TRoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:417
msgid "You will be made to serve... Come admire me. Feel my love."
msgstr "Serás obrigado a servir... Ven admirarme. Sente o meu amor."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:422
msgid "She’s... She’s beautiful..."
msgstr "Ela é... Ela é fermosa..."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:427
msgid ""
"Knock it off, lady! Don’t any of you listen to her, she’s nothing but an "
"illusion!"
msgstr "¡Para xa, señora! Que ninguén a escoite, non é máis que unha ilusión!"

#. [message]: speaker=Vampire
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:443
msgid ""
"Insolent man-lings! I was immortal queen of this isle since before your kind "
"had learned to walk! You will learn to show proper respect!"
msgstr ""
"Homes insolentes! Eu era a raíña inmortal desta illa desde antes de que a "
"vosa especie aprendese a camiñar! Aprenderedes a mostrar o debido respecto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:459
msgid "Hey. I’m Harper. Aren’t you a sight for sore eyes."
msgstr "Ola. Son Harper. Non es un pracer para a vista?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:463
msgid ""
"You’re the leader of the outlaws? Err, we came to rescue you, and to put an "
"end to the undead threat on the isle. What happened in this place?!"
msgstr ""
"¿Es o líder dos foras da lei? Ehm, viñemos rescatarte e poñer fin á ameaza "
"dos mortos viventes na illa. ¿Que pasou neste lugar?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:467
msgid ""
"Well... some weeks ago I led some hunters down here lookin’ fer magic, "
"treasure, anythin’ that could help really make a difference ’gainst that "
"stinker Queen Asheviere. Really thought I’d found somethin’ too."
msgstr ""
"Ben... hai unhas semanas levei aquí a uns cazadores en busca de maxia, "
"tesouros, calquera cousa que puidese axudar de verdade a marcar a diferenza "
"contra esa pútrida raíña Asheviere. Eu tamén pensei que atopara algo."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:471
msgid ""
"’stead all my hard work just got people killed. I awoke that “Midnight "
"Queen”, an’ now I’m the last one of us who came down here what’s left "
"alive..."
msgstr ""
"En vez diso, todo o meu traballo duro acabou coa morte de xente. Despertei a "
"\"Raíña da Medianoite\", e agora son a última de nós que baixou aquí, a que "
"queda viva..."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:475
msgid ""
"But there be no time for talk. C’mon, we gots to finish her off afore she "
"gets her glamour put back on!"
msgstr ""
"Pero non hai tempo para falar. Vaia, temos que rematala antes de que lle "
"volvan poñer o seu glamour!"

#. [message]: speaker=Vampire
#. This is an elven druid from long, long ago, now turned to a lich. "Lilanas" is her name for "The Three Sisters"
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:492
msgid ""
"Fools! You mayflies cannot kill me! I am the greatest of the druids of "
"Lilanas; my spirit is the isle’s wind, my bones its earth, my blood its "
"beasts!"
msgstr ""
"Tolos! Vós, efemerógrafas, non me podedes matar! Son o maior dos druídas de "
"Lilanas; o meu espírito é o vento da illa, os meus ósos a súa terra, o meu "
"sangue as súas bestas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Vampire
#. it's been a little over 500 years since Haldric arrived, fought, and killed her. Now she's back - and killed again for another 500 years
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:497
msgid ""
"You may destroy me now, but in 500 years I shall return! So long as the isle "
"stands... I shall always return..."
msgstr ""
"Podes destruírme agora, pero dentro de 500 anos volverei! Mentres a illa "
"exista... sempre volverei..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:505
msgid "Death to tyrants, now and forevermore!"
msgstr "Morte aos tiranos, agora e para sempre!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:509
msgid "... do you think she meant what she said about returning in 500 years?"
msgstr ""
"... cres que ela quería dicir o que dixo sobre volver dentro de 500 anos?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:512
msgid ""
"Sure, aye, when trolls fly! Ah ain’t never heard such a lot o’ "
"ninnyhammerin’ tripe since th’ last time my pa’ got too deep in ’is drink. "
"We got nothin’ to worry about."
msgstr ""
"Claro, si, cando os troles voan! Ah, nunca escoitei tantas callosidades "
"dende a última vez que meu pai se meteu demasiado na súa bebida. Non temos "
"nada do que preocuparnos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:513
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:514
msgid ""
"Whatever powers she had in life or undeath, there’s no magic that can revive "
"the dead. I don’t think we have anything to worry about."
msgstr ""
"Sexan cales fosen os poderes que tiña en vida ou na non vida, non hai maxia "
"que poida revivir aos mortos. Non creo que teñamos nada de que preocuparnos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:515
msgid ""
"An accursed curse by an accursed creature, Konrad! Even in death, she still "
"aims to beguile us with her foul lies."
msgstr ""
"Unha maldición maldita por unha criatura maldita, Konrad! Mesmo na morte, "
"ela aínda pretende enganarnos coas súas repugnantes mentiras."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:519
msgid ""
"C’mon, let’s be gettin’ back to the village. And on the way, you boys better "
"be tellin’ me just who exactly you all are."
msgstr ""
"Imos, volvamos á aldea. E polo camiño, rapaces, mellor que me digades quen "
"sodes exactamente."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:536
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We musn’t take too long down here. The air is foul and growing fouler by "
#| "the minute; if we cannot defeat the leader of the undead, we shall soon "
#| "be forecd to return to the surface."
msgid ""
"We musn’t take too long down here. The air is foul and growing fouler by the "
"minute; if we cannot defeat the leader of the undead, we shall soon be "
"forced to return to the surface."
msgstr ""
"Non podemos demorar demasiado aquí abaixo. O aire é viciado e cada vez máis "
"pútrido; se non podemos derrotar ao líder dos mortos viventes, pronto nos "
"veremos obrigados a volver á superficie."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/08b_Isle_of_the_Damned_part2.cfg:543
msgid ""
"I can barely continue to breathe in air so foul, much less fight. I am sorry "
"to flee, but if we stay here any longer we shall surely suffocate."
msgstr ""
"Apenas podo seguir respirando un aire tan fétido, e moito menos loitar. "
"Síntoo moito ter que fuxir, pero se quedamos aquí máis tempo, seguro que "
"afogaremos."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:16
msgid "The Siege of Elensefar"
msgstr "O cerco de Elensefar"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:83
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:54
msgid "Agadla"
msgstr "Agadla"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:84
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:55
msgid "Drodrish"
msgstr "Drodrish"

#. [event]
#. "Daneth" is the name of Lord Maddock's late son, as referenced in Liberty. This ship also appears in Liberty's S04, with the same name.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:457
msgid "The Daneth"
msgstr "O Daneth"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:458
msgid "Elyn's Folly"
msgstr "A loucura de Elyn"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:459
msgid "Charlock"
msgstr "Charlock"

#. [message]: speaker=wesnoth4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:542
msgid ""
"Push, you blaggards! We take the isle or it’s back to the gallows for us all!"
msgstr "Empuxade, parvos! Tomamos a illa ou volvemos todos á forca!"

#. [message]: speaker=wesnoth4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:563
msgid ""
"Damnations, still no progress! The defenders can’t keep this up forever — "
"prepare another assault."
msgstr ""
"Maldicións, aínda non hai progreso! Os defensores non poden seguir así para "
"sempre. Preparade outro asalto."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:623
msgid ""
"Welcome to Elensefar, young master. Delfador has told me a great deal about "
"you over the years! If you truly possess the potential that he claims, now "
"is the time to start living up to it."
msgstr ""
"Benvido a Elensefar, xove amo. Delfador contoume moitas cousas sobre ti ao "
"longo dos anos! Se realmente posúes o potencial que el afirma, agora é o "
"momento de comezar a estar á altura."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:629
msgid ""
"As you can see we’re hard-pressed, for Asheviere’s loyalists besiege the "
"south bridge while orcs push in from the north. Every attack has been "
"repelled, but that lieutenant of theirs is right about one thing — we can’t "
"keep it up forever."
msgstr ""
"Como podedes ver, estamos en apuros, xa que os fieis de Asheviere asedian a "
"ponte sur mentres os orcos avanzan desde o norte. Todos os ataques foron "
"repelidos, pero ese tenente seu ten razón nunha cousa: non podemos seguir "
"así para sempre."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:633
msgid ""
"Sir Kaylan sends his regards, Lord Maddock. Konrad has brought the knights "
"of Blackwater Port to stand with you."
msgstr ""
"Sir Kaylan envía os seus saúdos, señor Maddock. Konrad trouxo os cabaleiros "
"de Blackwater Port para loitar ao teu lado."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:634
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Got yourself into trouble again, Madock? Ain’t no cursed soldiers this "
#| "time, but we’re still here to help."
msgid ""
"Got yourself into trouble again, Maddock? Ain’t no cursed soldiers this "
"time, but we’re still here to help."
msgstr ""
"Metecheste en problemas outra vez, Madock? Esta vez non hai soldados "
"malditos, pero aínda estamos aquí para axudar."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:635
msgid ""
"Ah’m not afraid! Jus’ give the word an’ I’ll see them chicken-hearted pox "
"wrinklers clear back to Weldyn!"
msgstr ""
"Non teñas medo! Avisade e eu axudarei a eses malvados da varicela a volver a "
"Weldyn!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:636
msgid ""
"The dark queen’s shadow spreads, but the Light shall burn her back! We shall "
"stand together against the darkness!"
msgstr ""
"A sombra da raíña escura esténdese, pero a Luz queimará as súas costas! "
"Enfrontarémonos xuntos á escuridade!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:637
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We’re here to help, Lord Maddock. Elensefar has long been a bastion of "
#| "freedom against Asheviere’s tyrrany. We can’t let it fall!"
msgid ""
"We’re here to help, Lord Maddock. Elensefar has long been a bastion of "
"freedom against Asheviere’s tyranny. We can’t let it fall!"
msgstr ""
"Estamos aquí para axudar, Lord Maddock. Elensefar leva moito tempo sendo un "
"baluarte da liberdade fronte á tiranía de Asheviere. Non podemos deixalo "
"caer!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:641
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Exposing yourself here is a great risk, master Konrad. But your position "
#| "behind enemy lines does afford us opportunity for a counterattack."
msgid ""
"Exposing yourself here is a great risk, Master Konrad. But your position "
"behind enemy lines does afford us opportunity for a counterattack."
msgstr ""
"Expoñerse aquí é un gran risco, mestre Konrad. Pero a súa posición detrás "
"das liñas inimigas ofrécenos a oportunidade de contraatacar."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:645
msgid ""
"If you can defeat enough of their leaders to break the siege, the remainder "
"will most certainly be forced to withdraw."
msgstr ""
"Se podes derrotar a suficientes dos seus líderes para romper o asedio, o "
"resto seguramente verase obrigado a retirarse."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:649
msgid "I won’t let you down, Delfador. Prepare for battle!"
msgstr "Non te defraudarei, Delfador. Prepárate para a batalla!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:660
msgid "Defeat any $leaders_to_kill enemy leaders"
msgstr "Derrota a calquera líder inimigo $leaders_to_kill"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. $leaders_to_kill is always 3. $leaders_killed will be either 1 or 2.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:668
msgid "Defeat any $leaders_to_kill enemy leaders ($leaders_killed defeated)"
msgstr ""
"Derrota a calquera líder inimigo $leaders_to_kill ($leaders_killed derrotado)"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:680
msgid "Death of Lord Maddock"
msgstr "Morte do Lord Maddock"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:699
msgid "It’s good to see you again, Delfador. I’m glad you’re still okay!"
msgstr "Que ben verte de novo, Delfador. Alégrome de que aínda esteas ben!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:703
msgid ""
"Alive and kicking indeed, young master. But there is no time for idle "
"chatter."
msgstr "Vivo e coleando, mozo amo. Pero non hai tempo para charlas ociosas."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:717
msgid ""
"Tried t’ tell you this would happen, Maddock. You shoulda fought with us "
"back when the going was better."
msgstr ""
"Intentei dicirche que isto ía pasar, Maddock. Deberías ter loitado connosco "
"cando as cousas ían mellor."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:721
msgid ""
"You’ll recall that I did, through my son. It is not by mere chance that "
"Elensefar has been kept free thus far, and nor is it by chance that it will "
"stay that way today."
msgstr ""
"Recordarás que o fixen a través do meu fillo. Non é por mera casualidade que "
"Elensefar se manteña libre ata agora, e tampouco é por casualidade que hoxe "
"siga así."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:755
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "What’s this? Lord Maddock, master Konrad, I scry many small ships coming "
#| "down the river! An ill tiding indeed, for they carry fresh fighters from "
#| "Weldyn."
msgid ""
"What’s this? Lord Maddock, Master Konrad, I scry many small ships coming "
"down the river! An ill tiding indeed, for they carry fresh fighters from "
"Weldyn."
msgstr ""
"Que é isto? Señor Maddock, mestre Konrad, diviso moitas naves pequenas "
"baixando polo río! Unha mala nova, de feito, pois levan novos combatentes de "
"Weldyn."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:759
msgid ""
"Impossible! What remains of the royal fleet already withdrew to the "
"blockade; they don’t have the numbers for another amphibious attack."
msgstr ""
"Imposible! O que queda da frota real xa se retirou ao bloqueo; non teñen "
"efectivos para outro ataque anfibio."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:800
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Damn... converted smallcraft. I shouldn’t have committed so many warships "
#| "to the bridge defense.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Charlock, move to intercept! Those transports must not be allowed to land "
#| "on the isle!"
msgid ""
"Damn... converted smallcraft. I shouldn’t have committed so many warships to "
"the bridge defense."
msgstr ""
"Maldita sexa... pequenas naves convertidas. Non debería ter destinado tantos "
"buques de guerra á defensa da ponte.\n"
"\n"
"Charlock, móvete para interceptar! Non se debe permitir que eses transportes "
"desembarquen na illa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:802
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Damn... converted smallcraft. I shouldn’t have committed so many warships "
#| "to the bridge defense.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Charlock, move to intercept! Those transports must not be allowed to land "
#| "on the isle!"
msgid ""
"Charlock, move to intercept! Those transports must not be allowed to land on "
"the isle!"
msgstr ""
"Maldita sexa... pequenas naves convertidas. Non debería ter destinado tantos "
"buques de guerra á defensa da ponte.\n"
"\n"
"Charlock, móvete para interceptar! Non se debe permitir que eses transportes "
"desembarquen na illa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:839
msgid ""
"Elensefar Isle. Good work everyone — they weren’t ready for us to press the "
"Carcyn fishers into service. But our fight’s not done yet."
msgstr ""
"Illa de Elensefar. Bo traballo a todos. Non estaban preparados para que nós "
"obrigásemos aos pescadores de Carcyn a entrar en servizo. Pero a nosa loita "
"aínda non rematou."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:848
msgid ""
"Secure a beachhead and prepare to receive the rest of the boats. We must act "
"swiftly, before they can pivot their defenses."
msgstr ""
"Asegurade unha cabeza de praia e preparádevos para recibir o resto dos "
"barcos. Debemos actuar con rapidez antes de que poidan virar as súas "
"defensas."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:858
msgid ""
"We meet again, princess! I’ve beaten you before, and I’ll do so again. "
"Elensefar deserves a better ruler than you."
msgstr ""
"Volvemos a encontrarnos, princesa! Xa che gañei antes e fareino de novo. "
"Elensefar merece un gobernante mellor que ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:862
msgid ""
"Konrad. I underestimated you once before — never again. You should have "
"picked a different battle, princeling."
msgstr ""
"Konrad. Xa te subestimei unha vez... nunca máis. Deberías ter escollido unha "
"batalla diferente, principiño."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:867
msgid ""
"Your Highness, we meet at last! I’ve heard stories about the battles you’ve "
"won in your mother’s name. I won’t let Elensefar be one of them!"
msgstr ""
"Vosa Alteza, por fin nos atopamos! Escoitei historias das batallas que "
"vostede gañou en nome da súa nai. Non deixarei que Elensefar sexa unha delas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:871
msgid ""
"Hello, “Konrad.” I think you’re a little out of your depth, pretender — the "
"battlefield is no place for a con man."
msgstr ""
"Ola, «Konrad». Creo que estás un pouco fóra de lugar, farsante. O campo de "
"batalla non é lugar para un estafador."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:875
msgid ""
"Your lies have sown enough discord and chaos among my people. How convenient "
"that you’re here; I can capture both you and Maddock at the same time."
msgstr ""
"As túas mentiras sembraron xa abondo discordia e caos entre o meu pobo. Que "
"conveniente que esteas aquí; podo capturar tanto a ti como a Maddock ao "
"mesmo tempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:887
msgid ""
"You’ve been a capable lord, Maddock, and from what I can tell you truly care "
"about your city. If it’s any consolation, when all’s said and done I intend "
"to make sure you stand a fair trial."
msgstr ""
"Fuches un señor capaz, Maddock, e polo que podo ver realmente te preocupas "
"pola túa cidade. Se che serve de consolo, cando todo isto remate, teño a "
"intención de asegurarme de que teñas un xuízo xusto."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:891
msgid ""
"As for you, Delfador... you’re going to regret what you did to my brother."
msgstr ""
"En canto a ti, Delfador... vas arrepentirte do que lle fixeches ao meu irmán."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:895
msgid ""
"Elensefar has weathered countless storms, Your Highness. Your queen will be "
"neither the first nor the last that breaks upon our shores."
msgstr ""
"Elensefar capeou incontables tormentas, Alteza. A súa raíña non será nin a "
"primeira nin a última en chegar ás nosas costas."

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:916
msgid "{ON_DIFFICULTY4 15 25 30 40} gold"
msgstr "{ON_DIFFICULTY4 15 25 30 40} ouro"

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:927
msgid "{ON_DIFFICULTY4 10 15 20 25} gold"
msgstr "{ON_DIFFICULTY4 10 15 20 25} ouro"

#. [message]: role=lisar_skiff
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:973
msgid "—how did you know?! It seems I’m not half so clever as I thought."
msgstr ""
"—como o soubeches?! Parece que non son nin a metade de listo do que pensaba."

#. [message]: role=lisar_skiff
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:979
msgid ""
"You win this round, Konrad. I need to get out of here before this boat takes "
"any more damage."
msgstr ""
"Gañas esta rolda, Konrad. Teño que marchar de aquí antes de que este barco "
"sufra máis danos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:998
msgid ""
"My last landed boat is badly damaged! I hate to retreat, but I can’t risk "
"being trapped here and captured."
msgstr ""
"O meu último bote en terra está moi danado! Detesto retirarme, pero non podo "
"arriscarme a quedar atrapado aquí e capturado."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1015
msgid ""
"You prove your skills once again, cousin. A worthy foe indeed... Elensefar "
"survives another day."
msgstr ""
"Demóstras de novo as túas habilidades, curmán. Un inimigo digno, sen "
"dúbida... Elensefar sobrevive un día máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1020
msgid ""
"I underestimated you, “cousin” — it seems you’re more than just a good actor "
"and a pretty face. I may be forced to flee the field today, but this isn’t "
"over."
msgstr ""
"Subestimeite, \"curmán\" — parece que es algo máis que un bo actor e unha "
"cara bonita. Pode que hoxe me vexa obrigado a fuxir do campo, pero isto non "
"rematou."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1056
msgid ""
"That’s the first of the besieging leaders defeated! Keep pressing the attack!"
msgstr ""
"Ese é o primeiro dos líderes sitiadores derrotado! Segue presionando o "
"ataque!"

#. [message]: race=orc
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1087
msgid ""
"Forget this! I was promised an easy fight full of plunder, not a flank and a "
"rout! Deal with your problems yourselves, pink-skins."
msgstr ""
"Esquecede isto! Prometéronme unha loita fácil chea de botín, non un flanco e "
"unha derrota! Ocupádevos dos vosos problemas vós mesmos, peles rosas."

#. [message]: id=(self.hitpoints>0)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1093
msgid ""
"They’ve gone. I hate to retreat, but without support I can’t risk being "
"trapped here and captured. We came so, so close to taking the city!"
msgstr ""
"Xa se foron. Odeio ter que retroceder, pero sen apoio non me podo arriscar a "
"quedar atrapado aquí e ser capturado. Estivemos tan, tan preto de tomar a "
"cidade!"

#. [message]: id=(self.hitpoints>0)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1098
msgid ""
"They’ve gone. I hate to retreat, but without support I can’t risk being "
"trapped here and captured. We already pushed dangerously hard just to get "
"this far."
msgstr ""
"Xa se foron. Odeio ter que retroceder, pero sen apoio non me podo arriscar a "
"quedar atrapado aquí e ser capturado. Xa empurramos perigosamente forte só "
"para chegar ata aquí."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1110
msgid "Useless orcs! You were hired for a siege, not a rout!"
msgstr ""
"Orcos inútiles! Fostes contratados para un cerco, non para unha desbandada!"

#. [message]: id=Lisar {OR( side=2,3,4 {AND canrecruit=yes} )}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1115
msgid ""
"I hate to retreat, but we’re already overextended pushing this far into the "
"city. With the north shore fallen, I can’t risk the whole army any further. "
"We came so, so close to taking the city!"
msgstr ""
"Detesto ter que retirarme, pero xa estamos sobrecargados de tropas "
"adentrándonos ata aquí na cidade. Coa costa norte caída, non podo arriscar "
"máis a todo o exército. Estivemos tan, tan preto de tomar a cidade!"

#. [message]: id=Lisar {OR( side=2,3,4 {AND canrecruit=yes} )}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1120
msgid ""
"I hate to retreat, but with the north shore fallen we have little hope of "
"taking the city. We already pushed dangerously hard just to get this far — I "
"can’t risk things any further."
msgstr ""
"Detesto ter que retirarme, pero coa costa norte caída temos poucas "
"esperanzas de tomar a cidade. Xa presionamos perigosamente só para chegar "
"ata aquí; non podo arriscarme máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1139
msgid "We’ve driven them back! The siege of Elensefar is over!"
msgstr "Os repelimos! O cerco de Elensefar rematou!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1143
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Well done, Konrad. I was worried when you decided to join the fight, but "
#| "Maddock and I could not have carried the day without your help. Together "
#| "we have won a great victory over tyrrany."
msgid ""
"Well done, Konrad. I was worried when you decided to join the fight, but "
"Maddock and I could not have carried the day without your help. Together we "
"have won a great victory over tyranny."
msgstr ""
"Ben feito, Konrad. Preocupábame cando decidiches unirte á loita, pero "
"Maddock e eu non poderiamos ter triunfado sen a túa axuda. Xuntos obtivemos "
"unha gran vitoria contra a tiranía."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1147
msgid ""
"Pigs will fly before the silver city bows to any queen. After the thrashing "
"we gave them, they won’t return anytime soon."
msgstr ""
"Os porcos voarán antes de que a cidade prateada se incline ante calquera "
"raíña. Despois da malleira que lles demos, non volverán axiña."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1151
msgid ""
"Konrad, Elensefar is in your debt today. What soldiers I can spare are now "
"yours to command — as well as many of the Elensefar thieves’ guild’s more "
"enterprising young robbers."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, Elensefar está hoxe en débeda contigo. Os soldados que teño "
"dispoñibles agora están ao teu mando, así como a moitos dos mozos ladróns "
"máis emprendedores da asociación de ladróns de Elensefar."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1153
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Swordsmen, Pikemen, and Thieves!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar espadachines, piqueiros e ladróns!"

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1156
msgid "May they serve you well. Keep up the good fight, my lord."
msgstr "Que che sirvan ben. Continúa na boa loita, meu señor."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1178
msgid ""
"Sirs, we’re running low on supplies. We have only a few more chances to take "
"Elensefar castle’s storerooms before we’ll be forced to retreat!"
msgstr ""
"Señores, estamos a quedar sen subministracións. Só nos quedan unhas poucas "
"oportunidades de tomar os almacéns do castelo de Elensefar antes de verte "
"obrigado a retirarnos!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1182
msgid ""
"Bah, this is starting to get ridiculous. I’m not sticking around forever, no "
"matter what your queen promises me!"
msgstr ""
"Bah, isto comeza a ser ridículo. Non vou quedar por aquí para sempre, non "
"importa o que me prometa a túa raíña!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1193
msgid ""
"Forget this! I was promised an easy fight full of plunder, not this siege "
"that never ends! Deal with your problems yourselves, pink-skins."
msgstr ""
"Esquecédeo! Prometéronme unha loita fácil chea de botín, non este asedio que "
"nunca remata! Ocupádevos vós mesmos dos vosos problemas, peles rosas."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1197
msgid ""
"I hate to retreat, but we’re already overextended pushing just this far. We "
"already exerted ourselves dangerously hard — I can’t risk things any further."
msgstr ""
"Detesto ter que retirarme, pero xa estamos sobrecargados de esforzo ata "
"aquí. Xa nos esforzamos perigosamente; non podo arriscarme máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1211
msgid "I surrender! I am beaten!"
msgstr "Réndome! Estou derrotado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/10_Elensefar_Before.cfg:1215
msgid "Alas, Maddock has capitulated. Elensefar is lost!"
msgstr "Ai, Maddock capitulou. Elensefar está perdida!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:230
msgid "Fine, you idiots can keep the north shore! Orcs, retreat to the city."
msgstr ""
"Ben, idiotas podedes quedar coa costa norte! Orcos, retirádevos á cidade."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:236
msgid "Fine, you idiots can keep the south shore! Orcs, retreat to the city."
msgstr ""
"Ben, idiotas podedes quedar coa costa sur! Orcos, retirádevos á cidade."

#. [message]: speaker=foxtail1
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:291
msgid ""
"Hahaha, this town is great! Top-quality slaves, houses made with real "
"shingles, and all the gold and silver in the world!"
msgstr ""
"Hahaha, esta vila é xenial! Escravos de primeira calidade, casas feitas con "
"tellas de verdade e todo o ouro e a prata do mundo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:319
msgid ""
"If Asheviere has truly given Elensefar to the orcs like they claim, it can "
"only be because she expects them to ravage it."
msgstr ""
"Se Asheviere realmente lles deu Elensefar aos orcos como afirman, só pode "
"ser porque agarda que a devasten."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:323
msgid ""
"She must believe the people will never submit to her rule, and would rather "
"ruin them entirely than risk another revolt. How awful."
msgstr ""
"Ela debe crer que o pobo nunca se someterá ao seu goberno, e preferiría "
"arruinalo por completo antes que arriscarse a outra revolta. Que horrible."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:327
msgid "We can’t let that happen. To arms, warriors!"
msgstr "Non podemos permitir que iso aconteza. A armas, guerreiros!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:333
msgid "Five"
msgstr "Cinco"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:333
msgid "Four"
msgstr "Catro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:333
msgid "Three"
msgstr "Tres"

#. [note]
#. $thief_count will be the word "Three" "Four" or "Five"
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:347
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "{ON_DIFFICULTY4 Three Four Five Five} thieves/rogues will join your "
#| "attack once you capture any village on one of Elensefar’s islands."
msgid ""
"$thief_count thieves/rogues will join your attack once you capture any "
"village on one of Elensefar’s islands."
msgstr ""
"Os ladróns/pícaros {ON_DIFFICULTY4 Tres Catro Cinco Cinco} uniranse ao teu "
"ataque unha vez que captures calquera aldea nunha das illas de Elensefar."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:364
msgid ""
"Look, Konrad! I see a human fording the river, sneaking out of the city "
"towards us."
msgstr ""
"Mira, Konrad! Vexo un humano vadeando o río, saíndo da cidade ás agachadas "
"cara a nós."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:365
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:366
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:367
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Look, Konrad! I see a human fording the river, sneaking out of the city "
#| "towards us."
msgid ""
"Look, Konrad! A man is fording the river, sneaking out of the city towards "
"us."
msgstr ""
"Mira, Konrad! Vexo un humano vadeando o río, saíndo da cidade ás agachadas "
"cara a nós."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:368
msgid ""
"Look there, boy! One o’ ’em city-folk’s gone yellow. I think he’s sneakin’ "
"out to see us."
msgstr ""
"Mira alí, rapaz! Un deses da cidade púxose amarelo. Creo que vén vernos ás "
"agachadas."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:369
msgid ""
"Look, Konrad! Someone’s fording the river, sneakin’ out to see us. How is he "
"movin’ across the deep water?!"
msgstr ""
"Mira, Konrad! Alguén está a vadear o río, a saír ás agachadas para vernos. "
"Como se move polas augas fondas?!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:370
msgid ""
"Hark, Konrad! One of the cityfolk steals across the river towards our shore!"
msgstr ""
"Escoita, Konrad! Un dos cidadáns cruza o río furtivamente cara á nosa beira!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:371
msgid ""
"Oh, hello? Err... I think I see — yes, Konrad, someone’s sneaking across the "
"river towards us."
msgstr ""
"Ola? Eh... Creo que vexo... si, Konrad, alguén está cruzando o río "
"furtivamente cara a nós."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:372
msgid ""
"Look there, Konrad. Dosh is seein’ a softskin sneakin’ across dis river "
"towards us."
msgstr ""
"Mira alí, Konrad. Dosh está a ver unha criatura de pel branda que cruza este "
"río furtivamente cara a nós."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:373
msgid ""
"Look, someone’s fording the river! I think he’s sneaking out of the city "
"towards us."
msgstr ""
"Mirade, alguén está a vadear o río! Creo que está saíndo da cidade ás "
"agachadas cara a nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:384
msgid "Halt! Who goes there, friend or foe?"
msgstr "Alto! Quen vai alí, amigo ou inimigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:388
msgid ""
"Greetings, friend. I am Reglok, guildmaster of the Elensefar thieves. We "
"would like to help you against the orcs."
msgstr ""
"Saúdos, amigo. Son Reglok, mestre do gremio dos ladróns de Elensefar. "
"Queremos axudarte contra os orcos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:392
msgid ""
"I know the sort of aid offered by a thief, Reglok. We do not trust you and "
"we do not need you."
msgstr ""
"Sei o tipo de axuda que ofrece un ladrón, Reglok. Non confiamos en ti e non "
"te necesitamos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:393
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I know the sort of aid offered by a thief, Reglok. We do not trust you "
#| "and we do not need you."
msgid ""
"Is that so? What honor is there among thieves? We do not trust you and we do "
"not need you."
msgstr ""
"Sei o tipo de axuda que ofrece un ladrón, Reglok. Non confiamos en ti e non "
"te necesitamos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:394
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:395
msgid ""
"I don’t like the idea of working with thieves. Who says we can trust you? We "
"should send him on his way, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"Non me gusta a idea de traballar con ladróns. Quen di que podemos confiar en "
"ti? Deberiamos mandalo polo seu camiño, Konrad."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:396
msgid ""
"Aye, sure ye do. An’ as soon as our backs are turned we’ll find yer fingers "
"down our purses an’ yer knives stickin’ out o’ our spleens! What sort o’ "
"chucklehead do ye take me for?"
msgstr ""
"Si, claro que si. E en canto nos dean as costas atoparemos os vosos dedos "
"nos petos e os vosos coitelos saíndo dos bazos! Por que clase de parvo me "
"tomades?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:397
msgid "Uh huh. I’ve dealt with thieves before. What’s in it for you, Reglok?"
msgstr ""
"Ah, si. Xa me enfrontéi a ladróns antes. Que gañas ti con isto, Reglok?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:398
msgid ""
"There is no Light within you, thief. You lie and you steal and you kill. Who "
"says we can trust such as you?"
msgstr ""
"Non hai luz en ti, ladrón. Mentes, roubas e matas. Quen di que podemos "
"confiar en alguén coma ti?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:399
msgid ""
"That’s very kind of you to offer! But, well, you’re a thief? The lying and "
"stealing and... killing kind of thief?"
msgstr ""
"É moi amable da túa parte ofrecerllo! Pero, bueno, es un ladrón? Do tipo de "
"ladrón que mente, rouba e... mata?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:400
msgid ""
"Dosh not be trustin’ any thief. Dosh know what thieves do. Lie and steal and "
"kill."
msgstr ""
"Non te fías de ningún ladrón. Sabes o que fan os ladróns. Mentir, roubar e "
"matar."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:401
msgid "Thieves, hmmm? Who says we can trust such as you?"
msgstr "Ladróns, hmmm? Quen di que podemos confiar en xente coma vós?"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:405
msgid ""
"We would understand if you didn’t trust us, of course, but it is in our "
"mutual interest to rid the city of the orcs. Since Lord Maddock was dragged "
"off in chains, our new overlords have done nothing but riot and steal. That "
"infringes on our monopoly."
msgstr ""
"Entenderíamos se non confías en nós, por suposto, pero está no noso interese "
"mutuo librar a cidade dos orcos. Desde que o señor Maddock foi arrastrado "
"encadeado, os nosos novos señores non fixeron máis que saquear e roubar. Iso "
"infrinxe o noso monopolio."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:409
msgid ""
"You shall find that there is honor, even among thieves. We served Maddock "
"well, and if you can liberate Elensefar we shall do the same for you."
msgstr ""
"Descubrirás que hai honra mesmo entre ladróns. Servimos ben a Maddock, e se "
"podes liberar Elensefar, faremos o mesmo por ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:413
msgid "Yes, but where is your fighting force? How can you help us?"
msgstr "Si, pero onde está o teu exército? Como nos podes axudar?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:419
msgid "five"
msgstr "cinco"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:419
msgid "four"
msgstr "catro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:419
msgid "three"
msgstr "tres"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:425
msgid ""
"There is a hidden ford on the southwest side of the city, but coming from "
"the north that shall be of little use. Instead, we shall lay in wait until "
"you give us a signal then ambush the orcs’ rear."
msgstr ""
"Hai un vado oculto no lado suroeste da cidade, pero chegando dende o norte "
"iso servirá de pouco. En vez diso, agardaremos ata que nos deas un sinal e "
"logo emboscaremos a retagarda dos orcos."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#. $thief_count will be the word "three" "four" or "five"
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:430
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "When you raise your blue banner over any village in the city proper, we "
#| "will see the sign and attack from the city’s center. Expect "
#| "{ON_DIFFICULTY4 three four five five} of us to join the attack."
msgid ""
"When you raise your blue banner over any village in the city proper, we will "
"see the sign and attack from the city’s center. Expect $thief_count of us to "
"join the attack."
msgstr ""
"Cando ences o teu estandarte azul sobre calquera aldea do núcleo urbano, "
"veremos o sinal e atacaremos dende o centro da cidade. Agarda que "
"{ON_DIFFICULTY4 tres catro cinco cinco} de nós se unan ao ataque."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:434
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:519
msgid "Agreed. But, will you be able to see our flag if it’s dark?"
msgstr "De acordo. Pero, poderás ver a nosa bandeira se está escuro?"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:438
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:523
msgid ""
"Yes, we will see it. In fact, we prefer to fight at night. I pray you do not "
"lead us into slaughter."
msgstr ""
"Si, o veremos. De feito, preferimos loitar pola noite. Rezo para que non nos "
"conduzas á matanza."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:442
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:527
msgid ""
"Do not fear, friends. There will be a slaughter here, but it will be orcish "
"blood staining the streets."
msgstr ""
"Non teñades medo, amigos. Haberá unha masacre aquí, pero será sangue orco "
"manchando as rúas."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:454
msgid ""
"Information, child. There is a hidden ford on the southwest side of the "
"city. Very few people know about it, least of all the orcs. I can show you "
"how to cross."
msgstr ""
"Información, rapaza. Hai un vao agochado no lado suroeste da cidade. Moi "
"pouca xente o sabe, e menos os orcos. Podo amosarche como cruzalo."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#. $thief_count will be the word "three" "four" or "five"
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:459
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Alternatively, we can lay in wait until you give us a signal then ambush "
#| "the orcs’ rear. Expect {ON_DIFFICULTY4 three four five five} of us to "
#| "join the attack."
msgid ""
"Alternatively, we can lay in wait until you give us a signal then ambush the "
"orcs’ rear. Expect $thief_count of us to join the attack."
msgstr ""
"Como alternativa, podemos esperar ata que nos deas un sinal e logo emboscar "
"a retagarda dos orcos. Agarda que {ON_DIFFICULTY4 three four five five} de "
"nós nos unamos ao ataque."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:468
msgid "Help us infiltrate the city. We can do the rest."
msgstr "Axúdanos a infiltrarnos na cidade. Nós podemos facer o resto."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:472
msgid "Very well. Watch exactly where I step."
msgstr "Moi ben. Mira exactamente onde piso."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:501
msgid ""
"You see? When the tide is at its lowest, the turbulent waters reveal a ford "
"wide enough for two soldiers to march shoulder-to-shoulder. The orcs know "
"not where to step. Now you do."
msgstr ""
"Ves? Cando a marea está no seu punto máis baixo, as augas turbulentas "
"revelan un vado tan amplo que dous soldados poden marchar ombreiro con "
"ombreiro. Os orcos non saben onde pisar. Agora ti xa o sabes."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:505
msgid "Good luck. You shall see me again if you succeed."
msgstr "Boa sorte. Verásme de novo se tes éxito."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:511
msgid "I want you to reinforce us once we break through their line."
msgstr "Quero que nos reforces unha vez que rompamos a súa liña."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:515
msgid ""
"Very well. When you raise your blue banner over any village in the city "
"proper, we will see the sign and attack from the city’s center."
msgstr ""
"Moi ben. Cando ences a túa bandeira azul sobre calquera aldea do núcleo "
"urbano, veremos o sinal e atacaremos desde o centro da cidade."

#. [message]: speaker=foxtail1
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:547
msgid "What!? How are you walking on water?"
msgstr "Que!? Como estás a camiñar sobre a auga?"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:567
msgid ""
"That’s their banner! Let’s expel these invaders. Today, the city is ours "
"again!"
msgstr ""
"Esa é a súa bandeira! Expulsemos a estes invasores. Hoxe, a cidade é nosa de "
"novo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:610
msgid ""
"We tried t’ tell Maddock this would happen. We had a real chance after "
"Halstead fell, back when his son helped us fight."
msgstr ""
"Intentamos dicirlle a Maddock que isto ía pasar. Tivemos unha verdadeira "
"oportunidade despois de que caeu Halstead, cando o seu fillo nos axudou a "
"loitar."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:614
msgid ""
"I suppose he kept his city safe for a while. But were it worth it in the end?"
msgstr ""
"Supoño que mantivo a súa cidade segura durante un tempo. Pero, ao final, "
"valeu a pena?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:636
msgid "Arrgh! Lousy humans..."
msgstr "Arrgh! Humanos miserables..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. I say that the orc wasn't actually wearing the sandals, because otherwise we'd have to change his behavior in-game
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:648
msgid ""
"Look — that orc had in his pouch some strange, magical-looking sandals, "
"likely looted from some wealthy merchant or ship captain. They seem oddly "
"dry, despite the water all around."
msgstr ""
"Mira... ese orco tiña na súa bolsa unhas sandalias estrañas, de aspecto "
"máxico, probablemente roubadas a algún rico comerciante ou capitán de barco. "
"Parecen estrañamente secas, a pesar da auga que hai ao redor."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:655
msgid "Seafarer’s Sandals"
msgstr "Sandalias do mariñeiro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:656
msgid ""
"This enchanted footwear repels nearby water, allowing\n"
"its wearer to walk on water, swamp, or snow as if standing on solid ground."
msgstr ""
"Este calzado encantado repele a auga próxima, permitindo ao seu portador "
"camiñar sobre a auga, o pantán ou a neve como se estivese sobre terra firme."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:662
msgid ""
"Magic of this caliber is most rare and hard-to-come-by! I shall wear them "
"myself, and be grateful for the boon. Now, to finish off the remaining "
"orcish leader."
msgstr ""
"A maxia deste calibre é moi rara e difícil de conseguir! Eu mesmo as levarei "
"postas e estarei agradecido pola bendición. Agora, a rematar co líder orco "
"restante."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:676
msgid "I’m not dying! Orcs never die! I just... need a moment..."
msgstr "Non estou morrendo! Os orcos nunca morren! Só... preciso un momento..."

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:684
msgid ""
"Well done, well done! Elensefar is finally rid of those loathsome beasts."
msgstr ""
"Ben feito, ben feito! Elensefar finalmente está libre desas bestas "
"repulsivas."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:688
msgid ""
"You walk free once more! But for how long? Once we leave, who will remain to "
"defend the bridges?"
msgstr ""
"Camiñas libre unha vez máis! Pero por canto tempo? Cando nos marchemos, quen "
"quedará para defender as pontes?"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:692
msgid ""
"They say the best defense is a good offense, no? I place the thieves of "
"Elensefar in your service, your exaltedness, ready to take the fight to the "
"dark queen."
msgstr ""
"Din que a mellor defensa é un bo ataque, non? Póñoos os ladróns de Elensefar "
"ao voso servizo, vosa exaltaidade, listos para levar a loita á raíña escura."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:694
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Thieves!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar ladróns!"

#. [message]: speaker=Reglok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:697
msgid ""
"I myself must of course remain behind to oversee the city. You understand."
msgstr "Eu mesmo teño que quedar atrás para supervisar a cidade. Enténdes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:701
msgid ""
"All too well. Rule wisely, ambitious Reglok, for I shall return to Elensefar "
"once Asheviere is defeated and I am king. Prove yourself a better lord than "
"the orcs."
msgstr ""
"Moi ben. Goberna con sabedoría, ambicioso Reglok, porque volverei a "
"Elensefar unha vez que Asheviere sexa derrotado e eu sexa rei. Demostra que "
"es mellor señor que os orcos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:720
msgid ""
"Between the siege and our attack, Elensefar has been badly damaged. "
"Countless townsfolk will die if we cannot finish things off soon!"
msgstr ""
"Entre o asedio e o noso ataque, Elensefar sufriu graves danos. Innumerables "
"habitantes morrerán se non podemos rematar todo pronto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/11_Elensefar_After.cfg:727
msgid ""
"Our battle has dragged on too long; Elensefar is all but destroyed. Even if "
"we defeat these orcs, the city will never-again return to its former "
"splendor..."
msgstr ""
"A nosa batalla prolongouse demasiado; Elensefar está practicamente "
"destruída. Mesmo se derrotamos a estes orcos, a cidade nunca volverá ao seu "
"antigo esplendor..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:18
msgid "scenario name^Fort Tahn"
msgstr "Fort Tahn"

#. [side]: type=Master Bowman, id=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:47
msgid "Fort Tahn Garrison"
msgstr "Guarnición Fort Tahn"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:160
msgid ""
"Villains! You have pillaged a great treasure from the halls of my home. "
"Return it at once, and your lives may yet be spared!"
msgstr ""
"Viláns! Pillastes un gran tesouro dos corredores da miña casa. Devolvedo de "
"inmediato e aínda podedes salvar as vosas vidas!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader3
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:164
msgid "You— you’re Konrad! The false prince himself, here?!"
msgstr "Ti… ti es Konrad! O propio príncipe falso, aquí?!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:168
msgid ""
"I’m not about to surrender myself nor my property to a rebel! To arms, "
"loyalists, and make ready to repel the invaders!"
msgstr ""
"Non vou entregarme nin as miñas propiedades a un rebelde! Ás armas, leais, e "
"preparádevos para repeler os invasores!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:172
msgid ""
"It is war, then. Such an insult against my Aethenwood kin shall not go "
"unpunished."
msgstr ""
"É guerra, entón. Semellante insulto contra os meus parentes de Aethenwood "
"non quedará impune."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:180
msgid "Defeat the Master Bowman"
msgstr "Derrota ao Arcoeiro Mestre"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:214
msgid ""
"Seeing all this stolen gold and broken treasures kindles a great coldness in "
"my heart. Asheviere has much to pay for..."
msgstr ""
"Ver todo este ouro roubado e tesouros rotos acende unha gran frialdade no "
"meu corazón. Asheviere ten moito que pagar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:239
msgid ""
"You dare use that bow against us? The Moonbows belong to the elves; you know "
"nothing about them and have no right to lay a hand on one!"
msgstr ""
"¿Atreves a usar ese arco contra nós? Os arcos lunares pertencen aos elfos; "
"non sabes nada deles e non tes ningún dereito a poñerlles a man enriba!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:243
msgid ""
"I know enough: I’ve trained in archery my entire life and never seen a bow "
"to rival this one. Fighting with it is my best chance at beating you!"
msgstr ""
"Eu sei dabondo: adestrei tiro con arco toda a miña vida e nunca vin un arco "
"que puidese rivalizar con este. Loitar con el é a miña mellor oportunidade "
"de vencerte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:274
msgid "One leader has been defeated, but he is not the one who holds the bow."
msgstr "Un líder foi derrotado, pero non é el quen empuña o arco."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:294
msgid ""
"The rebels are too powerful! Mercy, Konrad! I’m just doing my duty to defend "
"my country, as ordered by my sovereign, the queen!"
msgstr ""
"Os rebeldes son demasiado poderosos!  Misericordia, Konrad!  Só estou "
"cumprindo co meu deber de defender o meu país, como ordenou a miña soberana, "
"a raíña!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:298
msgid ""
"Surrender your elven weapon, and swear an oath to never again take up arms "
"against me or my allies. I am the true sovereign in Wesnoth, and will give "
"you but one chance at redemption."
msgstr ""
"Entrega a túa arma élfica e xura nunca máis empuñar as armas contra min nin "
"contra os meus aliados. Son o verdadeiro soberano en Wesnoth e só che darei "
"unha oportunidade de redención."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:302
msgid ""
"But Asheviere will kill me! ...I suppose you will too. If you really are the "
"heir, and an elf-lover besides, then I suppose our pillage does most "
"rightfully belong to you. Here, take it, and leave the rest of us alive!"
msgstr ""
"Pero Asheviere mataráme!... Supoño que ti tamén o farás. Se de verdade es o "
"herdeiro, e ademais un amante dos elfos, entón supoño que o noso botín che "
"pertence por dereito. Toma, tómao e déixanos vivos ao resto!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:328
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:501
msgid "You have gained 300 gold!"
msgstr "Gañaches 300 ouro!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:351
msgid ""
"As for the rest of you — begone! Return to your homes in Westin and never "
"again trouble my people, lest the wrath of the elves fall upon you!"
msgstr ""
"En canto ao resto de vós... idevos! Voltade aos vosos fogares en Westin e "
"nunca máis molestade á miña xente, non vaia ser que a ira dos elfos caia "
"sobre vós!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:352
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And that goes for the rest of you too! Return to your homes in Westin, "
#| "and trouble the Aethenwood no more."
msgid ""
"Your master has fled — now begone, servants of the false queen! Return to "
"your homes in Westin, and trouble the true heir no more."
msgstr ""
"E iso tamén se aplica ao resto de vós! Voltade aos vosos fogares en Westin e "
"non molestedes máis o Bosque de Aethen."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:353
msgid ""
"Hah! Yeah, you’d better run! And that goes for the rest of you, too, now "
"that your leader has fled!"
msgstr ""
"Ha! Si, mellor será que fuxas! E iso vai tamén para o resto de vós, agora "
"que o voso líder fuxiu!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:354
msgid ""
"An’ that goes for th’ rest o’ you too! Get out o’ here, an’ tell Westin we "
"sent you!"
msgstr ""
"E iso tamén se aplica ao resto de vós! Saíde de aquí e dille a Westin que "
"vos enviamos nós!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:355
msgid ""
"And the rest of you — begone! For lo! The Light stands with Konrad, and only "
"those of darkness dare to oppose him."
msgstr ""
"E o resto de vós... idevos! Porque mirade! A Luz está con Konrad, e só os da "
"escuridade se atreven a opoñerse a el."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:356
msgid ""
"An’ that goes for th’ rest o’ you too, ye horse-faced sons o’ elves! Run "
"back to Westin afore I boil yer kneecaps inside yer skulls!"
msgstr ""
"E iso tamén se aplica ao resto de vós, fillos de elfos con cara de cabalo! "
"Correde de volta a Westin antes de que vos ferva as rótulas dentro dos "
"cranios!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:358
msgid ""
"Da rest of you better be leavin’ now too. Konrad good troll-friend. You don’ "
"wanna see what troll do to you if you keep fightin’ Konrad."
msgstr ""
"É mellor que o resto de vós tamén marchedes agora. Konrad, bo amigo trol. "
"Non queres ver o que che fará o trol se segues loitando contra Konrad."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:359
msgid ""
"And that goes for the rest of you too! Return to your homes in Westin, and "
"trouble the Aethenwood no more."
msgstr ""
"E iso tamén se aplica ao resto de vós! Voltade aos vosos fogares en Westin e "
"non molestedes máis o Bosque de Aethen."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. Konrad is level 1, and does not have a bow attack. Once he reaches level 2 and gains a bow attack, the Moonbow will strengthen it.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:371
msgid ""
"With that, Fort Tahn is ours, the Aethenwood’s gold reclaimed, and this "
"Moonbow recaptured! Once my archery improves I shall take it for my own, and "
"someday wield it in battle against the dark queen. May its silver never "
"tarnish."
msgstr ""
"Con iso, Fort Tahn é noso, o ouro de Aethenwood recuperado e este Arco Lunar "
"recapturado! Cando a miña habilidade co arco mellore, fareino meu e algún "
"día empuñareino na batalla contra a raíña escura. Que a súa prata nunca se "
"oxide."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:376
msgid ""
"With that, Fort Tahn is ours, the Aethenwood’s gold reclaimed, and this "
"Moonbow recaptured! Once peace is restored this weapon belongs back in the "
"Aethenwood, but for now I choose to wield it in battle against the dark "
"queen. May its silver never tarnish."
msgstr ""
"Con iso, Fort Tahn é noso, o ouro do Bosque de Aethenwood recuperado e este "
"Arco Lunar recapturado! Unha vez restablecida a paz, esta arma pertencerá de "
"novo ao Bosque de Aethenwood, pero de momento elixo empunhaláa na batalla "
"contra a raíña escura. Que a súa prata nunca se oxide."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:385
msgid "Elvish Moonbow"
msgstr "Arco da vella elfo"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:386
msgid ""
"This magical weapon adds 3 strikes, the <i>slows</i> special, and the "
"<i>arcane</i> special to Konrad’s bow attacks."
msgstr ""
"Esta arma máxica engade 3 golpes, o especial <i>de ralentización</i> e o "
"especial <i>arcanico</i> aos ataques de arco de Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:401
msgid ""
"The false prince is proving a more difficult foe that I had expected. Some "
"soldiers left for Westin not long ago — I’d better send a messenger and call "
"them back to help."
msgstr ""
"O falso príncipe está a resultar un inimigo máis difícil do que eu esperaba. "
"Algúns soldados partiron para Westin non hai moito; mellor que envíe un "
"mensaxeiro e os chame para que volvan axudar."

#. [message]: role=reinforcement
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:416
msgid ""
"You called for aid, Castellan? We’ve come to fight, and the Westin militia "
"is not far behind!"
msgstr ""
"Pediches axuda, Castellán? Viñemos loitar, e a milicia de Westin non está "
"lonxe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/13_Fort_Tahn.cfg:420
msgid ""
"We’ve taken too long to sack the fort, and now more soldiers have arrived! "
"Even if we defeat them all, we’ll suffer greatly from the delay..."
msgstr ""
"Levamos demasiado tempo para saquear o forte, e agora chegaron máis "
"soldados! Mesmo se os derrotamos a todos, sufriremos moito polo atraso..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:8
msgid "scenario name^Gryphon Mountain"
msgstr "Monte Gryphon"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:37
msgid "Burlin’s Crew"
msgstr "A tripulación de Burlin"

#. [side]: type=Gryphon, id=Mother Gryphon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:65
msgid "Mother Gryphon"
msgstr "Máter Gryphon"

#. [side]: type=Gryphon, id=Mother Gryphon
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:72
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:109
msgid "Gryphons"
msgstr "Grifóns"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:167
msgid ""
"The fabled Gryphon Mountain! It’s not the tallest mountain in Wesnoth, nor "
"the widest, but is held in renown by poets and scholars alike for the "
"beautiful gryphons who come here to nest. It’s nice to take a break from all "
"our fighting and experience nature."
msgstr ""
"O lendario Monte dos Grifóns! Non é a montaña máis alta de Wesnoth, nin a "
"máis ancha, pero é recoñecida tanto por poetas como por estudosos polos "
"fermosos grifóns que veñen aquí aniñar. É agradable facer unha pausa de "
"todas as nosas loitas e experimentar a natureza."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:172
msgid "Hey! Hey, kid!"
msgstr "Ei! Ei, neno!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:177
msgid ""
"You look like a strapping young lad! What do you say about doin’ a bit o’ "
"work for old uncle Burlin?"
msgstr ""
"Pareceches un rapaz forte e robusto! Que dis a facer un pouco de traballo "
"para o vello tío Burlin?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:181
msgid "I might be interested. What kind of work?"
msgstr "Podería interesarme. Que tipo de traballo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:185
msgid ""
"The <b><i>best</i></b> kind o’ work: well-paying! I’s got a contract to "
"collect fifty gryphon eggs, see? But I ain’t excited to risk my crew’s lives "
"on the job."
msgstr ""
"O <b><i>mellor</i></b> traballo: ben remunerado! Teño un contrato para "
"recoller cincuenta ovos de grifón, ves? Pero non me entusiasma arriscar as "
"vidas da miña tripulación no traballo."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:189
msgid ""
"So, I say you an’ I make a deal. You kill off the gryphons for me, an’ when "
"I make my sale t’ the queen I’ll split the profit with ye’, 70-30."
msgstr ""
"Entón, eu fago un trato. Mata os grifóns por min e, cando lle faga a venda á "
"raíña, repartirei o beneficio contigo, 70-30."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:193
msgid ""
"The queen? You’re working for Asheviere?! I’d never ally myself with such a "
"villain!"
msgstr ""
"A raíña? Estás a traballar para Asheviere?! Nunca me aliaría cun vilán así!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:197
msgid ""
"... well aye, o’ course I’m workin’ for her! Ain’t this the middle o’ "
"Wesnoth? Who else would be in charge, that good-for-nothin’ rebel Konrad? Hey"
"— did I say 70-30? I meant 50-50!"
msgstr ""
"... pois si, claro que estou traballando para ela! Non é isto o centro de "
"Wesnoth? Quen máis estaría ao mando, ese rebelde inútil de Konrad? Ei... "
"dixen 70-30? Quería dicir 50-50!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:202
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Tha’s a ripe load o’ tripe if ah’ve e’er heard one! What kind o’ dwarf-"
#| "traitor slackjaw gives up ’is own kind? An’ this IS the prince Konrad, "
#| "you numbskull! Show some respect!"
msgid ""
"Tha’s a ripe load o’ tripe if ah’ve e’er heard one! What kind o’ dwarf-"
"traitor slackjaw gives up ’is own kind? An’ this IS Prince Konrad, you "
"numbskull! Show some respect!"
msgstr ""
"Iso é unha morea de tripas se é que algunha vez oín unha! Que clase de anano "
"traidor e falcón renuncia á súa propia especie? E este É o príncipe Konrad, "
"parvo! Mostra un pouco de respecto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:207
msgid ""
"I <b><i>am</i></b> Konrad, heir to the throne of Wesnoth and a sworn enemy "
"of Asheviere’s! No amount of money will turn my blade. Raise your axe and "
"make ready for battle, villain!"
msgstr ""
"<b><i>Son</i></b> Konrad, herdeiro ao trono de Wesnoth e inimigo declarado "
"de Asheviere! Nin sequera cantidade de diñeiro fará xirar a miña folla. "
"Levanta o teu machado e prepárate para a batalla, vilán!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:212
msgid ""
"Err... look, Your Highness, this is just business. I’ve got nothin’ ’gainst "
"neither you nor Asheviere, but I do want to keep my word an’ do my job."
msgstr ""
"Eh... mire, Alteza, isto son só negocios. Non teño nada contra vostede nin "
"contra Asheviere, pero quero cumprir a miña palabra e facer o meu traballo."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:216
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Work together with me now, an’ once I’ve cleaned out the nests I’ll let "
#| "you have your pick of the eggs. Gryphons’re worth somethin’ fierce in a "
#| "scrap, ye ken?\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I’ll even send some o’ my crew with you, to help you train your gryphons "
#| "once they hatch!"
msgid ""
"Work together with me now, an’ once I’ve cleaned out the nests I’ll let you "
"have your pick of the eggs. Gryphons’re worth somethin’ fierce in a scrap, "
"ye ken?"
msgstr ""
"Traballa comigo agora e, unha vez que haxa limpo os niños, deixaréiche "
"escoller os ovos que queiras. Os grifóns valen un ollo de a cara nunha "
"pelexa, xa sabes? Incluso mandaréiche algúns dos meus homes contigo para "
"axudarche a adestrar os teus grifóns cando eclosionen!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:218
msgid ""
"I’ll even send some o’ my crew with you, to help you train your gryphons "
"once they hatch!"
msgstr ""
"Mesmo enviarei algúns da miña tripulación contigo, para axudarche a adestrar "
"os teus grifóns cando nazan!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:222
msgid ""
"You get yer rebel army, an’ I get my big sack o’ gold from the queen. "
"Everyone wins, an’ nobody has to die."
msgstr ""
"Ti consigues o teu exército rebelde e eu o meu gran saco de ouro da raíña. "
"Todos gañan e ninguén ten que morrer."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:228
msgid ""
"Agree to Burlin’s deal: Konrad learns to recruit Gryphon Riders and Dwarvish "
"Scouts"
msgstr ""
"Acepta o trato de Burlin: Konrad aprende a recrutar xinetes de grifos e "
"exploradores ananos"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:235
msgid ""
"Fight Burlin: Asheviere loses $s50_burlin_income_penalty income and cannot "
"recruit Gryphon Riders in the final scenario"
msgstr ""
"Loita contra Burlin: Asheviere perde $s50_burlin_income_penalty de ingresos "
"e non pode recrutar xinetes de grifos no escenario final."

#. [message]: type=Young Ogre
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:263
msgid "Uhh... who you? You squishy! Me squish you!"
msgstr "Uhh... quen es ti? Es blanducho! Eu espremerte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:298
msgid ""
"Very well. I don’t like aligning myself in any way with the dark queen, but "
"you make a valid point. I’ll need gryphons and dwarves if I want my army to "
"be victorious."
msgstr ""
"Moi ben. Non me gusta aliñarme de ningún xeito coa raíña escura, pero tes un "
"punto válido. Necesitarei grifos e ananos se quero que o meu exército sexa "
"victorioso."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:302
msgid ""
"Great! I knew ye’d come round. Tha’ big gryphon in the middle is the "
"matriarch — kill her off an’ we’ll have no trouble gettin’ the eggs we need."
msgstr ""
"Xenial! Sabía que virías. Ese grifón grande do medio é a matriarca. Mátaa e "
"non teremos ningún problema en conseguir os ovos que necesitamos."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:314
msgid "Defeat the gryphon leader"
msgstr "Derrota ao líder do grifo"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:320
msgid "Death of Burlin"
msgstr "Morte de Burlin"

#. [message]: speaker=Mother Gryphon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:337
msgid "Krawww! Krawww..."
msgstr "Que cabrón! Que cabrón..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:348
msgid ""
"With the matriarch dead, the rest of them have fled! The mountain is silent "
"once again."
msgstr ""
"Coa matriarca morta, o resto deles fuxiu! A montaña está de novo en silencio."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:353
msgid "Twenty..."
msgstr "Vinte..."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:358
msgid "Forty..."
msgstr "Corenta..."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:363
msgid ""
"Fifty! That’s all I need. As promised, the rest of the eggs are yours. And "
"here’s some o’ my crew to help you ride ’em once they hatch. Great work, kid."
msgstr ""
"Cincuenta! Iso é todo o que preciso. Como che prometín, o resto dos ovos son "
"teus. E aquí tes a algúns membros da miña tripulación para axudarte a "
"montalos unha vez que eclosionen. Bo traballo, rapaz."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:365
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Gryphon Riders and Dwarvish Scouts!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar Xinetes de Grifos e Exploradores Ananos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:381
msgid "Ack! So much fer my gold..."
msgstr "Ack! So much fer my gold..."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:395
msgid ""
"Oy, can ye hurry it up? Time is money, an’ I ain’t makin’ any standin’ "
"around!"
msgstr "Ei, podes apuralo? O tempo é ouro, e eu non vou aturarme por aí!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:402
msgid ""
"Ah, forget it, yer takin’ too long. I’ll deal with this meself — an’ keep "
"all the reward for meself too!"
msgstr ""
"Ah, esquéceo, estás tardando demasiado. Encargareime disto eu mesmo... e "
"gardarei toda a recompensa para min tamén!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:425
msgid ""
"I said raise your axe, villain! Any friend of Asheviere’s is a foe of mine!"
msgstr ""
"Dixen que levantas o teu machado, vilán! Calquera amigo de Asheviere é un "
"inimigo meu!"

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:429
msgid "Well, I tried. It’s yer funeral, kid."
msgstr "Pois o tentei. É o teu funeral, rapaz."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:436
msgid ""
"Hey boys, wake up an’ set up camp! Looks like we’re gonna need to fight fer "
"it after all!"
msgstr ""
"Ei, rapaces, espertade e montade o campamento! Parece que teremos que loitar "
"por iso despois de todo!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:451
msgid "Defeat Burlin"
msgstr "Derrota a Burlin"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:471
msgid ""
"You’d think these gryphons would show a little more gratitude, instead of "
"trying to kill us..."
msgstr ""
"Pensarías que estes grifos amosarían un pouco máis de gratitude, en lugar de "
"intentar matarnos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:483
msgid ""
"Ah, humbug. Now the queen’ll ne’er get her gryphons... an’ I’ll ne’er get my "
"gold..."
msgstr ""
"Ah, parvadas. Agora a raíña nunca máis recuperará os seus grifóns... e eu "
"nunca máis recuperarei o meu ouro..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:490
msgid "Even on his deathbed, money is all he cares about."
msgstr "Mesmo no seu leito de morte, o diñeiro é o único que lle importa."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:498
msgid ""
"That’s why we have to fight her. Not for my sake, but for all the people "
"suffering under Asheviere’s lash."
msgstr ""
"Por iso temos que loitar contra ela. Non por min, senón por toda a xente que "
"sofre baixo os azoutes de Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:517
msgid ""
"Argh, this is takin’ too long. I’d better send a messenger to Dan’Tonk an’ "
"call for help."
msgstr ""
"Argh, isto está a tardar demasiado. Mellor enviar un mensaxeiro a Dan'Tonk e "
"pedir axuda."

#. [message]: role=messenger
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/14_Gryphon_Mountain.cfg:533
msgid ""
"Ah’m back, Burlin! An’ I’ve brought a whole army with me — th’ queen’s "
"pretty excited to finally capture the rebel prince!"
msgstr ""
"Ah, volvín, Burlin! E trouxen un exército enteiro comigo. A raíña está moi "
"emocionada por capturar por fin o príncipe rebelde!"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:7
msgid "scenario name^Valley of Death"
msgstr "Valado da Morte"

#. [side]: type=Shock Trooper, id=Kaelor
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:37
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:100
msgid "Warrior Monks"
msgstr "Monxes guerreiros"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:233
msgid ""
"Hail, strangers! The seals are failing, and the sister senior sent us to "
"find aid. You must return with us to help our home, else all may soon be "
"lost!"
msgstr ""
"Saúde, estraños! Os selos están a fallar, e a irmá maior enviounos a buscar "
"axuda. Debedes volver connosco para axudar ao noso fogar, se non, todo pode "
"perderse axiña!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:237
msgid ""
"Don’t worry, warrior, we’ve already been to your home and fought to restore "
"the seals! Your people are safe."
msgstr ""
"Non te preocupes, guerreiro, xa fomos á túa casa e loitamos para restaurar "
"os selos! A túa xente está a salvo."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:241
msgid ""
"Can it be true? Joyous news! You have my deepest gratitude, young one. Aid "
"us in battle against these undead stragglers, and my warriors and I shall be "
"glad to join you."
msgstr ""
"Pode ser verdade? Boas novas! Tes a miña máis profunda gratitude, mozo. "
"Axúdanos na batalla contra estes mortos viventes rezagados, e os meus "
"guerreiros e eu estaremos encantados de unirnos a ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:247
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:281
msgid "Hail, strangers! How have these undead come to trouble you?"
msgstr "Saúde, estraños! Como viñeron estes mortos viventes a molestarvos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#. "brother" is not literal, instead referring to fellow warrior monks (heavy infantry) of Moremirmu's order
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:252
msgid ""
"Strangers? No, Konrad, these are my brethren! Kaelor, it is good to once "
"again lay eyes upon a fellow brother of the faith. But what are undead doing "
"so near to our hallowed home?"
msgstr ""
"Estranxeiros? Non, Konrad, estes son os meus irmáns! Kaelor, é bo volver ver "
"a un irmán da fe. Pero que fan os mortos viventes tan preto do noso fogar "
"sagrado?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#. "brother" is not literal, instead referring to fellow warrior monks (heavy infantry) of Kaleor's order
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:257
msgid ""
"Grim tidings, brother Moremirmu! The seals are failing, and the sister "
"senior sent us to cut through these restless dead and find aid for our home!"
msgstr ""
"¡Que malas novas, irmán Moremirmu! Os selos están fallando, e a irmá maior "
"enviounos a abrirnos paso entre estes mortos inquedos e buscar axuda para o "
"noso fogar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#. "brother" is not literal, instead referring to fellow warrior monks (heavy infantry) of Moremirmu's order
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:262
msgid ""
"The seals? By the Light! I have been away from home for far too long, "
"brother. Yet now have I returned — and with me comes a lost prince and his "
"warriors most righteous, ready to aid you!"
msgstr ""
"Os selos? Pola Luz! Estiven lonxe de casa demasiado tempo, irmán. Pero agora "
"voltei — e comigo veñen un príncipe perdido e os seus guerreiros máis "
"xustos, dispostos a axudarche!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:267
msgid "I don’t understand. Moremirmu, what’s going on?"
msgstr "Non o entendo. Moremirmu, que está a pasar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:271
msgid ""
"These are fellow servants of the light, Konrad. Men from my home — a "
"monastery, some days travel northwards. There is a powerful magic protecting "
"my home, yet Kaelor reports that it is weakening. Undead have begun to slip "
"through."
msgstr ""
"Estes son compañeiros serventes da luz, Konrad. Homes da miña casa — un "
"mosteiro, a varios días de camiño cara ao norte. Hai unha poderosa maxia que "
"protexe o meu fogar, pero Kaelor informa de que se está debilitando. Os "
"mortos viventes comezaron a colarse."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:275
msgid ""
"We must fight through these undead and go at once to their aid, for without "
"our help they may soon lose all!"
msgstr ""
"Temos que loitar contra estes mortos viventes e acudir de inmediato en súa "
"axuda, pois sen a nosa axuda poden perder todo moi pronto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:285
msgid ""
"Nay, ’tis we who have come to trouble them! The seals are failing, and the "
"sister senior sent us to cut through these restless dead and find aid for "
"our home! But who are you to ask, stranger of the south?"
msgstr ""
"Non, somos nós os que viñemos molestalos! As focas están fallando, e a irmá "
"maior enviounos a abrirnos paso entre estes mortos inquedos e buscar axuda "
"para o noso fogar! Pero quen es ti para preguntarlle, estraño do sur?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:289
msgid ""
"Well met. I am Konrad. But I don’t understand — you said you’re looking for "
"help?"
msgstr ""
"Encantado de coñecerche. Son Konrad. Pero non entendo: dis que buscas axuda?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:293
msgid ""
"Indeed. I come from a monastery, some days travel northwards. A powerful "
"magic that once protected my home has weakened, and I was sent to seek aid."
msgstr ""
"De feito. Veño dun mosteiro, algúns días viaxo cara ao norte. Unha poderosa "
"maxia que antes protexía o meu fogar debilitouse e enviáronme a buscar axuda."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:297
msgid ""
"But if you serve the light and not the darkness, then that aid is you! Fight "
"alongside me to vanquish these undead now, then return with us north and "
"help our home. Otherwise, all shall soon be lost!"
msgstr ""
"Pero se serves á luz e non á escuridade, entón esa axuda es ti! Loita xunto "
"a min para vencer a estes mortos viventes agora, despois volve connosco ao "
"norte e axuda ao noso fogar. Se non, todo estará perdido axiña!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. [objective]: description=<span strikethrough='true' color='#A9A9A9'>, condition=win
#. if Kaelor is protected, Konrad will learn to recruit Heavy Infantrymen
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:313
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:321
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Konrad can now recruit Heavy Infantrymen!"
msgid "Protect Kaelor: recruit Heavy Infantrymen"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar infantes pesados!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:349
msgid "Kaelor, who are you people? How did all these undead come to be here?"
msgstr ""
"Kaelor, quen sodes vós? Como chegaron todos estes mortos viventes a estar "
"aquí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:353
msgid ""
"The hills to the north — now the home of my order — were once a wholly "
"accursed place, blighted by necromancy and consumed by darkness."
msgstr ""
"As montañas ao norte —agora o fogar da miña orde— foron noutro tempo un "
"lugar totalmente maldito, asolagado pola necromancia e consumido pola "
"escuridade."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:357
msgid ""
"We know not from whence the evil came. Some think the necromancers to be "
"lich-lords, survivors of their invasion from the west; others believe they "
"are stragglers of Ras-Tabahn’s. We only know that centuries ago, the crown "
"used the ruby to seal them underground with powerful magic."
msgstr ""
"Non sabemos de onde veu o mal. Algúns cren que os necromantes son señores "
"liches, superviventes da súa invasión desde o oeste; outros cren que son "
"rezagados de Ras-Tabahn. Só sabemos que, hai séculos, a coroa usou o rubí "
"para selalos baixo terra con poderosa maxia."

#. [message]: speaker=$speaker
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:361
msgid ""
"Men and women of our order, servants of the light, have made it our mission "
"to cleanse this place of evil. We built our monastery here to ensure that "
"the darkness never escapes."
msgstr ""
"Homes e mulleres da nosa orde, servos da luz, fixemos da nosa misión limpar "
"este lugar de mal. Construímos o noso mosteiro aquí para garantir que a "
"escuridade nunca escape."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:365
msgid ""
"But it has been decades since the Crown sent to us men or supplies, and the "
"power of our order has waned. Now the seals are beginning to fail..."
msgstr ""
"Pero pasaron décadas desde que a Coroa nos enviou homes ou subministracións, "
"e o poder da nosa orde minguou. Agora os selos están empezando a fallar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:380
msgid "My light fades..."
msgstr "A miña luz esvaece..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:384
msgid ""
"Those armored warriors would surely have been of great help in our fight for "
"the crown. If only we could have protected them..."
msgstr ""
"Aqueles guerreiros blindados terían sido de gran axuda na nosa loita pola "
"coroa. Se só puidésemos protexelos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:408
msgid ""
"This ruined skeleton bears a curious amulet. Magical, perhaps? There is an "
"inscription explaining its function..."
msgstr ""
"Este esqueleto en ruínas leva un curioso amuleto. Quizais máxico? Hai unha "
"inscrición que explica a súa función..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:420
msgid ""
"How odd. In death, this skeleton was a puppet. But in life, he or she must "
"have been a craftsman of legendary skill. Fortune has smiled upon us today — "
"I will take this artifact for myself."
msgstr ""
"Que estraño. Na morte, este esqueleto era unha marioneta. Pero en vida, el "
"ou ela debía ser un artesán de habilidade lendaria. A fortuna sorriunos hoxe "
"— levarei este artefacto para min."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:439
msgid ""
"Lo, our victory is won! And with the seal already restored and our home "
"already rescued, there is nothing to prevent my brothers and I from joining "
"you on your quest, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"Velaquí, a nosa vitoria está gañada! E co selo xa restaurado e o noso fogar "
"xa rescatado, non hai nada que nos impida aos meus irmáns e a min unirnos a "
"ti na túa misión, Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#. "brother" is not literal, instead referring to fellow warrior monks (heavy infantry) of Kaleor's order
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:445
msgid ""
"Lo and behold! We have won a bright victory against the forces of darkness, "
"good warrior. My brothers and I would be honored to continue fighting by "
"your side."
msgstr ""
"Velaquí! Obtivemos unha brillante vitoria contra as forzas da escuridade, bo "
"guerreiro. Os meus irmáns e eu seríamos unha honra para nós seguir loitando "
"ao teu carón."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:449
msgid ""
"Yet these few abominations were but a moth, drawn to the dark flame that "
"stems from what lies to the north! I implore you, brave Konrad, travel north "
"and rescue my home!"
msgstr ""
"Con todo, estas poucas abominacións non eran máis que unha polilla atraída "
"pola chama escura que xorde do que se atopa ao norte! Te imploro, valente "
"Konrad, viaxa ao norte e rescata o meu fogar!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:454
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Heavy Infantrymen!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar infantes pesados!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:461
msgid ""
"The undead have been defeated! Yet with the leader of the warrior monks "
"slain, we have lost the opportunity to gain a new ally in our fight for the "
"crown."
msgstr ""
"Os mortos viventes foron derrotados! Con todo, ao caer o líder dos monxes "
"guerreiros, perdemos a oportunidade de gañar un novo aliado na nosa loita "
"pola coroa."

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:484
msgid ""
"Make haste, Konrad! Should we tarry too long, the seals shall surely break "
"and our home shall surely be destroyed!"
msgstr ""
"Apresúrate, Konrad! Se tardamos demasiado, os selos romperanse e o noso "
"fogar será destruído!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaelor
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15a_Valley_of_Death_part1.cfg:495
msgid ""
"Alas, we have tarried too long. Even should we yet win the battle today, "
"surely the seals have already broken, destroying our home...."
msgstr ""
"Ai, tardamos demasiado. Mesmo se gañásemos a batalla hoxe, seguro que os "
"selos xa se romperon, destruíndo o noso fogar..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:20
msgid "scenario name^Valley of Death II"
msgstr "Valado da Morte II"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:67
msgid "Aimucasur"
msgstr "Aimucasur"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:77
msgid "Selda-Mana"
msgstr "Selda-Maná"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:129
msgid "Sister Kenara"
msgstr "Irmá %s"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:131
msgid "Brother Vinrar"
msgstr "Irmán Vinrar"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:132
msgid "Sister Miryan"
msgstr "Irmá Miryan"

#. [message]: speaker=$speaker
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:176
msgid ""
"Lo and behold, Konrad: my home! At last I return... but we are too late! "
"Undead! The seal has already broken!"
msgstr ""
"Velaquí, Konrad: o meu fogar! Por fin volvo... pero chegamos demasiado "
"tarde! Non mortos! O selo xa se rompeu!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:182
msgid ""
"Lo and behold, Konrad! Fate has brought us to my home; the monastery of my "
"order."
msgstr ""
"E velaquí, Konrad! O destino trouxonos á miña casa; o mosteiro da miña orde."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:186
msgid "... but what calamity is this? Undead! The sacred seal has broken!"
msgstr "... pero que calamidade é esta? Non mortos! O selo sagrado rompeu!"

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#. "Brother" is not literal. Rather, the speaker and the "brother" are both members of a monastic society
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:205
msgid ""
"Brother, you return to us! And with aid from the outside! Yet your arrival "
"is but a silver lining, too little too late, for our strength has failed."
msgstr ""
"Irmán, volves con nós! E con axuda do exterior! Porén, a túa chegada non é "
"máis que un revestimento de esperanza, demasiado pouca e demasiado tarde, "
"porque as nosas forzas fallaron."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:210
msgid ""
"Stranger, we welcome you to our home! Long have we awaited aid from the "
"outside... Yet your arrival is but a silver lining, too little too late, for "
"our strength has failed."
msgstr ""
"Estranxeiro, dámosche a benvida ao noso fogar! Levamos moito tempo agardando "
"axuda do exterior... Porén, a túa chegada non é máis que un raio de "
"esperanza, demasiado pouca e demasiado tarde, porque as nosas forzas "
"fallaron."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:215
msgid ""
"Dark magic streams forth from the underlevels, granting terrible un-life to "
"things sprung from the deepest nightmares of humanity. With the spell broken "
"that once sealed them below, the undead emerge to destroy us all!"
msgstr ""
"A maxia escura mana dos niveis subterráneos, outorgando unha terrible non-"
"vida ás cousas xurdidas dos pesadelos máis profundos da humanidade. Co "
"feitizo roto que antes os selaba nos baixos, os mortos viventes emerxen para "
"destruírnos a todos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Don’t give up hope! You sent Kaelor to find help, and he found me — Konrad, "
"heir to the throne of Wesnoth. If there are undead here then it is my duty "
"to help you stop them."
msgstr ""
"Non perdas a esperanza! Enviaches a Kaelor para buscar axuda, e el atopoume "
"a min: Konrad, herdeiro ao trono de Wesnoth. Se hai mortos viventes aquí, "
"entón é o meu deber axudarche a detelos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:231
msgid ""
"You say there was once a spell that sealed these dead underground. Can you "
"cast it again?"
msgstr ""
"Dices que houbo unha vez un conxuro que selou estes mortos baixo terra. "
"Podes lanzalo de novo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:236
msgid ""
"Don’t give up hope! I am Konrad, heir to the throne of Wesnoth, and if there "
"are undead here then it is my duty to help you stop them."
msgstr ""
"Non perdas a esperanza! Son Konrad, herdeiro ao trono de Wesnoth, e se hai "
"mortos viventes aquí, entón é o meu deber axudarche a detelos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:240
msgid ""
"But what is this place? You say there was once a spell that sealed these "
"dead underground. Can you cast it again?"
msgstr ""
"Pero que lugar é este? Dis que houbo unha vez un feitizo que selaba estes "
"mortos baixo terra. Podes lanzalo de novo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:245
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Without the ruby? No. There are none alive today, save perhaps the great "
#| "Delfador, with the might to again from-naught weave such a seal.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "But the pieces of our shattered spell still linger. With time, it could "
#| "be repaired."
msgid ""
"Without the ruby? No. There are none alive today, save perhaps the great "
"Delfador, with the might to again from-naught weave such a seal."
msgstr ""
"Sen o rubí? Non. Hoxe non hai ninguén vivo, agás quizais o gran Delfador, "
"con poder para tecer de novo un selo así a partir do nada. Pero os anacos do "
"noso conxuro roto aínda persisten. Co tempo, podería repararse."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:247
msgid ""
"But the pieces of our shattered spell still linger. With time, it could be "
"repaired."
msgstr ""
"Pero os fragmentos do noso feitizo esnaquizado aínda permanecen. Co tempo, "
"podería ser reparado."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:251
msgid ""
"We have tried before, nearly to our doom. The attempt brought the full "
"horrors of the undead crashing down upon our humble home, and many perished. "
"Light save them."
msgstr ""
"Xa tentamos antes, case ata a nosa perdición. O intento trouxo os horrores "
"completos dos mortos viventes sobre a nosa humilde casa, e moitos pereceron. "
"Que a Luz os salve."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:255
msgid ""
"I understand — alone, you could not defend yourself. But now I am here. I "
"will help you."
msgstr ""
"Enténdoo: só, non podías defenderte. Pero agora estou aquí. Vouche axudar."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:263
msgid "You are a blessing, Konrad. With your help, perhaps it is possible."
msgstr "Ti es unha bendición, Konrad. Coa túa axuda, quizais sexa posible."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:294
msgid ""
"There are only four of us left who have the power to repair the seal. The "
"rest of us — the novices — I entrust into your command."
msgstr ""
"Só quedamos catro de nós que temos o poder de reparar o selo. O resto de nós "
"— os novatos — confío no teu mando."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:298
msgid ""
"Defend our monastery while the seniors and I work. In forty-eight hours’ "
"time our ritual shall complete, and the seal shall be repaired, trapping the "
"undead back underground."
msgstr ""
"Defendede o noso mosteiro mentres os maiores e eu traballamos. En corenta e "
"oito horas o noso ritual completarase e o selo repararase, atrapando os "
"mortos viventes de volta baixo terra."

#. [then]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:314
msgid "You can now advance Mages to White Mages!"
msgstr "Agora podes ascender aos Magos a Magos Brancos!"

#. [else]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:317
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Mages, and advance them to (only) White Mages!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar magos e avanzalos a (só) magos brancos!"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:356
msgid "Death of Myrilell or Kenara"
msgstr "Morte de Myrilell ou Kenara"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:365
msgid "Your allies will not move, but can attack adjacent enemies."
msgstr ""
"Os teus aliados non se moverán, pero poden atacar aos inimigos adxacentes."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:379
msgid ""
"Myrilell, how can our magic have weakened so? Where is Sister Tristia, my "
"mentor? What of Brother Percy, keeper of the ancient texts? They should have "
"stopped this."
msgstr ""
"Myrilell, como é posible que a nosa maxia se debilitase tanto? Onde está a "
"irmá Tristia, a miña mentora? Que pasa co irmán Percy, gardián dos textos "
"antigos? Deberían ter parado isto."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:383
msgid ""
"Dead, both. Fallen to the swelling tide of undead. You have been sorely "
"missed, Moremirmu, away on your quest to spread light across the wider world."
msgstr ""
"Mortos, ambos. Caídos na crecente marea de mortos viventes. Botámoste moito "
"de menos, Moremirmu, na túa misión de espallar a luz por todo o mundo."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:387
msgid "Dead!? So many dead."
msgstr "Morto!? Tantos mortos."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:393
msgid ""
"The seal shattered, my home imperiled, my friends slain. This is the work of "
"a dozen lifetimes undone."
msgstr ""
"O selo esvaeceuse, a miña casa en perigo, os meus amigos asasinados. Este é "
"o labor dunha ducia de vidas desfeito."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:397
msgid ""
"Konrad, I am overcome by grief. I am brought to tears. The very foundation "
"of my faith is shaken."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, síntome abrumado pola dor. Estou cheo de bágoas. Os propios "
"alicerces da miña fe están abalados."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:405
msgid ""
"I am sorry. I cannot battle today. I must meditate, and ponder on my "
"emotions."
msgstr ""
"Síntoo. Non podo loitar hoxe. Debo meditar e reflexionar sobre as miñas "
"emocións."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:409
msgid ""
"Ponder your emotions? Moremirmu, I know it’s a shock to see your home in "
"crisis, but we’re about to fight a battle!"
msgstr ""
"Reflexionas sobre as túas emocións? Moremirmu, sei que é un shock ver a túa "
"casa en crise, pero estamos a piques de librar unha batalla!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:413
msgid ""
"I am a warrior of the Light, Konrad. My Light cannot shine while there "
"within me beats a heart touched by the Dark."
msgstr ""
"Son un guerreiro da Luz, Konrad. A miña Luz non pode brillar mentres dentro "
"de min latexa un corazón tocado pola Escuridade."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:424
msgid "He’s gone!"
msgstr "¡Xa se foi!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:439
msgid ""
"Myrilell, what is this place we now defend? How did you all come to be here?"
msgstr ""
"Myrilell, que lugar é este que defendemos agora? Como chegastes todos aquí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:443
msgid ""
"These hills — now our home — were once a wholly accursed place, blighted by "
"necromancy and consumed by darkness."
msgstr ""
"Estas colinas — agora o noso fogar — foron noutro tempo un lugar "
"completamente maldito, asolagado pola necromancia e consumido polas trebas."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:447
msgid ""
"We know not from whence the evil came. Some think the necromancers to be "
"lich-lords, survivors of their invasion from the west; others believe they "
"are stragglers of Ras-Tabahn’s. We only know that centuries ago, the crown "
"sealed them underground with powerful magic."
msgstr ""
"Non sabemos de onde veu o mal. Algúns cren que os necromantes son señores "
"liches, superviventes da súa invasión desde o oeste; outros cren que son "
"rezagados de Ras-Tabahn. Só sabemos que hai séculos a coroa os selou baixo "
"terra con poderosa maxia."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:451
msgid ""
"Men and women of our order, servants of the Light, have made it our mission "
"to cleanse this place of evil. We built our monastery here to ensure that "
"the darkness never escapes."
msgstr ""
"Homes e mulleres da nosa orde, servos da Luz, fixemos da nosa misión limpar "
"este lugar de mal. Construímos o noso mosteiro aquí para garantir que a "
"escuridade nunca escape."

#. [message]: speaker=Vinrar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:455
msgid ""
"But it’s been decades since the Crown last sent to us men or supplies, and "
"the power of our order has waned. And now even the seal has fallen..."
msgstr ""
"Pero pasaron décadas dende a última vez que a Coroa nos enviou homes ou "
"subministracións, e o poder da nosa orde minguou. E agora mesmo o selo "
"caeu..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:467
msgid "Look out! They’re preparing another assault."
msgstr "Coidado! Están preparando outro asalto."

#. [message]: type=Lich
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:471
msgid ""
"For too long have we been trapped by your accursed seal! The undertunnels "
"shall be thrown open and our followers shall flood across the land! You "
"cannot stop the eternal life that we bring!"
msgstr ""
"Levamos demasiado tempo atrapados polo teu selo maldito! Os túneles "
"subterráneos abriranse de par en par e os nosos seguidores inundarán a "
"terra! Non podes deter a vida eterna que traemos!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:475
msgid ""
"Eternal life is no blessing, lich, but a curse. I have tasted from the cup "
"of which you offer, and we will not allow such poison to spread."
msgstr ""
"A vida eterna non é unha bendición, lich, senón unha maldición. Probei a "
"copa que ofreces, e non permitiremos que se estenda tal veleno."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:476
msgid ""
"For too long has the crown neglected this place. Now, the spirit of Garard "
"comes to put things right."
msgstr ""
"Durante demasiado tempo a coroa descoidou este lugar. Agora, o espírito de "
"Garard vén poñer as cousas no seu sitio."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:477
msgid ""
"As tempting as the thought may be, I’ve heard more than a few stories of "
"promising young magi tempted by necromancy. It never ends well."
msgstr ""
"Por moi tentadora que poida ser a idea, oín máis dunha historia de novos "
"meigos prometedores seducidos pola necromancia. Nunca acaba ben."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:478
msgid ""
"As tempting as the thought may be, I’ve seen more than a few promising young "
"magi tempted by necromancy. It never ends well."
msgstr ""
"Por moi tentadora que poida ser a idea, vin máis dunha historia de novos "
"meigos prometedores seducidos pola necromancia. Nunca acaba ben."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:479
msgid ""
"Fancy talk comin’ from a stick-handed sixpenny skull, ye soused gurnet! Jus’ "
"wait ’til ah stick my axe through one o’yer wrinklin’ ribs!"
msgstr ""
"Que fala dun cranio de seis peniques con mans de paus, es unha carambola "
"mollada! Agarda a que che crave o meu machado nunha das túas costelas "
"engurradas!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:480
msgid ""
"You’re not the first lich we’ve fought. Want to hear what we did to the last "
"one?"
msgstr ""
"Non es o primeiro lich contra o que loitamos. Queres saber o que lle fixemos "
"ao último?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:482
msgid ""
"Really, eternal life? I’d love to discuss some of my alchemical theories "
"with you! ...wait, ah, no, you mean undeath, don’t you."
msgstr ""
"De verdade, vida eterna? Encantaríame comentar algunhas das miñas teorías "
"alquímicas contigo! ...espera, ah, non, queres dicir morte vivente, non si?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:483
msgid ""
"Ya ya ya. Dosh heard dis all before. Always someone be thinkin’ dey know "
"what’s best for everyone else."
msgstr ""
"Xa, xa, xa. Dosh xa escoitou todo isto antes. Sempre hai alguén que pensa "
"que sabe o que é mellor para todos os demais."

#. [message]: speaker=Vinrar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:520
msgid "At last, I see the light..."
msgstr "Por fin vexo a luz..."

#. [message]: speaker=Miryan
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:528
msgid "Yield not one inch to the darkness..."
msgstr "Non cedas nin un milímetro á escuridade..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:540
msgid ""
"This body is merely a puppet! You cannot stop us from enlightening your "
"world to the bliss of eternal un-life!"
msgstr ""
"Este corpo é meramente un boneco! Non podes impedirnos de iluminar o teu "
"mundo coa ledicia da vida eterna!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:547
msgid ""
"Your fighting only delays the inevitable! There are more of us than you "
"could ever imagine!"
msgstr ""
"A vosa loita só atrasa o inevitable! Somos máis que nunca poderías imaxinar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:551
msgid "One fewer now."
msgstr "Agora un menos."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:570
msgid "Lo! My faith has been tested! And lo! It has endured!"
msgstr "Velaquí! A miña fe foi posta a proba! E velaquí! Perseverou!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:607
msgid "In the crucible of the Light, evil shall be purged!"
msgstr "No crisol da Luz, o mal será purgado!"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:626
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Moremirmu has returned! He has gained +2 damage, +20 hitpoints,\n"
#| "and the powerful “smite” ability!\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Smite: each time Mormirmu strikes a finishing blow, he will deal\n"
#| "30 arcane damage to all adjacent enemies."
msgid ""
"Moremirmu has returned! He has gained +2 damage, +20 hitpoints,\n"
"and the powerful “smite” ability!\n"
"\n"
"Smite: each time Moremirmu strikes a finishing blow, he will deal\n"
"30 arcane damage to all adjacent enemies."
msgstr ""
"Moremirmu volveu! Gañou +2 de dano, +20 puntos de vida\n"
"e a poderosa habilidade \"golpear\"!\n"
"\n"
"Golpear: cada vez que Mormirmu dea un golpe final, inflixirá\n"
"30 de dano arcano a todos os inimigos adxacentes."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:651
msgid "Nearly done, Konrad! Hold strong and we shall yet be victorious!"
msgstr ""
"Case rematamos, Konrad! Manteñádevos fortes e aínda así sairemos vitoriosos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:659
msgid "Light save us all! It is finished."
msgstr "Luz, salvade a todos nós! Xa rematou."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:689
msgid "They’re gone!"
msgstr "Xa non están!"

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:695
msgid ""
"With the seal restored, the undead have once more been banished underground. "
"We are in your debt, Your Highness."
msgstr ""
"Co selo restaurado, os mortos viventes foron de novo desterrados baixo "
"terra. Estamos en débeda con vostede, Alteza."

#. [message]: speaker=Myrilell
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:699
msgid ""
"The seniors and I must remain here, to continue strengthening our magic and "
"to ensure the undead never again escape. But into your hands I entrust our "
"young mages, and the nascent Light that they nurture within. May they serve "
"you well as you journey on to reclaim your throne."
msgstr ""
"Os anciáns e eu debemos permanecer aquí para seguir fortalecendo a nosa "
"maxia e para garantir que os mortos viventes nunca máis escapen. Pero nas "
"vosas mans confío os nosos xoves magos e a Luz nacente que cultivan no seu "
"interior. Que vos sirvan ben mentres viaxades para reclamar o voso trono."

#. [message]: id=Myrilell,Kenara
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:729
msgid "No! Without her help, I have no hope of restoring the seal."
msgstr "Non! Sen a súa axuda, non teño esperanza de restaurar o selo."

#. [message]: id=Myrilell,Kenara
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/15b_Valley_of_Death_part2.cfg:733
msgid ""
"The undead will continue to pour forth and pour forth, until we are all "
"overwhelmed..."
msgstr ""
"Os mortos viventes seguirán a saír e a saír, ata que todos sexamos "
"aniquilados..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:14
msgid "scenario name^Crossroads"
msgstr "Cruce"

#. [side]: type=Knight, id=knight
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:58
msgid "Raery"
msgstr "Raery"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#. Lisar has prisoners, and is trying to lure Konrad into an ambush. The player has just decided to play this scenario.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:206
msgid ""
"He’s taken the bait. Quick, get down into the mines and alert the others."
msgstr "Mordeu o anzol. Depresa, baixa ás minas e alerta aos demais."

#. [message]: speaker=knight
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:215
msgid ""
"What about the prisoners, m’lady? Shall we execute them before the imposter "
"arrives?"
msgstr ""
"E os prisioneiros, miña señora? Executámolos antes de que chegue o impostor?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. Ulfdain throws lots of hard-to-understand old-fashioned insults at Li'sar. This is his usual way of speaking.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:220
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "C’mere and try it, ye yellow-bellied, cow-handed bluderbuss of a "
#| "princess! Jus’ gimme the chance an’ I’ll rip that head right off yer "
#| "ninnyhammerin’ neck, ye white-livered gasser!"
msgid ""
"C’mere and try it, ye yellow-bellied, cow-handed blunderbuss of a princess! "
"Jus’ gimme the chance an’ I’ll rip that head right off yer ninnyhammerin’ "
"neck, ye white-livered gasser!"
msgstr ""
"Ven e inténtao, princesa de barriga amarela e mans de vaca! Dáme unha "
"oportunidade e arrancareiche esa cabeza do teu pescozo, gasador de fígado "
"branco!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:224
msgid ""
"As tempting as the thought may be, Raery, I’m not about to kill innocents in "
"cold blood. But we do need to get the dwarves out of here — both for their "
"own safety and to keep them out of the rebels’ hands."
msgstr ""
"Por moi tentadora que sexa a idea, Raery, non estou disposto a matar "
"inocentes a sangue frío. Pero si que temos que sacar os ananos de aquí, "
"tanto pola súa propia seguridade como para mantelos fóra das mans dos "
"rebeldes."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:234
msgid "Too late, Konrad has come! Forget the prisoners and prepare for battle."
msgstr ""
"Xa é demasiado tarde, Konrad chegou! Esquece os prisioneiros e prepárate "
"para a batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:260
msgid ""
"I’ve come to face you, princess! Only a true villain would threaten "
"innocents to force someone into a fight."
msgstr ""
"Vin enfrontarme a ti, princesa! Só un verdadeiro vilán ameazaría a inocentes "
"para obrigar a alguén a unha loita."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:264
msgid ""
"Oh please, the dwarves were never in any danger. You on the other hand, "
"“prince” — I will not allow you to sow any more discord and chaos among my "
"people. Your rebellion ends here."
msgstr ""
"Oh, por favor, os ananos nunca estiveron en perigo. Ti, pola contra, "
"«príncipe», non che permitirei sementar máis discordia e caos entre o meu "
"pobo. A túa rebelión remata aquí."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:272
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:462
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:889
msgid "Defeat Li’sar"
msgstr "Derrota a Li'sar"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:279
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:469
msgid "Defeat Yrogin"
msgstr "Derrota a Yrogin"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:287
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:477
msgid "Rescue Ulfdain"
msgstr "Rescate de Ulfdain"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:312
msgid "Look! Someone approaches from the eastern road."
msgstr "Mira! Alguén se achega dende o camiño do leste."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:314
msgid "Yrogin"
msgstr "Yrogin"

#. [message]: speaker=Yrogin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:319
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Message from the queen, your highness! The boats are ready, but there is "
#| "only a short window in which to act before Elensefar recovers."
msgid ""
"Message from the queen, Your Highness! The boats are ready, but there is "
"only a short window in which to act before Elensefar recovers."
msgstr ""
"Mensaxe da raíña, Súa Alteza! Os barcos están listos, pero só hai unha "
"pequena xanela para actuar antes de que Elensefar se recupere."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:323
msgid "Poor timing; I’m a little busy at the moment..."
msgstr "Mal momento; estou un pouco ocupado neste momento..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:327
msgid ""
"Still, Elensefar is too important a prize to let slip. I cannot risk Maddock "
"regaining his footing before we have a chance to deal the finishing blow."
msgstr ""
"Aínda así, Elensefar é un premio demasiado importante como para deixalo "
"escapar. Non podo arriscarme a que Maddock recupere o equilibrio antes de "
"que teñamos a oportunidade de asestar o golpe final."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:331
msgid ""
"I’ll depart immediately. Yrogin, you assume command here. It shouldn’t take "
"much to defeat this con-man now that we’ve lured him into battle."
msgstr ""
"Marcharei inmediatamente. Yrogin, asume o mando aquí. Non debería custar "
"moito derrotar a este estafador agora que o atraemos á batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:436
msgid "For Her Highness! Kill the imposter!"
msgstr "Pola súa Alteza! Mata ao impostor!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:439
msgid ""
"Caution, Konrad! These hills are full of old mineshafts, their entrances "
"overgrown with grass and weeds. Li’sar must be using them to ambush us."
msgstr ""
"Coidado, Konrad! Estas montañas están cheas de vellos pozos de minas, coas "
"súas entradas cubertas de herba e maleza. Li’sar debe estar a usalas para "
"tendernos unha emboscada."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:440
msgid ""
"Look out, Your Highness! Your cousin has stationed ambushers across the "
"hills, lurking in old mineshafts."
msgstr ""
"Coidado, Alteza! O seu curmán colocou emboscados nas montañas, agochados en "
"vellos pozos de minas."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:441
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:442
msgid ""
"Where did you come from?! Careful, Konrad, I think there are ambushers "
"hiding in old mineshafts all across these hills."
msgstr ""
"De onde saíches?! Coidado, Konrad, creo que hai emboscadores agochados en "
"antigas minas por todas estas lombas"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:443
msgid ""
"Lo! The forces of evil ambush us at every turn — even the very ground itself "
"succors our foes within its old mines."
msgstr ""
"Velaquí! As forzas do mal nos emboscan a cada paso; mesmo o propio chan "
"socorre aos nosos inimigos dentro das súas antigas minas."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:446
msgid ""
"Those ambushers burst right out of the ground! There must be old mineshafts "
"everywhere in these hills, overgrown with grass and weeds."
msgstr ""
"Aqueles emboscadores saíron disparados do chan! Deben de haber vellas "
"galerías de mina por todas estas colinas, cubertas de herba e matogueira."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:450
msgid "Wait, stop! I’m not an imposter, I’m the real Konrad!"
msgstr "Espera, para! Non son un impostor, son o verdadeiro Konrad!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:454
msgid "... there’s nothing I can say to save these woodsmen, is there?"
msgstr ""
"... non hai nada que poida dicir para salvar a estes leñadores, non si?"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:490
msgid "Invisible ambushers hide throughout the hills."
msgstr "Emboscadores invisibles escóndense polas montañas."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:513
msgid ""
"He’s slain nearly the last of our ambushers, Your Highness! What do we do?"
msgstr "Case matou ao último dos nosos emboscados, Alteza! Que facemos?"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:518
msgid "He’s slain nearly the last of our ambushers, lieutenant! What do we do?"
msgstr "Case matou ao último dos nosos emboscados, tenente! Que facemos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar,Yrogin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:523
msgid "This isn’t over. Keep up the fight!"
msgstr "Isto non rematou. Segue loitando!"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:539
msgid "Free the prisoners"
msgstr "Liberade os prisioneiros"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:545
msgid "Wait"
msgstr "Agarda"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:555
msgid ""
"Here are the prisoners! We can set them free, but if they join our side they "
"will certainly come under attack."
msgstr ""
"Aquí están os prisioneiros! Podemos liberalos, pero se se unen ao noso "
"bando, seguro que serán atacados."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. Ulfdain is still locked up, and challenges Konrad's unit who's come nearby
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:560
msgid ""
"Come an’ git some, ye nigmenog bolting-hutch of beastliness! Ah dare ye to "
"square up an’ fight me, dwarf-to-dwarf!"
msgstr ""
"Ven e colle algo, cabana de bestas negras e salvaxes! Ah, atréveste a "
"enfrontarte e loitar comigo, anano contra anano!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:564
msgid "Wait a minute! I don’t want to fight you. I’m here to rescue you!"
msgstr ""
"Espera un minuto! Non quero loitar contigo. Estou aquí para rescatarte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. Ulfdain asks Konrad to let him and his dwarf miner allies out of their cages so they can help fight Li'sar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:569
msgid ""
"Oh, what’s that? Seems ah misjudged ye, son. Hurry up then, ye spoony cub, "
"lemme an’ my boys out o’ these here cages so we can get to th’ fight!"
msgstr ""
"Oh, que é iso? Parece que te xulgaches mal, fillo. Depresa, cachorro "
"cutreiro, saca aos meus rapaces destas gaiolas para que poidamos ir á loita!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:580
msgid "You’re free now! How did you come to be imprisoned?"
msgstr "Xa es libre! Como acabaches encarcerado?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. Much better, thank you for freeing us. That's the last time I dig a mine for your human queen, let me tell you.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:585
msgid ""
"Much better, thank ye for freein’ us! Tha’s the last time I dig a mine for "
"yer human queen, lemme tell you. “Clean up the old crossroads mines”, she "
"says. “The princess needs ’em for somethin’!”"
msgstr ""
"Moito mellor, grazas por liberarnos! Esta é a última vez que cavo unha mina "
"para a túa raíña humana, déixame dicircho. «Limpa as vellas minas do "
"cruzamento», di ela. «A princesa necesítaas para algo!»"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. All we do is insult the queen a few times, in a friendly manner, and she gibbeted us. You humans just don't appreciate a good insult.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:590
msgid ""
"All we do is insult th’ queen a few times, all friendly-like and such, an’ "
"it was straight to the gibbet! You beanpoles jus’ dinnae appreciate a good "
"insult!"
msgstr ""
"O único que facemos é insultar á raíña unhas cantas veces, todos amigables e "
"demais, e ía directo á forca! Vós, parvos, non apreciades un bo insulto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. And now my job is gone; guess I have nothing left for me now but revenge. So if you're out to beat the queen, me and my boys are with you. (after this line, the player gains dwarvish miners as a recruit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:595
msgid ""
"An’ now tha’s my job gone; guess I got naught left fer me now but revenge. "
"So if yer out to beat the queen, me an’ my boys are with ye!"
msgstr ""
"E agora xa non teño traballo; supoño que non me queda nada máis que "
"vinganza. Así que, se queres vencer á raíña, os meus rapaces e eu estamos "
"contigo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:597
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Miners!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar mineiros ananos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:606
msgid ""
"... hey, what the— that axe! That axe you’re holdin’, that’s my father’s!"
msgstr "... ei, que... ese machado! Ese machado que tes na man é do meu pai!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:610
msgid ""
"Give it back, ye obscene trunk of tallow-keech! You milksop, you coward, "
"give it back or I’ll cut it from yer steamin’ corpse!"
msgstr ""
"Devólveo, tronco obsceno de sebo! Molón de leite, covarde, devólveo ou cho "
"cortarei do teu cadáver fumegante!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:614
msgid ""
"Calm down, calm down! I found this axe in the ruins of west Knalga. If it "
"truly is your father’s, of course you’re entitled to it. Here."
msgstr ""
"Calma, calma! Atopei esta machada nas ruínas do oeste de Knalga. Se "
"realmente é do teu pai, por suposto que tes dereito a ela. Toma."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:636
msgid "Com’ere you chicken-faced by-blow! Fight me like a dwarf!"
msgstr "¡Vén aquí, cara de galiña! ¡Loita comigo coma un anano!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:655
msgid ""
"Oy princess! Ah got an axe right ’ere with yer name on it! By Thursagan’s "
"beard, ah’ll teach you and yer men to lock me up!"
msgstr ""
"¡Oi, princesa! Teño aquí mesmo un machado co teu nome! Pola barba de "
"Thursagan, ensinareivos a ti e aos teus homes a encerrarme!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:669
msgid ""
"Where is Isolde? This battle is not so one-sided as I had hoped, but if "
"Konrad cannot defeat us soon he shall surely be trapped once my "
"reinforcements arrive."
msgstr ""
"Onde está Isolde? Esta batalla non é tan desigual como agardaba, pero se "
"Konrad non nos derrota pronto, sen dúbida quedará atrapado cando cheguen os "
"meus reforzos."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:681
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "We're finally here, your highness! Apologies for the delay."
msgid "We're finally here, Your Highness! Apologies for the delay."
msgstr "Por fin estamos aquí, alteza! Desculpas polo atraso."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:697
msgid ""
"More of them have come from behind! Even if we manage to defeat Li’sar, we "
"have no hope of escaping this battle alive..."
msgstr ""
"Máis deles viñeron por detrás! Mesmo se conseguimos derrotar a Li'sar, non "
"temos esperanza de escapar vivos desta batalla..."

#. [message]: speaker=knight
#. [message]: speaker=leader7
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:713
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:997
msgid "Fight on without me, Your Highness!"
msgstr "Loita sen min, Vosa Alteza!"

#. [message]: speaker=knight
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:718
msgid "Fight on without me, friends!"
msgstr "Loitade sen min, amigos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#. Lisar might not exist here, in which case nothing is said.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:726
#, fuzzy
msgid "You’ll pay for that, cousin!"
msgstr "Meus prisioneiros!! Pagarás por iso..."

#. [message]: speaker=Yrogin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:739
msgid "Aaargh! They said you were just a pretender... a puppet..."
msgstr "Aaargh! Dixeron que só eras un farsante... unha marioneta..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:771
msgid ""
"Not so tough now, are ye princess? Got any las’ words b’fer I bury m’ axe in "
"tha’ hollow skull, ye grubby wisenheimerin’ blockhead?"
msgstr ""
"Non es tan dura agora, non si? Tes algunha outra palabra antes de que "
"enterre o meu machado nese cranio oco, parvo e sucio de Wisenheimer?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:775
msgid ""
"Get off me, dwarf! I can’t fall here; there’s too much left to do. I may be "
"forced to flee the field today, “cousin”, but I will not rest until you face "
"justice for all the chaos you have caused."
msgstr ""
"¡Baixa de min, anano! Non podo caer aquí; queda moito por facer. Pode que me "
"vexa obrigado a fuxir do campo hoxe, \"primo\", pero non descansarei ata que "
"te enfrontes á xustiza por todo o caos que causaches."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:783
msgid ""
"So, Delfador “the Great” draws the blood of his betters once more. Do not "
"expect me to repeat the mistakes of my brother, old man — I shall flee the "
"field today, but I will not rest until you and your puppet face justice for "
"all the chaos you have caused."
msgstr ""
"Así que, Delfador “o Grande” volve sacar o sangue dos seus superiores. Non "
"esperes que repita os erros do meu irmán, vello. Fuxirei do campo hoxe, pero "
"non descansarei ata que ti e o teu monicreque sexades xustificados por todo "
"o caos que causastes."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:790
msgid ""
"So “cousin”, it seems you’re more than just a good actor and a pretty face. "
"No matter — I may be forced to flee the field today, but I will not rest "
"until you and your puppetmaster face justice for all the chaos you have "
"caused."
msgstr ""
"Entón, \"primo\", parece que es algo máis que un bo actor e unha cara "
"bonita. Non importa: pode que me vexa obrigado a fuxir do campo hoxe, pero "
"non descansarei ata que ti e o teu titiriteiro se enfrontedes á xustiza por "
"todo o caos que causastes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/17_Crossroads.cfg:807
msgid ""
"We carried the field, but the princess escaped! I doubt this is the last "
"we’ve seen of her..."
msgstr ""
"Recorrimos todo o campo, pero a princesa escapou! Dúbido que esta sexa a "
"última vez que a vimos..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:19
msgid "scenario name^The Highwaymen"
msgstr "Os Asasinos da Estrada"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:181
msgid "En garde!"
msgstr "En garda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:202
msgid ""
"Our timing is perfect: the first of our several targets is approaching the "
"city. Our scouts spotted several convoys nearby, but the others must not "
"have arrived yet."
msgstr ""
"O noso momento é perfecto: o primeiro dos nosos varios obxectivos está a "
"achegarse á cidade. Os nosos exploradores avistaron varios convois nas "
"proximidades, pero os outros aínda non deben ter chegado."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:207
msgid ""
"Each caravan will be brimming with supplies and weapons, so the more we "
"plunder, the more new types of soldiers we’ll be able to equip!"
msgstr ""
"Cada caravana estará chea de subministracións e armas, polo que canto máis "
"saqueemos, máis tipos novos de soldados poderemos equipar!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:210
msgid ""
"Aye, an’ good fer us that rain an’ fog ’ave come in. Those mole-eyed chicken-"
"city buffoons will have no idea we’re here, as long as we keep our distance "
"from th’ walls."
msgstr ""
"Si, e ben por nós que entraron a choiva e a néboa. Eses bufóns de ollos de "
"toupa da cidade das galiñas non terán nin idea de que estamos aquí, mentres "
"manteñamos a distancia dos muros."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:211
msgid ""
"Back in the day I remember doin’ something like this with Baldras an’ "
"Helicrom. Lucky for us that the fog’s out. As long as we’re careful an’ keep "
"our distance, th’ city won’t know we’re here."
msgstr ""
"Lembro que fixera algo así con Baldras e Helicrom. Por sorte para nós, non "
"hai néboa. Mentres teñamos coidado e manteñamos as distancias, a cidade non "
"saberá que estamos aquí."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:212
msgid ""
"Hark and behold! The Light provides, for rain and fog have come to shroud us "
"from our foes. As long as we keep our distance from the city, Dan’Tonk shall "
"surely remain ignorant of our presence."
msgstr ""
"Escoitade e contemplade! A Luz provén, porque a choiva e a néboa viñeron a "
"agocharnos dos nosos inimigos. Mentres manteñamos a distancia da cidade, "
"Dan'Tonk seguramente ignorará a nosa presenza."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:213
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:214
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "And look at all this fog! Well, that’s probably a good thing for us. If "
#| "we keep our distance from the city itself, I’m sure it’ll be some time "
#| "until the garrison is alerted."
msgid ""
"And look at all this fog! Well, that’s probably a good thing for us. If we "
"keep our distance from the city itself, I’m sure it’ll be some time before "
"the garrison is alerted."
msgstr ""
"E mira toda esta néboa! Ben, iso probablemente sexa algo bo para nós. Se "
"mantemos as distancias da cidade, estou seguro de que pasará algún tempo ata "
"que a guarnición sexa alertada."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:215
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:216
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:217
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:218
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "It is lucky for us that this rain has come with a thick fog. As long as "
#| "we keep our distance from the city proper, it may be some time until the "
#| "garrison is alerted to our presence."
msgid ""
"It is lucky for us that this rain has come with a thick fog. As long as we "
"keep our distance from the city proper, it may be some time before the "
"garrison is alerted to our presence."
msgstr ""
"É unha sorte para nós que esta choiva viñese cunha néboa espesa. Mentres "
"manteñamos a distancia da cidade, pode que pase algún tempo ata que a "
"guarnición sexa alertada da nosa presenza."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. $dead_wagons is a number; probably between 0 and 15
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:230
msgid ""
"Intercept enemy wagons before they reach Dan’Tonk ($dead_wagons destroyed so "
"far)"
msgstr ""
"Intercepta os vagóns inimigos antes de que cheguen a Dan'Tonk (vagóns mortos "
"destruídos ata o de agora)"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. [objective]: condition=win, description=<span strikethrough='true'>
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:235
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:242
msgid "5+ destroyed: recruit Fencers"
msgstr "5+ destruídos: recluta esgrimistas"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. [objective]: condition=win, description=<span strikethrough='true'>
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:250
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:257
msgid "8+ destroyed: recruit Spearmen"
msgstr "8+ destruídos: recluta lanzadores"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:265
msgid "all 11 destroyed: recruit Bowmen"
msgstr "Todos os 11 destruídos: recluta arqueiros"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:274
msgid ""
"The scenario will end once any caravan reaches Dan’Tonk and alerts the "
"garrison, or if any of Konrad’s units move within 4 hexes of the the "
"Dan’Tonk city walls (the unwalkable castle hexes)."
msgstr ""
"O escenario rematará unha vez que calquera caravana chegue a Dan'Tonk e "
"alerte a guarnición, ou se algunha das unidades de Konrad se achegue a menos "
"de 4 hexágonos das murallas da cidade de Dan'Tonk (os hexágonos do castelo "
"intransitables a pé)."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:303
msgid "Outlaws, here?! I warn you, I’m armed!"
msgstr "Foraxidos, aquí?! Avísovos, estou armado!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:316
msgid ""
"I hate being stuck all the way out here on observation duty. What’s the "
"point?"
msgstr ""
"Detesto estar aquí fóra facendo gardas de observación. Cal é o sentido?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. this helps tell the player that they can safely fight these guards without alerting Dan'Tonk
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:321
msgid ""
"Even if some bandits were to foolishly come this near to Dan’Tonk, what does "
"the lieutenant expect me to do? It’s not as if I have any way to warn the "
"city..."
msgstr ""
"Mesmo se algúns bandidos se achegasen tolamente a Dan'Tonk, que espera o "
"tenente que faga eu? Non é como se tivese ningunha maneira de avisar á "
"cidade..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:345
msgid ""
"Bandits in the fog! We’re under attack! It’s too far to warn the city — grab "
"your weapons!"
msgstr ""
"Bandidos na néboa! Estamos baixo ataque! Está demasiado lonxe para avisar á "
"cidade. Collede as vosas armas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:359
msgid ""
"We are approaching the walls of Dan’Tonk! Careful — if we come much closer, "
"the guards will spot us and we’ll be forced to abandon our mission."
msgstr ""
"Estamos achegándonos ás murallas de Dan'Tonk! Coidado: se nos achegamos "
"máis, os gardas detectaranos e veremosnos obrigados a abandonar a nosa "
"misión."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:373
msgid ""
"I’m sure I see shapes moving in the rain nearby, but with so much fog it’s "
"hard to tell exactly who it is. Hopefully one of our convoys."
msgstr ""
"Estou seguro de que vexo formas movéndose baixo a choiva nas proximidades, "
"pero con tanta néboa é difícil saber exactamente quen é. Oxalá sexa un dos "
"nosos convois."

#. [message]: role=wagons_mid
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:452
msgid "It’s an ambush! How did Maddock’s mercenaries get this far inland?!"
msgstr ""
"É unha emboscada! Como chegaron os mercenarios de Maddock tan lonxe terra "
"adentro?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:464
msgid ""
"That’s the first caravan destroyed! Well done, everyone — now we must stop "
"the second, too!"
msgstr ""
"Esa é a primeira caravana destruída! Ben feito a todos. Agora tamén debemos "
"deter a segunda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:469
msgid ""
"That’s the first caravan destroyed! Well done, everyone. We should continue "
"expanding our control over this area — there will be more caravans soon."
msgstr ""
"Esa é a primeira caravana destruída! Ben feito a todos. Deberíamos seguir "
"expandindo o noso control sobre esta zona; pronto haberá máis caravanas."

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:482
msgid ""
"Lieutenant, weren’t we expecting a weapons convoy some hours ago? I hope "
"they haven’t gotten into any trouble."
msgstr ""
"Tenente, non esperabamos un convoi de armas hai unhas horas? Espero que non "
"teñan ningún problema."

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:487
msgid ""
"The fog’s been causing delays for schedules all around the city, ma’am. The "
"shipment’s probably just stuck in some mud."
msgstr ""
"A néboa está a causar atrasos nos horarios de toda a cidade, señora. O envío "
"probablemente estea atascado na lama."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:515
msgid ""
"Another caravan is approaching the city, this time from the northern path!"
msgstr "Outra caravana achégase á cidade, esta vez polo camiño do norte!"

#. [message]: role=wagons_top {FILTER_ADJACENT side=1}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:526
msgid ""
"Outlaws on the road! Fighting elves in that awful forest was bad enough, and "
"now this?"
msgstr ""
"Foraxidos no camiño! Loitar contra elfos nese bosque horrible xa era "
"bastante malo, e agora isto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:531
msgid ""
"You speak in the presence of High Lord Kalenz of the elves, human! The wrath "
"of elf-kind falls upon you today!"
msgstr ""
"Falaches na presenza do Alto Señor Kalenz dos elfos, humano! A ira da raza "
"elfa cae sobre ti hoxe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:536
msgid ""
"Vengeance for the Aethenwood! You should never have left your city to come "
"burn my home!"
msgstr ""
"Vinganza polo Aethenwood! Nunca deberías ter abandonado a túa cidade para "
"vir queimar a miña casa!"

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:553
msgid ""
"Still no word from the wagon trains? Something’s wrong. Lieutenant, dispatch "
"a squad to patrol the area — we may be dealing with roadside bandits."
msgstr ""
"Aínda non hai noticias das caravanas? Algo vai mal. Tenente, envíe un "
"escuadrón para patrullar a zona; pode que esteamos a tratar con bandidos de "
"beira de estrada."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:556
msgid "Teory"
msgstr "Teoría"

#. [message]: speaker=squad_leader
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:594
msgid ""
"Ah ha, found you! We aren’t dealing with just any petty bandits — these are "
"Konrad’s rebels! I’ll see you hang for your crimes!"
msgstr ""
"Ah, ha, atopámoste! Non estamos a tratar con calquera bandido... estes son "
"os rebeldes de Konrad! Vouche aforcar polos teus crimes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:627
msgid ""
"A third convoy, along the southern path this time! This one is larger than "
"the previous two. Better-defended. but also a more valuable prize!"
msgstr ""
"Un terceiro convoi, esta vez polo camiño sur! Este é máis grande que os dous "
"anteriores. Mellor defendido. Pero tamén un premio máis valioso!"

#. [message]: role=wagons_bot {FILTER_ADJACENT side=1}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:638
msgid "Look out! Bandits on the road!"
msgstr "¡Coidado! ¡Bandidos na estrada!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:696
msgid ""
"The final convoy we’re waiting for has arrived — and this one approaches "
"from two directions at once!"
msgstr ""
"Chegou o último convoi que agardabamos, e este achégase desde dúas "
"direccións á vez!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:700
msgid ""
"We shall have to split our forces if we want to stop both. Or, if we lack "
"the strength, even defeating only one will still provide us with many "
"valuable weapons!"
msgstr ""
"Temos que dividir as nosas forzas se queremos deter a ambos. Ou, se nos "
"falta forza, mesmo derrotar só a un seguirá proporcionándonos moitas armas "
"valiosas!"

#. [message]: role=wagons_top {OR role=wagons_bot} {FILTER_ADJACENT side=1}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:712
msgid ""
"I knew I heard the sound of fighting in the fog! You’ll find we’re battle-"
"hardened veterans from Elensefar, and no easy prey for petty outlaws."
msgstr ""
"Sabía que escoitaba o son da loita na néboa! Verás que somos veteranos "
"curtidos na batalla de Elensefar e non somos presa fácil para os foraxidos "
"de pouca monta."

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:731
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:764
msgid ""
"Enough! Whether we see them or not, there’s clearly some capable enemy "
"lurking out in the fog. To arms, soldiers! This city is our place of "
"strength, and our armies far outnumber any petty bandits or rebels. "
"Whatever’s going on out there, it ends now."
msgstr ""
"Abonda! Vémolos ou non, hai claramente algún inimigo capaz agochado na "
"néboa. Ás armas, soldados! Esta cidade é o noso lugar de forza, e os nosos "
"exércitos superan en número a calquera pequeno bandido ou rebelde. Sexa o "
"que sexa o que estea a suceder aí fóra, remata agora."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:735
msgid ""
"As we knew would happen eventually, Dan’Tonk has become aware of our "
"presence, and Wesnoth’s armies are mobilizing to surround us. Quick, "
"everyone, let us make our escape and tally our plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Como sabiamos que acabaría acontecendo, Dan’Tonk decatouse da nosa presenza "
"e os exércitos de Wesnoth están a mobilizarse para rodearnos. Depresa, "
"todos, fuxamos e recontemos o noso botín!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:758
msgid ""
"That’s the last of these wagons! We’ve done well to capture so many supplies "
"and weapons. If we continue waiting here even more may yet arrive, but I "
"suspect we’ve pushed our luck staying as long as we have already."
msgstr ""
"Esa é a última destas carretas! Fixemos ben en capturar tantas "
"subministracións e armas. Se seguimos esperando aquí, pode que cheguen aínda "
"máis, pero sospeito que tentamos a sorte quedándonos tanto tempo como xa o "
"fixemos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#. "speak of a lich" is a made-up saying, with the same meaning as "speak of the devil"
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:769
msgid ""
"Speak of a lich... As we knew would happen eventually, Dan’Tonk has become "
"aware of our presence, and Wesnoth’s armies are mobilizing to surround us. "
"Quick, everyone, let us make our escape and tally our plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Falando dun liche... Como sabiamos que acabaría pasando, Dan’Tonk decatouse "
"da nosa presenza e os exércitos de Wesnoth están a mobilizarse para "
"rodearnos. Depresa, todos, escapemos e recontemos o noso botín!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:786
msgid ""
"I’ve reached the city walls! Alarm! Alarm! We spotted Konrad and his rebels "
"are lying in wait on the road!"
msgstr ""
"Cheguei ás murallas da cidade! Alarma! Alarma! Vimos a Konrad e os seus "
"rebeldes agardando no camiño!"

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:791
msgid ""
"The rebel army, here?! Those fools! To arms, soldiers! This city is our "
"place of strength, and I know us to far outnumber Konrad’s forces. We must "
"bring the false prince to justice!"
msgstr ""
"O exército rebelde, aquí?! Eses tolos! A armas, soldados! Esta cidade é o "
"noso punto forte, e sei que somos moito máis numerosos que as forzas de "
"Konrad. Debemos levar ao falso príncipe ante a xustiza!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:795
msgid ""
"A caravan has reached Dan’Tonk, and Wesnoth’s armies are mobilizing to "
"surround us! Quick, everyone, let us make our escape and tally our plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Unha caravana chegou a Dan’Tonk e os exércitos de Wesnoth están a "
"mobilizarse para rodearnos! Depresa, todos, fuxamos e recontemos o noso "
"botín!"

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:813
msgid ""
"Look — there! That figure can only be one of Konrad’s rebels, foolishly come "
"to fight Dan’Tonk itself."
msgstr ""
"Mira... alí! Esa figura só pode ser un dos rebeldes de Konrad, tolamente "
"chegado a loitar contra o propio Dan'Tonk."

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:817
msgid ""
"To arms, soldiers! This city is our place of strength, and I know us to far "
"outnumber Konrad’s forces. We must capture the false prince and bring him to "
"justice!"
msgstr ""
"A armas, soldados! Esta cidade é o noso lugar de forza, e sei que somos "
"moito máis numerosos que as forzas de Konrad. Debemos capturar o falso "
"príncipe e levalo ante a xustiza!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:821
msgid ""
"We’ve come too close to the city walls, and have been spotted! Quick, "
"everyone, let us make our escape and tally our plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Achegámonos demasiado ás murallas da cidade e detectáronnos! Rápido, todos, "
"fuxamos e contemos o botín!"

#. [message]: role=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:839
msgid ""
"What?! What sort of unseen enemy has attacked me without ever approaching "
"the city walls? I must flee!"
msgstr ""
"Que?! Que tipo de inimigo invisible me atacou sen achegarse nunca ás "
"murallas da cidade? Teño que fuxir!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/18_The_Highwaymen.cfg:846
msgid "Quick, everyone, let us make our escape and tally our plunder!"
msgstr "Depresa, todos, imos escapar e contabilizar o noso botín!"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:12
msgid "scenario name^The Ford of Abez"
msgstr "A Forca de Abez"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:38
msgid "Clan Stoneskin"
msgstr "Clan Pelapeito"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:141
msgid ""
"Have you reconsidered, troll? Let us pass, and bloodshed may yet be averted."
msgstr ""
"Reconsideráchelo, trol? Déixanos pasar, e pode que se evite o derramamento "
"de sangue."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Sorry, I done already told you, softskin. You gots to pay if you wants to "
"cross. Stoneskins fight hard to own ford, kill lotsa other trolls ’n orcs. "
"Dosh kill you too, no big whoop."
msgstr ""
"Desculpa, xa cho dixen, pel branda. Tes que pagar se queres cruzar. Os peles "
"de pedra loitan arreo para controlar o vao, matan a moitos outros troles e "
"orcos. Que te maten tamén a ti, sen problema."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:149
msgid ""
"The Ford of Abez was here long before you, and it will be here long after. "
"You have no more right to own it than do I, or any of the free peoples of "
"Wesnoth. Prepare for battle!"
msgstr ""
"O Vao de Abez estivo aquí moito antes ca vós, e estará aquí moito despois. "
"Non tedes máis dereito a posuílo que eu, ou calquera dos pobos libres de "
"Wesnoth. Preparádevos para a batalla!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:157
msgid "Defeat Dosh"
msgstr "Derrota a Dosh"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:175
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:176
msgid ""
"This is where the final betrayal took place. Where Eldred killed Garard and "
"his allies, opening the way for Asheviere’s domination. She has much to "
"answer for."
msgstr ""
"Aquí tivo lugar a traizón final. Aquí Eldred matou a Garard e aos seus "
"aliados, abrindo o camiño para a dominación de Asheviere. Ela ten moito que "
"responder."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:177
msgid ""
"Many terrible battles were once fought at this ford, Konrad. May ours prove "
"itself less deadly."
msgstr ""
"Moitas batallas terribles libráronse neste vao, Konrad. Que a nosa sexa "
"menos mortífera."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:178
msgid ""
"Delfador told me about the many terrible battles that were fought here. I "
"hope ours won’t prove itself so deadly."
msgstr ""
"Delfador contoume as moitas batallas terribles que se libraron aquí. Espero "
"que a nosa non sexa tan mortífera."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:201
msgid "Urgh... Dosh don’ feel so good. Maybe fight was mistake..."
msgstr "Urgh... Dosh non me sinto tan ben. Quizais a loita foi un erro..."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:210
msgid "Run away!"
msgstr "Fuxe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:228
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The leader of the trolls is defeated, and we have secured safe passage "
#| "across the ford! Great work, everyone — onwards into the northlands!"
msgid ""
"The leader of the trolls is defeated, and we have secured safe passage "
"across the ford! Great work, everyone — onwards into the Northlands!"
msgstr ""
"O líder dos troles foi derrotado e aseguramos unha pasaxe segura a través do "
"vao! Bo traballo, todos. Adiante, cara ás terras do norte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:233
msgid ""
"The leader of the trolls is defeated, and we have secured safe passage "
"across the ford! Great work, everyone — we can now return to Wesnoth!"
msgstr ""
"O líder dos troles foi derrotado e aseguramos unha pasaxe segura a través do "
"vao! Bo traballo, todos. Agora podemos volver a Wesnoth!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:248
msgid "Ormok"
msgstr "Ormok"

#. [message]: speaker=Ormok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:256
msgid "Ha ha ha, what’s this? Someone’s trying to dethrone the Stoneskins!"
msgstr ""
"Ha ha ha, que é isto? Alguén está a tentar destronar os Peles de Pedra!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ormok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:260
msgid "Hope you don’t mind if we take over! C’mon, boys, let’s kill ’em all!"
msgstr ""
"Espero que non vos importe se tomamos o control! Imos, rapaces, matémolos a "
"todos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/20_The_Ford_of_Abez.cfg:264
msgid ""
"We’ve taken too long to secure the ford! Now more orcs have arrived! Even if "
"we defeat them all, we’ll suffer greatly from the delay..."
msgstr ""
"Levamos demasiado tempo asegurando a vadiña! Agora chegaron máis orcos! "
"Mesmo se os derrotamos a todos, sufriremos moito polo atraso..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:18
msgid "scenario name^Glamdrol"
msgstr "Glamdrol"

#. [side]
#. [side]: type={TYPE}, id=leader{SIDE}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:45
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:63
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:47
msgid "Bloody Sword Clan"
msgstr "Clan da Espada Sangrenta"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:91
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:107
msgid "Stoneskin Clan"
msgstr "Clan da Pele de Pedra"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:129
msgid "Hu-nash"
msgstr "Hu-nash"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:132
msgid "Vikkak the Old"
msgstr "Vikkak o Vello"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:204
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:205
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:206
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:207
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:208
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:209
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:210
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:211
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:212
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:213
msgid "150 gold"
msgstr "150 de ouro"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:233
msgid "Get lost, you troll-sniffing degenerates!"
msgstr "¡Despérdaos, dexenerados cheireadores de trolls!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#. "Khazg" refers to Khazg Black-Tusk, the late leader of the Bloody Sword clan, mentioned in Northern Rebirth
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:238
msgid ""
"Khazg-worshipping tuskers! We come to trade and this is how you greet us? "
"Some hospitality."
msgstr ""
"¡Cascos adoradores dos Khazg! Vimos comerciar e así é como nos saúdan? Un "
"pouco de hospitalidade."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:242
msgid ""
"Trade? You came here to sneak inside and slaughter us all in our sleep! I’m "
"not having it. Get lost!"
msgstr ""
"Comercio? Viñeches aquí para colarte e masacrarnos a todos mentres "
"durmíamos! Non o vou permitir. Fóra!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:246
msgid "Oh yeah? Well— ...wait, do you see that?"
msgstr "Ah, de verdade? Pois... agarda, ves iso?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:345
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:348
msgid ""
"Humans! What’s an army of boot-licking humans doing so close to Glamdrol?"
msgstr ""
"Humanos! Que fai un exército de humanos lamber botas tan preto de Glamdrol?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:346
msgid ""
"Elves! What’s an army of tree-shagging elves doing so close to Glamdrol?"
msgstr ""
"Elfos! Que fai un exército de elfos que pelean as árbores tan preto de "
"Glamdrol?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:347
msgid ""
"Dwarves! What’s an army of dirt-grubbing dwarves doing so close to Glamdrol?"
msgstr ""
"Ananos! Que fai un exército de ananos lambentes de terra tan preto de "
"Glamdrol?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:349
msgid ""
"Invaders! What’s an army of boot-licking worms doing so close to Glamdrol?"
msgstr ""
"Invasores! Que fai un exército de vermes lambebotas tan preto de Glamdrol?"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:353
msgid ""
"Grr... we can settle things between us later. Right now we work together and "
"kill the vermin."
msgstr ""
"Grr... podemos arranxar as cousas entre nós máis tarde. Agora mesmo "
"traballamos xuntos e matamos as alimañas."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:365
msgid "Pillage as much gold as you can before turns run out"
msgstr "Pilla todo o ouro que poidas antes de que rematen as quendas"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:373
msgid ""
"Fulfill your pledge: end the scenario with at least $bm_s22_gold_cost gold"
msgstr ""
"Cumpre o teu xuramento: remata o escenario con polo menos $bm_s22_gold_cost "
"moedas de ouro"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:382
msgid "Defeat the orcish shaman to claim the Horn of Glamdrol"
msgstr "Derrota o xamán orco para reclamar o Corno de Glamdrol"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:390
msgid ""
"Fail your pledge: end the scenario with less than $bm_s22_gold_cost gold"
msgstr ""
"Fracasa no teu xuramento: remata o escenario con menos de $bm_s22_gold_cost "
"moedas de ouro"

#. [note]
#. "enemy" includes any enemy side. When one enemy dies, other enemies gain the "regenerates" ability for one turn.
#. The Horn of Glamdrol is an item, currently held by an enemy, that has this effect.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:404
msgid ""
"Horn of Glamdrol: Whenever you defeat one enemy, other enemies gain "
"regeneration for one turn"
msgstr ""
"Corno de Glamdrol: Sempre que derrotas a un inimigo, os outros inimigos "
"gañan rexeneración durante un turno"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:421
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We’re here for a quick raid, not to try to conquer the fortess outright. "
#| "Move swiftly, grab as much gold as we can, and get out!"
msgid ""
"We’re here for a quick raid, not to try to conquer the fortress outright. "
"Move swiftly, grab as much gold as we can, and get out!"
msgstr ""
"Estamos aquí para unha incursión rápida, non para tentar conquistar a "
"fortaleza de forma directa. Moveos con rapidez, collede todo o ouro que "
"poidamos e saíde!"

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:429
msgid "Konrad, look! Dem north side orcs be from da Stoneskin clan, like me."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, mira! Eses orcos do lado norte son do clan Pel de Pedra, coma min."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:433
msgid ""
"Dey ain’t so bad. No reason for us to be fighting. Dosh gona go talk to dem."
msgstr ""
"Non son tan malos. Non hai razón para que esteamos pelexando. Temos que ir "
"falar con eles."

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:453
msgid ""
"Hey, you! I recognize you; you’re the ford troll. What’re you doing working "
"for some lousy human?"
msgstr ""
"Ei, ti! Recoñézote; es o trol de Ford. Que fas traballando para un humano "
"desagradable?"

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:457
msgid ""
"Konrad not some lousy human. He is a big prince, and a great troll-friend! "
"Konrad paid Dosh much money, and now Dosh helps Konrad. You should help "
"Konrad too."
msgstr ""
"Konrad non é un humano desagradable. É un gran príncipe e un gran amigo "
"trol! Konrad pagoulle moito diñeiro a Dosh e agora Dosh axuda a Konrad. Ti "
"tamén deberías axudar a Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:461
msgid ""
"Hah. Well, sure, you tell your big prince to pay <i><b>me</b></i> big money, "
"and then maybe I will. It’s true that these Bloody Swords have owned "
"Glamdrol for long enough..."
msgstr ""
"Ha. Ben, claro, dígalle ao teu gran príncipe que <i><b>me</b></i> pague "
"moito diñeiro, e entón quizais o faga. É certo que estas Espadas "
"Sanguinarias levan tempo dominando Glamdrol..."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:470
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Pledge 300 gold: recruit troll whelps"
msgid "Pledge 400 gold: negotiate a truce and learn to recruit Troll Whelps"
msgstr "Promesa de 300 de ouro: recruta crías de trol"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:475
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Want more fighters like Dosh, do you? Har har, sure, that much gold is "
#| "worth at least a few whelps. Only because you’ve been vouched for."
msgid ""
"Want more fighters like that one, do you? Sure, 400 gold is worth at least a "
"few whelps. But I’m only offering because Dosh says you’re all right."
msgstr ""
"¿Queres máis loitadores coma Dosh, non? Har har, claro, esa cantidade de "
"ouro vale polo menos uns cantos filhotes. Só porque che avalaron."

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:479
msgid ""
"Trolls’re a bit dim, usually even more so than the one you’ve already got, "
"but you tell ’em who to smash and they’ll smash ’em good."
msgstr ""
"Os trols son un pouco parvos, normalmente aínda máis que o que xa tes, pero "
"dilles a quen hai que esmagar e esmagarán ben."

#. [command]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:481
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Troll Whelps!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar crías de trol!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:484
msgid ""
"Have fun sacking the city. When all’s said and done, you pay us out of the "
"coin you’ve looted — or else."
msgstr ""
"Divírtete saqueando a cidade. Cando todo estea dito e feito, págasnos coas "
"moedas que saqueaches... ou se non."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:496
msgid "Pledge 100 gold: negotiate a truce"
msgstr "Prometer 100 de ouro: negociar unha tregua"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:501
msgid ""
"100 gold for a truce? Deal. We’ll stay out of your way while you raid the "
"fortress, and when all’s said and done you pay us out of the coin you’ve "
"looted — or else."
msgstr ""
"100 de ouro por unha tregua? Acordo. Manterémonos á marxe mentres atacas a "
"fortaleza e, ao final, págasnos coas moedas que saqueaches... ou se non."

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:517
msgid ""
"Hah! Some friend you’ve got there, Dosh. Don’t worry, we’ll take all the "
"gold we want from your treasury once we kill you!"
msgstr ""
"Ha! Tes algún amigo aí, Dosh. Non te preocupes, colleremos todo o ouro que "
"queiramos do teu tesouro unha vez que te matemos!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:530
msgid ""
"I knew it! Filthy human-lover! You want to ruin us so you can take over "
"Glamdrol!"
msgstr ""
"Eu o sabía! Amante humano porco! Queres arruinarnos para poder apoderarte de "
"Glamdrol!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:534
msgid "What can I say? I came to trade, and the human boy offered a good one!"
msgstr "Que podo dicir? Vin a comerciar, e o rapaz humano ofreceume un de bo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:583
msgid ""
"I should be careful not to recruit too many extra units. While it’s tempting "
"to use the orcs’ gold to conquer their fortress, we’re ultimately here to "
"gather gold in preparation for our next battle. Clearing the fortress won’t "
"do us much good if we leave poorer than we arrived!"
msgstr ""
"Debería ter coidado de non recrutar demasiadas unidades adicionais. Aínda "
"que sexa tentador usar o ouro dos orcos para conquistar a súa fortaleza, en "
"última instancia estamos aquí para recoller ouro e prepararnos para a nosa "
"próxima batalla. Limpar a fortaleza non nos servirá de moito se marchamos "
"máis pobres do que chegamos!"

#. [companion_message]
#. TRoW's Jessene says that when orcs game to the Green Isle, the lich-lords "built a great stone gate to the heart of the homeland of the orcs in the distant west"
#. TRoW's Aethyr says that when orcs came to the Great Continent, they "must have seized all remaining boats on the Green Isle", but that's a guess rather than an observation
#. here, we establish that while some ships were definitely involved (we see them in TRoW), at least one magical gate was also used to bring orcs to the Great Continent.
#. I think that's sensible behavior for the Lich-Lords, and also explains how so many orcs were able to reach Wesnoth so fast. Only 20 years after the orcs first arrive, they're so powerful as to rival all the elves combined (LoW)
#. TRoW's Jessene says that when orcs game to the Green Isle, the lich-lords "built a great stone gate to the heart of the homeland of the orcs in the distant west"
#. TRoW's Aethyr says that when orcs came to the Great Continent, they "must have seized all remaining boats on the Green Isle", but that's a guess rather than an observation
#. here, we establish that while some ships were definitely involved (we see them in TRoW), at least one magical gate was also used to bring orcs to the Great Continent.
#. I think that's sensible behavior for the Lich-Lords, and also explains how so many orcs were able to reach Wesnoth so fast. Only 20 years after the orcs first arrive, they're so powerful as to rival all the elves combined (LoW)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:610
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:615
msgid ""
"A foul odor. A blight upon the wind. Konrad, this is a gateway created by "
"the lich-lords of ages past, during their genocidal hunt for the Ruby."
msgstr ""
"Un cheiro fétido. Unha praga para o vento. Konrad, esta é unha porta creada "
"polos señores lich de épocas pasadas, durante a súa caza xenocida do Rubí."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:616
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:617
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "A foul odor. A blight upon the wind. Konrad, this is a gateway created by "
#| "the lich-lords of ages past, during their genocidal hunt for the Ruby."
msgid ""
"A great orc-gate! To see one in person is... chilling. Konrad, this is a "
"gateway created by the lich-lords of ages past, during their genocidal hunt "
"for the Ruby."
msgstr ""
"Un cheiro fétido. Unha praga para o vento. Konrad, esta é unha porta creada "
"polos señores lich de épocas pasadas, durante a súa caza xenocida do Rubí."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:618
msgid ""
"There must have been magic in this chasm once, but it’s still and dead now. "
"Whatever power once created it has been long since vanished."
msgstr ""
"Debeu haber maxia neste abismo nalgún momento, pero agora está quieto e "
"morto. Calquera poder que o creou xa desapareceu hai moito tempo."

#. [companion_message]
#. TRoW's Jessene says that when orcs game to the Green Isle, the lich-lords "built a great stone gate to the heart of the homeland of the orcs in the distant west"
#. TRoW's Aethyr says that when orcs came to the Great Continent, they "must have seized all remaining boats on the Green Isle", but that's a guess rather than an observation
#. here, we establish that while some ships were definitely involved (we see them in TRoW), at least one magical gate was also used to bring orcs to the Great Continent.
#. I think that's sensible behavior for the Lich-Lords, and also explains how so many orcs were able to reach Wesnoth so fast. Only 20 years after the orcs first arrive, they're so powerful as to rival all the elves combined (LoW)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:627
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "They say it is through gates like this one that man first met orc, over "
#| "five hundred years ago. And when orc pursued man here to the Great "
#| "Continent, they came in such numbers as to nearly ruin my own people as "
#| "well.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "But that is ancient history. This gate died long ago; died alongside the "
#| "foul powers that created it, when they were slain by the human-kings of "
#| "old. May it never again awaken."
msgid ""
"They say it was through a gate like this one that man first met orc, over "
"five hundred years ago. And when orc pursued man here to the Great "
"Continent, they came in such numbers as to nearly ruin my own people as well."
msgstr ""
"Din que foi a través de portas coma esta que o home se atopou por primeira "
"vez co orco, hai máis de cincocentos anos. E cando o orco perseguiu o home "
"ata o Gran Continente, chegou en tal número que case arrasou tamén ao meu "
"propio pobo. Pero iso é historia antiga. Esta porta morreu hai moito tempo; "
"morreu xunto cos poderes abominables que a crearon, cando foron abatidos "
"polos antigos reis humanos. Que nunca volva espertar."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:629
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "They say it is through gates like this one that man first met orc, over "
#| "five hundred years ago. And when orc pursued man here to the Great "
#| "Continent, they came in such numbers as to nearly ruin my own people as "
#| "well.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "But that is ancient history. This gate died long ago; died alongside the "
#| "foul powers that created it, when they were slain by the human-kings of "
#| "old. May it never again awaken."
msgid ""
"But that is ancient history. This gate died long ago; died alongside the "
"foul powers that created it, when they were slain by the human-kings of old. "
"May it never again awaken."
msgstr ""
"Din que foi a través de portas coma esta que o home se atopou por primeira "
"vez co orco, hai máis de cincocentos anos. E cando o orco perseguiu o home "
"ata o Gran Continente, chegou en tal número que case arrasou tamén ao meu "
"propio pobo. Pero iso é historia antiga. Esta porta morreu hai moito tempo; "
"morreu xunto cos poderes abominables que a crearon, cando foron abatidos "
"polos antigos reis humanos. Que nunca volva espertar."

#. [companion_message]
#. TRoW's Jessene says that when orcs game to the Green Isle, the lich-lords "built a great stone gate to the heart of the homeland of the orcs in the distant west"
#. TRoW's Aethyr says that when orcs came to the Great Continent, they "must have seized all remaining boats on the Green Isle", but that's a guess rather than an observation
#. here, we establish that while some ships were definitely involved (we see them in TRoW), at least one magical gate was also used to bring orcs to the Great Continent.
#. I think that's sensible behavior for the Lich-Lords, and also explains how so many orcs were able to reach Wesnoth so fast. Only 20 years after the orcs first arrive, they're so powerful as to rival all the elves combined (LoW)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:635
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The elders record that it is through gates like this one that man first "
#| "met orc, over five hundred years ago. Lo! Darkness drove us from our "
#| "homes, and lo! Our proud people became a band of refugees.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Yet the Light has delivered us, for today we stand whole and strong. This "
#| "gateway died long ago. May it remain so until the end of days, until the "
#| "sun itself rains down from the heavens as sulfur and fire and all the "
#| "darkness is cleansed from this world."
msgid ""
"The elders record that it was through a gate like this one that man first "
"met orc, over five hundred years ago. Lo! Darkness drove us from our homes, "
"and lo! Our proud people became a band of refugees."
msgstr ""
"Os anciáns rexistran que foi a través de portas coma esta que o home coñeceu "
"por primeira vez aos orcos, hai máis de cincocentos anos. Velaquí! A "
"escuridade botounos dos nosos fogares, e velaquí! O noso orgulloso pobo "
"converteuse nunha banda de refuxiados.\n"
"\n"
"Porén, a Luz librounos, porque hoxe permanecemos enteiros e fortes. Esta "
"porta morreu hai moito tempo. Que permaneza así ata o fin dos días, ata que "
"o propio sol chova dos ceos como xofre e lume e toda a escuridade sexa limpa "
"deste mundo."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:637
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The elders record that it is through gates like this one that man first "
#| "met orc, over five hundred years ago. Lo! Darkness drove us from our "
#| "homes, and lo! Our proud people became a band of refugees.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Yet the Light has delivered us, for today we stand whole and strong. This "
#| "gateway died long ago. May it remain so until the end of days, until the "
#| "sun itself rains down from the heavens as sulfur and fire and all the "
#| "darkness is cleansed from this world."
msgid ""
"Yet the Light has delivered us, for today we stand whole and strong. This "
"gateway died long ago. May it remain so until the end of days, until the sun "
"itself rains down from the heavens as sulfur and fire and all the darkness "
"is cleansed from this world."
msgstr ""
"Os anciáns rexistran que foi a través de portas coma esta que o home coñeceu "
"por primeira vez aos orcos, hai máis de cincocentos anos. Velaquí! A "
"escuridade botounos dos nosos fogares, e velaquí! O noso orgulloso pobo "
"converteuse nunha banda de refuxiados.\n"
"\n"
"Porén, a Luz librounos, porque hoxe permanecemos enteiros e fortes. Esta "
"porta morreu hai moito tempo. Que permaneza así ata o fin dos días, ata que "
"o propio sol chova dos ceos como xofre e lume e toda a escuridade sexa limpa "
"deste mundo."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:639
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:640
msgid ""
"If I remember my histories, it was through a gate like this one that the "
"lich-lords’ orcs first invaded the Green Isle. Luckily for us, that was a "
"very long time ago, and the gates have long-since gone quiet — hopefully for "
"good."
msgstr ""
"Se lembro ben as historias, foi por unha porta coma esta pola que os orcos "
"dos señores liche invadiron por primeira vez a Illa Verde. Por sorte, iso "
"foi hai moito tempo, e as portas levan caladas dende entón… agardemos que "
"para sempre."

#. [companion_message]
#. TRoW's Jessene says that when orcs game to the Green Isle, the lich-lords "built a great stone gate to the heart of the homeland of the orcs in the distant west"
#. TRoW's Aethyr says that when orcs came to the Great Continent, they "must have seized all remaining boats on the Green Isle", but that's a guess rather than an observation
#. here, we establish that while some ships were definitely involved (we see them in TRoW), at least one magical gate was also used to bring orcs to the Great Continent.
#. I think that's sensible behavior for the Lich-Lords, and also explains how so many orcs were able to reach Wesnoth so fast. Only 20 years after the orcs first arrive, they're so powerful as to rival all the elves combined (LoW)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:646
msgid ""
"Dis da great orc-gate, Konrad. Once, long ago, lots o’ dem used it to come "
"here from far away and fight you softskins. But dey didn’t build it, and now "
"dey don’t know how to turn it back on again. Maybe nobody ever will."
msgstr ""
"Esta é a gran porta dos orcos, Konrad. Hai moito tempo, moitos deles usárona "
"para vir aquí de lonxe e loitar contra vós, os peles brandas. Pero eles non "
"a construíron, e agora non saben como volvela a activar. Quizais ninguén o "
"saiba facer nunca."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:660
msgid "One of our horde is dead! Blow the horn, shaman."
msgstr "Un dos nosos está morto! Toca o corno, xamán."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:697
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:698
msgid ""
"Urgh, my head! What kind of instrument could make such a sound? There’s "
"magic in that horn, Konrad, mark my words."
msgstr ""
"Argh, a miña cabeza! Que clase de instrumento pode facer un son así? Hai "
"maxia nese corno, Konrad, asegúrocho."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:699
msgid ""
"Urgh... that sound hurts my head somethin’ fierce. I’ve heard a lot o’ orc-"
"horns before, Konrad, an’ this one ain’t normal."
msgstr ""
"Urgh... ese son doeume a cabeza de xeito tremendo. Xa escoitei moitos cornos "
"de orco antes, Konrad, e este non é normal."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:700
msgid ""
"The air rings with power and might! Hark! I recognize orcish magic when I "
"hear it, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"O aire resoa de poder e forza! Escoita! Recoñezo a maxia orca cando a oio, "
"Konrad."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:701
msgid ""
"Gah! Now thar’s a sound to split an eardrum! Ah’ve heard plenty o’ scumbreed "
"half-dog warhorns before, Konrad, but this one ain’t normal."
msgstr ""
"Buf! Iso si que é un son para partir un tímpano! Xa escoitei moitos cornos "
"de guerra medio can esnaquizados antes, Konrad, pero este non é normal."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:702
msgid ""
"Ow! Ow, ow, that hurts my ears, and sets my bones all a-shaking! That can’t "
"be a mundane, every-day warhorn, can it?"
msgstr ""
"Ai! Ai, ai, iso dóeme os oídos e faime tremer os ósos! Iso non pode ser unha "
"trompeta mundana e cotiá, non si?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:703
msgid ""
"Dat’s a bad sound for us, Konrad. Dosh been hearin’ dis horn before — it’s "
"not no normal warhorn. It’s got some kind of orc-magic."
msgstr ""
"Iso soa mal para nós, Konrad. Xa oíra este corno antes... Non é un corno de "
"guerra normal. Ten algún tipo de maxia orca."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:704
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:705
msgid ""
"From the fortress rings a piercing sound of sacrifice, death, and rebirth! "
"There is orcish magic at work here, Konrad."
msgstr ""
"Dende a fortaleza resoa un estridente son de sacrificio, morte e "
"renacemento! Aquí hai maxia orca traballando, Konrad."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:706
msgid ""
"From the fortress rings a piercing sound of sacrifice, death, and rebirth! "
"There is orcish magic at work here."
msgstr ""
"Dende a fortaleza resoa un son estridente de sacrificio, morte e "
"renacemento! Aquí hai maxia orca en acción."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:711
msgid ""
"Tremble before the Horn of Glamdrol, worms! Whenever one of us falls, the "
"rest shall be healed anew!"
msgstr ""
"Tembredes ante o Cuerno de Glamdrol, vermes! Cada vez que un de nós cae, os "
"demais serán curados de novo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:727
msgid ""
"What’s this? That orc was carrying a strange horn with magical markings. I "
"will take it and examine it when I have time — for now we must continue to "
"fight."
msgstr ""
"Que é isto? Ese orco levaba un corno estraño con marcas máxicas. Collereino "
"e examinareino cando teña tempo — por agora temos que seguir loitando."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:732
msgid ""
"The shaman is dead, and we’ve claimed her magical horn for ourselves! There "
"will be time to examine it later — for now we must continue to fight."
msgstr ""
"O xamán está morto, e reclamamos para nós o seu corno máxico! Haberá tempo "
"para examinalo máis tarde — por agora debemos seguir loitando."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:751
msgid ""
"What are we doing fighting up here? The orcs’ gold is in their city, not "
"here among these trolls!"
msgstr ""
"Que estamos a facer loitando aquí enriba? O ouro dos orcos está na súa "
"cidade, non aquí entre estes trols!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:769
msgid "The chiefs are dead! Run for the hills!"
msgstr "Os xefes están mortos! Fuxide ás colinas!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:783
msgid "I spit my last breath at you!"
msgstr "Cuspín o meu último alento enriba de ti!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:792
msgid ""
"Let’s get out of here! Filthy invaders, I’m finding the high chief and "
"bringing his warriors back from their raid! You’d better not be here when he "
"gets back!"
msgstr ""
"¡Vaia de aquí! Invasores noxentos, vou atopar o gran xefe e traer os seus "
"guerreiros de volta da súa incursión! Será mellor que non esteades aquí "
"cando volva!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:805
msgid ""
"We have defeated all of the orcs! An incredible challenge — well done, "
"everyone. Time to take our leave of this place, and to tally our plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Derrotamos a todos os orcos! Un desafío incrible — ben feito, a todos. É "
"hora de marcharnos deste lugar e de contar o noso botín!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:822
msgid ""
"We can afford to fight here only a little longer! This is orcish territory, "
"and every minute here only further risks our enemies being reinforced."
msgstr ""
"Podemos permitirnos loitar aquí só un pouco máis! Este é territorio orco, e "
"cada minuto que permanecemos aquí só aumenta o risco de que os nosos "
"inimigos sexan reforzados."

#. [message]: speaker=$speaker_id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:837
msgid ""
"That’s it! You pinkskins are proving way too much of a nuisance. I’m finding "
"the high chief and bringing his warriors back from their raid!"
msgstr ""
"Iso é! Vós, os peles rosas, estades a ser unha molestia demasiado grande. "
"Vou atopar o xefe supremo e traer os seus guerreiros de volta da súa "
"incursión!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:844
msgid ""
"That sounds like our cue to leave. We can’t risk being pinned down and "
"eradicated. Quick, everyone, let us make our escape and tally our plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Iso parece a nosa sinal para marchar. Non podemos arriscarnos a ser "
"atrapados e erradicados. Rápido, todos, fuxamos e recontemos o noso botín!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:862
msgid "Hey, what about my gold? You made a pledge!"
msgstr "Eh, e o meu ouro que? Fixeches unha promesa!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:866
msgid ""
"I’m sorry, but we didn’t pillage enough from Glamdrol to cover all "
"$bm_s22_gold_cost gold. Can I pay you later?"
msgstr ""
"Síntoo, pero non saqueamos o suficiente de Glamdrol para cubrir as "
"$bm_s22_gold_cost moedas de ouro. Podo pagarche máis adiante?"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/22_Glamdrol.cfg:870
msgid ""
"Oh, that’s no problem — we’ll just take what we’re owed off your corpse. "
"Attack! Don’t let them escape!"
msgstr ""
"Oh, non hai problema… simplemente cobraremos o que se nos debe do teu "
"cadáver. Ao ataque! Non os deixedes escapar!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:105
msgid "Infirm Yeti"
msgstr "Yeti enfermo"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:159
msgid ""
"Brrr... it may not be winter, but with the storm swirling about overhead it "
"certainly feels like it. This place is freezing!"
msgstr ""
"Brrr... pode que non sexa inverno, pero coa tormenta xirando por riba da "
"cabeza parece que si. Este lugar está xeado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:164
msgid ""
"Hello! Are you all right? What’re you doing out here in the cold? ...she’s "
"still not paying attention."
msgstr ""
"Ola! Estás ben? Que fas aquí fóra co frío? ...ela aínda non está prestando "
"atención."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:176
msgid "Err, hello? HELLO!"
msgstr "Err, ola? OLA!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:184
msgid ""
"Aaah! Don’t sneak up on a woman like that; the jump you gave me nearly "
"ruined three days’ work!"
msgstr ""
"¡Aaah! Non te achegues así a unha muller ás agachadas; o salto que me deches "
"case arruinou tres días de traballo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:188
msgid ""
"I’m sorry, I just wanted to see if everything is all right. What’re you "
"doing alone and unarmed all the way up here in these snows?"
msgstr ""
"Síntoo, só quería ver se todo está ben. Que fas só e desarmado aquí arriba, "
"nestas neves?"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:192
msgid ""
"Ah, I’m glad you asked! You see, I’m an — err, how should I say it — "
"alchemist, yes, yes, alchemist is right. A researcher!"
msgstr ""
"Ah, alégrome de que mo preguntases! Verás, son un... eh, como o diría... "
"alquimista, si, si, o alquimista ten razón. Un investigador!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:196
msgid ""
"You’re a mage? That explains why you’re not carrying any weapons. Are you "
"conducting some sort of magical experiment?"
msgstr ""
"Es un mago? Iso explica por que non levas ningunha arma. Estás a realizar "
"algún tipo de experimento máxico?"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:200
msgid ""
"No, no! I’m not one of those stuffy bleary-eyed academics; I don’t make "
"magic, I cause chemistry! There’s all sorts of valuable alchemical reagents "
"here in the mountains. I’m certain my theories are correct, I just need the "
"ingredients to prove it!"
msgstr ""
"Non, non! Non son un deses académicos abafados e con ollos cansos; non fago "
"maxia, provoco química! Hai todo tipo de reactivos alquímicos valiosos aquí "
"nas montañas. Estou seguro de que as miñas teorías son correctas, só preciso "
"os ingredientes para demostralo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:204
msgid ""
"Most of the herbs, you see, I’ve had no trouble collecting. Err, but, well, "
"the local fauna — as you may surmise, the fauna has proven somewhat less "
"cooperative than for which I was prepared... Right! But now you’re here to "
"help!"
msgstr ""
"A maioría das herbas, como vedes, non tiven ningún problema en recollelas. "
"Eh, pero, bueno, a fauna local... como podedes supoñer, a fauna demostrou "
"ser algo menos cooperativa do que estaba preparado... Certo! Pero agora "
"estades aquí para axudar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Here, take this leather pouch for the tongue... and yes, this glass jar for "
"the bile— No! Not that one, this one—"
msgstr ""
"Toma, colle esta bolsa de coiro para a lingua... e si, este frasco de vidro "
"para a bile... Non! Ese non, este..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:216
msgid ""
"What is all this stuff? You... want me to gather some alchemy components for "
"you, is that right?"
msgstr ""
"Que é todo isto? Ti… queres que recolla compoñentes de alquimia para ti, é "
"iso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:218
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "What is all this stuff? You... want me to gather some alchemy components "
#| "for you, is that right?\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I am Konrad, heir to the throne of Wesnoth, and on a quest to depose the "
#| "dark queen Asheviere. I’m happy to leave you with food or gold if you’re "
#| "in trouble, but I’m not sure my army and I can spare the time to stop and "
#| "help you collect ingredients."
msgid ""
"I am Konrad, heir to the throne of Wesnoth, and on a quest to depose the "
"dark queen Asheviere. I’m happy to leave you with food or gold if you’re in "
"trouble, but I’m not sure my army and I can spare the time to stop and help "
"you collect ingredients."
msgstr ""
"Que é todo isto? Queres que reúnan algúns compoñentes de alquimia para ti, "
"¿é iso? Son Konrad, herdeiro do trono de Wesnoth, e estou nunha misión para "
"depor á escura raíña Asheviere. Estarei encantado de deixarte comida ou ouro "
"se estás en apuros, pero non estou seguro de que o meu exército e eu "
"poidamos dispoñer do tempo para detérmonos e axudarche a recoller os "
"ingredientes."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:222
msgid ""
"Yes, ingredients, precisely! And if you did take the time to help me out, "
"I’d be very grateful. And... and! If you help me, I’ll help you in return "
"and come with you on your quest. A great chance to field-test my concoctions "
"against that queen of yours."
msgstr ""
"Si, ingredientes, precisamente! E se che tomases o tempo para axudarme, "
"estaríache moi agradecido. E... e! Se me axudas, axudareche a cambio e "
"acompañareiche na túa misión. Unha gran oportunidade para probar no terreo "
"as miñas pocións contra esa raíña túa."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:226
msgid ""
"I only need three more ingredients to complete my experiments. Icemonax "
"bile. Giant Spider venom — that one’s a doozy. And, err, believe it or not, "
"Yeti tongue. If Yetis exist."
msgstr ""
"Só preciso tres ingredientes máis para completar os meus experimentos. Bile "
"de Icemonax. Veleno de araña xigante (ese si que é xenial). E, crédeo ou "
"non, lingua de yeti. Se é que os yetis existen."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:230
msgid ""
"... and if we can collect all three of these, you’ll come with us to help us "
"fight against Asheviere? I suppose that sounds like a fair trade."
msgstr ""
"... e se podemos recoller estes tres, virás connosco para axudarnos a loitar "
"contra Asheviere? Supoño que iso parece un intercambio xusto."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:234
msgid ""
"Absolutely! I may not be of much use right now, but once you get my "
"ingredients for me I’ll be able to help you fight through the use of a "
"variety of alchemical concoctions. For now, the keep is yours — I’ve noticed "
"a very interesting species of beetle over here..."
msgstr ""
"Absolutamente! Pode que non sexa de moita utilidade agora mesmo, pero unha "
"vez que me traias os meus ingredientes poderei axudarte a loitar mediante o "
"uso dunha variedade de mesturas alquímicas. Por agora, a fortaleza é túa. "
"Notei unha especie de escaravello moi interesante por aquí..."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:249
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Pillage as much gold as you can before turns run out"
msgid "Gather as many ingredients as you can before turns run out:"
msgstr "Pilla todo o ouro que poidas antes de que rematen as quendas"

