#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:291
msgid "Defeat a Yeti"
msgstr "Derrota a un ieti"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:299
msgid "Death of Jeniver"
msgstr "Morte de Jeniver"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:307
msgid ""
"Springtime Storm: at the end of every third turn (1, 4, 7, etc), Konrad’s "
"forces will become slowed."
msgstr ""
"Treboada de primavera: ao final de cada terceiro turno (1, 4, 7, etc.), as "
"forzas de Konrad reduciranse."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:313
msgid ""
"Summer Storm: at the end of every fourth turn (1, 5, 9, etc), Konrad’s "
"forces will become slowed."
msgstr ""
"Treboada de verán: ao final de cada cuarto turno (1, 5, 9, etc.), as forzas "
"de Konrad reduciranse."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:319
msgid ""
"Autumn Storm: at the end of every third turn (1, 4, 7, etc), Konrad’s forces "
"will become slowed."
msgstr ""
"Treboada de outono: ao final de cada terceiro turno (1, 4, 7, etc.), as "
"forzas de Konrad reduciranse."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:325
msgid ""
"Winter Storm: at the end of every second turn (1, 3, 5, etc), Konrad’s "
"forces will become slowed."
msgstr ""
"Tormenta de inverno: ao final de cada segundo turno (1, 3, 5, etc.), as "
"forzas de Konrad quedarán ralentizadas."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:353
msgid ""
"Brr! This snowstorm is paralyzing me with cold! It’s springtime; surely the "
"weather should be warmer than this?"
msgstr ""
"Brr! Esta tormenta de neve está a paralizarme de frío! É primavera; seguro "
"que o tempo debería ser máis cálido ca este, non si?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:354
msgid ""
"Brr! This snowstorm is paralyzing me with cold! At least it’s summertime; "
"the weather would surely be far worse in winter."
msgstr ""
"Brr! Esta tormenta de neve está a paralizarme de frío! Polo menos é verán; o "
"tempo seguramente sería moito peor no inverno."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:355
msgid ""
"Brr! This snowstorm is paralyzing me with cold! It’s only autumn; surely the "
"weather should be warmer than this?"
msgstr ""
"Brr! Esta tormenta de neve está a paralizarme de frío! Só é outono; seguro "
"que o tempo debería ser máis cálido ca este, non si?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:356
msgid ""
"Brr! This snowstorm is paralyzing me with cold! The weather here must be "
"especially bad in the winter months, like now."
msgstr ""
"Brr! Esta tormenta de neve está a paralizarme de frío! O tempo aquí debe ser "
"especialmente malo nos meses de inverno, como agora."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:364
msgid ""
"Hmm? Oh, ah, did I forget to mention the chill? Silly me — there’s, err, yes "
"there’s virtually always a storm blowing here; you’ll all be slowed down "
"quite often, trying to keep warm while trudging through the deepening "
"snowbanks. The local fauna are, of course, quite impervious to the cold."
msgstr ""
"Mmm? Ah, ah, esquecín mencionar o frío? Que parva son... aquí, eh, si, case "
"sempre hai unha tormenta soprando; a miúdo frearédesvos a todos, intentando "
"mantervos quentes mentres camiñades penosamente polos bancos de neve que se "
"fan máis profundos. A fauna local é, por suposto, bastante impermeable ao "
"frío."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:367
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:368
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We will not be able to fight in this blizzard forever, Konrad. Unless we "
#| "have very fast warriors, we may have to split up if we want to collect "
#| "all of Jeniver’s ingredients before we run out of time and the cold "
#| "drives us away. The northeastern mountains look especially hard to reach!"
msgid ""
"Brrr... this is a far cry from the warm shores of Alduin. Unless we have "
"very fast warriors, we may have to split up if we want to collect all of "
"Jeniver’s ingredients before we run out of time and the cold drives us away. "
"The northeastern mountains look especially hard to reach."
msgstr ""
"Non poderemos loitar nesta ventisca para sempre, Konrad. A menos que teñamos "
"guerreiros moi rápidos, teremos que separarnos se queremos recoller todos os "
"ingredientes de Jeniver antes de que se nos esgote o tempo e o frío nos faga "
"fuxir. As montañas do nordeste parecen especialmente difíciles de alcanzar!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:369
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:370
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "We will not be able to fight in this blizzard forever, Konrad. Unless we "
#| "have very fast warriors, we may have to split up if we want to collect "
#| "all of Jeniver’s ingredients before we run out of time and the cold "
#| "drives us away. The northeastern mountains look especially hard to reach!"
msgid ""
"We will not be able to fight in this blizzard forever, Konrad. Unless we "
"have very fast warriors, we may have to split up if we want to collect all "
"of Jeniver’s ingredients before we run out of time and the cold drives us "
"away. The northeastern mountains look especially hard to reach."
msgstr ""
"Non poderemos loitar nesta ventisca para sempre, Konrad. A menos que teñamos "
"guerreiros moi rápidos, teremos que separarnos se queremos recoller todos os "
"ingredientes de Jeniver antes de que se nos esgote o tempo e o frío nos faga "
"fuxir. As montañas do nordeste parecen especialmente difíciles de alcanzar!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:371
msgid ""
"We won’t be able t’ fight in th’ blizzard forever, Konrad. Unless we have "
"very fast warriors, we might want t’ split up to collect all o’ Jeniver’s "
"ingredients afore we run out o’ time and the cold drives us away. Them "
"northeastern mountains look ’specially hard t’ reach!"
msgstr ""
"Non poderemos loitar na ventisca para sempre, Konrad. A menos que teñamos "
"guerreiros moi rápidos, quizais queiramos separarnos para recoller todos os "
"ingredientes de Jeniver antes de que se nos esgote o tempo e o frío nos "
"afaste. Esas montañas do nordeste parecen especialmente difíciles de "
"alcanzar!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:372
msgid ""
"The Light warms us, yet this chill blizzard takes its toll, Konrad. Unless "
"we have very fast warriors, we may have to split up should we hope to "
"collect all of Jeniver’s ingredients before our time runs short and the cold "
"drives us away. The northeastern mountains loom especially distant!"
msgstr ""
"A Luz quéntanos, pero esta fría tormenta de neve pasa factura, Konrad. A "
"menos que teñamos guerreiros moi rápidos, pode que teñamos que separarnos se "
"queremos recoller todos os ingredientes de Jeniver antes de que o noso tempo "
"se esgote e o frío nos afaste. As montañas do nordeste alzanse especialmente "
"lonxe!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:373
msgid ""
"We ain’t prepared t’ fight ferever in a blizzard like this, Konrad. Lest "
"ye’ve got some very fast warriors, we may be havin’ to split up t’ get all "
"o’ Jeniver’s ingredients afore we run out o’ time and the cold drives us "
"away. Them northeastern mountains look ’specially hard t’ reach!"
msgstr ""
"Non estamos preparados para loitar para sempre nunha ventisca coma esta, "
"Konrad. A menos que teñas algúns guerreiros moi rápidos, teremos que "
"separarnos para conseguir todos os ingredientes de Jeniver antes de que se "
"nos esgote o tempo e o frío nos faga fuxir. Esas montañas do nordeste "
"parecen especialmente difíciles de alcanzar!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:374
msgid ""
"Storm too cold, Konrad. Unless you got some fast fighters, Dosh is thinking "
"we’ve got no time get all da ’gredients unless you splits us up. Otherwise "
"we get too cold and den have to leave. Northeast mountains look ’specially "
"hard to be gettin’ to."
msgstr ""
"Demasiado frío hai unha treboada, Konrad. A non ser que teñas algúns cazas "
"rápidos, Dosh pensa que non temos tempo para conseguir todos os ingredientes "
"a non ser que nos separes. Se non, arrefriaremos demasiado e teremos que "
"marchar. As montañas do nordeste parecen especialmente difíciles de alcanzar."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:375
msgid ""
"We won’t be able to fight in this blizzard forever. Unless we have very fast "
"warriors, we may have to split up if we want to collect all of your "
"ingredients before we run out of time and the cold drives us away. The "
"northeastern mountains look especially hard to reach!"
msgstr ""
"Non poderemos loitar nesta ventisca para sempre. A menos que teñamos "
"guerreiros moi rápidos, teremos que separarnos se queremos recoller todos os "
"teus ingredientes antes de que se esgote o tempo e o frío nos faga fuxir. As "
"montañas do nordeste parecen especialmente difíciles de alcanzar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:379
msgid ""
"True, true, but, well, you know, I suppose there’d really be no harm in "
"coming with you even if you don’t get them all— yes, I think I’ll join you "
"no matter what. You seem the nice sort, very chivalrous and all that."
msgstr ""
"É certo, é certo, pero, ben, xa sabes, supoño que non habería ningún "
"problema en vir contigo aínda que non consigas todos—si, creo que me "
"xuntarei contigo pase o que pase. Paréceme que es dunha boa persoa, moi "
"cabaleiresco e todo iso."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:383
msgid ""
"But— err, of course I suppose I wouldn’t really be of much use to you unless "
"you can gather at least some ingredients so that I can get my — you know — "
"alchemical concoctions prepared. The more the better!"
msgstr ""
"Pero... eh, por suposto, supoño que non che sería de moita utilidade a menos "
"que poidas reunir polo menos algúns ingredientes para que eu poida preparar "
"as miñas... xa sabes... mesturas alquímicas. Canto máis, mellor!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:422
msgid ""
"These are the Knalgan caves we exited from. No point going back, at least "
"not until we’ve finished helping Jeniver collect her ingredients."
msgstr ""
"Estas son as covas Knalgan das que saímos. Non ten sentido volver, polo "
"menos non ata que rematemos de axudar a Jeniver a recoller os seus "
"ingredientes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:427
msgid ""
"This cave must be an entrance to the great underground empire of Knalga! We "
"may decide to go that way later, but for now we should help Jeniver collect "
"her ingredients."
msgstr ""
"Esta cova debe de ser a entrada ao gran imperio subterráneo de Knalga! "
"Podemos decidir ir por alí máis tarde, pero por agora deberíamos axudar a "
"Jeniver a recoller os seus ingredientes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:446
msgid ""
"I’ve defeated one of the young Icemonax, Jeniver! How do I get the bile you "
"wanted?"
msgstr ""
"Derrotei a un dos mozos Icemonax, Jeniver! Como consigo a bile que querías?"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:450
msgid ""
"Oh, ah, I neglected to mention: only the Great Icemonax have the requisite "
"liver chemistry for producing bile. You’ll have to down one of the bigger "
"ones before I can collect what I need."
msgstr ""
"Ah, ah, esquecín mencionar: só os Grandes Icemonax teñen a química hepática "
"necesaria para producir bile. Terás que tragar un dos máis grandes antes de "
"que poida recoller o que preciso."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:464
msgid "Oh, the Icemonax is dead! Yes, yes... allow me to extract the bile..."
msgstr "Oh, o Icemonax está morto! Si, si... permíteme extraer a bile..."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:469
msgid ""
"... there! Now add essence of wandweed... bone of the tyrant... a lit torch—"
"<i><b>stand back!</b></i>"
msgstr ""
"... xa está! Agora engade esencia de herba varita... óso do tirano... unha "
"tocha acesa... <i><b>¡afágate!</b></i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:480
msgid ""
"Smoke! Yes, earth turned to air... most useful for befuddling and bewitching "
"the unprepared, and a validation of my theory of elemental humors!"
msgstr ""
"Fume! Si, a terra convertida en aire... moi útil para confundir e embruxar "
"aos desprevenidos, e unha validación da miña teoría dos humores elementais!"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:486
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:555
msgid "New Attack"
msgstr "Novo ataque"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:487
msgid "Jeniver has gained a powerful <i>flashpowder</i> attack!"
msgstr "Jeniver gañou un poderoso ataque <i>de pólvora destellante</i> !"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:506
msgid "Look out! That giant spider is furious, and it’s coming right at us!"
msgstr "Coidado! Esa araña xigante está furiosa e vén cara a nós!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#. Jeniver is incorrect; the spider will mind. This message plays when spiders and Konrad's forces are about to engage in battle.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:511
msgid ""
"Oh, come now, I’m sure it just wants to make friends. No need for violence; "
"to get what I need, all you need to do is lever apart the front incisors and "
"gently massage the venom sacks. I’m sure the spider won’t mind."
msgstr ""
"Vaia, estou segura de que só quere facer amigos. Non hai necesidade de "
"violencia; para conseguir o que necesito, o único que tes que facer é "
"separar os incisivos frontais e masaxear suavemente os sacos de veleno. "
"Seguro que á araña non lle importará."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:522
msgid ""
"You have the spider venom! Fantastic! I shall just add a distillation of "
"euphoria... a dash of elf-hair, a few other bits and bobs..."
msgstr ""
"Tes o veleno de araña! Fantástico! Engadirei simplemente unha destilación de "
"euforia... un chisco de pelo de elfo, algunhas outras cosiñas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:527
msgid "And... and! And my elixir of immortality is ready!"
msgstr "Compra o elixir para Owaec (30 ouros)."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:542
msgid "Blarghh!!!"
msgstr "Que rabia!!!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:549
msgid ""
"Ugh... well, so much for my treatise on the life-extending properties of "
"venoms. Ah, well— well, setbacks are inevitable! At least the toxin, "
"properly prepared, may make for a useful weapon."
msgstr ""
"Ugh... pois tanto por o meu tratado sobre as propiedades prolongadoras da "
"vida dos venenos. Ah, ben— ben, os contratempos son inevitables! Polo menos "
"o tóxico, debidamente preparado, pode converterse nunha arma útil."

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:556
msgid "Jeniver has gained a poisoned <i>blowgun</i> attack!"
msgstr "Jeniver gañou un ataque <i>de cerbatana</i> envelenada!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:575
msgid ""
"They truly are real! This Yeti would be a majestic sight, if not for how "
"determined it is to beat our heads in with its bare fists!"
msgstr ""
"¡Realmente son reais! Este Yeti sería unha vista majestuosa, se non fose "
"pola súa determinación de machucarnos as cabezas cos seus puños nus!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:586
msgid "Fantastic, the Yeti is defeated! Let me take a look at that tongue..."
msgstr ""
"Fantástico, o Yeti está derrotado! Déixame botarlle unha ollada a esa "
"lingua..."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:591
msgid ""
"Yes, yes, now one dash of mugwort... essence of skyworm, heated under a cold "
"flame... and... and— And golden transmutation is achieved!"
msgstr ""
"Si, si, agora unha pinga de milfo... esencia de verme do ceo, quentada baixo "
"unha chama fría... e... e— E a transmutación dourada conséguese!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:597
msgid ""
"Golden transmutation? You mean you can transmute other substances into gold? "
"That’s an incredible accomplishment!"
msgstr ""
"Transmutación áurea? Queres dicir que podes transmutar outras substancias en "
"ouro? Iso é un logro incrible!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:601
msgid ""
"Err, well, no, not quite. It’s more of a... distillation — yes, a process "
"for refining and extracting more value out of your existing coin. But "
"“transmutation” is a much more exciting word for alchemists. And etymology "
"aside, my discovery will certainly help boost your income!"
msgstr ""
"Eh, pois non, non exactamente. É máis ben unha... destilación; si, un "
"proceso para refinar e extraer máis valor da túa moeda existente. Pero "
"\"transmutación\" é unha palabra moito máis emocionante para os alquimistas. "
"E deixando de lado a etimoloxía, o meu descubrimento certamente axudará a "
"aumentar os teus ingresos!"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:607
msgid "New Ability"
msgstr "Nova habilidade"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:608
msgid "Jeniver has gained the powerful <i>transmutation</i> ability!"
msgstr "Jeniver gañou a poderosa habilidade <i>de transmutación</i> !"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:638
msgid ""
"And with that— yes, with that, I have everything I needed from the north! "
"Excellent! I wonder what substances I should turn my study to next..."
msgstr ""
"E con iso... si, con iso, teño todo o que necesitaba do norte! Excelente! "
"Pregúntome a que substancias debería centrar o meu estudo a continuación..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:642
msgid ""
"I’m glad to help! But don’t forget, you’d said you would join us if we "
"helped you here."
msgstr ""
"Encántame axudar! Pero non esquezas que dixeches que te unirías a nós se che "
"axudábamos aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:646
msgid ""
"Hmm? Oh yes, yes, that’s quite right, of course. In fact I’ve got some new "
"ideas that I’m just longing to pursue; perhaps joining you on your travels "
"will provide me with a good opportunity for travel and research. I’d be glad "
"to accompany you on your travels, Konrad!"
msgstr ""
"Mmm? Ah, si, si, iso é correcto, por suposto. De feito, teño algunhas ideas "
"novas que anhelo levar a cabo; quizais acompañarte nas túas viaxes me "
"proporcione unha boa oportunidade para viaxar e investigar. Encantaríame "
"acompañarte nas túas viaxes, Konrad!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:661
msgid ""
"We musn’t take too long helping Jeniver. The air is frigid and growing worse "
"by the minute; meanwhile Asheviere continues to grow stronger and stronger "
"unchecked."
msgstr ""
"Non debemos tardar demasiado en axudar a Jeniver. O aire está xeado e "
"empeora cada minuto; mentres tanto, Asheviere segue medrando cada vez máis "
"sen control."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:665
msgid ""
"Jeniver has said she will still follow us even if we run out of time, but "
"without all three ingredients she also won’t be as useful as she might "
"otherwise have been."
msgstr ""
"Jeniver dixo que nos seguirá mesmo se nos quedamos sen tempo, pero sen os "
"tres ingredientes tampouco será tan útil como podería ter sido doutro xeito."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:672
msgid ""
"Jeniver, I know we’d promised to help gather your alchemical ingredients, "
"but between the cold and the threat of Asheviere we simply can’t spare any "
"more time to help you."
msgstr ""
"Jeniver, sei que prometémosche axudar a reunir os teus ingredientes "
"alquímicos, pero entre o frío e a ameaza de Asheviere simplemente non "
"podemos dedicar máis tempo a axudarte."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:676
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Oh, yes, no I understand; that’s quite all right. In fact I’ve got some "
#| "new ideas that I’m just longing to pursue; irregardless of the remaining "
#| "ingredients here, perhaps joining you on your travels will provide me "
#| "with a good opportunity for travel and research. If you’ll have me, of "
#| "course!"
msgid ""
"Oh, yes, no I understand; that’s quite all right. In fact I’ve got some new "
"ideas that I’m just longing to pursue; regardless of the remaining "
"ingredients here, perhaps joining you on your travels will provide me with a "
"good opportunity for travel and research. If you’ll have me, of course!"
msgstr ""
"Ah, si, non, entendo; está ben. De feito, teño algunhas ideas novas que "
"anhelo levar a cabo; independentemente dos ingredientes restantes, quizais "
"acompañarte nas túas viaxes me proporcione unha boa oportunidade para viaxar "
"e investigar. Se me aceptas, por suposto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:692
msgid ""
"Oh no! We promised to help Jeniver find her alchemical ingredients, but "
"instead we’ve let her die..."
msgstr ""
"Oh, non! Prometemos axudar a Jeniver a atopar os seus ingredientes "
"alquímicos, pero no seu lugar deixámola morrer..."

#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:701
msgid "scenario name^Northern Spring"
msgstr "Primavera do Norte"

#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:702
msgid "scenario name^Northern Summer"
msgstr "Verán do Norte"

#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:703
msgid "scenario name^Northern Autumn"
msgstr "Outono do Norte"

#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/23_Northern_Winter.cfg:704
msgid "scenario name^Northern Winter"
msgstr "Inverno do Norte"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:8
msgid "scenario name^An Old Friend"
msgstr "Un vello amigo"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:64
msgid "Deoran"
msgstr "Deoran"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:140
msgid ""
"You have led us to a dark part of the jungle, great-granddaughter. And "
"undead? What are undead doing in Wesmere?!"
msgstr ""
"Leváchesnos a unha parte escura da selva, bisneta. E mortos viventes? Que "
"fan os mortos viventes en Wesmere?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Not any undead. That dark rider is our friend Deoran, risen anew as a wight "
"after Eldred so cruelly struck him down. He remembers nothing but echoes. It "
"is terrible, Kalenz!"
msgstr ""
"Non calquera morto vivente. Ese xinete escuro é o noso amigo Deoran, "
"resucitado de novo como un espectro despois de que Eldred o derrubase tan "
"cruelmente. Non lembra nada máis que ecos. É terrible, Kalenz!"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:149
msgid "Death... I lowered my sword... A blade in my chest..."
msgstr "Morte... Baixei a miña espada... Unha folla no meu peito..."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:153
msgid ""
"I don’t know whether Deoran was turned to undeath as some insult of "
"Asheviere’s or by the dark magic of Eldred’s fall, but now he has come here "
"to Wesmere. He has sought me out..."
msgstr ""
"Non sei se Deoran se converteu en non-morte por algún insulto de Asheviere "
"ou pola maxia escura da caída de Eldred, pero agora veu aquí a Wesmere. "
"Buscoume..."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:157
msgid ""
"Deoran was a good man, and deserved better than the end he met. I know you "
"and he were close, Chantal, and I am sorry."
msgstr ""
"Deoran era un bo home e merecía un final mellor que o que sufriu. Sei que ti "
"e el erades moi próximos, Chantal, e síntoo."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:161
msgid ""
"I had not the heart to kill him... one death was enough pain. But I know "
"that we cannot leave him to rampage through Wesmere. Now that you are here, "
"if his bones must be crushed and his body destroyed, so be it."
msgstr ""
"Non tiven valor para matalo... unha morte xa era dor dabondo. Pero sei que "
"non podemos deixalo arrasar Wesmere. Agora que estades aquí, se os seus ósos "
"deben ser esmagados e o seu corpo destruído, que así sexa."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:165
msgid ""
"Indeed, it would a mercy to put this cursed being out of his misery. But "
"perhaps it can be done without the violence that you would so abhor."
msgstr ""
"De feito, sería unha mágoa poñer fin á miseria deste ser maldito. Pero "
"quizais se poida facer sen a violencia que tanto aborrecerías."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:172
msgid ""
"Not far from here is a place of old magic; a burial ground once prepared for "
"one of our lords of old. It was never used, but remains a place of great "
"peace and rest. You say Deoran has sought you out; I believe he has sought "
"out this tomb."
msgstr ""
"Non moi lonxe de aquí hai un lugar de maxia antiga; un cemiterio preparado "
"noutro tempo para un dos nosos señores de antano. Nunca se usou, pero segue "
"sendo un lugar de gran paz e descanso. Dis que Deoran te buscou; eu creo que "
"buscou esta tumba."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:176
msgid ""
"If we can lure him into the tomb without destroying him, his tired bones may "
"at last find the peace they have so long been denied. And your tired heart "
"may at last find closure, great-granddaughter."
msgstr ""
"Se podemos atraelo á tumba sen destruílo, os seus ósos cansos poderán atopar "
"por fin a paz que lles foi negada durante tanto tempo. E o teu corazón canso "
"poderá atopar por fin un peche, bisneta."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:184
msgid "Lure undead Deoran into the burial chamber, and leave him alone inside."
msgstr "Atrae a Deoran morto vivente á cámara funeraria e déixao só dentro."

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:188
msgid "Death of Deoran"
msgstr "Morte de Déoran"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:192
msgid "Death of Kalenz or Chantal"
msgstr "Morte de Kalenz ou Chantal"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:200
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:539
msgid "In this scenario, you can neither gain nor spend gold."
msgstr "Neste escenario, non podes nin gañar nin gastar ouro."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:203
msgid "Deoran will prefer to target Chantal."
msgstr "Deoran preferirá dirixirse a Chantal."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:215
msgid "Blackcrests... more, to the north... Rally! Form ranks..."
msgstr "Blackcrests... máis, ao norte... Reunídevos! Formade filas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:228
msgid ""
"You don’t remember me, do you, Deoran... We shared good memories together, "
"back in the Lintanir."
msgstr ""
"Non te lembras de min, non si, Deoran... Compartimos bos recordos xuntos, no "
"Lintanir."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:232
msgid "... Chantal? No, not here... War is no... place for you..."
msgstr ""
"... Chantal? Non, non estás aquí... A guerra non... é un lugar para ti..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#. Deoran references Mebrin from TSG, and Kalenz's lich-eye potion from LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:246
msgid ""
"Mebrin... I sense eye... of lich... Your time has come... once-wise sage..."
msgstr ""
"Mebrin... sinto o ollo... de lich... Chegou a túa hora... outrora sabio..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#. Deoran references Mebrin's line from TSG S06b: "I curse you, Deoran of Wesnoth! I curse you... may you one day know the same pain that your kind have inflicted on me..."
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:251
msgid "You cursed me... you cursed me... to know the same pain..."
msgstr "Maldicichesme... maldicichesme... para saber a mesma dor..."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:263
msgid "He’s inside! Now we need to exit the tomb and leave him there."
msgstr "Está dentro! Agora temos que saír da tumba e deixalo alí."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:322
msgid "There! Now shut the gate and the magic will begin to do its work."
msgstr "Alí! Agora pecha a porta e a maxia comezará a facer o seu traballo."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:334
msgid "Is it working?"
msgstr "¿Está a funcionar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:338
msgid "My... head..."
msgstr "A miña... cabeza..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:353
msgid "I died. How am I here? I remember better places... happier times..."
msgstr ""
"Morrín. Como estou aquí? Lembro mellores lugares... tempos máis felices..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:357
msgid "... goodbye, Chantal."
msgstr "Adeus, Mebrin."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:363
msgid "Goodbye."
msgstr "Adeus."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:385
msgid "Eldred—"
msgstr "Eldred"

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:391
msgid "No! He has been broken to pieces..."
msgstr "Non! Foi despezado en anacos..."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:413
msgid "Argh! I am finished!"
msgstr "Argh! Xa rematei!"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:434
msgid ""
"The undead Deoran is beginning to cast his head wildly this way and that. If "
"we cannot complete our task, I fear he shall soon flee into the river, and "
"vanish to bring harm to some other land."
msgstr ""
"O non morto Deoran comeza a xirar a cabeza salvaxemente de aquí para alá. Se "
"non podemos completar a nosa tarefa, temo que pronto fuxirá ao río e "
"desaparecerá para causar dano noutro lugar."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:441
msgid "You cannot... trap me, Mebrin... I see my escape..."
msgstr "Non podes... atraparme, Mebrin... Vexo a miña escapada..."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/24_An_Old_Friend.cfg:447
msgid ""
"Deoran has gone! We’ve taken too long to seal him away, and now we may never "
"find him again..."
msgstr ""
"Deoran xa non está! Tardamos demasiado en selalo, e agora pode que nunca o "
"volvamos atopar..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:17
msgid "scenario name^The Dwarven Doors"
msgstr "As Portas Ananas"

#. [message]: role=angry_orc
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:209
msgid ""
"Back into your hovel, worms! Your masters will deal with this idiot attack."
msgstr ""
"De volta á vosa cabana, vermes! Os vosos amos encargaranse deste ataque "
"idiota."

#. [message]: role=angry_orc
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:217
msgid ""
"And stay in there. Any pinkskin sticks its head out, it won’t have a head "
"for much longer!"
msgstr ""
"E quédate aí dentro. Calquera pel rosada que saque a cabeza, non a terá por "
"moito máis tempo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:238
msgid ""
"Hark! The darkness fills this valley: orcs. More than even my light can "
"purify! Our crossing will be difficult, yet cross we must, if the dwarven "
"caverns we wish to exit."
msgstr ""
"Escoitade! A escuridade enche este val: orcos. Máis do que mesmo a miña luz "
"pode purificar! A nosa travesía será difícil, pero debemos cruzala se "
"queremos saír das cavernas ananas."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:239
msgid ""
"There’s orcs here; lots of orcs. More than we can fight, I’m thinkin’. But "
"we’ve gots to get through if’n we want to get out o’ these dwarf tunnels!"
msgstr ""
"Hai orcos aquí; moitos orcos. Máis dos que podemos combater, creo. Pero "
"temos que seguir adiante se queremos saír destes túneles ananos!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:240
msgid ""
"There are orcs here; many orcs, likely more than we can defeat. Yet we must "
"pass through this valley if we wish to exit the dwarven caverns."
msgstr ""
"Hai orcos aquí; moitos orcos, probablemente máis dos que podemos derrotar. "
"Con todo, debemos atravesar este val se queremos saír das cavernas dos "
"ananos."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:242
msgid ""
"Hark! The darkness fills this valley: orcs. More than even my light can "
"purify! Our crossing will be difficult, yet cross we must, if the dwarven "
"caverns we wish to enter."
msgstr ""
"Escoitade! A escuridade enche este val: orcos. Máis do que mesmo a miña luz "
"pode purificar! A nosa travesía será difícil, pero debemos cruzala se "
"queremos entrar nas cavernas ananas."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:243
msgid ""
"There’s orcs here; lots of orcs. More than we can fight, I’m thinkin’. But "
"we’ve gots to get through if’n we want to into them dwarf tunnels!"
msgstr ""
"Hai orcos aquí; moitos orcos. Máis dos que podemos combater, creo. Pero "
"temos que pasar se queremos chegar a esas galerías dos ananos!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:244
msgid ""
"There are orcs here; many orcs, likely more than we can defeat. Yet we must "
"pass through this valley if we wish to enter the dwarvish caverns beyond."
msgstr ""
"Hai orcos aquí; moitos orcos, probablemente máis dos que podemos derrotar. "
"Con todo, debemos atravesar este val se queremos entrar nas cavernas dos "
"ananos máis alá."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:247
msgid ""
"Filthy white-livered orcish cowards, squatting here in the ruins o’ the city "
"o’ the dwarf-friends! Swallow-tiltin’ marmalade drinkers! I say we take an "
"axe to every last one o’ the wretches!"
msgstr ""
"Covardes orcos de fígado branco e sucios, agachados aquí nas ruínas da "
"cidade dos amigos-ananos! Bebedores de marmelada a tragar! Eu digo que lle "
"demos un machado a cada un destes desgraciados!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:250
msgid ""
"Oh! Oh wow, that’s really a lot of orcs! I mean I knew there would be a lot "
"but... wow! And slaves! I’d no idea there were so many humans living up in "
"the north."
msgstr ""
"Oh! Oh, caramba, cantos orcos! Sabía que habería moitos, pero... caramba! E "
"escravos! Non tiña nin idea de que houbese tantos humanos vivindo no norte."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:251
msgid ""
"Mmm... Konrad better be bein’ careful. Dese be da Bloody Sword orcs. Ever "
"since dey took over dis valley, dey’ve got really big and really strong. How "
"you thinkin’ we should fight?"
msgstr ""
"Mmm... mellor que Konrad teña coidado. Estes son os orcos da Espada "
"Sanguenta. Desde que se apoderaron deste val, volvéronse moi grandes e "
"fortes. Como cres que deberiamos loitar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:258
msgid ""
"As much as I wish we could stay and liberate all these poor slaves, there "
"are just too many foes to fight. We’ve caught them by surprise right now, "
"but that won’t last long."
msgstr ""
"Por moito que desexe que puidésemos quedar e liberar a todos estes pobres "
"escravos, hai demasiados inimigos contra os que loitar. Xa os collemos por "
"sorpresa, pero iso non durará moito."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:261
msgid ""
"We’ll have to focus on fighting our way through to the south exit, and free "
"as many slaves as we can along the way!"
msgstr ""
"Temos que centrarnos en loitar ata a saída sur e liberar o maior número de "
"escravos posible polo camiño!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:263
msgid ""
"We’ll have to focus on fighting our way through to the north exit, and free "
"as many slaves as we can along the way!"
msgstr ""
"Temos que centrarnos en loitar ata a saída norte e liberar tantos escravos "
"como poidamos polo camiño!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:276
msgid "Move Konrad to the marked tunnel entrance"
msgstr "Mover a Konrad á entrada do túnel sinalada"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:283
msgid "Move Konrad to the southern edge of the map"
msgstr "Mover a Konrad ao bordo sur do mapa"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:291
msgid "Rescue as many slaves as possible"
msgstr "Rescata tantos escravos como sexa posible"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:301
msgid ""
"Liberating a village will free the slaves inside. The more slaves are with "
"you, the fewer new ones will appear."
msgstr ""
"Liberar unha aldea liberará os escravos do seu interior. Cantos máis "
"escravos haxa contigo, menos aparecerán novos."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:304
msgid "Each surviving slave increases your gold carryover by 10."
msgstr "Cada escravo sobrevivente aumenta o teu ouro residual en 10."

#. [modify_unit]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:352
msgid "Tanry"
msgstr "Tanry"

#. [message]: role=freed_slave {NOT id=$unit.id}
#. the speaking peasant/woodsman refers to a time when Baldras and some allies tried to help the Doors, but got captured. The player may or may not know about at this point.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:361
msgid ""
"I— I can’t believe it. Have you come to rescue us? Others have tried "
"before..."
msgstr ""
"Eu... eu non o podo crer. Viñeches rescatarnos? Outros xa o intentaron "
"antes..."

#. [message]: id=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:366
msgid ""
"By the Lords of Light, we’re saved! Take us with you! I don’t care who you "
"are or where you’re going, as long as it’s away!"
msgstr ""
"Polos Señores da Luz, estamos salvos! Lévanos convosco! Non me importa quen "
"sexas nin onde vaias, sempre que sexa lonxe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:370
msgid ""
"I am Konrad, son of Arand and rightful heir to the throne of Wesnoth. Words "
"cannot express my grief at the sorry state of you and your people here. Of "
"course you may come with us, as may any other slaves who we are able to free!"
msgstr ""
"Son Konrad, fillo de Arand e lexítimo herdeiro ao trono de Wesnoth. As "
"palabras non poden expresar a miña dor polo lamentable estado en que vos "
"atopades aquí, vostede e o seu pobo. Por suposto, podedes vir connosco, así "
"como calquera outro escravo que poidamos liberar!"

#. [message]: id=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:382
msgid ""
"You’re making for the dwarven caves? I heard the masters say the central "
"gate’s been collapsed for years — them dwarves did it to keep orcs out. "
"Maybe you could come up from underground through there, if you had time to "
"clear a path. But there’s no way down."
msgstr ""
"¿Vas cara ás covas dos ananos? Escoitei aos mestres dicir que a porta "
"central leva anos esboroada — foron os ananos quen a derrubaron para manter "
"fóra aos orcos. Quizais poidas subir desde as entrañas da terra por alí, se "
"tes tempo para abrir un camiño. Pero non hai forma de baixar."

#. [message]: id=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:386
msgid ""
"They tried to knock down the eastern mineshaft too, but its since been "
"cleared. Lots o’ orcs and trolls go in, trying to finish off the last "
"dwarves and claim Knalga’s treasure for themselves. That’s the only way "
"underground now."
msgstr ""
"Tamén tentaron derrubar o pozo mineiro oriental, pero dende entón foi "
"despexado. Moitos orcos e trols entran alí, tentando acabar cos últimos "
"ananos e facerse co tesouro de Knalga. Esa é agora a única vía subterránea."

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:405
msgid "Who’s there? What’s goin’ on?"
msgstr "Quen é? Que está a pasar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:413
msgid "... Uncle Somf? Is that really you? What’re you doing here!"
msgstr "... Tío Somf? Es ti de verdade? Que fas aquí!"

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:417
msgid "Harper!? Well, I never— my, how ye’ve grown!"
msgstr "Harper!? Pois eu nunca... meu Deus, como medraches!"

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:421
msgid ""
"How did ye find me? When we left the Three Sisters to try an’ help these "
"people, Baldras ne’er told any o’ ye where we was goin’, fer fear o’ the "
"orcs catchin’ wind."
msgstr ""
"Como me atopastes? Cando deixamos as Tres Irmás para tentar axudar a esta "
"xente, Baldras nunca vos dixo a ninguén onde iamos, por medo aos orcos que "
"collesen vento."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:425
msgid ""
"When you all didn’t come back, Delurin thought you was all dead, but I never "
"lost hope. Where’s Uncle Baldras? I’ve so many things to tell him!"
msgstr ""
"Cando non volvésedes, Delurin pensou que estabades todos mortos, pero eu "
"nunca perdín a esperanza. Onde está o tío Baldras? Teño tantas cousas para "
"dicirlle!"

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:429
msgid ""
"Ah... I’m sorry Harper, but he’s dead. Died a hero; saved us all when things "
"went bad."
msgstr ""
"Ah... Síntoo, Harper, pero está morto. Morreu como un heroe; salvounos a "
"todos cando as cousas ían mal."

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:433
msgid ""
"Them orcs caught us soon as we got close, before we e’en got a chance to "
"start smugglin’ people out. Yer uncle took the blame fer the whole thin’; "
"said he was an escaped slave causin’ trouble, an’ that the rest of us were "
"jus’ innocents mixed up in it all."
msgstr ""
"Eses orcos atrapáronnos en canto nos achegamos, antes mesmo de que tivésemos "
"a oportunidade de comezar a sacar xente de contrabando. O teu tío asumiu a "
"culpa de todo; dixo que era un escravo fuxido que estaba a causar problemas "
"e que o resto de nós eramos simplemente inocentes metidos en todo isto."

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:437
msgid ""
"Orcs can’t hardly tell humans apart, you know; they believed every word he "
"said. The rest o’ us they chained up and whipped a few times, afore throwin’ "
"us into the fields to be slaves. But Baldras they made an’ example out of."
msgstr ""
"Os orcos case non poden distinguir os humanos, sabes? Crían cada palabra que "
"dicía. Ao resto de nós encadeáronos e azoutáronos unhas cantas veces, antes "
"de botarnos aos campos para ser escravos. Pero de Baldras puxeron un exemplo."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:441
msgid ""
"I was so sure he’d be okay... but I suppose it woulda been too good to be "
"true. At least you’ve survived, Somf."
msgstr ""
"Estaba tan segura de que estaría ben... pero supoño que sería demasiado bo "
"para ser verdade. Polo menos sobreviviches, Somf."

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:449
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "... Konrad, this is Somf — a friend from the Three Sisters. Somf, this is "
#| "His Royal Highness Konrad, prince of Wesnoth. I’m fighting in his army, "
#| "an’ now you are too."
msgid ""
"... Konrad, this is Somf — a friend from the Three Sisters. Somf, this is "
"His Royal Highness Konrad, Prince of Wesnoth. I’m fighting in his army, an’ "
"now you are too."
msgstr ""
"... Konrad, este é Somf, un amigo das Tres Irmás. Somf, este é Súa Alteza "
"Real Konrad, príncipe de Wesnoth. Eu loito no seu exército e agora ti tamén."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:458
msgid ""
"I am Konrad, heir to the throne of Wesnoth. I’m here to rescue you from "
"these slavers! Will you join me and help fight in my army?"
msgstr ""
"Son Konrad, herdeiro ao trono de Wesnoth. Estou aquí para rescatarvos destes "
"escravistas! Unirédesvos a min e axudaredes a loitar no meu exército?"

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:462
msgid ""
"That’s mighty fine of you to offer, boy; liberatin’ me from one master only "
"to offer yerself as my new one. Hah, I weren’t born yesterday!"
msgstr ""
"Moi xenial da túa parte ofrecerte, rapaz; liberándome dun só amo para "
"ofrecerte a ti mesmo como o meu novo amo. Ha, non nacín onte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:468
msgid ""
"That man looked like he could’ve made a capable warrior! I am sorry to see "
"him go — but least we have given him the freedom to choose his own path."
msgstr ""
"Parecía que ese home podería ter sido un guerreiro competente! Síntoo moito "
"por marchar, pero polo menos démoslle a liberdade de elixir o seu propio "
"camiño."

#. [message]: type=Cuttle Fish,Kraken
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:488
msgid "Ruarrrrr!!!"
msgstr "Ruarrrr!!!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:491
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:492
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:493
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Gah! Look out, there’s some kind of monster in the lake!"
msgid "By Haldric! There’s some sort of monster in the lake!"
msgstr "Bu! Coidado, hai algún tipo de monstro no lago!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:494
msgid ""
"Aaah! There’s— it’s— well, I don’t mean to sound unscientific, but it’s a "
"monster!"
msgstr "Aaah! Hai— é— ben, non quero soar pouco científico, pero é un monstro!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:495
msgid "Thursagan’s beard! There’s a great galumphing monster in the lake!"
msgstr "Barba de Thursagan! Hai un gran monstro tropeante no lago!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:496
msgid "By the Light! A monster most foul lurks within the waters!"
msgstr "Pola Luz! Un monstro moi repugnante agóchase nas augas!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:497
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Gah! Look out, there’s some kind of monster in the lake!"
msgid "Dere be some kind of monster in da lake!"
msgstr "Bu! Coidado, hai algún tipo de monstro no lago!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:498
msgid "Gah! Look out, there’s some kind of monster in the lake!"
msgstr "Bu! Coidado, hai algún tipo de monstro no lago!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:502
msgid ""
"The legend was true! They say there’s always tentacled creatures hiding in "
"lakes near dwarven tunnels."
msgstr ""
"A lenda era certa! Din que sempre hai criaturas con tentáculos agochadas en "
"lagos preto dos túneles ananos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:514
msgid ""
"Here stand the pillars of Thunedain. He were a great lord o’ my kind; the "
"last o’ the heroes o’ the Doors. Here did he stand, an’ here did he fall."
msgstr ""
"Aquí álzanse os piares de Thunedain. Foi un gran señor da miña especie; o "
"último dos heroes das Portas. Aquí se ergueu e aquí caeu."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:515
msgid ""
"I think these to be the pillars of Thunedain, Konrad. He was a legendary "
"dwarvish lord who made his last stand here. May we triumph where he fell."
msgstr ""
"Creo que estes son os piares de Thunedain, Konrad. Foi un señor anano "
"lendario que fixo a súa última batalla aquí. Que triunfemos onde el caeu."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:516
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:517
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:518
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Is this— yes, these must be the pillars of Thunedain. He was a great "
#| "dwarvish lord who made his last stand here. May we triumph where he fell."
msgid ""
"Is this— yes, these must be the pillars of Thunedain. I read about this. He "
"was a great dwarvish lord who made his last stand here."
msgstr ""
"É isto... si, estes deben ser os piares de Thunedain. Foi un gran señor "
"anano que fixo a súa última batalla aquí. Que triunfemos onde el caeu."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:544
msgid ""
"We’ve reached the southern exit to the valley, and have dealt a great blow "
"to these orcs! If only we could have truly liberated this place... but I "
"know that far more people are suffering under Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Chegamos á saída sur do val e infliximos un gran golpe a estes orcos! Se só "
"puidésemos liberar de verdade este lugar... pero sei que moita máis xente "
"está a padecer baixo Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:548
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:569
msgid ""
"At least we did our best to help those who were enslaved here. To those who "
"remain; to those we could not save I say: <i>Hold fast your hope, for one "
"day you shall be free!</i>"
msgstr ""
"Polo menos fixemos todo o posible por axudar aos que estaban escravizados "
"aquí. Aos que quedan; aos que non puidemos salvar, dígolles: <i>Mantede a "
"esperanza, porque algún día seredes libres!</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:565
msgid ""
"We’ve reached the entrance to the dwarven tunnels, and have dealt a great "
"blow to these orcs! If only we could have truly liberated this place... but "
"I know that far more people are suffering under Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Chegamos á entrada dos túneles ananos e asestamos un gran golpe a estes "
"orcos! Oxalá puidésemos liberar de verdade este lugar... pero sei que moita "
"máis xente está a sufrir baixo Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:587
msgid ""
"As we were warned, the central tunnels have been collapsed. We shall have to "
"make for the eastern mineshaft instead."
msgstr ""
"Como nos avisaron, os túneles centrais derrubáronse. Teremos que dirixirnos "
"ao pozo da mina leste."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:592
msgid ""
"The central tunnels are collapsed! Maybe some of the slaves knew about this, "
"but I freed so few... We shall have to make for the eastern mineshaft, and "
"hope that entrance is still open."
msgstr ""
"Os túneles centrais están derrubados! Pode que algúns dos escravos o "
"soubesen, pero liberei a tan poucos... Teremos que dirixirnos ao pozo "
"oriental da mina e esperar que a entrada aínda estea aberta."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:608
msgid "Death to slavers!"
msgstr "Morte aos traficantes de escravos!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:620
msgid "This isn’t going so well..."
msgstr "Isto non vai tan ben..."

#. [message]: id=$last_leader.id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:642
msgid ""
"Okay, forget this. I’m taking the rest of our slaves, getting the chief, and "
"bringing the horde! You invaders had better not be here when we get back!"
msgstr ""
"Vale, esquece isto. Vou levar o resto dos nosos escravos, conseguir o xefe e "
"traer a horda! É mellor que vós, invasores, non esteades aquí cando volvamos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:663
msgid ""
"The orcs are escaping, along with many of their slaves! I cannot rescue you "
"all... but please, remember: <i>Hold fast your hope, for one day you shall "
"be free!</i>"
msgstr ""
"Os orcos están a escapar, xunto con moitos dos seus escravos! Non podo "
"rescatarvos a todos... pero, por favor, lembrade: <i>Manténdevos firmes na "
"esperanza, porque algún día seredes libres!</i>"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:692
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Peasants and Woodsmen!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode reclutar Campesiños e Madeireiros!"

#. [message]: role=freed_slave
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:695
msgid ""
"Thank you for helping me escape, Konrad! On our way out, each of those you "
"freed have grabbed as much of the orcs’ gold and supplies as we could."
msgstr ""
"Grazas por axudarme a escapar, Konrad! De camiño á saída, cada un dos que "
"liberaches colleu todo o ouro e as provisións dos orcos que puidemos."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. $freed_slaves.length is more than 0, and probably less than 20. $carryover is more than 4, and probably less than 100
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:703
msgid ""
"You have rescued $freed_slaves.length slaves, and will have $carryover extra "
"gold in the next scenario!"
msgstr ""
"Rescataches $freed_slaves.length escravos e terás $carryover ouro extra no "
"seguinte escenario!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:718
msgid ""
"... not a single slave has escaped along with us. I had hoped that our good "
"deed here would help us gain new allies, but it seems my hopes were in vain. "
"We must press onwards alone."
msgstr ""
"... nin un só escravo escapou connosco. Tiña a esperanza de que a nosa boa "
"acción aquí nos axudase a gañar novos aliados, pero parece que as miñas "
"esperanzas foron en van. Debemos seguir adiante sós."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:732
msgid ""
"Bah, when’s the chief getting back with the horde? These invaders are being "
"a real nuisance."
msgstr ""
"Bah, cando volve o xefe coa horda? Estes invasores están a ser unha "
"auténtica molestia."

#. [message]: role=warlord
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:755
msgid ""
"What’s goin’ on here? Slave revolt, is it? Hah! None o’ you’re getting out "
"o’ this valley alive!"
msgstr ""
"Que está a pasar aquí? ¿Unha revolta de escravos, non si? ¡Xa! Ningún de vós "
"sairá con vida deste val!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/26_The_Dwarven_Doors.cfg:759
msgid ""
"More orcs have arrived, and have positioned themselves to stop us "
"progressing! Even if we manage to win this fight, the cost will surely be "
"too great for our small army to bear..."
msgstr ""
"Chegaron máis orcos e posicionáronse para impedir o noso progreso! Mesmo se "
"conseguimos gañar esta batalla, o custo seguramente será demasiado grande "
"para que o noso pequeno exército o poida soportar..."

#. [side]: type={TYPE}, id={ID}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:74
msgid "Trolls"
msgstr "Troles"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:221
msgid ""
"From what Delfador has taught me, I recognize us to be in the ruins of the "
"great western hall of Knalga."
msgstr ""
"Polo que me ensinou Delfador, recoñezo que estamos nas ruínas do gran salón "
"occidental de Knalga."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:225
msgid ""
"It is a sad sight to see, but we may yet find here something of value that "
"was missed by the conquering orcs. We just have to drive off the local "
"trolls first."
msgstr ""
"É unha visión triste, pero aínda pode que atopemos aquí algo de valor que os "
"orcos conquistadores pasaron por alto. Só temos que espantar primeiro os "
"troles locais."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:229
msgid ""
"Caves and crypts are no place for the fair folk, Konrad, and dwarvish "
"tunnels even less so. I am not eager to proceed, but what must be done must "
"be done."
msgstr ""
"As covas e as criptas non son lugar para a xente xusta, Konrad, e os túneles "
"dos ananos aínda menos. Non estou ansioso por continuar, pero o que hai que "
"facer, hai que facelo."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:230
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Caves and crypts are no place for the fair folk, Konrad, and dwarvish "
#| "tunnels even less so. I am not eager to proceed, but what must be done "
#| "must be done."
msgid ""
"Cave and crypts are no place for cavalry, Konrad, and dwarvish tunnels even "
"less so. I am not eager to proceed, but what must be done must be done."
msgstr ""
"As covas e as criptas non son lugar para a xente xusta, Konrad, e os túneles "
"dos ananos aínda menos. Non estou ansioso por continuar, pero o que hai que "
"facer, hai que facelo."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:231
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:232
msgid ""
"Well, this is a far cry from the sunny shores of Alduin. And it stinks of "
"troll excrement! Let’s do what needs to be done and get it over with."
msgstr ""
"Ben, isto está moi lonxe das soleadas costas de Alduin. E cheira a "
"excremento de troll! Fagamos o que hai que facer e rematemos canto antes."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:233
msgid ""
"Aye, an’ <b><i>I</i></b> may find me father’s defiled bones, or me "
"grandfather’s. Cheery thoughts all around, eh?"
msgstr ""
"Si, e <b><i>podo</i></b> atopar os ósos contaminados do meu pai ou do meu "
"avó. Pensamentos alegres por todas partes, non si?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:234
msgid ""
"Away in the deep darkness, we are cut off from the light. But hark! Not from "
"the Light, nor ever from the Light, for the Light shall always guide the "
"faithful."
msgstr ""
"Lonxe, na profunda escuridade, estamos separados da luz. Pero escoitade! Non "
"da Luz, nin nunca da Luz, porque a Luz sempre guiará os fieis."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:235
msgid ""
"Well, don’ this place be bringin’ back some bad memories. Jus’ hope we don’ "
"find no Midnight Queen down these caves this time."
msgstr ""
"Ben, que este lugar non nos traia malos recordos. Só agardo que desta vez "
"non atopeemos ningunha Raíña da Medianoite nestas covas."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:236
msgid ""
"You know, I’ve always wanted to meet a wild troll! Well, at least I think "
"I’ve always wanted to. Do you think they know how their regeneration works, "
"or does it just happen by instinct?"
msgstr ""
"Sabes, sempre quixen coñecer un trol salvaxe! Pois, polo menos creo que "
"sempre quixen. Pensas que saben como funciona a súa rexeneración, ou "
"simplemente sucede por instinto?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:237
msgid ""
"Don’t be lookin’ at me, Konrad. Jus’ cuz Dosh is a troll don’t mean Dosh "
"knows all the trolls on da continent. An’ don’t get Dosh mixed up with one "
"o’ dem other trolls while we’re fighting, okay?"
msgstr ""
"Non me esteas mirando, Konrad. Que Dosh sexa un trol non significa que Dosh "
"coñeza todos os trols do continente. E non mestures a Dosh con ningún deses "
"outros trols mentres loitamos, vale?"

#. [message]: race=dwarf,gryphon {NOT id=Ulfdain}
#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:302
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:307
msgid ""
"I remember that passageway. Me uncle’s whole family drowned here after th’ "
"orcs flooded th’ halls. I were young, very young..."
msgstr ""
"Lembro aquela pasaxe. Toda a familia do meu tío afogouse aquí despois de que "
"os orcos inundasen os corredores. Eu era novo, moi novo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:344
msgid "Listen! Do you hear that?"
msgstr "Escoita! Escoitas iso?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:350
msgid ""
"Kill the trolls... kill them all... scour the caverns... search the halls..."
msgstr ""
"Mata os trolls... mátaos a todos... rastrexa as cavernas... rexistra os "
"corredores..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:393
msgid ""
"More orcs at the gates... Send Eller... for reinforcements. The west hall. "
"Where... are my dragoons?"
msgstr ""
"Máis orcos ás portas... Manda a Eller... por reforzos. O salón oeste. "
"Onde... están os meus dragóns?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:400
msgid "No more recruits. I will lead the sortie... personally."
msgstr "Non máis recrutas. Liderarei a saída... persoalmente."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:412
msgid ""
"Look at the strange axe that death knight is holding! What an unusual weapon."
msgstr ""
"Mira a estraña machada que sostén o cabaleiro da morte! Que arma tan pouco "
"común."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:417
msgid "I... that..."
msgstr "Eu... iso..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:421
msgid "<i>THAT’S MY FATHER’S AXE!</i>"
msgstr "<i>ESA É A MACHADA DO MEU PAI!</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:425
msgid ""
"Give it back, ye beastly bag o’ bones! I’ll rip out yer ribs and stuff ’em "
"down yer eye sockets!"
msgstr ""
"Devólveo, maldito saco de ósos! Arrancareiche as costelas e meteréichelas "
"nas cuencas dos ollos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:429
msgid ""
"I’ll boil yer teeth. I’ll invert your kneecaps. Death is too good for ye. UN-"
"death is too good fer ye!"
msgstr ""
"Vouche ferver os dentes. Vouche inverter as rótulas. A morte é demasiado boa "
"para ti. A ONU-morte é demasiado boa para ti!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:433
msgid "Ulfdain, calm down! What are you talking about?"
msgstr "Ulfdain, tranquilízate! De que estás a falar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:437
msgid ""
"That coward, that yaldson, that spawn of utter darkness is holdin’ my "
"father’s axe! His bloodaxe, one o’ the last few in the world!"
msgstr ""
"Ese covarde, ese cabaleiro, esa progenie da escuridade absoluta, está a "
"suxeitar o machado do meu pai! O seu machado sangrante, un dos últimos que "
"hai no mundo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:441
msgid ""
"By Thursagan’s beard, we’re goin’ to get it back or we’re goin’ to die "
"tryin’! Charge!"
msgstr ""
"Pola barba de Thursagan, imos recuperala ou imos morrer intentándoo! ¡Carga!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:456
msgid ""
"Lost? No... do not speak that word. We will... prevail. We will find... the "
"sceptre..."
msgstr ""
"Perdido? Non... non digas esa palabra. Prevaleceremos... Atoparemos... o "
"cetro..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:460
msgid ""
"The Sceptre? Of Fire?! Who are you, foul creature that we fight? Speak your "
"name, that I may know the foe I slay!"
msgstr ""
"O Cetro? De Fogo?! Quen es ti, abominable criatura contra a que loitamos? Di "
"o teu nome, para que coñeza o inimigo que mato!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#. Lionel repeats a line from TDG's S06
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:465
msgid "We swore our oaths... now we do our duty..."
msgstr "Xuramos os nosos xuramentos... agora cumprimos co noso deber..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:480
msgid ""
"I am Konrad, nephew of Garard, son of Arand and rightful heir to the throne "
"of Wesnoth! And in their names, I end your undead suffering."
msgstr ""
"Son Konrad, sobriño de Garard, fillo de Arand e lexítimo herdeiro ao trono "
"de Wesnoth! E nos seus nomes, poño fin ao voso sufrimento de mortos viventes."

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#. Lionel foreshadows the reveal that Konrad is not in fact the heir
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:485
msgid "Arand? You look... nothing like Arand..."
msgstr "Arand? Non te pareces... en nada a Arand..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:496
msgid ""
"So this vile creature was once a man, searching for the Sceptre of Fire. "
"Neither in life nor un-life could he find the object of his quest — but it "
"seems he still gathered many other riches and things of value."
msgstr ""
"Así que esta vil criatura foi unha vez un home, buscando o Cetro de Lume. "
"Nin en vida nin na morte puido atopar o obxecto da súa misión, pero parece "
"que aínda así reuniu moitas outras riquezas e cousas de valor."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:518
msgid ""
"His gold will be useful to us, but his axe may be even more so. The runes "
"carved into it look dwarvish, and ancient..."
msgstr ""
"O seu ouro serános útil, pero o seu machado pode selo aínda máis. As runas "
"gravadas nel parecen ananas e antigas..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:533
msgid ""
"Aye... like I said ’twere my father’s, but ’tweren’t he who forged it. Been "
"with us dwarves since times o’ legend, have th’ bloodaxes. I never thought "
"I’d again see such a sight! Not since th’ dark days began..."
msgstr ""
"Si... como dixen, eran do meu pai, pero non era el quen as forxou. Levan con "
"nós, os ananos, dende os tempos das lendas, as machadas de sangue. Nunca "
"pensei que volvería ver tal cousa! Non dende que comezaron os días escuros..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:541
msgid ""
"Perhaps th’ spirit o’ Knalga ain’t so dead an’ buried after all. Ah’m a "
"Bloodaxe now, like my father an’ his father an’ his father afore him! Ah’m "
"in yer debt once again, Konrad. Ye given me hope."
msgstr ""
"Quizais o espírito de Knalga non estea tan morto e enterrado despois de "
"todo. Agora son un Machado Sanguinario, coma o meu pai, o seu pai e o seu "
"pai antes del! Estou en débeda contigo unha vez máis, Konrad. Déchesme "
"esperanza."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:556
msgid ""
"A weapon worthy of a king — or a prince. I shall personally wield this axe "
"against the dark queen."
msgstr ""
"Unha arma digna dun rei... ou dun príncipe. Eu mesmo empuñarei esta machada "
"contra a raíña escura."

#. [event]
#. [unit_type]: id=Dwarvish Bloodaxe, race=dwarf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:561
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Dwarvish_Bloodaxe.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Bloodaxe"
msgstr "Axeda de sangue anana"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:562
msgid ""
"This runic axe increases Konrad’s melee damage by 3, and grants him the "
"<i>drains</i> special on his melee attacks."
msgstr ""
"Este machado rúnico aumenta o dano en corpo a corpo de Konrad en 3 e "
"concédelle a habilidade especial <i>Drains</i> nos seus ataques corpo a "
"corpo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:594
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am glad; the halls of your ancesters are at peace once more, Ulfdain. "
#| "Now it is time for us to move on."
msgid ""
"I am glad; the halls of your ancestors are at peace once more, Ulfdain. Now "
"it is time for us to move on."
msgstr ""
"Alégrome; os salóns dos teus antepasados están en paz unha vez máis, "
"Ulfdain. Agora é hora de seguir adiante."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:599
msgid ""
"More trolls will move in soon, but for now, the caverns are empty. Time for "
"us to move on."
msgstr ""
"Máis troles chegarán pronto, pero por agora, as cavernas están baleiras. É "
"hora de seguir adiante."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:626
msgid ""
"These halls are old, and our fighting is damaging the walls and pillars. If "
"we cannot finish soon, the whole cavern might collapse on us!"
msgstr ""
"Estas salas son vellas, e a nosa loita está a danar as paredes e os pilares. "
"Se non podemos rematar pronto, toda a cova podería colapsar sobre nós!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/28_The_Lost_General.cfg:640
msgid ""
"Our fighting has caused too much damage to these old ruins! The whole "
"mountain is falling down on us!"
msgstr ""
"A nosa loita causou demasiados danos nestas vellas ruínas! Toda a montaña "
"está a caer sobre nós!"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:51
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:71
msgid "Knalgans"
msgstr "Knalgans"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:170
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:179
msgid ""
"The Knalgans led Konrad and his men, blindfolded, through a maze of twisting "
"tunnels and passageways."
msgstr ""
"Os knalganos guiaron a Konrad e aos seus homes, cos ollos vendados, a través "
"dun labirinto de túneles retortos e pasaxes."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:172
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>The Knalgans led Konrad and his men, blindfolded, through a maze of "
#| "twisting tunnels and passageways.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sound of hammers echoed through the stale cave air, then pickaxes, "
#| "then the quiet murmur of low dwarvish voices, interspersed with louder "
#| "remarks from the still-seeing dwarves of Konrad’s own party. And at long "
#| "last, silence.</i>"
msgid ""
"The sound of hammers echoed through the stale cave air, then pickaxes, then "
"the quiet murmur of low dwarvish voices, interspersed with louder remarks "
"from the still-seeing dwarves of Konrad’s own party. And at long last, "
"silence."
msgstr ""
"<i>Os knalganos levaron a Konrad e os seus homes, con ollos vendados, a "
"través dun labirinto de túneles e pasadizos sinuosos. O son dos martelos "
"resoaba no aire viciado da cova, despois dos picos e, finalmente, o murmurio "
"silencioso das voces baixas dos ananos, intercalado con comentarios máis "
"altos dos ananos do propio grupo de Konrad, que aínda vían. E, por fin, o "
"silencio.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:181
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>The Knalgans led Konrad and his men, blindfolded, through a maze of "
#| "twisting tunnels and passageways.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sound of hammers echoed through the stale cave air, then pickaxes, "
#| "then the quiet murmur of low dwarvish voices. And at long last, silence.</"
#| "i>"
msgid ""
"The sound of hammers echoed through the stale cave air, then pickaxes, then "
"the quiet murmur of low dwarvish voices. And at long last, silence."
msgstr ""
"<i>Os knalganos levaron a Konrad e os seus homes, con ollos vendados, a "
"través dun labirinto de túneles e pasadizos sinuosos. O son dos martelos "
"resoaba no aire viciado da cova, despois dos picos, e despois o murmurio "
"silencioso das voces baixas dos ananos. E por fin, o silencio.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Geldar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:195
msgid ""
"Here we are. The start o’ the cave-in. Somewhere beyond here, past all "
"manner of beasts and vermin, lie our trapped miners. Rescue them, and you’ll "
"be rewarded."
msgstr ""
"Aquí estamos. O comezo do derrubamento. Algún lugar máis alá, máis alá de "
"todo tipo de bestas e bichos, atópanse os nosos mineiros atrapados. "
"Rescátaos e serás recompensado."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:199
msgid ""
"It’s just a solid wall of rock. How am I supposed to get through and find "
"your comrades?"
msgstr ""
"É só un sólido muro de rocha. Como vou atravesalo e atopar os teus camaradas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Geldar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:203
msgid "Dig, human. I must return to my guard duties."
msgstr "Escava, humano. Debo volver ás miñas tarefas de garda."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:214
msgid "Find the missing dwarves"
msgstr "Atopa os ananos que faltan"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:234
msgid ""
"Ulfdain, the Knalgans here have been very evasive about what’s going on. Do "
"you have any insights?"
msgstr ""
"Ulfdain, os Knalgans aquí foron moi evasivos sobre o que está a suceder. Tes "
"algunha idea?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. [message]: race=dwarf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:238
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:249
msgid ""
"Aye, I think I can guess. But I cannae tell an outsider, Konrad, not even "
"you."
msgstr ""
"Si, creo que podo adiviñar. Pero non llo podo dicir a un alleo, Konrad, nin "
"sequera a ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:244
msgid ""
"Friend dwarf, the Knalgans here have been very evasive about what’s going "
"on. Do you have any insights?"
msgstr ""
"Amigo anano, os knalganos de aquí foron moi evasivos sobre o que está a "
"suceder. Tes algunha información?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:324
msgid ""
"The walls here are weak enough for swords and spears to break down. It’ll be "
"slow going, but we’ll be able to dig our way through the cave-in. That must "
"be what Geldar meant."
msgstr ""
"As paredes aquí son tan débiles que espadas e lanzas poden derrubalas. Será "
"un avance lento, pero poderemos cavar o noso camiño a través do "
"desprendemento. Iso debe ser o que Geldar quería dicir."

#. [message]: type=Dwarvish Miner
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:343
msgid "Mining’s a lot easier when you’ve got the proper equipment, aye?"
msgstr "A minería é moito máis doada cando tes o equipo axeitado, non si?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:393
msgid ""
"Look out! The cavern beyond this wall is filled with water, and it’s "
"flooding into our caves!"
msgstr ""
"Coidado! A caverna que hai máis alá deste muro está chea de auga e está a "
"inundar as nosas covas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:448
msgid "<i>(cough)</i> Who’s there?"
msgstr "<i>(tose)</i> Quen está aí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:452
msgid ""
"I am Prince Konrad of Wesnoth, and a friend of Knalga. I’ve come to rescue "
"you!"
msgstr "Son o príncipe Konrad de Wesnoth e amigo de Knalga. Vin rescatarvos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Angarthing
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:456
msgid ""
"Aye, that so? ...ye weren’t who I was expectin’. <i>(cough)</i> But I’m not "
"about to turn down help."
msgstr ""
"Si, iso si? ...non eras quen eu esperaba. <i>(tose)</i> Pero non vou "
"rexeitar axuda."

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:464
msgid "Yer alive! Quick, git ’im to th’ great hall."
msgstr "Estás vivo! Rápido, lévao ao gran salón."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:471
msgid ""
"All this, Relgorn, for just a single dwarf? I understand the value of life, "
"but I was led to believe there was a whole posse trapped down here. What’s "
"the meaning of this?"
msgstr ""
"Todo isto, Relgorn, por un só anano? Entendo o valor da vida, pero fixéronme "
"crer que había toda unha cuadrilla atrapada aquí abaixo. Cal é o significado "
"disto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:475
msgid ""
"Never ye mind, human. But you did right by us, so we’ll do right by you."
msgstr ""
"Non te importa, humano. Pero fixeches o ben con nós, así que nós faremos o "
"ben contigo."

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:479
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I know ye’ll be wantin’ all of our warrior types, but we dinnae have "
#| "enough o’ everyone to spare. But those we do have are tough, and well-"
#| "practiced in the art of battle.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Choose two — Fighters, Guardsmen, Thunderers, or Ulfserkers — an’ we’ll "
#| "send ye’ enough Knalgans to make a difference in yer quest."
msgid ""
"I know ye’ll be wantin’ all of our warrior types, but we dinnae have enough "
"o’ everyone to spare. But those we do have are tough, and well-practiced in "
"the art of battle."
msgstr ""
"Sei que quereredes todos os nosos tipos de guerreiros, pero non temos "
"dabondo de todos de sobra. Pero os que temos son fortes e ben adestrados na "
"arte da batalla.\n"
"\n"
"Escollede dous (guerreiros, gardas, tronos ou ulfserkers) e enviarémosvos "
"suficientes knalganos para marcar a diferenza na vosa misión."

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:481
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I know ye’ll be wantin’ all of our warrior types, but we dinnae have "
#| "enough o’ everyone to spare. But those we do have are tough, and well-"
#| "practiced in the art of battle.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Choose two — Fighters, Guardsmen, Thunderers, or Ulfserkers — an’ we’ll "
#| "send ye’ enough Knalgans to make a difference in yer quest."
msgid ""
"Choose two — Fighters, Guardsmen, Thunderers, or Ulfserkers — an’ we’ll send "
"ye’ enough Knalgans to make a difference in yer quest."
msgstr ""
"Sei que quereredes todos os nosos tipos de guerreiros, pero non temos "
"dabondo de todos de sobra. Pero os que temos son fortes e ben adestrados na "
"arte da batalla.\n"
"\n"
"Escollede dous (guerreiros, gardas, tronos ou ulfserkers) e enviarémosvos "
"suficientes knalganos para marcar a diferenza na vosa misión."

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:494
msgid ""
"It shall be done, Konrad. May you someday reclaim your birthright — and us "
"ours."
msgstr ""
"Farase, Konrad. Oxalá algún día poidas reclamar o teu dereito de nacemento, "
"e nós o noso."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:509
msgid "Choose Dwarvish Fighters and Guardsmen"
msgstr "Escolle guerreiros e gardas ananos"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:510
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Fighters and Guardsmen!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar guerreiros e gardas ananos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:515
msgid "Choose Dwarvish Fighters and Thunderers"
msgstr "Elixe loitadores e troadores ananos"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:516
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Fighters and Thunderers!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar Guerreiros Ananos e Tronadores!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:521
msgid "Choose Dwarvish Fighters and Ulfserkers"
msgstr "Elixe loitadores ananos e ulfserkers"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:522
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Fighters and Ulfserkers!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar Guerreiros Ananos e Ulfserkers!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:527
msgid "Choose Dwarvish Guardsmen and Thunderers"
msgstr "Escolle gardas ananos e truenadores"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:528
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Guardsmen and Thunderers!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar Gardas Ananos e Tronadores!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:533
msgid "Choose Dwarvish Guardsmen and Ulfserkers"
msgstr "Escolle gardas ananos e ulfserkers"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:534
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Guardsmen and Ulfserkers!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar gardas ananos e ulfserkers!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:539
msgid "Choose Dwarvish Thunderers and Ulfserkers"
msgstr "Escolle os Tronadores Ananos e os Ulfserkers"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:540
msgid "Konrad can now recruit Dwarvish Thunderers and Ulfserkers!"
msgstr "Konrad agora pode recrutar Ananos Tronadores e Ulfserkers!"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:545
msgid "Ask for more"
msgstr "Pide máis"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:552
msgid ""
"Once I defeat Asheviere and reclaim my throne, I would be more than happy to "
"send aid to Knalga. I understand you have little to give, but right now it "
"is in both of our best interests to work together!"
msgstr ""
"Unha vez que derrote a Asheviere e recupere o meu trono, estarei encantado "
"de enviar axuda a Knalga. Entendo que tedes pouco que dar, pero agora mesmo "
"o mellor para nós dous é traballar xuntos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:556
msgid ""
"Aye, an’ I thought I’d live out a peaceful life in th’ west halls, but here "
"we both are. We can’t spare any more, Konrad, not even for a prince."
msgstr ""
"Si, e eu pensaba que viviría unha vida tranquila nos pazos occidentais, pero "
"aquí estamos os dous. Non podemos aforrar máis, Konrad, nin sequera por un "
"príncipe."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:562
msgid "Refuse payment"
msgstr "Rexeitar o pago"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:566
msgid ""
"Friend dwarf, you need all the fighters you can get. What right do I have to "
"demand bread from a starving man? Keep your warriors for Knalga, and may "
"Knalga one day prosper again."
msgstr ""
"Amigo anano, necesitas todos os loitadores que poidas conseguir. Que dereito "
"teño para esixirlle pan a un home famento? Garda os teus guerreiros para "
"Knalga, e que Knalga algún día volva prosperar."

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:570
msgid ""
"You’re a good lad, Konrad. Thank ye, an’ I’m sorry we were so suspicious "
"when ye first showed up."
msgstr ""
"Es un bo rapaz, Konrad. Grazas, e sinto que fuésemos tan desconfiados cando "
"chegaches por primeira vez."

#. [message]: speaker=Relgorn
#. this is a hint to the player that there's a special event if they also complete "Lost General" and entirely wipe out the orcs in "Dwarven Doors"
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:575
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Whether you get yer throne back or not, you’ll always be welcome in "
#| "Knalga — what remains o’ it, at least."
msgid ""
"Whether you get yer throne back or not, you’ll always be welcome in Knalga — "
"what remains o’ it, at least. Between the trolls in the west an’ the orcs in "
"the Doors we’re just spread too thin. Mebbe if those were gone..."
msgstr ""
"Teñas ou non o teu trono de volta, sempre serás benvido en Knalga — polo "
"menos do que dela queda."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:603
msgid ""
"We must hurry. We promised Relgorn we would rescue his lost kin, but every "
"hour we wait is an hour in which some misfortune may befall them."
msgstr ""
"Temos que apurarnos. Prometerámoslle a Relgorn que rescataríamos aos seus "
"parentes perdidos, pero cada hora que agardamos é unha hora na que lles pode "
"suceder algunha desgraza."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/29_Digging_for_Dwarves.cfg:610
msgid ""
"We have taken so long to search for the missing dwarves! Even should we "
"eventually find them, we will surely find only their corpses..."
msgstr ""
"Levamos tanto tempo buscando aos ananos desaparecidos! Mesmo que finalmente "
"os encontremos, seguramente só atoparemos os seus cadáveres..."

#. [side]: type=Fire Ant Queen, id=ant_leader
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:62
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:92
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:77
msgid "Monsters"
msgstr "Monstros"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:259
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>The last dwarvish ruin far behind them, the party descended into the "
#| "deepest parts of the hewn caverns. Except for disturbances caused by the "
#| "occasional rodent, the air in the lower passages was still and tomblike.</"
#| "i>"
msgid ""
"The last dwarvish ruin far behind them, the party descended into the deepest "
"parts of the hewn caverns. Except for disturbances caused by the occasional "
"rodent, the air in the lower passages was still and tomblike."
msgstr ""
"<i>Coa última ruína anana moi atrás, o grupo descendeu ás partes máis "
"profundas das cavernas escavadas. Agás as molestias causadas por algún "
"roedor ocasional, o aire nas pasaxes inferiores era quieto e semellante a "
"unha tumba.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:265
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Stepping through a low corridor, Konrad and Delfador emerged from the "
#| "maze-like catacombs into icy blackness. Darkness seemed to crush them. "
#| "Lights flickered and went out. Even the staff of the elder mage struggled "
#| "to produce enough light to see by.</i>"
msgid ""
"Stepping through a low corridor, Konrad and Delfador emerged from the maze-"
"like catacombs into icy blackness. Darkness seemed to crush them. Lights "
"flickered and went out. Even the staff of the elder mage struggled to "
"produce enough light to see by."
msgstr ""
"<i>Atravesando un corredor baixo, Konrad e Delfador emerxeron das catacumbas "
"labirínticas cara a unha escuridade xeada. A escuridade parecía esmagalos. "
"As luces parpadeaban e apagabanse. Mesmo o bastón do mago ancián loitaba por "
"producir luz dabondo para ver.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:271
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>A cavernous void stretched out ahead, across which no ceiling or walls "
#| "were visible. Wind howled and whipped over narrow ledges bridging the "
#| "depths, almost as if animated by powerful nearby magic... and approaching "
#| "evil.</i>"
msgid ""
"A cavernous void stretched out ahead, across which no ceiling or walls were "
"visible. Wind howled and whipped over narrow ledges bridging the depths, "
"almost as if animated by powerful nearby magic... and approaching evil."
msgstr ""
"<i>Un baleiro cavernoso estendíase diante, a través do cal non se vían "
"teitos nin paredes. O vento uivaba e azoutaba as estreitas cornixas que "
"enlazaban as profundidades, case coma se estivese animado por unha poderosa "
"maxia próxima... e un mal que se achegaba.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:295
msgid ""
"We’ve been traveling for days upon days. Surely the Sceptre is getting close!"
msgstr ""
"Levamos viaxando días e días. Seguro que o Sceptre está a piques de chegar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:299
msgid ""
"Yes, I feel it is near here. It calls out to be freed... it is near; very "
"near! The Sceptre was forged here, not far where we now stand. The sheer "
"power of it!"
msgstr ""
"Si, sinto que está preto de aquí. Clama por ser liberado... está preto; moi "
"preto! O Cetro forxouse aquí, non moi lonxe de onde agora estamos. ¡A súa "
"pura potencia!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:302
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:303
msgid ""
"It is the fault of my people — Landar’s rebels — that the Sceptre was lost. "
"It is only fair that I help get it back. Which way should we go, Delfador?"
msgstr ""
"É culpa do meu pobo —os rebeldes de Landar— que o Cetro se perdese. É xusto "
"que eu axude a recuperalo. Que camiño debemos tomar, Delfador?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:304
msgid ""
"Growin’ up they used to tell me fairytales about the Sceptre... Never "
"thought I might actually be seein’ it in person. Which way do we go, "
"Delfador?"
msgstr ""
"De pequeno, adoitaban contarme contos de fadas sobre o Cetro... Nunca pensei "
"que o podería estar a ver en persoa. Que camiño imos, Delfador?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:305
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Yea, the hallowed fire shall bring Light to the places of darkness! So "
#| "proclaim the texts, and so shall it be. Where can the Sceptre be found, "
#| "scholar?"
msgid ""
"Yea, the hallowed fire shall bring Light to the places of darkness! So "
"proclaim the texts, and so shall it be. Whither shall we go to find the "
"Sceptre, scholar?"
msgstr ""
"Si, o lume sagrado traerá Luz aos lugares da escuridade! Así proclaman os "
"textos, e así será. Onde se pode atopar o Cetro, erudito?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:306
msgid ""
"’twere my people who made it fer ye humans, and ’twere my people who lost "
"it, long ago. Now ’tis only right that I help ye get it back. Where be the "
"Sceptre, scholar?"
msgstr ""
"Foi o meu pobo quen o fixo para vós, os humanos, e foi o meu pobo quen o "
"perdeu, hai moito tempo. Agora é xusto que eu vos axude a recuperalo. Onde "
"está o cetro, erudito?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:307
msgid ""
"I’ve read so much about the lost Sceptre of Fire! I never though I would, "
"well, actually help <i>find</i> it. Where do we go, Delfador?"
msgstr ""
"Lin tanto sobre o Cetro de Lume perdido! Nunca pensei que axudaría <i>a "
"atopalo</i> . Onde imos, Delfador?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:308
msgid ""
"At long last, Garard’s edict will be fulfilled. You shall seize the Sceptre, "
"Konrad, and right the many wrongs of Asheviere. Whither shall we go, "
"Delfador?"
msgstr ""
"Por fin, o edicto de Garard cumprirase. Debes apoderarte do Cetro, Konrad, e "
"reparar as moitas inxustizas de Asheviere. A onde iremos, Delfador?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:309
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:310
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "It’s overwhelming! I never— well, Delfador, thank you for trusting me to "
#| "be here with you. Where shall we start the search?"
msgid ""
"I feel the power! It’s overwhelming! I never— well, Delfador, thank you for "
"trusting me to be here with you. Where shall we start the search?"
msgstr ""
"É abrumador! Eu nunca... ben, Delfador, grazas por confiar en min para estar "
"aquí contigo. Por onde imos comezar a busca?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:311
msgid ""
"Dis cave good place for troll, but no good place for softskins. Better find "
"your scep-tar an’ get back to sun-lit places. Which way should we start?"
msgstr ""
"Esta cova é un bo lugar para os trols, pero non para os de pel branda. "
"Mellor que busques o teu cetro e volvas a lugares soleados. Por onde "
"deberiamos comezar?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:312
msgid "Very well — then where? How do we find it?"
msgstr "Moi ben — entón onde? Como o atopamos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:316
msgid ""
"North and east. More than that, I cannot tell. Whatever beasts, monsters, "
"and other denizens of the dark lurk ahead, I know that we shall prevail."
msgstr ""
"Norte e leste. Máis ca iso, non podo dicilo. Sexan cales sexan as bestas, os "
"monstros e outros habitantes da escuridade que acechan diante, sei que "
"prevaleceremos."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:324
msgid "Defeat the enemy leader"
msgstr "Derrota o líder inimigo"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. this is deliberately vague, and foreshadows Li'sar's appearance in part two of this scenario
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:329
msgid "Then, fight to claim the Sceptre"
msgstr "Entón, loita para reclamar o cetro"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:339
msgid ""
"The longer you take to defeat the enemy leader, the more time your other "
"enemies will have to accrue gold."
msgstr ""
"Canto máis tardes en derrotar o líder inimigo, máis tempo terán os teus "
"outros inimigos para acumular ouro."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:351
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Delfador, you’ve told me the importance of the Sceptre of Fire. And I "
#| "believe you! A powerful magical artifact, and the fabled symbol of the "
#| "kings of Wesnoth. With the Sceptre in my hand even Asheviere would "
#| "struggle to deny my claim of heirship."
msgid ""
"Delfador, you’ve told me the importance of the Sceptre of Fire. And I "
"believe you! A powerful magical artifact, and the fabled symbol of the kings "
"of Wesnoth. With the Sceptre in my hand even Asheviere would struggle to "
"deny my claim to the throne."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, dixéchesme a importancia do Cetro de Lume. E eu créoche! Un "
"poderoso artefacto máxico e o lendario símbolo dos reis de Wesnoth. Co Cetro "
"na miña man, mesmo Asheviere tería dificultades para negar a miña "
"reclamación de herdeiro."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:355
msgid ""
"Yet it pains me to know that while we delve deep under these mountains, "
"countless people back home are suffering. Elves, men, dwarves; people we’ve "
"missed out helping because we had to come here instead. I hope it’ll be "
"worth it in the end."
msgstr ""
"Con todo, dóeme saber que, mentres nos afundimos nas profundidades destas "
"montañas, incontables persoas na nosa terra están a padecer. Elfos, homes, "
"ananos; xente á que non puidemos axudar porque tivemos que vir aquí. Agardo "
"que ao final valga a pena."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:366
msgid ""
"Delfador... other than the prophecy about the Sceptre, you haven’t been "
"keeping any other secrets from me “for my own good”, have you?"
msgstr ""
"Delfador... ademais da profecía sobre o Cetro, non me ocultaches ningún "
"outro segredo \"polo meu propio ben\", non si?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:370
msgid ""
"One. But I ask you to restrain your curiosity, for I hope it will never have "
"to come to light. Here and now, we must focus on finding the Sceptre if you "
"are ever to become king."
msgstr ""
"Un. Pero pídoche que conteñas a túa curiosidade, porque espero que nunca "
"teña que saír á luz. Aquí e agora, debemos centrarnos en atopar o Cetro se "
"algunha vez queres converterte en rei."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:407
msgid ""
"What a strange rock formation. Could this be the resting place of the "
"Sceptre?"
msgstr ""
"Que estraña formación rochosa. Podería esta ser o lugar de descanso do Cetro?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:411
msgid ""
"There is some power about it, to be sure. But we must clear out the leader "
"of the local fauna before we can investigate further."
msgstr ""
"Hai algo de poder nisto, sen dúbida. Pero temos que eliminar o líder da "
"fauna local antes de poder investigar máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:426
msgid ""
"We’ve been wandering for so long, and we still haven’t cleared our way to "
"the Sceptre."
msgstr "Levamos tanto tempo vagando e aínda non abrimos camiño ata o Cetro."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:430
msgid ""
"Even if it really is somewhere here, I fear it is beyond our power to "
"obtain..."
msgstr ""
"Mesmo se realmente está nalgún lugar aquí, temo que está máis alá do noso "
"poder obtelo..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:454
msgid ""
"That wasn’t so bad! The vermin are defeated, and the way is clear to explore "
"further."
msgstr ""
"Iso non foi tan malo! As alimañas están derrotadas e o camiño está despexado "
"para seguir explorando."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:458
msgid ""
"I sense great power emanating from the chasm nearby. Everyone, gather round."
msgstr "Sinto unha gran forza que emana do abismo próximo. Todos, reunídevos."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:560
msgid "55 gold"
msgstr "55 de ouro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:560
msgid ""
"Li’sar’s soldiers have stockpiled some gold here! We’ll put it to better use."
msgstr ""
"Os soldados de Li'sar acumularon algo de ouro aquí! Darémoslle un mellor uso."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:599
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Near the chasm, the air almost crackled with magical energy. It also "
#| "became steadily warmer. The floor was smooth and glassy in places, and a "
#| "faint glow provided a small reprieve from the thick blackness. Volcanic "
#| "fumes drifted up from cracks in the floor.</i>"
msgid ""
"Near the chasm, the air almost crackled with magical energy. It also became "
"steadily warmer. The floor was smooth and glassy in places, and a faint glow "
"provided a small reprieve from the thick blackness. Volcanic fumes drifted "
"up from cracks in the floor."
msgstr ""
"<i>Preto do abismo, o aire case crepitaba con enerxía máxica. Tamén se "
"volvía cada vez máis cálido. O chan era liso e cristalino nalgúns lugares, e "
"un brillo tenue proporcionaba un pequeno alivio da espesa escuridade. Os "
"fumes volcánicos ascendían polas gretas do chan.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:603
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Distant rumbles and earthquakes made it difficult to keep steady "
#| "footing. The very earth had come alive, heaving, struggling to be "
#| "relieved of its centuries-old burden...</i>"
msgid ""
"Distant rumbles and earthquakes made it difficult to keep steady footing. "
"The very earth had come alive, heaving, struggling to be relieved of its "
"centuries-old burden..."
msgstr ""
"<i>Ruxidos e terremotos distantes dificultaban manter o equilibrio. A propia "
"terra cobrara vida, axitándose, loitando por liberarse do seu fardo "
"secular...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:616
msgid ""
"We are here. The Sceptre... the earth... the fire... the air around us... "
"everything! It calls out to be freed — I can barely hold it back in my mind."
msgstr ""
"Estamos aquí. O cetro... a terra... o lume... o aire que nos rodea... todo! "
"Clama por ser liberado — apenas podo contelo na miña mente."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:619
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:620
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:621
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:622
msgid ""
"I sense it too... there is a strangeness in the air. A fire in the soul of "
"this place. But where? The cave is empty!"
msgstr ""
"Eu tamén o sinto... hai unha estrañeza no aire. Un lume na alma deste lugar. "
"Pero onde? A cova está baleira!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:623
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aye, tha’s nice... except there’s nothin’ here, ye cloud-headed "
#| "flapdragon! It’s empty cave!"
msgid ""
"Aye, tha’s nice... except there’s nothin’ here, ye cloud-headed flapdragon! "
"It’s an empty cave!"
msgstr ""
"Si, iso está ben... agás que aquí non hai nada, dragón de cabeza de nube! É "
"unha cova baleira!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:624
msgid ""
"But where is it, o’ great Delfador? The cave here is empty. Do we stand in "
"the wrong place?"
msgstr ""
"Pero onde está, oh gran Delfador? A cova está baleira. Estamos no lugar "
"equivocado?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:625
msgid ""
"Err... is this one o’ those confusing wizard things? Where’s the Sceptre? "
"Th’ cave looks pretty empty to me."
msgstr ""
"Eh... é esta unha desas cousas de magos confusas? Onde está o Cetro? A cova "
"paréceme bastante baleira."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:626
msgid ""
"Yea, truly there is a strangeness in the air here... not of the Light, but "
"of something else entirely. But where is the source? The cave stands empty."
msgstr ""
"Si, de verdade hai unha estrañeza no aire aquí... non da Luz, senón de algo "
"completamente distinto. Pero onde está a fonte? A cova permanece baleira."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:627
msgid ""
"Err... it— it does? I don’t see anything... Oh! Is this a metaphor? The real "
"treasure is the friends we made along the way?"
msgstr ""
"Eh... si... si que o fai? Non vexo nada... Oh! É unha metáfora? O verdadeiro "
"tesouro son os amigos que fixemos polo camiño?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:628
msgid ""
"Dey say trolls are slow, but even Dosh can see dere’s nothing here. Flat and "
"empty. Nothing for us to take, is dere?"
msgstr ""
"Din que os troles son lentos, pero mesmo Dosh pode ver que non hai nada "
"aquí. Plano e baleiro. Nada que poidamos levar, non si?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:629
msgid "But where is it? I don’t see a thing!"
msgstr "Esta néboa destruída é tan espesa! Non podo ver nada!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:633
msgid ""
"On the contrary! My research leads me to believe that we stand in the center "
"of a dormant volcano, which erupted centuries ago and buried the Sceptre in "
"rock. It is indeed here, under the cave floor."
msgstr ""
"Ao contrario! A miña investigación lévame a crer que estamos no centro dun "
"volcán inactivo, que entrou en erupción hai séculos e sepultou o Cetro na "
"rocha. De feito, está aquí, baixo o chan da cova."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:659
msgid "It shall take time, but my magic can dig the Sceptre out."
msgstr "Levará tempo, pero a miña maxia pode desenterrar o Cetro."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:695
msgid ""
"A sound like that can mean only one thing: Konrad and his handler have "
"reached the Sceptre of Fire."
msgstr ""
"Un son coma ese só pode significar unha cousa: Konrad e o seu adestrador "
"chegaron ao Cetro de Lume."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:699
msgid ""
"Princess Li’sar! Villain! Asheviere’s greed must extend far if she would "
"risk her last child this far from Wesnoth, deep under the northern mountains."
msgstr ""
"Princesa Li’sar! Vilán! A cobiza de Asheviere debe estenderse lonxe se "
"arriscaba o seu último fillo tan lonxe de Wesnoth, nas profundidades das "
"montañas do norte."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:721
msgid ""
"Loyalists, this is it. Within these caves lurks my usurping cousin; the "
"false prince; the puppet of Delfador."
msgstr ""
"Lealistas, isto é todo. Dentro destas covas agóchase o meu primo usurpador; "
"o falso príncipe; o monicreque de Delfador."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:741
#, fuzzy
msgid "your comrades dead at Elensefar"
msgstr "O Rei está morto"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:742
msgid "Elensefar ruled by thieves"
msgstr "Elensefar gobernada por ladróns"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:743
msgid "supplies pillaged at Fort Tahn"
msgstr "Subministracións saqueadas no Forte Tahn"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:744
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "convoys burning outside Dan’Tonk"
msgid "convoys aflame outside Dan’Tonk"
msgstr "convois ardendo fóra de Dan'Tonk"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:745
#, fuzzy
msgid "zombified townsfolk at the peninsula"
msgstr "Veciños da vila"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:746
msgid "dead slaves at the Dwarven Doors"
msgstr "escravos mortos nas portas ananas"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:747
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "libraries burning at Alduin"
msgid "libraries aflame at Alduin"
msgstr "bibliotecas queimándose en Alduin"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:748
msgid "rebels at Blackwater Port"
msgstr "rebeldes no Porto de Blackwater"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:749
msgid "riots at the Bay of Pearls"
msgstr "disturbios na Baía das Perlas"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:750
msgid "undead amok in the hills"
msgstr "non mortos fóra de control nos outeiros"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:751
msgid "elvish criminals escaping into the south"
msgstr "delincuentes elficos fuxindo cara ao sur"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:752
msgid "trouble with the orcs at Glamdrol"
msgstr "problemas cos orcos en Glamdrol"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:753
msgid "corpses clogging up the Ford"
msgstr "Choose to keep corpses present."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:754
msgid "blood-stained slopes on Gryphon Mountain"
msgstr "ladeiras manchadas de sangue no Monte Gryphon"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:756
msgid ": $lisar_speech."
msgstr ": $lisar_speech."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:757
msgid ""
". You have heard the lies he tells, misleading those who would otherwise "
"oppose him"
msgstr ""
"Escoitaches as mentiras que di, enganando a aqueles que doutro xeito se "
"oporían a el"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#. several of the strings above are joined to create $lisar_speech.
#. For example, this message might read something like "in his wake: dead slaves at the Dwarven Doors, zombified townsfolk at the peninsula... Today, we put a stop to it."
#. If translating a dynamic string like this is difficult or impossible in your language, you can replace $lisar_speech with ". You have heard the lies he tells, misleading those who would otherwise oppose him."
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:764
msgid ""
"You know the blood and chaos that follow in his wake$lisar_speech|... Today, "
"we put a stop to it. Is everyone in position?"
msgstr ""
"Coñeces a sangue e o caos que o seguen no seu rastro$lisar_speech|... Hoxe "
"poñémoslle fin. ¿Está todo o mundo en posición?"

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:784
msgid "Northern company ready and reporting, ma’am."
msgstr "Empresa do norte preparada e informando, señora."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:788
msgid "Yrridyn"
msgstr "Yrridyn"

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:800
msgid ""
"We’ve burned the trolls out of the eastern tunnels. Our way forward is clear."
msgstr ""
"Queimamos os trols fóra dos túneles orientais. O noso camiño cara adiante "
"está libre."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:804
msgid "Arynnoc"
msgstr "Arynnoc"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:805
msgid "Gwytharyn"
msgstr "Gwytharyn"

#. [message]: speaker=leader7
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:817
msgid ""
"My bowmen and I are ready and waiting at the far passage. They won’t get "
"through us, Your Highness."
msgstr ""
"Os meus arqueiros e eu estamos listos e agardando na pasaxe máis afastada. "
"Non pasarán por diante de nós, Alteza."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:825
msgid ""
"Good. And Mirya — scout around for any other exits we’ve missed. We must not "
"allow Konrad to escape with the Sceptre of Fire."
msgstr ""
"Ben. E Mirya, explora se temos outras saídas que non vimos. Non debemos "
"permitir que Konrad escape co Cetro de Lume."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:861
msgid ""
"Li’sar expects us to try to escape? No, I will not yield so easily. Hold "
"strong, friends. We must guard Delfador while he unearths the Sceptre, or "
"perhaps even attack and defeat Li’sar herself!"
msgstr ""
"Li’sar agarda que intentemos escapar? Non, non me renderei tan facilmente. "
"Manteñádevos fortes, amigos. Debemos protexer a Delfador mentres desenterra "
"o Cetro, ou quizais mesmo atacar e derrotar á propia Li’sar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:865
msgid ""
"The Sceptre is valuable, but your life is even more so, Konrad. If our "
"forces are not yet strong enough to confront the army of Wesnoth, do not be "
"afraid to swallow your pride and flee. I feel fresh air coming from the "
"north."
msgstr ""
"O Cetro é valioso, pero a túa vida o é aínda máis, Konrad. Se as nosas "
"forzas aínda non son o suficientemente fortes para enfrontarse ao exército "
"de Wesnoth, non teñas medo de tragar o teu orgullo e fuxir. Sinto aire "
"fresco chegando do norte."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:869
msgid "Of course, fleeing would surely mean leaving the Sceptre behind..."
msgstr "Por suposto, fuxir significaría deixar atrás o Cetro..."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:877
msgid "Cowardly Victory:"
msgstr "Goblin covarde"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:878
msgid "Move Konrad to any edge of the map"
msgstr "Mover a Konrad a calquera beira do mapa"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:882
msgid "Normal Victory:"
msgstr "Vitoria normal:"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:883
msgid "(gain the Sceptre of Fire)"
msgstr "(ganar o Cetro de Fogo)"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:883
msgid "Protect Delfador until he unearths the sceptre"
msgstr "Protexe a Delfador ata que desenterre o cetro"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:888
msgid "Heroic Victory:"
msgstr "Victoria Heroica:"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:889
msgid "(gain the Sceptre of Fire, and special armor for Konrad)"
msgstr "(obtén o Cetro de Fogo e unha armadura especial para Konrad)"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:913
msgid ""
"You know I am here to claim the Sceptre as my birthright, Li’sar. Is your "
"hatred so great that you would rather chase after us than even <b><i>try</"
"i></b> to save Wesnoth from the ruin it has fallen to at the hands of your "
"mother?"
msgstr ""
"Xa sabes que estou aquí para reclamar o Cetro como o meu dereito de "
"nacemento, Li'sar. ¿É tan grande o teu odio que prefires perseguirnos en "
"lugar de <b><i>tentar</i></b> salvar Wesnoth da ruína na que caeu polas mans "
"da túa nai?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:918
msgid ""
"I <i>am</i> trying to save it — from you. Do you have any idea how much "
"chaos you and your little gang of ruffians have caused?"
msgstr ""
"<i>Estou</i> intentando salvalo... de ti. Tes algunha idea de canto caos "
"causastes ti e a túa pequena banda de rufiáns?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:922
msgid ""
"Asheviere took control of Wesnoth with violence, and violence has filled "
"every part of her reign. All she knows is blood! And all she cares about is "
"power."
msgstr ""
"Asheviere tomou o control de Wesnoth con violencia, e a violencia encheu "
"cada parte do seu reinado. Só coñece sangue! E o único que lle importa é o "
"poder."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:926
msgid ""
"You really are just a child. Maybe the Aethenwood runs on friendship and "
"flowers, but here in the real world sometimes people get hurt. And yes, "
"sometimes that means unsavory decisions, like the kind the queen has to make "
"every day."
msgstr ""
"En realidade, só es un neno. Quizais o Aethenwood funcione con amizade e "
"flores, pero aquí, no mundo real, ás veces a xente sae ferida. E si, ás "
"veces iso implica tomar decisións desagradables, coma as que a raíña ten que "
"tomar cada día."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:930
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Perhaps you truly think you’re acting for the best. But know this: with "
#| "me today stand free peoples from all corners of Wesnoth, united as one "
#| "against the tyrrany of Asheviere. Whether we defeat you now or never, "
#| "Wesnoth will never stop fighting for what is right!"
msgid ""
"Perhaps you truly think you’re acting for the best. But know this: with me "
"today stand free peoples from all corners of Wesnoth, united as one against "
"the tyranny of Asheviere. Whether we defeat you now or never, Wesnoth will "
"never stop fighting for what is right!"
msgstr ""
"Se cadra pensades de verdade que estades a actuar para o mellor. Pero sabede "
"isto: hoxe comigo están pobos libres de todos os recunchos de Wesnoth, "
"unidos como un só contra a tiranía de Asheviere. Tanto se vos derrotamos "
"agora como se nunca, Wesnoth nunca deixará de loitar polo que é xusto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:935
msgid ""
"... not bad, as hero speeches go. We’ll see how the palace dungeons change "
"your tune."
msgstr ""
"... non está mal, como discursos de heroe. Veremos como as mazmorras do "
"palacio che cambian a melodía."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:953
msgid ""
"I am making progress, Konrad! We are perhaps half of the way to the Sceptre."
msgstr ""
"Estou a facer progresos, Konrad! Quizais esteamos na metade do camiño cara "
"ao Cetro."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:960
msgid "Almost done, Konrad. We shall soon hold the Sceptre in our hands!"
msgstr "Case rematamos, Konrad. Pronto teremos o Cetro nas nosas mans!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:967
msgid ""
"I see red and gold poking though the earth! We shall have the Sceptre in but "
"another moment!"
msgstr "Vexo vermello e ouro asomando pola terra! Teremos o Cetro nun intre!"

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:979
msgid "Argh! He’s more powerful than we thought. I have to get away!"
msgstr "Argh! É máis poderoso do que pensabamos. Teño que marchar!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:989
msgid "Decades of study and practice, only to die in a cave..."
msgstr "Décadas de estudo e práctica, só para morrer nunha cova..."

#. [message]: speaker=leader7b
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1005
msgid "Ack! I’m sorry, Your Highness, I couldn’t stop them..."
msgstr "Ai! Enterra Em baixo as Chairas dos Cavalos..."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1024
msgid "For the Aethenwood! For Wesnoth! For all the world!"
msgstr "Por Aethenwood! Por Wesnoth! Por todo o mundo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1026
msgid "The wrath of the elves falls upon you, girl!"
msgstr "A ira dos elfos cae sobre ti, rapaza!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1027
msgid "Your mother has much to answer for. We shall start with you."
msgstr "A túa nai ten moito que explicar. Comezaremos contigo."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1028
msgid ""
"Ah’ll teach you and yer men to cage me up, ye obscene trunk of tallow-keech!"
msgstr ""
"Ensinareiche a ti e aos teus homes a engaiolarme, obsceno tronco de sebo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1029
msgid ""
"The blood of traitors runs in your veins, girl. In Garard’s name, I strike "
"you down!"
msgstr ""
"O sangue dos traidores corre polas túas veas, rapaza. En nome de Garard, "
"derrúbote!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1030
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1031
msgid "Behold the flames of Alduin!"
msgstr "Mirade as chamas de Alduin!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1032
msgid "By the Light we were made! Lo, and by the Light shall you be un-made!"
msgstr "Pola Luz fomos feitos! Velaquí, e pola Luz seredes desfeitos!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1033
msgid "This is for Baldras!"
msgstr "Isto é para Baldras!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1034
msgid "Sorry about this, but it has to be done!"
msgstr "Desculpa por isto, pero hai que facelo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1035
msgid "You done made wrong enemy, softskin!"
msgstr "Fizeste un inimigo equivocado, pelacúmbrio!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1124
msgid ""
"I have found an exit from the cavern! Quick, everyone, follow me and we may "
"yet evade Li’sar within the twisting tunnels!"
msgstr ""
"Atopei unha saída da caverna! Depresa, todos, seguideme e aínda poderemos "
"escapar de Li'sar polos túneles sinuosos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1150
msgid ""
"Did you hear that? An earthquake! What sorcery of yours is this, Delfador? "
"Are you collapsing this whole cavern?"
msgstr ""
"Oíches iso? Un terremoto! Que bruxería é esta túa, Delfador? Estás a "
"derrubar toda esta caverna?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1155
msgid ""
"I am not the cause of these tremors — what does that fool mage of yours "
"think she is doing? The volcano is awakening! Is she trying to kill us and "
"you both!?"
msgstr ""
"Eu non son a causa destes tremores. Que se cre que está facendo esa maga "
"parva túa? O volcán está espertando! Está a tentar matarnos a nós e a vós "
"dous!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1159
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1232
msgid ""
"Sorry, Your Highness, queen’s orders. Better that nobody leaves than Konrad "
"does."
msgstr ""
"Desculpade, Alteza, ordes da raíña. É mellor que ninguén marche que o faga "
"Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1163
msgid ""
"What?! Mirya, there’s no need for this! They’ve left without the Sceptre, "
"and it is a long way to the surface. We’ll have plenty of time to chase them "
"down!"
msgstr ""
"Que?! Mirya, non hai necesidade para isto! Marcharon sen o Cetro, e a "
"superficie está moi lonxe. Teremos moito tempo para perseguilos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1171
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1244
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1356
msgid ""
"We are all in terrible danger! Konrad, stay close. You and I must flee with "
"great haste — my spells shall speed our steps!"
msgstr ""
"Todos estamos en perigro terrible! Konrad, mantente preto. Ti e eu debemos "
"fuxir con gran présa — os meus conxuros acelerarán os nosos pasos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1197
msgid ""
"It is here! We have found it! The Sceptre of Fire; the Ruby of the Wesfolk; "
"the staff of kings. Konrad, you must come at once!"
msgstr ""
"Está aquí! Atopámolo! O Cetro de Lume; o Rubí dos Pobos do Oeste; o bastón "
"dos reis. Konrad, debes vir de inmediato!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1202
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1299
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>The Sceptre, initially dulled from centuries of dust and debris, began "
#| "to glow from its ruby’s inner fire. Dwarvish runes on the golden handle "
#| "lit up in pulsating blue as Konrad’s fingers wrapped around the staff.</i>"
msgid ""
"The Sceptre, initially dulled from centuries of dust and debris, began to "
"glow from its ruby’s inner fire. Dwarvish runes on the golden handle lit up "
"in pulsating blue as Konrad’s fingers wrapped around the staff."
msgstr ""
"<i>O cetro, inicialmente apagado por séculos de po e cascallos, comezou a "
"brillar co lume interior do seu rubí. As runas ananas no mango dourado "
"ilumináronse nun azul pulsante mentres os dedos de Konrad se envolvían "
"arredor do bastón.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1209
msgid ""
"The Sceptre is ours! It is not just a great weapon, but also a symbol; a way "
"to convince the people that I would truly belong as king. Now we finally "
"have the upper hand against Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"O cetro é noso! Non é só unha gran arma, senón tamén un símbolo; unha forma "
"de convencer o pobo de que eu realmente pertenzo como rei. Agora finalmente "
"temos a vantaxe sobre Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1219
msgid ""
"An earthquake!? Delfador, is this your doing? Has removing the Sceptre "
"somehow damaged the cavern?"
msgstr ""
"Un terremoto!? Delfador, é cousa túa? Retirar o Cetro danou dalgún xeito a "
"caverna?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1224
msgid ""
"I am not the cause of these tremors — what does that fool mage of Li’sar’s "
"think she is doing? The volcano is awakening! Is she trying to kill us and "
"the princess both!?"
msgstr ""
"Eu non son a causa destes tremores. Que se cre que está a facer esa maga "
"tola de Li'sar? O volcán está a espertar! Está a tentar matarnos a nós e á "
"princesa!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1228
msgid ""
"What?! Mirya, you’re supposed to be scouting the tunnels, not destroying "
"them."
msgstr "Que?! Mirya, deberías estar explorando os túneles, non destruíndoos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1236
msgid ""
"What?! Mirya, there’s no need for this! Konrad may have the Sceptre, but we "
"have them surrounded. Even if they escape to the surface we’ll have plenty "
"of time to chase them down!"
msgstr ""
"Que?! Mirya, non hai necesidade para isto! Konrad pode ter o Cetro, pero "
"temoslles rodeados. Mesmo se fuxen á superficie, teremos tempo de sobra para "
"perseguilos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1248
msgid "But we have only just taken hold of the Sceptre! What about—"
msgstr "Pero acabamos de apoderármonos do Cetro! Que tal..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1252
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1364
msgid "There is no time! Run, Konrad, run!"
msgstr "Non hai tempo! Corre, Konrad, corre!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1272
msgid ""
"You are beaten, villain! With your defeat, we have severed the right hand of "
"Asheviere!"
msgstr ""
"Estás vencido, vilán! Coa túa derrota, cortámoslle a man dereita a Asheviere!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1276
msgid ""
"I can’t believe it. Bested so far from home, and during my own ambush. "
"Embarrassing... Make it quick, then."
msgstr ""
"Non o podo crer. Derrotado tan lonxe da casa, e durante a miña propia "
"emboscada. Vergoñoso... Pois faino rápido."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1281
msgid ""
"No. You are to be my prisoner, and we shall ransom you to your mother in "
"exchange for her abdication; a better and more merciful use of your head "
"than petty vengeance. Delfador, do you have the Sceptre yet?"
msgstr ""
"Non. Serás o meu prisioneiro e pagarémosche un rescate á túa nai a cambio da "
"súa abdicación; un uso mellor e máis misericordioso da túa cabeza que unha "
"vinganza mesquiña. Delfador, tes xa o Cetro?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1292
msgid ""
"I do! It is here — the Sceptre of Fire; the Ruby of the Wesfolk; the staff "
"of kings. Konrad, I shall bring it to you at once."
msgstr ""
"Si! Está aquí: o Cetro de Lume; o Rubí dos Pobos do Oeste; o bastón dos "
"reis. Konrad, traereicho de inmediato."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1305
msgid ""
"The Sceptre is ours. It is not just a great weapon, Konrad, but also a "
"symbol; more proof of your kingship. And with Li’sar defeated, I wonder if "
"we might add yet another symbol to your claim..."
msgstr ""
"O cetro é noso. Non é só unha gran arma, Konrad, senón tamén un símbolo; "
"máis proba do teu reinado. E coa Li'sar derrotada, pregúntome se poderiamos "
"engadir aínda outro símbolo á túa pretensión..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1319
msgid ""
"What have you done, old man? You hold something that looks exactly like my "
"armor, finely crafted and inscribed with symbols of royalty, yet what I "
"still wear is intact. How is this possible?"
msgstr ""
"Que fixeches, vello? Tes algo que se parece exactamente á miña armadura, "
"finamente elaborada e inscrita con símbolos da realeza, e, con todo, a que "
"eu aínda levo posta está intacta. Como é posible isto?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1323
msgid ""
"A magical copy, with some improvements and details adjusted for Konrad! It "
"will exist only for a year and a day, but that will be more than enough time "
"to overthrow Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Unha copia máxica, con algunhas melloras e detalles axustados para Konrad! "
"Existirá só durante un ano e un día, pero será tempo máis que suficiente "
"para derrocar a Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad # no variation, so we can see him with both the sceptre and the chainmail
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1329
msgid ""
"Thank you, Delfador. This is truly a great boon! Now, to bind our prisoner "
"and once more ascend to the surface."
msgstr ""
"Grazas, Delfador. Isto é unha gran bendición! Agora, atar o noso prisioneiro "
"e ascender de novo á superficie."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1339
msgid ""
"An earthquake!? Delfador, is this also your doing? Has removing the Sceptre "
"somehow damaged the cavern?"
msgstr ""
"Un terremoto!? Delfador, tamén é obra túa? Retirar o Cetro danou dalgún "
"xeito a caverna?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1344
msgid ""
"I am not the cause of these tremors — what does that fool mage of Li’sar’s "
"think she is doing? The volcano is awakening! Is she trying to kill us and "
"her princess both!?"
msgstr ""
"Eu non son a causa destes tremores. Que se cre que está a facer esa maga "
"tola de Li'sar? O volcán está a espertar! Está a tentar matarnos a nós e á "
"súa princesa!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1348
msgid ""
"Sorry, Li’sar, queen’s orders. You had your chance and you failed. Now it’s "
"time for the backup plan."
msgstr ""
"Desculpa, Li’sar, ordes da raíña. Tiveches a túa oportunidade e fallaches. "
"Agora é a hora do plan de respaldo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/30_The_Sceptre_of_Fire.cfg:1360
msgid "I have the princess tied up! But what about—"
msgstr "Teño a princesa atada! Pero que pasa con..."

#. [time]: id=underground
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:17
msgid "Underground"
msgstr "subterráneo"

#. [generator]: id=cavegen
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:97
msgid "Plunging Into Darkness Caves"
msgstr "Sumergíndose nas covas da escuridade"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:327
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward "
#| "plunged into the corrosive water with supernatural haste, resurfacing "
#| "moments later inside a larger chamber.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"Blue sparks leapt from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward plunged "
"into the corrosive water with supernatural haste, resurfacing moments later "
"inside a larger chamber."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se mergullaban na auga corrosiva cunha présa sobrenatural, reaparecendo "
"momentos despois dentro dunha cámara máis grande. Os sons da terra rompendo "
"detrás eleváronse a un crescendo, logo esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres "
"unha calor incómoda lles presionaba as costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:329
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:339
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:359
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:369
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:379
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward "
#| "plunged into the corrosive water with supernatural haste, resurfacing "
#| "moments later inside a larger chamber.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
"the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
"backs."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se mergullaban na auga corrosiva cunha présa sobrenatural, reaparecendo "
"momentos despois dentro dunha cámara máis grande. Os sons da terra rompendo "
"detrás eleváronse a un crescendo, logo esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres "
"unha calor incómoda lles presionaba as costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:337
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped "
#| "away from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The few veterans able "
#| "to follow dashed madly through the cave, then passed alongside Konrad "
#| "into a larger chamber.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"Blue sparks leapt from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped away "
"from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The few veterans able to "
"follow dashed madly through the cave, then passed alongside Konrad into a "
"larger chamber."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se afastaban da lava crecente cunha présa sobrenatural. Os poucos veteranos "
"que puideron seguilos correron como tolos pola cova e logo pasaron xunto a "
"Konrad a unha cámara máis grande. Os sons da terra que se rompeu ás súas "
"costas aumentaron ata un crescendo e logo esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres "
"unha calor incómoda lles oprimía as costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:347
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped "
#| "away from the rising lava with supernatural haste, leaving both their "
#| "brave volunteers and Li’sar’s distracted soldiers far behind as they "
#| "passed into a larger chamber.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth rose to a crescendo, then faded into the "
#| "distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their backs."
#| "</i>"
msgid ""
"Blue sparks leapt from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped away "
"from the rising lava with supernatural haste, leaving both their brave "
"volunteers and Li’sar’s distracted soldiers far behind as they passed into a "
"larger chamber."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se afastaban da lava crecente cunha présa sobrenatural, deixando atrás aos "
"seus valentes voluntarios e aos soldados distraídos de Li'sar ao entrar "
"nunha cámara máis grande. Os sons da terra crebando eleváronse a un "
"crescendo e logo esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres unha calor incómoda lles "
"oprimía as costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:349
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward "
#| "plunged into the corrosive water with supernatural haste, resurfacing "
#| "moments later inside a larger chamber.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"The sounds of rupturing earth rose to a crescendo, then faded into the "
"distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their backs."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se mergullaban na auga corrosiva cunha présa sobrenatural, reaparecendo "
"momentos despois dentro dunha cámara máis grande. Os sons da terra rompendo "
"detrás eleváronse a un crescendo, logo esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres "
"unha calor incómoda lles presionaba as costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:357
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped "
#| "away from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The harried soldiers "
#| "plunged deeper and deeper into the smothering darkness, further and "
#| "further from the light of the sun.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"Blue sparks leapt from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped away "
"from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The harried soldiers plunged "
"deeper and deeper into the smothering darkness, further and further from the "
"light of the sun."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se afastaban da lava crecente cunha présa sobrenatural. Os acosados soldados "
"mergulláronse cada vez máis na escuridade asfixiante, máis e máis lonxe da "
"luz do sol. Os sons da terra crebando ás súas costas eleváronse a un "
"crescendo e logo esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres unha calor incómoda lles "
"oprimía as costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:367
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped "
#| "away from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The harried soldiers "
#| "held back vomit as they beat a path through the horrifying squalor "
#| "filling their tunnel, then passed thankfully into a larger chamber.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"Blue sparks leapt from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped away "
"from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The harried soldiers held back "
"vomit as they beat a path through the horrifying squalor filling their "
"tunnel, then passed thankfully into a larger chamber."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se afastaban da lava crecente cunha présa sobrenatural. Os acosados soldados "
"contiveron o vómito mentres se abrían camiño a través da horrible miseria "
"que enchía o seu túnel, e logo pasaron afortunadamente a unha cámara máis "
"grande. Os sons da terra crebando detrás eleváronse a un crescendo, logo "
"esvaecéronse na distancia, mentres unha calor incómoda lles oprimía as "
"costas.</i>"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:377
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Blue sparks lept from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped "
#| "away from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The harried soldiers "
#| "rushed thankfully through the miraculously opened passage.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The sounds of rupturing earth behind rose to a crescendo, then faded into "
#| "the distance, as meanwhile an uncomfortable heat pressed close at their "
#| "backs.</i>"
msgid ""
"Blue sparks leapt from the wizard’s staff as he and his young ward sped away "
"from the rising lava with supernatural haste. The harried soldiers rushed "
"thankfully through the miraculously opened passage."
msgstr ""
"<i>Faíscas azuis brotaron do bastón do mago mentres el e o seu mozo pupilo "
"se afastaban da lava crecente cunha présa sobrenatural. Os acosados soldados "
"correron afortunadamente a través da pasaxe milagrosamente aberta. Os sons "
"da terra crebando detrás eleváronse a un crescendo, logo esvaecéronse na "
"distancia, mentres unha calor incómoda lles oprimía as costas.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:460
msgid ""
"Faster, faster! My speeding spells begin to fade, but the fires continue to "
"rise! Hurry, Konrad; we must keep ahead of the lava until it recedes! Is Her "
"Highness secure?"
msgstr ""
"Máis rápido, máis rápido! Os meus feitizos de velocidade comezan a "
"esvaecerse, pero os lumes seguen a aumentar! Apresúrate, Konrad; debemos "
"adiantarnos á lava ata que retroceda! Está Súa Alteza a salvo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:464
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I have chained her wrist to mine, Delfador. But our friends and allies "
#| "all with us? We can’t leave anyone behind!"
msgid ""
"I have chained her wrist to mine, Delfador. But are our friends and allies "
"all with us? We can’t leave anyone behind!"
msgstr ""
"Encadeei o seu pulso ao meu, Delfador. Pero, ¿están todos os nosos amigos e "
"aliados connosco? Non podemos deixar a ninguén atrás!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:468
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:494
msgid ""
"Yes, they’re all still here. But everyone is running willy-nilly, and I "
"doubt we will find a keep in which to rally. If we do not hurry we shall "
"surely be caught by the lava, or else by some pursuing ally of Li’sar’s!"
msgstr ""
"Si, aínda están todos aquí. Pero todos corren sen rumbo, e dubido que atope "
"un castelo no que nos poidamos reagrupar. Se non nos apuramos, de seguro que "
"a lava nos alcanzará, ou ben algún aliado de Li'sar que nos persiga!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:472
msgid ""
"No! Surely those we did not defeat have burned to death. This has been a "
"tight thing for us even with your magic to help!"
msgstr ""
"Non! Seguramente aqueles aos que non derrotamos morreron queimados. Isto foi "
"difícil para nós mesmo coa túa axuda maxia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:476
msgid ""
"Perhaps so, perhaps not. In any case I cannot imagine our prisoner’s army "
"has fared well — and the same fate will meet us too if you do not <i><b>stop "
"talking and start running</b></i>!"
msgstr ""
"Quizais si, quizais non. En calquera caso, non podo imaxinar que ao exército "
"dos nosos prisioneiros lle fora ben... e nós correremos o mesmo destino se "
"non <i><b>parades de falar e comezades a correr</b></i> !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:486
msgid ""
"Faster, faster! My speeding spells begin to fade, but the fires continue to "
"rise! Hurry, Konrad; we must keep ahead of the lava until it recedes!"
msgstr ""
"Máis rápido, máis rápido! Os meus feitizos de velocidade comezan a "
"esvaecerse, pero os lumes seguen a aumentar! Apresúrate, Konrad; debemos "
"adiantarnos á lava ata que retroceda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:490
msgid ""
"Are our friends and allies all with us, Delfador? We can’t leave anyone "
"behind!"
msgstr ""
"Están todos os nosos amigos e aliados con nós, Delfador? Non podemos deixar "
"a ninguén atrás!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:498
msgid ""
"No! Surely Li’sar and her loyalists have burned to death. This has been a "
"tight thing for us even with your magic to help!"
msgstr ""
"Non! Seguro que Li’sar e os seus leais morreron queimados. Isto foi difícil "
"para nós mesmo coa axuda da túa maxia!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:502
msgid ""
"Perhaps so, perhaps not. In any case I cannot imagine her army has fared "
"well — and the same fate will meet us too if you do not <i><b>stop talking "
"and start running</b></i>!"
msgstr ""
"Quizais si, quizais non. En calquera caso, non podo imaxinar que ao seu "
"exército lle fora ben... e nós correremos o mesmo destino se non "
"<i><b>parades de falar e comezades a correr</b></i> !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:511
msgid "Move Konrad or Delfador to the east edge of the map"
msgstr "Move tanto Aiglondur como Angardin ao extremo leste do mapa"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:516
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:535
msgid "Death of Li’sar"
msgstr "Morte de Li’sar"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:527
msgid ""
"Lava expands 1 hex in every direction each turn, and will kill Konrad if it "
"reaches him."
msgstr ""
"A lava expándese 1 hexágono en cada dirección cada quenda e matará a Konrad "
"se o alcanza."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:529
msgid ""
"Lava expands 2 hexes in every direction each turn, and will kill Konrad if "
"it reaches him."
msgstr ""
"A lava expándese 2 hexágonos en cada dirección cada quenda e matará a Konrad "
"se o alcanza."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:533
msgid "Li’sar is chained to Konrad, and will follow one hex behind him."
msgstr "Li’sar está encadeado a Konrad e seguirao un hexágono detrás."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:586
msgid ""
"What are we doing? Li’sar is a prisoner of great value! I have no desire to "
"execute an unarmed woman, enemy though she may be."
msgstr ""
"Que estamos a facer? Li'sar é unha prisioneira de gran valor! Non teño "
"ningún desexo de executar unha muller desarmada, aínda que sexa inimiga."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:629
msgid ""
"Undead! What are such things doing down here? They will surely try to stop "
"us — and with no regard for their own safety!"
msgstr ""
"¡Mortos viventes! Que fan cousas así aquí abaixo? Seguro que tentarán "
"detelos — e sen ter en conta a súa propia seguridade!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:633
msgid ""
"Then give me my sword and I will cut them down. Or are you too afraid to let "
"me out of these chains?"
msgstr ""
"Entón dáme a miña espada e eu cortareinos. Ou tes demasiado medo de soltarme "
"destas cadeas?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:637
msgid ""
"Hmph. We cannot afford to become bogged down fighting. At least one good "
"thing comes of all this flame: it is easy to summon fire elementals!"
msgstr ""
"Hmph. Non podemos permitirnos o luxo de quedar atascados loitando. Polo "
"menos unha cousa boa sae de todas estas lapas: é doado invocar elementais de "
"lume!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:658
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1290
msgid "Aaaaah! I can’t believe it should end like this..."
msgstr "Aaaaah! Non podo crer que isto teña que acabar así..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:664
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1296
msgid ""
"Our prisoner has perished! She was an enemy, but I cannot shake the feeling "
"that Her Highness yet had a role to play in all this..."
msgstr ""
"A nosa prisioneira pereceu! Era unha inimiga, pero non podo evitar a "
"sensación de que Súa Alteza aínda tivo algún papel que desempeñar en todo "
"isto..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:683
msgid ""
"The cave here slopes sharply upwards, and the lava behind is slowing! We’ve "
"done it, Delfador; we have escaped — and with Li’sar as our prisoner! The "
"gambit of that mage of Asheviere’s has failed."
msgstr ""
"A cova aquí inclínase bruscamente cara arriba, e a lava detrás está a "
"diminuír! Conseguímolo, Delfador; escapamos... e con Li'sar como "
"prisioneiro! A táctica dese mago de Asheviere fallou."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:688
msgid ""
"The cave here slopes sharply upwards, and the lava behind is slowing! We’ve "
"done it, Delfador; we have escaped! The gambit of that mage of Asheviere’s "
"has failed."
msgstr ""
"A cova aquí inclínase bruscamente cara arriba, e a lava que hai detrás está "
"a diminuír! Conseguímolo, Delfador; escapamos! A táctica dese mago de "
"Asheviere fallou."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:699
msgid ""
"Failed in part, but not in whole. While we gathered many low-quality weapons "
"during our escape, much of our veterans’ equipment suffered serious damage. "
"Repairing them may prove costly."
msgstr ""
"Fracasou en parte, pero non na súa totalidade. Aínda que reunimos moitas "
"armas de baixa calidade durante a nosa fuxida, gran parte do equipamento dos "
"nosos veteranos sufriu danos graves. Reparalos pode resultar custoso."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:706
msgid ""
"Failed in part, but not in whole. My mind feels oddly sharp, but what of our "
"trainees? I sense some magical malady upon them, sapping their intellect. "
"Training more veterans may prove difficult."
msgstr ""
"Fracasou en parte, pero non na súa totalidade. A miña mente paréceme "
"estrañamente aguda, pero que pasa cos nosos aprendices? Presento que padecen "
"algunha enfermidade máxica, que lles minou o intelecto. Adestrar máis "
"veteranos pode resultar difícil."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:714
msgid ""
"Failed in part, but not in whole. While thus far we have been fortunate "
"enough to evade the lava, we are still lost deep underground, with the bulk "
"of our stores and rations lost to flame."
msgstr ""
"Fallou en parte, pero non na súa totalidade. Aínda que ata o de agora "
"tivemos a sorte de escapar da lava, seguimos perdidos nas profundidades do "
"subsolo, coa maior parte das nosas provisións e racións perdidas polas lapas."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:718
msgid ""
"Indeed, hunger and weakness already gnaw at my stomach. We must find a way "
"to the surface soon, or these caves may yet prove our doom..."
msgstr ""
"De feito, a fame e a debilidade xa me roen o estómago. Temos que atopar un "
"xeito de chegar á superficie axiña, ou estas covas poden ser a nosa "
"perdición..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/31_Plunging_into_Darkness.cfg:733
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Even worse, the bulk of our stores and rations have been lost to the "
#| "lava! Hunger and weakness already knaw at my stomach. We must find a way "
#| "to the surface soon, or these caves may yet prove our doom..."
msgid ""
"Even worse, the bulk of our stores and rations have been lost to the lava! "
"Hunger and weakness already gnaw at my stomach. We must find a way to the "
"surface soon, or these caves may yet prove our doom..."
msgstr ""
"Peor aínda, a lava perdeu a maior parte das nosas provisións e racións! A "
"fame e a debilidade xa me doían o estómago. Debemos atopar un xeito de "
"chegar á superficie canto antes, ou estas covas poderían ser a nosa "
"perdición..."

#. [scenario]: id=32_The_Swamp_of_Dread
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:7
msgid "scenario name^The Swamp of Dread"
msgstr "O Pantán do Medo"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:284
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Konrad, Delfador, and their army wandered for days, lost in lonely "
#| "corridors and abandoned tunnels under the trackless mountains. What few "
#| "foodstuffs had been salvaged from the lava dwindled, then vanished "
#| "entirely. For the first time Konrad saw signs of fatigue in the old "
#| "wizard’s normally inscrutable face.</i>"
msgid ""
"Konrad, Delfador, and their army wandered for days, lost in lonely corridors "
"and abandoned tunnels under the trackless mountains. What few foodstuffs had "
"been salvaged from the lava dwindled, then vanished entirely. For the first "
"time Konrad saw signs of fatigue in the old wizard’s normally inscrutable "
"face."
msgstr ""
"<i>Konrad, Delfador e o seu exército vagaron durante días, perdidos en "
"corredores solitarios e túneles abandonados baixo as montañas sen camiños. "
"Os poucos alimentos que se rescataran da lava minguaron e logo desapareceron "
"por completo. Por primeira vez, Konrad viu signos de fatiga no rostro "
"normalmente inescrutable do vello mago.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:288
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>Finally, weakened and battered by their ordeal, the exhausted rebels "
#| "emerged into an unknown valley...</i>"
msgid ""
"Finally, weakened and battered by their ordeal, the exhausted rebels emerged "
"into an unknown valley..."
msgstr ""
"<i>Finalmente, debilitados e maltreitos pola súa terrible experiencia, os "
"rebeldes exhaustos emerxeron a un val descoñecido...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:300
msgid ""
"Oh, my old bones! Long has it been since I exerted myself so, especially on "
"an empty stomach. We were most fortunate we have at last found our way to "
"the surface."
msgstr ""
"Oh, meus vellos ósos! Fai moito tempo que non me esforzo tanto, sobre todo "
"co estómago baleiro. Tivemos moita sorte de atopar por fin o camiño cara á "
"superficie."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:306
msgid ""
"But what matters is that you are alive, Konrad, and that we have escaped the "
"caves and found daylight again. And with both Li’sar and the Sceptre in our "
"hands!"
msgstr ""
"Pero o que importa é que estás vivo, Konrad, e que escapamos das covas e "
"atopamos de novo a luz do día. E con Li'sar e o Cetro nas nosas mans!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:311
msgid ""
"But what matters is that you are alive, Konrad, and that we have escaped the "
"caves and found daylight again. And although Li’sar has escaped us, at least "
"we still have the Sceptre in our hands."
msgstr ""
"Pero o que importa é que estás vivo, Konrad, e que escapamos das covas e "
"atopamos de novo a luz do día. E aínda que Li'sar escapou de nós, polo menos "
"aínda temos o Cetro nas nosas mans."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:318
msgid ""
"But what matters is that you are alive, Konrad, and that we have escaped the "
"caves and found daylight again. And we have the Sceptre as well! Despite our "
"difficulties, our quest has been a success."
msgstr ""
"Pero o que importa é que estás vivo, Konrad, e que escapamos das covas e "
"atopamos de novo a luz do día. E tamén temos o Cetro! A pesar das nosas "
"dificultades, a nosa misión foi un éxito."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:324
msgid ""
"But what matters is that you are alive, Konrad, and that we have escaped the "
"caves and found daylight again. If only we had the Sceptre with us... it is "
"surely now buried beyond all hope of reclamation."
msgstr ""
"Pero o que importa é que estás vivo, Konrad, e que escapamos das covas e "
"atopamos de novo a luz do día. Oxalá tivésemos o Cetro connosco... "
"seguramente agora está enterrado sen ningunha esperanza de recuperación."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:329
msgid "Yes, but look! We are not the only army to have escaped the caves!"
msgstr "Si, pero mira! Non somos o único exército que escapou das covas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:347
msgid ""
"My expeditionary company! Or at least a small fragment of it, with a "
"precious few survivors. And fighting many undead?!"
msgstr ""
"A miña compañía expedicionaria! Ou polo menos un pequeno fragmento dela, con "
"uns poucos superviventes. E loitando contra moitos mortos viventes?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:352
msgid ""
"That’s a grim look, but even embattled they’re more than a match for your "
"rebels, Konrad, weakened and gold-deprived as you are from your long days "
"underground."
msgstr ""
"É unha mirada sombría, pero mesmo asediados son máis que un rival para os "
"teus rebeldes, Konrad, debilitados e privados de ouro como estás despois dos "
"teus longos días baixo terra."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar # default portrait, so that if she has her Sceptre it's shown in her portrait
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:357
msgid ""
"Keep moving. Don’t get pinned. I know this looks bad, but there is no choice "
"but to fight! Fight, fight or die!"
msgstr ""
"Segue adiante. Non te quedes atrapado. Sei que isto pinta mal, pero non hai "
"máis remedio que loitar! Loitar, loitar ou morrer!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:361
msgid ""
"Even if others have escaped the lava elsewhere, we’ve no chance of finding "
"them unless we can first evade these undead!"
msgstr ""
"Mesmo se outros escaparon da lava noutro lugar, non temos ningunha "
"posibilidade de atopalos a menos que primeiro poidamos escapar destes mortos "
"viventes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:375
msgid ""
"I shouldn’t be surprised that some part of your army has survived, princess; "
"you surely trained them well."
msgstr ""
"Non me sorprende que parte do teu exército sobrevivise, princesa; seguro que "
"os adestraches ben."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:377
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I shouldn’t be surprised that some part of your army has survived, "
#| "princess; you surely trained them well.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "But from what I can see, they stand both outnumbered and surrounded. If "
#| "we keep our distance the soldiers may not notice us, and will surely "
#| "perish at the hands of the zombies!"
msgid ""
"But from what I can see, they stand both outnumbered and surrounded. If we "
"keep our distance the soldiers may not notice us, and will surely perish at "
"the hands of the zombies!"
msgstr ""
"Non me sorprendería que algunha parte do teu exército sobrevivise, princesa; "
"seguro que os adestraches ben.\n"
"\n"
"Pero polo que vexo, están superados en número e rodeados. Se mantemos a "
"distancia, os soldados poden non notarnos e, sen dúbida, morrerán a mans dos "
"zombis!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:381
msgid ""
"On the other hand... you are right that we ourselves are weakened from long "
"days of hunger and travel, and these undead will only become stronger with "
"the addition of the bodies of the royal soldiers — I see many fresh corpses "
"among their numbers already."
msgstr ""
"Doutra banda... tes razón en que nós mesmos estamos debilitados por longos "
"días de fame e viaxes, e estes mortos viventes só se farán máis fortes coa "
"incorporación dos corpos dos soldados reais; xa vexo moitos cadáveres "
"recentes entre eles."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:385
msgid ""
"I have seen firsthand the dangers of the spawn of Asheviere, Konrad, and I "
"have learned the harm that comes from lending ear to their lies. This may be "
"our only chance to vanquish these soldiers and still keep our prisoner! I "
"think it best that we ensure their defeat first, and only afterwards give "
"thought to our escape."
msgstr ""
"Vin de primeira man os perigos da progenie de Asheviere, Konrad, e aprendín "
"o dano que supón escoitar as súas mentiras. Esta pode ser a nosa única "
"oportunidade de derrotar estes soldados e aínda así manter o noso "
"prisioneiro! Creo que o mellor é que primeiro aseguremos a súa derrota e só "
"despois pensemos na nosa fuga."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:393
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:476
msgid "Maybe... but no food, no shelter, little gold..."
msgstr "Quizais... pero sen comida, sen refuxio, pouco ouro..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:397
msgid ""
"I have no love for the villains who tried to take my life, but neither am I "
"willing to doom my comrades just to spite them. That is how Asheviere "
"fights; more invested in the death of enemies than the life of friends — or "
"daughters. Did you yourself not tell me <i>“be forgiving, be wise, be kind”</"
"i>?"
msgstr ""
"Non sinto ningún amor polos viláns que intentaron quitarme a vida, pero "
"tampouco estou disposto a condenar os meus camaradas só para lles facer "
"mella. Así é como loita Asheviere; máis investido na morte dos inimigos que "
"na vida dos amigos... ou das fillas. Non me dixeches ti mesmo <i>\"sé "
"indulxente, sé sabio, sé amable\"</i> ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:401
msgid ""
"Unless all the living stand together against the dead, I fear things shall "
"end badly for us all — and from her palace safe in Weldyn, Asheviere will "
"laugh."
msgstr ""
"A menos que todos os vivos se unan contra os mortos, temo que todo rematará "
"mal para nós — e dende o seu palacio, a salvo en Weldyn, Asheviere rirá."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:405
msgid ""
"No. Li’sar, my cousin and prisoner, I offer you a trade. We shall make "
"ourselves known to your army, and you will command them to ally with us "
"against the undead. In return, once this place is cleansed, they will be "
"free to leave."
msgstr ""
"Non. Li’sar, curmán meu e prisioneiro, ofrézoche un intercambio. Darémosche "
"a coñecer ao teu exército e ordenaráslles que se alien connosco contra os "
"mortos viventes. A cambio, unha vez que este lugar sexa limpo, serán libres "
"de marchar."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:409
msgid "Perhaps. And I would be free to leave along with them?"
msgstr "Quizais. E eu sería libre de marchar con eles?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:413
msgid ""
"This is not a negotiation. You are my prisoner and at my mercy, and I still "
"mean to ransom you back to your mother in exchange for her abdication."
msgstr ""
"Isto non é unha negociación. Ti es o meu prisioneiro e estás á miña mercé, e "
"sigo tendo a intención de rescatarte e devolvelo á túa nai a cambio da súa "
"abdicación."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:417
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Do not be a fool; neither we nor your soldiers can preavil alone. And if "
#| "we fall to the undead, you will surely perish with us. Choose: will you "
#| "command your allies to aid us, or are we all to fight and bleed and die "
#| "until our bodies cold are buried under crimson snow?"
msgid ""
"Do not be a fool; neither we nor your soldiers can prevail alone. And if we "
"fall to the undead, you will surely perish with us. Choose: will you command "
"your allies to aid us, or are we all to fight and bleed and die until our "
"bodies cold are buried under crimson snow?"
msgstr ""
"Non sexas parvo; nin nós nin os teus soldados podemos prevalecer sós. E se "
"caemos ante os mortos viventes, seguramente perecerás connosco. Escolle: "
"ordenarás aos teus aliados que nos axuden ou imos loitar, sangrar e morrer "
"todos ata que os nosos corpos estean enterrados baixo a neve carmesí?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:425
msgid ""
"I’m not excited to join forces with the enemy, but neither do I want to "
"watch my friends and comrades lose a hopeless battle on two fronts. I agree "
"to your deal. I’ll remain prisoner while my soldiers fight as your allies."
msgstr ""
"Non me entusiasma unir forzas co inimigo, pero tampouco quero ver os meus "
"amigos e camaradas perder unha batalla sen esperanza en dúas frontes. Acepto "
"o teu trato. Permanecerei prisioneiro mentres os meus soldados loitan como "
"os teus aliados."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:429
msgid ""
"But once these undead are finished, there will be no leaving peacefully. "
"Prisoner or not, this battlefield still has loyalists ready to fight for "
"their queen — and you and I have a score to settle."
msgstr ""
"Pero unha vez que estes mortos viventes sexan acabados, non haberá saída en "
"paz. Prisioneiros ou non, este campo de batalla aínda ten leais dispostos a "
"loitar pola súa raíña, e ti e eu temos contas que axustar."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:443
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "So, the princess has survived — and she has the Sceptre of Fire! I "
#| "shouldn’t be surprised; villains often seem hard to finish off, don’t "
#| "they?\n"
#| "\n"
#| "And what’s more, she is fighting a great horde of undead! If we keep our "
#| "distance she may not notice us, and will surely perish at the hands of "
#| "the zombies!"
msgid ""
"So, the princess has survived — and she has the Sceptre of Fire! I shouldn’t "
"be surprised; villains often seem hard to finish off, don’t they?"
msgstr ""
"Entón, a princesa sobreviviu... e ten o Cetro de Lume! Non me sorprendería; "
"os viláns adoitan parecer difíciles de acabar, non si?\n"
"\n"
"E o que é máis, está a loitar contra unha gran horda de mortos viventes! Se "
"mantemos a distancia, pode que non nos vexa e, sen dúbida, morrerá a mans "
"dos zombis!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:445
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:452
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "So, the princess has survived after all. I shouldn’t be surprised; "
#| "villains often seem hard to finish off, don’t they?\n"
#| "\n"
#| "And what’s more, she is fighting a great horde of undead! If we keep our "
#| "distance she may not notice us, and will surely perish at the hands of "
#| "the zombies!"
msgid ""
"And what’s more, she is fighting a great horde of undead! If we keep our "
"distance she may not notice us, and will surely perish at the hands of the "
"zombies!"
msgstr ""
"Entón, a princesa sobreviviu despois de todo. Non debería sorprenderme; os "
"viláns adoitan parecer difíciles de acabar, non si?\n"
"\n"
"E o que é máis, está loitando contra unha gran horda de mortos viventes! Se "
"mantemos a distancia, pode que non nos vexa e seguramente morrerá a mans dos "
"zombis!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:450
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "So, the princess has survived after all. I shouldn’t be surprised; "
#| "villains often seem hard to finish off, don’t they?\n"
#| "\n"
#| "And what’s more, she is fighting a great horde of undead! If we keep our "
#| "distance she may not notice us, and will surely perish at the hands of "
#| "the zombies!"
msgid ""
"So, the princess has survived after all. I shouldn’t be surprised; villains "
"often seem hard to finish off, don’t they?"
msgstr ""
"Entón, a princesa sobreviviu despois de todo. Non debería sorprenderme; os "
"viláns adoitan parecer difíciles de acabar, non si?\n"
"\n"
"E o que é máis, está loitando contra unha gran horda de mortos viventes! Se "
"mantemos a distancia, pode que non nos vexa e seguramente morrerá a mans dos "
"zombis!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:457
msgid ""
"On the other hand... we ourselves are weakened from long days of hunger and "
"travel, and these undead will only become stronger with the addition of the "
"bodies of Li’sar’s men — I see many fresh corpses among their numbers "
"already."
msgstr ""
"Doutra banda... nós mesmos estamos debilitados por longos días de fame e "
"viaxes, e estes mortos viventes só se farán máis fortes coa incorporación "
"dos corpos dos homes de Li'sar; xa vexo moitos cadáveres recentes entre eles."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:462
msgid ""
"I have seen firsthand the dangers of the spawn of Asheviere, Konrad, and I "
"have learned the value of swift action against them. Li’sar has already "
"escaped us once! I think it best that we ensure her defeat first, and only "
"afterwards give thought to our escape."
msgstr ""
"Vin de primeira man os perigos da progenie de Asheviere, Konrad, e aprendín "
"o valor dunha acción rápida contra eles. Li'sar xa nos escapou unha vez! "
"Creo que é mellor que primeiro aseguremos a súa derrota e só despois "
"pensemos na nosa fuga."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:467
msgid ""
"I have seen firsthand the dangers of the spawn of Asheviere, Konrad, and I "
"have learned the value of swift action against them. This may be our only "
"chance to vanquish Li’sar! I think it best that we ensure her defeat first, "
"and only afterwards give thought to our escape."
msgstr ""
"Vin de primeira man os perigos da progenie de Asheviere, Konrad, e aprendín "
"o valor dunha acción rápida contra eles. Esta pode ser a nosa única "
"oportunidade de derrotar a Li'sar! Creo que o mellor é que primeiro "
"aseguremos a súa derrota e só despois pensemos na nosa fuga."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:480
msgid ""
"I have no love for the villain who tried to take my life, but neither am I "
"willing to doom my comrades just to spite her. That is how Asheviere fights; "
"more invested in the death of enemies than the life of friends — or "
"daughters. Did you yourself not tell me <i>“be forgiving, be wise, be kind”</"
"i>?"
msgstr ""
"Non sinto ningún amor pola vilán que intentou quitarme a vida, pero tampouco "
"estou disposto a condenar os meus camaradas só para lle facerlle fastidio. "
"Así é como loita Asheviere; máis investida na morte dos inimigos que na vida "
"dos amigos... ou das fillas. Non me dixeches ti mesma <i>\"sé indulxente, sé "
"sabio, sé amable\"</i> ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:484
msgid ""
"Unless all the living stand together against the dead, I fear things shall "
"end badly for us all — and from her palace safe in Weldyn, Asheviere will "
"laugh. No, we should approach Li’sar and offer a brief alliance, at least "
"until these undead are defeated."
msgstr ""
"A menos que todos os vivos se unan contra os mortos, temo que todo rematará "
"mal para nós — e dende o seu palacio, a salvo en Weldyn, Asheviere rirá. "
"Non, deberiamos achegarnos a Li'sar e ofrecerlle unha breve alianza, polo "
"menos ata que estes mortos viventes sexan derrotados."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:488
msgid ""
"Although she is our enemy, I believe that she is trustworthy enough to honor "
"her word if she agrees not to harm us. I ask you to trust my judgement on "
"this, my mentor."
msgstr ""
"Aínda que é a nosa inimiga, creo que é o suficientemente digna de confianza "
"como para cumprir a súa palabra se acepta non facernos dano. Pídoche que "
"confíes no meu xuízo sobre isto, meu mentor."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:492
msgid ""
"The last time a king asked me to trust him, things ended rather badly for "
"the both of us. Nevertheless, you are my lord, Konrad, and I know you to be "
"growing wise beyond your years. Let us reach Li’sar and make your offer."
msgstr ""
"A última vez que un rei me pediu que confiase nel, as cousas acabaron "
"bastante mal para nós dous. Non obstante, ti es o meu señor, Konrad, e sei "
"que te estás a volver máis sabio que os teus anos. Vamos a Li'sar e fagamos "
"a túa oferta."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:501
msgid "Reach Li’sar’s loyalists before they are slain"
msgstr "Alcanza aos leais de Li'sar antes de que os maten"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:508
msgid "Then, defeat the primary enemy leader"
msgstr "Entón, derrota ao líder principal do inimigo."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:516
msgid "Defeat the primary enemy leader"
msgstr "Derrota ao líder principal do inimigo"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:525
msgid "Defeat Iliah-Malal"
msgstr "Derrota a Iliah-Malal"

#. [note]
#. because of the low starting gold, companions (who're usually recalled for free) would be overly powerful here
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:549
msgid ""
"Konrad’s forces are exhausted, and have less starting gold than usual. Loyal "
"companions (except Delfador) are not automatically recalled."
msgstr ""
"As forzas de Konrad están esgotadas e teñen menos ouro inicial do habitual. "
"Os compañeiros fieis (agás Delfador) non son chamados automaticamente."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:566
msgid ""
"These must be the tunnels from whence Li’sar’s soldiers emerged. Out of all "
"the countless exits from the underground, we just so happened to come "
"together here..."
msgstr ""
"Estes deben ser os túneles polos que saíron os soldados de Li'sar. De entre "
"todas as incontables saídas do subsolo, por pura casualidade acabamos todos "
"xuntos aquí..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#. [message]: role=leader7
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:581
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:593
msgid "We’re in dire straits. Deploy the reserves."
msgstr "Estamos nunha situación desesperada. Despregade as reservas."

#. [message]: role=leader7
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:675
msgid ""
"Living soldiers at the perimeter! It’s Konrad and his rebels, intact despite "
"the volcano! And... they’ve taken the princess prisoner?!"
msgstr ""
"Soldados vivos no perímetro! Son Konrad e os seus rebeldes, intactos a pesar "
"do volcán! E... fixeron prisioneira á princesa?!"

#. [message]: role=leader7
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:679
msgid ""
"I’d been hoping for reinforcements, for we are already hard-pressed, but if "
"we must fight a second foe to rescue our general I shall not shy away!"
msgstr ""
"Eu agardaba reforzos, porque xa estamos en apuros, pero se temos que loitar "
"contra un segundo inimigo para rescatar o noso xeneral, non me arrepiarei!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:683
msgid ""
"No, captain, that won’t be necessary. I am a prisoner, but we’ve agreed to a "
"temporary truce — emphasis on temporary. Until these undead are defeated, "
"you are to work together with Konrad against the dead."
msgstr ""
"Non, capitán, iso non será necesario. Son prisioneiro, pero acordamos unha "
"tregua temporal; énfase en temporal. Ata que estes mortos viventes sexan "
"derrotados, debes traballar xunto con Konrad contra os mortos."

#. [message]: role=leader7
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:687
msgid ""
"You’re certain? You’re not being coerced? Well, in the dire straits we’re in "
"I can hardly say no to an ally."
msgstr ""
"Estás seguro? Non estás a ser coaccionado? Pois, na difícil situación na que "
"nos atopamos, case non podo dicirlle que non a un aliado."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:706
msgid ""
"Konrad, should we not be concerned about Li’sar’s threats? Prisoner or no, "
"she has been very clear about her intentions to turn her allies against us "
"once these undead are defeated. And perhaps sooner, if she senses in us some "
"weakness!"
msgstr ""
"Konrad, non deberiamos preocuparnos polas ameazas de Li'sar? Prisioneira ou "
"non, ela foi moi clara sobre as súas intencións de volver aos seus aliados "
"contra nós unha vez que estes mortos viventes sexan derrotados. E quizais "
"antes, se ela percibe en nós algunha debilidade!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:710
msgid ""
"Li’sar is not Eldred. Although she is our enemy, I have come to believe Her "
"Highness cares about her people just as we do, and that she is trustworthy "
"enough to honor her word if she agrees not to harm us. I ask you to trust my "
"judgement on this, my mentor."
msgstr ""
"Li’sar non é Eldred. Aínda que é a nosa inimiga, cheguei a crer que Súa "
"Alteza se preocupa polo seu pobo igual que nós, e que é o suficientemente "
"digna de confianza como para cumprir a súa palabra se acepta non facernos "
"dano. Pídoche que confíes no meu xuízo sobre isto, meu mentor."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:714
msgid ""
"The last time a king asked me to trust him, things ended rather badly for "
"the both of us. Nevertheless, you are my lord, Konrad, and I know you to be "
"growing wise beyond your years. Let us set aside my worries and direct our "
"efforts against the undead."
msgstr ""
"A última vez que un rei me pediu que confiase nel, as cousas acabaron "
"bastante mal para nós dous. Non obstante, ti es o meu señor, Konrad, e sei "
"que te estás a volver máis sabio que os teus anos. Deixemos de lado as miñas "
"preocupacións e dirixamos os nosos esforzos contra os mortos viventes."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:728
msgid ""
"Living soldiers at the perimeter! ...Konrad, you’re here! And with your army "
"too, intact despite the volcano. I intend to have serious words with the "
"queen if we somehow get out of this alive..."
msgstr ""
"Soldados vivos no perímetro! ...Konrad, estás aquí! E co teu exército tamén, "
"intacto a pesar do volcán. Teño a intención de ter unhas palabras serias coa "
"raíña se dalgún xeito saímos vivos desta..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:732
msgid ""
"I am not here to fight you, Li’sar — at least not right now. You are "
"vulnerable, but so are we, and if we war the only winner will be the undead. "
"I propose a truce."
msgstr ""
"Non estou aquí para loitar contra ti, Li’sar, polo menos non agora mesmo. Es "
"vulnerable, pero nós tamén, e se facemos a guerra os únicos gañadores serán "
"os mortos viventes. Propoño unha tregua."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:736
msgid ""
"A truce? What ploy is this; are you so cruel that you would give my men hope "
"before snuffing it out? If you are come to slay me, fight me to my face!"
msgstr ""
"Unha tregua? Que estrataxema é esta? Es tan cruel que lles dás esperanza aos "
"meus homes antes de apagala? Se viñeches matarme, loita comigo á cara!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:740
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "There is no trick! Do not be a fool; surely you can see that if we do not "
#| "stand together, we shall die alone? It is in both of our interests to "
#| "work together!\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Do you agree to my proposal, Your Highness? Or are we to fight and bleed "
#| "and die until our bodies both are buried under crimson snow?"
msgid ""
"There is no trick! Do not be a fool; surely you can see that if we do not "
"stand together, we shall die alone? It is in both of our interests to work "
"together!"
msgstr ""
"Non hai trampa! Non sexas parvo; seguro que ves que se non estamos xuntos, "
"morreremos sós? É do interese de ambos traballar xuntos! Aceitas a miña "
"proposta, Alteza? Ou imos loitar, sangrar e morrer ata que os nosos corpos "
"estean enterrados baixo unha neve carmesína?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:742
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "There is no trick! Do not be a fool; surely you can see that if we do not "
#| "stand together, we shall die alone? It is in both of our interests to "
#| "work together!\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Do you agree to my proposal, Your Highness? Or are we to fight and bleed "
#| "and die until our bodies both are buried under crimson snow?"
msgid ""
"Do you agree to my proposal, Your Highness? Or are we to fight and bleed and "
"die until our bodies both are buried under crimson snow?"
msgstr ""
"Non hai trampa! Non sexas parvo; seguro que ves que se non estamos xuntos, "
"morreremos sós? É do interese de ambos traballar xuntos! Aceitas a miña "
"proposta, Alteza? Ou imos loitar, sangrar e morrer ata que os nosos corpos "
"estean enterrados baixo unha neve carmesína?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:750
msgid ""
"Very well, we shall work together for now. But do not forget that once these "
"undead are defeated, you and I have a score to settle."
msgstr ""
"Está ben, traballaremos xuntos por agora. Pero non esquezas que, unha vez "
"que estes mortos viventes sexan derrotados, ti e eu temos contas pendentes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:778
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "My men and I are desperately low on gold and supplies, Li’sar. Now we "
#| "have met with your allies —  do they have anything to spare?"
msgid ""
"My men and I are desperately low on gold and supplies, Li’sar. Now we have "
"met with your allies — do they have anything to spare?"
msgstr ""
"Os meus homes e eu andamos desesperadamente sen ouro e subministracións, "
"Li'sar. Agora que nos reunimos cos teus aliados... ¿teñen algo que lles "
"sobrar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:783
msgid ""
"My men and I are desperately low on gold and supplies, Li’sar. Now that we "
"are allies, do you have anything to spare?"
msgstr ""
"Os meus homes e eu andamos desesperadamente sen ouro e provisións, Li’sar. "
"Agora que somos aliados, tes algo que che sobrar?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:788
msgid ""
"We are allies only of convenience, cousin, and it is not in my best interest "
"for you or your rebels to be too well-supplied."
msgstr ""
"Somos aliados só por conveniencia, primo, e non me convén que ti nin os teus "
"rebeldes esteades demasiado ben abastecidos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:793
msgid ""
"... not that it matters, because I can see that my soldiers have barely "
"enough to outfit themselves as it is. It’s unfortunate that the queen’s "
"orders harmed us as much as they did you, if not more."
msgstr ""
"... non é que importe, porque xa vexo que os meus soldados apenas teñen o "
"suficiente para equiparse. É unha mágoa que as ordes da raíña nos "
"prexudicasen tanto como a vós, se non máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:798
msgid ""
"... not that it matters, because we have barely enough to outfit ourselves "
"as it is. It’s unfortunate that the queen’s orders harmed us as much as they "
"did you, if not more."
msgstr ""
"... non é que importe, porque xa case non temos para equiparnos. É unha "
"mágoa que as ordes da raíña nos prexudicasen tanto como a vós, se non máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:803
msgid ""
"It’s not “unfortunate” — your mother was more than willing to see you killed."
msgstr ""
"Non é \"desafortunado\": a túa nai estaba máis que disposta a verte "
"asasinado."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:807
msgid ""
"Asheviere gave Mirya the orders she thought were necessary to prevent you "
"from escaping. Whether they were wise orders or not is immaterial; she acted "
"to ensure that Wesnoth survives, even if I don’t. I cannot fault her for "
"that."
msgstr ""
"Asheviere deulle a Mirya as ordes que ela cría necesarias para impedirche "
"escapar. Se foron ordes sabias ou non, é irrelevante; ela actuou para "
"garantir que Wesnoth sobrevivise, mesmo que eu non o faga. Non podo culpala "
"por iso."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:811
msgid ""
"She acted to ensure her power remains unchallenged, you mean. The dark queen "
"cares only for herself."
msgstr ""
"Ela actuou para garantir que o seu poder permanecese indiscutible, queres "
"dicir. A raíña escura só se preocupa por si mesma."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:816
msgid ""
"“<i>The dark queen</i>,” pfft. I’ve heard enough slander; hold your tongue "
"or I shall have my men make an end to our truce and short work of you."
msgstr ""
"« <i>A raíña escura</i> », pfft. Xa escoitei abondo calumnias; cala ou farei "
"que os meus homes poñan fin á nosa tregua e te traten en pouco tempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:821
msgid ""
"“<i>The dark queen</i>,” pfft. I’ve heard enough slander; hold your tongue "
"or I shall make an end to our truce and short work of you."
msgstr ""
"« <i>A raíña escura</i> », pfft. Xa escoitei abondo calumnias; cala ou porei "
"fin á nosa tregua e acabarei contigo en pouco tempo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:863
msgid "Don’t wander around my keep, Konrad. We have a battle to fight."
msgstr "Non andes pola miña fortaleza, Konrad. Temos unha batalla que librar."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:878
msgid ""
"You have no tricks this time, Malal? Your magic is as weak as was your flesh!"
msgstr ""
"Non tes trucos desta vez, Malal? A túa maxia é tan débil coma o era a túa "
"carne!"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#. the same thing he says when fighting Delfador in The Deceiver's Gambait
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:883
msgid "Shadows consume you!"
msgstr "As sombras consumente!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:892
msgid "Delfador killed you once! Now it’s my turn!"
msgstr "Delfador matoute unha vez! Agora é a miña quenda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:901
msgid "Time to put you and your lies back in the ground!"
msgstr "É hora de volver enterrarche a ti e ás túas mentiras!"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:919
msgid "Eye of elf and bone of beast..."
msgstr "Ollo de elfo e óso de besta..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:924
msgid ""
"A lich! So here is the source of the undead. Something about this magic "
"feels familiar... very familiar..."
msgstr ""
"Un liche! Entón, aquí está a fonte dos mortos viventes. Algo nesta maxia "
"paréceme familiar... moi familiar..."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:929
msgid ""
"Hello, Delfador! Do you remember me? You’ve grown old. Perhaps you regret "
"passing up the temptations of necromancy, so long ago?"
msgstr ""
"Ola, Delfador! Lémbraste de min? Fixecheste vello. Quizais te arrepintas de "
"deixar pasar as tentacións da necromancia, hai tanto tempo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:933
msgid ""
"Iliah-Malal! A name most foul, and one that I have not spoken aloud since "
"our duel so many years ago. You’ll recall that I won. You should be dead and "
"gone."
msgstr ""
"Iliah-Malal! Un nome moi repugnante, e un que non pronunciei en voz alta "
"desde o noso duelo hai tantos anos. Lembrarás que gañei. Deberías estar "
"morto e desaparecido."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:935
msgid "Iliah-Malal"
msgstr "Ilia-Malal"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:938
msgid ""
"Dead, yes, but not quite gone. You have the good queen to thank for my "
"return. And I have you to thank for finding the Sceptre of Fire! Soon it "
"will be mine."
msgstr ""
"Morta, si, pero non xa non está de todo. Tes que agradecerlle á boa raíña o "
"meu regreso. E eu teño que agradecerche a ti por atopar o Cetro de Lume! "
"Pronto será meu."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:943
msgid ""
"I know my own mother, lich, and she would never be complicit in the "
"resurrection of an abomination like yourself."
msgstr ""
"Coñezo á miña propia nai, lich, e ela nunca sería cómplice na resurrección "
"dunha abominación coma ti."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1005
msgid ""
"You can’t deny, Li’sar, that th’ queen o’ yours was ready to massacre us "
"smallfolk in Delwyn an’ Dallben jus’ because we refused to swear fealty. An’ "
"she would’ve succeeded too, if we hadn’t fought back an’ fled an’ hid!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, Li'sar, que a túa raíña estaba disposta a masacrar a nós, a "
"xente común, en Delwyn e Dallben só porque nos negamos a xurar fidelidade. E "
"tería triunfado tamén se non nos defendésemos, fuxísemos e nos agochásemos!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1006
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1013
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told that region had always been home to "
"rebels, and that after the destruction of Halstead Mother was regrettably "
"forced to raze the villages."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que esa rexión sempre fora o fogar "
"de rebeldes e que, despois da destrución de Halstead, a Nai viuse obrigada, "
"por desgraza, a arrasar as aldeas."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1012
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere was ready to massacre the smallfolk "
"in Delwyn and Dallben just because they refused to swear fealty. They told "
"me the story: had they not fought back and fled and hid, they would all be "
"dead now."
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, primo, que Asheviere estaba disposto a masacrar o pobo "
"humilde de Delwyn e Dallben só porque se negaron a xurar fidelidade. "
"Contáronme a historia: se non se defendesen, fuxisen e se agochasen, agora "
"estarían todos mortos."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1020
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere passed control of Elensefar to the "
"orcish hordes when she found she could not bend the populace to her will. I "
"was there — it is only by my sword that the entire city was not enslaved!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que Asheviere entregou o control de Elensefar ás "
"hordas orcas cando descubriu que non podía someter á poboación á súa "
"vontade. Eu estaba alí: foi só grazas á miña espada que non se escravizou a "
"cidade enteira!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1021
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told that the city was under the control of "
"royal forces; the orcs were only supposed to aid in the attack."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que a cidade estaba baixo o control "
"das forzas reais; os orcos só debían axudar no ataque."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1022
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere gave control of Elensefar to the orcish hordes when "
"she found she could not bend the populace to her will? Without my "
"intervention the entire city would have been enslaved!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou con como Asheviere lles deu o control de Elensefar ás hordas "
"orcas cando descubriu que non podía someter a poboación á súa vontade? Sen a "
"miña intervención, toda a cidade estaría escravizada!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1027
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere allowed a necromancer to run amuck "
"on the Peninsula of Pearls, to weaken and create chaos in the west. I was "
"there — it is only by my sword that Muff Malal was killed!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, primo, que Asheviere permitiu que un necromante se desboque "
"na Península das Perlas, para debilitar e crear caos no oeste. Eu estaba alí "
"— só coa miña espada foi morto Muff Malal!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1028
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told that you rebels were the ones who "
"invited the necromancer in, and that royal forces were beaten back when they "
"came to render aid."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que fostes vós, os rebeldes, os que "
"convidastes ao necromante, e que as forzas reais foron derrotadas cando "
"viñeron axudar."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1029
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere allowed a necromancer to run amuck on the Peninsula "
"of Pearls, to weaken and create chaos in the west? Without my intervention "
"the entire coast might have been overrun!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou con como Asheviere permitiu que un necromante se descontrolase "
"na Península das Pérolas, que se debilitase e crease o caos no oeste? Sen a "
"miña intervención, toda a costa podería estar invadida!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1034
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere allowed her orcs to overrun the Bay "
"of Pearls, to enslave the peaceful merfolk and force them to dive for her "
"enrichment. I was there — it is only by my sword that they were freed!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que Asheviere permitiu que os seus orcos invadiran "
"a Baía das Perlas, escravisaran aos pacíficos habitantes mariños e os "
"obrigasen a mergullar para o seu enriquecemento. Eu estaba alí — só coa miña "
"espada foron liberados!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1035
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told the orcs were protecting the merfolk "
"against the rebels, not holding them as slaves."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que os orcos estaban a protexer os "
"sirénidos contra os rebeldes, non a ter como escravos."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1036
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere allowed her orcs to overrun the Bay of Pearls, to "
"enslave the peaceful merfolk and force them to dive for her enrichment? "
"Without my intervention they might never have been freed!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou con como Asheviere permitiu que os seus orcos invadisen a Baía "
"das Perlas, escravizaran as pacíficas sereas e as obrigasen a mergullarse "
"para o seu enriquecemento? Sen a miña intervención, quizais nunca se terían "
"liberado!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1042
msgid ""
"Li’sar, what about how yer gnashgabbin’ Asheviere locked me up jus’ fer a "
"couple o’ insults — an’ high-quality ones too, proper fit fer a queen! Ye "
"even helped keep me an’ my boys from escapin’!"
msgstr ""
"Li'sar, que che pareceu de como o teu Asheviere, o parvo de palabras, me "
"encerrou só por un par de insultos, e uns de moi boa calidade, axeitados "
"para unha raíña? Incluso axudaches a evitar que os meus fillos e eu "
"escapásemos!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1043
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told you dwarves were sentenced for sedition "
"and murder, not mere vulgarity."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que vos, os ananos, erades "
"condenados por sedición e asasinato, non por mera vulgaridade."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1044
msgid ""
"Ach, an’ what about how yer gnashgabbin’ Asheviere locked me up jus’ fer a "
"couple o’ insults — an’ high-quality ones too, proper fit fer a queen! Ye "
"even helped keep me an’ my boys from escapin’!"
msgstr ""
"Ai, e que che pareceu de como o teu Asheviere, o parvo de palabras, me "
"encerrou só por un par de insultos (e uns de alta calidade, axeitados para "
"unha raíña! Incluso axudaches a que os meus fillos e eu non escapásemos!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1049
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere locked up Ulfdain and his miners for "
"no crime but daring to criticise her! You even tried to stop me from freeing "
"them!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que Asheviere encarcerou a Ulfdain e aos seus "
"mineiros sen ningún delito, só por atreverse a criticarlla! Ata tentaches "
"impedir que eu os liberase!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1050
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told those dwarves were sentenced for "
"sedition and murder, not mere vulgarity."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que eses ananos foron condenados por "
"sedición e asasinato, non por mera vulgaridade."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1051
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere locked up Ulfdain and his miners for no crime but "
"daring to criticise her! You even tried to stop me from intervening to free "
"them!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou con como Asheviere encerrou a Ulfdain e aos seus mineiros sen "
"ningún delito, agás por ousar criticala! Incluso intentaches impedirme que "
"interviñese para liberalos!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1058
msgid ""
"You can scarcely deny, Li’sar, that after my peoples’ defeat at the "
"Aethenwood, Asheviere sent her armies to take our fleeing civilians as "
"slaves. It is only thanks to Konrad they escaped!"
msgstr ""
"Mal podes negar, Li'sar, que despois da derrota do meu pobo en Aethenwood, "
"Asheviere enviou os seus exércitos para capturar os nosos civís fuxitivos "
"como escravos. Só grazas a Konrad escaparon!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1059
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. Your Aethenwood elves are dangerous, hardly "
"civilians, but you were all to be afforded a fair trial and a just verdict, "
"not taken as slaves."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Os vosos elfos de Aethenwood son perigosos, "
"dificilmente civís, pero todos vós debíades ter un xuízo xusto e un "
"veredicto xusto, non ser tomados como escravos."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1060
msgid ""
"Or what of how after the elves’ defeat at the Aethenwood, Asheviere sent her "
"armies to take our fleeing civilians as slaves? Without Konrad’s "
"intervention they would be in chains in the mines!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou despois da derrota dos elfos no Bosque de Aethen, Asheviere "
"enviou os seus exércitos para levar aos nosos civís fuxitivos como escravos? "
"Sen a intervención de Konrad estarían encadeados nas minas!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1065
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that after the elves’ defeat at the Aethenwood, "
"Asheviere sent her armies to take the fleeing civilians as slaves. I was "
"there — it is only by my sword that they escaped!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que despois da derrota dos elfos en Aethenwood, "
"Asheviere enviou os seus exércitos para capturar os civís fuxitivos como "
"escravos. Eu estaba alí — só grazas á miña espada escaparon!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1066
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. The Aethenwood elves are dangerous, hardly "
"civilians, but they were to be afforded a fair trial and a just verdict, not "
"taken as slaves."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Os elfos de Aethenwood son perigosos, "
"dificilmente civís, pero debían recibir un xuízo xusto e un veredicto xusto, "
"non ser tomados como escravos."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1067
msgid ""
"Or what of how after the elves’ defeat at the Aethenwood, Asheviere sent her "
"armies to take the fleeing civilians as slaves? Without my intervention they "
"would be in chains in the mines!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou despois da derrota dos elfos no Bosque de Aethen, Asheviere "
"enviou os seus exércitos para levar como escravos aos civís que fuxían? Sen "
"a miña intervención estarían encadeados nas minas!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1074
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere sent her dwarvish lackies to slay "
"Wesnoth’s wild gryphons and steal their eggs! I was there — it is only by my "
"sword that Gryphon Mountain was not entirely ruined!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que Asheviere enviou os seus lacaios ananos para "
"matar os grifóns salvaxes de Wesnoth e roubar os seus ovos! Eu estaba alí — "
"só grazas á miña espada a Montaña dos Grifóns non quedou completamente "
"arruinada!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1075
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1081
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. I was told we’d decided against the egg "
"expedition, because of the intelligence of gryphons and the risks to their "
"population."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Dixéronme que decidiramos non facer a "
"expedición dos ovos, pola intelixencia dos grifóns e os riscos para a súa "
"poboación."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1076
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere sent her dwarvish lackies to slay Wesnoth’s wild "
"gryphons and steal their eggs? Without my intervention Gryphon Mountain "
"might have been entirely ruined!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou con como Asheviere enviou os seus lacaios ananos para matar os "
"grifóns salvaxes de Wesnoth e roubarlles os ovos? Sen a miña intervención, o "
"Monte Grifón podería estar completamente arruinado!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1080
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere sent her dwarvish lackies to slay "
"Wesnoth’s wild gryphons and steal their eggs! I may have benefitted from the "
"act, but that does not change Asheviere’s decision to do it."
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, primo, que Asheviere enviou os seus lacaios ananos para "
"matar os grifóns salvaxes de Wesnoth e roubar os seus ovos! Pode que eu me "
"beneficiase dese acto, pero iso non cambia a decisión de Asheviere de facelo."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1082
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere sent her dwarvish lackies to slay Wesnoth’s wild "
"gryphons and steal their eggs? I may have benefitted from the act, but that "
"does not change Asheviere’s decision to do it."
msgstr ""
"Ou que pasou con como Asheviere enviou os seus lacaios ananos para matar os "
"grifóns salvaxes de Wesnoth e roubarlles os ovos? Pode que eu me beneficiase "
"do acto, pero iso non cambia a decisión de Asheviere de facelo."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1089
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You can scarcely deny, Li’sar, that the dark queen deliberately withheld "
#| "aid from my home, leaving many of our number to die at the hands of "
#| "undead. It is only thanks to Konrad that our seal was restord and "
#| "calamity averted!"
msgid ""
"You can scarcely deny, Li’sar, that the dark queen deliberately withheld aid "
"from my home, leaving many of our number to die at the hands of undead. It "
"is only thanks to Konrad that our seal was restored and calamity averted!"
msgstr ""
"Mal podes negar, Li'sar, que a raíña escura retivese deliberadamente a axuda "
"ao meu fogar, deixando morrer moitos dos nosos a mans dos mortos viventes. "
"Só grazas a Konrad o noso selo foi restablecido e a calamidade evitada!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1090
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. You and your order are doing important work; it "
"should be the crown’s responsibility to keep you provisioned."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Ti e a túa orde estades a facer un traballo "
"importante; debería ser responsabilidade da coroa mantelos provisionados."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1091
msgid ""
"Lo! Or what of how Asheviere deliberately withheld aid from my home, leaving "
"many of our number to die at the hands of undead? Without Konrad’s "
"intervention our seal would never have been restored!"
msgstr ""
"Mira! Ou que hai de como Asheviere retirou deliberadamente axuda ao meu "
"fogar, deixando que moitos dos nosos morreran a mans de mortos viventes? Sen "
"a intervención de Konrad, o noso selo nunca se tería restaurado!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1096
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere deliberately withheld aid from "
#| "the Gryphon Mountain monastery, leaving many of their number to die at "
#| "the hands of undead. It is only by my sword that their seal was restord "
#| "and calamity averted!"
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere deliberately withheld aid from the "
"Gryphon Mountain monastery, leaving many of their number to die at the hands "
"of undead. It is only by my sword that their seal was restored and calamity "
"averted!"
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que Asheviere deliberadamente retivo axuda ao "
"mosteiro da Montaña do Grifón, deixando morrer a moitos dos seus a mans dos "
"mortos viventes. Só coa miña espada se restableceu o seu selo e se evitou a "
"calamidade!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1097
msgid ""
"—no, that can’t be right. The monastic mages are doing important work; it "
"should be the crown’s responsibility to keep them provisioned."
msgstr ""
"—non, iso non pode ser certo. Os magos monásticos están a facer un traballo "
"importante; debería ser responsabilidade da coroa mantelos abastecidos."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1098
msgid ""
"Or what of how Asheviere deliberately withheld aid from the Gryphon Mountain "
"monastery, leaving many of their number to die at the hands of undead? "
"Without my intervention their seal would never have been restored!"
msgstr ""
"Ou que hai de como Asheviere lle retirou deliberadamente axuda ao mosteiro "
"do Monte Grifón, deixando que moitos deles morreran a mans de mortos "
"viventes? Sen a miña intervención, o seu selo nunca se tería restaurado!"

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1105
msgid ""
"You can scarcely deny, Li’sar, that Asheviere’s quarrel with the Aethenwood "
"was more than just a quest to capture Konrad and Delfador. Asheviere has a "
"lust for control, and anyone who resists must be destroyed."
msgstr ""
"Pouco podes negar, Li'sar, que a disputa de Asheviere co Aethenwood foi máis "
"que unha simple misión para capturar a Konrad e a Delfador. Asheviere ten "
"unha ansia de control, e quen se lle opoña debe ser destruído."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1107
msgid ""
"Or what of Asheviere’s attack on the Aethenwood? This was more than just a "
"quest to capture Konrad and Delfador. Asheviere has a lust for control, and "
"anyone who resists must be destroyed."
msgstr ""
"Ou que hai do ataque de Asheviere ao Bosque de Aethen? Esta era máis que "
"unha simple misión para capturar a Konrad e Delfador. Asheviere ten unha "
"paixón polo control e calquera que se resista debe ser destruído."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1112
msgid ""
"You cannot deny, cousin, that Asheviere’s quarrel with the Aethenwood was "
"more than just a quest to capture me and Delfador. Asheviere has a lust for "
"control, and anyone who resists must be destroyed."
msgstr ""
"Non podes negar, curmán, que a disputa de Asheviere co Aethenwood foi máis "
"que unha simple misión para capturar a min e a Delfador. Asheviere ten unha "
"ansia de control, e quen se lle opoña debe ser destruído."

#. [event]: SPEAKER=Harper, SPEAKER=Ulfdain, SPEAKER=Kalenz, SPEAKER=Moremirmu, SPEAKER=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1114
msgid ""
"Or what of Asheviere’s attack on the Aethenwood? This was more than just a "
"quest to capture me and Delfador. Asheviere has a lust for control, and "
"anyone who resists must be destroyed."
msgstr ""
"Ou que hai do ataque de Asheviere ao Bosque de Aethen? Isto foi máis que "
"unha simple misión para capturarnos a min e a Delfador. Asheviere ten unha "
"paixón polo control e calquera que se resista debe ser destruído."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1144
msgid "I feel... nothing."
msgstr "Sinto... nada."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1173
msgid ""
"The lich is defeated, Li’sar, and our agreed-upon truce comes to an end. If "
"your soldiers and I are to battle, know that even weakened from the caves "
"they shall still find me a formidable foe."
msgstr ""
"O lich foi derrotado, Li’sar, e a nosa tregua acordada chega ao seu fin. Se "
"os teus soldados e eu temos que loitar, sabe que mesmo debilitados nas "
"covas, aínda me atoparán un inimigo formidable."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1178
msgid ""
"The lich is defeated, Li’sar, and our agreed-upon truce comes to an end. If "
"we are to battle, know that even weakened from the caves you shall still "
"find me a formidable foe."
msgstr ""
"O lich foi derrotado, Li’sar, e a nosa tregua acordada chega ao seu fin. Se "
"temos que loitar, debes saber que mesmo debilitado nas covas, seguirás a ser "
"un inimigo formidable."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1183
msgid ""
"But you heard my truths about Asheviere — and Malal’s. The dark queen has "
"already harmed countless lives, and will bring all that we love to ruin if "
"we do not stop her. If you are willing, I would welcome your aid in my fight "
"to make Wesnoth a better place."
msgstr ""
"Pero escoitaches as miñas verdades sobre Asheviere... e as de Malal. A raíña "
"escura xa prexudicou innumerables vidas e arruinará todo o que amamos se non "
"a detemos. Se estás disposto, agradecería a túa axuda na miña loita para "
"facer de Wesnoth un lugar mellor."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1187
msgid ""
"My mother has her flaws, but the crimes of which you’ve accused her... I "
"spent my entire childhood listening to my mother give orders and commanding "
"armies around. I’d always given her the benefit of the doubt."
msgstr ""
"A miña nai ten os seus defectos, pero os crimes dos que a acusas... Pasei "
"toda a miña infancia escoitando a miña nai dar ordes e comandando exércitos "
"arredor. Sempre lle dera o beneficio da dúbida."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1191
msgid ""
"But I cannot deny there have been signs. I became my mother’s most trusted "
"aide-de-camp. I was sent to quiet the worst of the various rebellions. Of "
"course they fought back. I was never told who most of these people were or "
"why they fought my mother. Now the volcano, and now this lich..."
msgstr ""
"Pero non podo negar que houbo sinais. Convertinme no axudante de campo de "
"maior confianza da miña nai. Enviáronme para acalar a peor das diversas "
"rebelións. Por suposto, eles contraatacaron. Nunca me dixeron quen era a "
"maioría destas persoas nin por que loitaban contra a miña nai. Agora o "
"volcán, e agora este lich..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1204
msgid ""
"Free me from these chains and I will join you, even if it means opposing my "
"own flesh. Perhaps together we can save our country in a way that neither of "
"us could alone."
msgstr ""
"Libérame destas cadeas e unireime a ti, mesmo que iso signifique opoñerme á "
"miña propia carne. Quizais xuntos poidamos salvar o noso país dun xeito que "
"ningún de nós podería facer só."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1210
msgid ""
"I will join you, even if it means opposing my own flesh. Perhaps together we "
"can save our country in a way that neither of us could alone."
msgstr ""
"Unireime a vós, mesmo que iso implique opoñerme á miña propia carne. Quizais "
"xuntos poidamos salvar o noso país dun xeito que ningún de nós podería facer "
"só."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1239
msgid ""
"We’ve come this far together. There is no reason for me to execute an "
"unarmed woman, enemy though she may be!"
msgstr ""
"Chegamos ata aquí xuntos. Non hai razón para que eu execute a unha muller "
"desarmada, aínda que sexa inimiga!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION defeat}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1258
msgid ""
"I can’t believe it. Bested so far from home.... and in part by the actions "
"of my own mother. Embarrassing..."
msgstr ""
"Non o podo crer. Derrotada tan lonxe da casa... e en parte polas accións da "
"miña propia nai. Vergoñoso..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1263
msgid ""
"We are beaten! Bested so far from home.... and in part by the actions of the "
"queen..."
msgstr ""
"Estamos derrotados! Vencidos tan lonxe de casa... e en parte polas accións "
"da raíña..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1274
msgid ""
"Li’sar’s soldiers have fallen, and their camps have become infested with "
"undead! I would rejoice, if we were not surely about to follow them into "
"undeath..."
msgstr ""
"Os soldados de Li'sar caeron e os seus campamentos están infestados de "
"mortos viventes! Alegraríame se non estivésemos a piques de seguilos cara á "
"non-morte..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1311
msgid ""
"Ugh... I am faint with hunger and exhausted from our long days underground. "
"We must finish these undead before we become too weak to fight!"
msgstr ""
"Ugh... Estou desmaiando de fame e esgotado polos nosos longos días baixo "
"terra. Temos que acabar con estes mortos viventes antes de que nos volvamos "
"demasiado débiles para loitar!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/32_The_Swamp_of_Dread.cfg:1318
msgid ""
"My heart... my head... our long ordeal has taken a toll on us all. I can "
"barely stand, much less fight, and the army is no better. Even if Li’sar is "
"still able to vanquish these undead without our aid, she will surely do the "
"same to us now that we have become so frail!"
msgstr ""
"O meu corazón... a miña cabeza... a nosa longa proba pasounos factura a "
"todos. Apenas podo manterme en pé, e moito menos loitar, e o exército non "
"mellora. Mesmo se Li'sar aínda é capaz de vencer a estes mortos viventes sen "
"a nosa axuda, seguramente fará o mesmo connosco agora que nos volvemos tan "
"fráxiles!"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:10
msgid "scenario name^Snow Plains"
msgstr "Planos de neve"

#. [side]: type=Orcish Warlord, id=leader2
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:41
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:57
msgid "Clan Fell-Hand"
msgstr "Clan Mán-Fele"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:214
msgid ""
"Your Highness, the Princess of Wesnoth! Can that be you, off in the "
"distance?! ...I’d be elated to see you, if you weren’t so clearly marching "
"in rapport with the traitor prince. This is a surprise."
msgstr ""
"Vosa Alteza, a Princesa de Wesnoth! ¿Pode ser vostede alí "
"lonxe?! ...Encantaríame velao, se non marchase tan claramente en perfecta "
"sintonía co príncipe traidor. Isto é unha sorpresa."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:218
msgid ""
"Konrad’s not the one who tried to kill his own allies in a flood of lava, "
"Mirya. Yet here I stand alive and free, while you are locked behind bars."
msgstr ""
"Konrad non foi quen intentou matar os seus propios aliados nunha enxurrada "
"de lava, Mirya. Pero aquí estou eu, viva e libre, mentres ti estás encerrada "
"tras as reixas."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:222
msgid ""
"For over a decade now, you’ve served as my mother’s fastest scout and most "
"reliable courier. You’ve seen every major event in the kingdom firsthand; "
"people and battles I’ve only read about in sanitized reports."
msgstr ""
"Durante máis dunha década, levas sendo o explorador máis rápido e o "
"mensaxeiro máis fiable da miña nai. Viches de primeira man todos os "
"acontecementos importantes do reino; xente e batallas das que só lin en "
"informes sen escrúpulos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:226
msgid ""
"Tell me, when did we stop trying to make Wesnoth a better place; a stronger "
"place? Or was it always this way and I was just too blind to see?"
msgstr ""
"Dime, cando deixamos de intentar facer de Wesnoth un lugar mellor; un lugar "
"máis forte? Ou foi sempre así e eu era demasiado cego para ver?"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:234
msgid ""
"Urag-Tifer, you must set me free at once. These soldiers before you are "
"rebels and traitors, orc-haters out for your head. Set me free and I will "
"help you fight."
msgstr ""
"Urag-Tifer, debes liberarme de inmediato. Estes soldados que tes diante son "
"rebeldes e traidores, odiadores de orcos que queren a túa cabeza. Liberame e "
"axudareiche a loitar."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:238
msgid ""
"Set you free so you can magic yourself away without us getting our ransom? "
"Fat chance. Just ’cause I’m an orc doesn’t mean I’m stupid."
msgstr ""
"Liberarte para que poidas maxia-te sen que nós paguemos o rescate? Poucas "
"posibilidades. Só porque son un orco non significa que sexa estúpido."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:242
msgid ""
"We’ll handle these soldiers the orcish way. C’mon, boys, grab your swords! "
"We’ve got a battle to win!"
msgstr ""
"Trataremos estes soldados á maneira orca.  Aínda, rapaces, collede as vosas "
"espadas! Temos unha batalla que gañar!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:274
msgid "Defeat Urag-Tifer"
msgstr "Derrota a Urag-Tifer"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:302
msgid ""
"There’s the mage, but there won’t be time to deal with her until we first "
"defeat these orcs!"
msgstr ""
"Está alí a maga, pero non haberá tempo para ocuparnos dela ata que antes "
"derrotemos a estes orcos!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:336
msgid "Gah, ah..."
msgstr "Gah, ah..."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:343
msgid "Hands off!! Not another swing at me, or the mage gets it!"
msgstr "Mans fóra!! Nin outro golpe cara a min, ou o mago o entenderá!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:351
msgid ""
"Okay, go ahead. We’re fighting to stop Mirya from returning to my mother, "
"not to rescue her or to keep her as prisoner."
msgstr ""
"De acordo, adiante. Loitamos para evitar que Mirya volva coa miña nai, non "
"para rescatala nin para mantela prisioneira."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:359
msgid "<b><i>That’s</i></b> all you want?!"
msgstr "<b><i>¿Só</i></b> iso queres?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:363
msgid "Wait—"
msgstr "Agarda—"

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:368
msgid "There, she’s dead. Better I lose a ransom than my life."
msgstr "Alí, ela está morta. Mellor perder un rescate que a miña vida."

#. [message]: speaker=leader2
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:372
msgid ""
"Now get out of here. You pinkskins and your politics have caused me enough "
"trouble already..."
msgstr ""
"Agora sae de aquí. Xa me causastes abondo problemas, peles rosas, e a vosa "
"política..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:388
msgid ""
"Mirya isn’t the type to leave her fate to chance, Konrad. While we’re busy "
"fighting, she’s certainly planning some kind of escape."
msgstr ""
"Mirya non é de deixar o seu destino ao azar, Konrad. Mentres nós estamos "
"ocupados loitando, ela seguro que está a planear algún tipo de fuga."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:392
msgid ""
"If we take too long to defeat these orcs and capture her, she may slip away "
"from us and back to Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Se tardamos demasiado en derrotar estes orcos e capturala, pode escapar de "
"nós e volver a Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/41_Snow_Plains.cfg:399
msgid ""
"Finally, I’ve burned an opening in these bars. And that oaf of an orc has "
"been too preoccupied with Li’sar to notice! Time to slip away..."
msgstr ""
"Por fin, fixen un burato nestas barras. E ese parvo de orco estivo demasiado "
"ocupado con Li'sar para decatarse! É hora de escapar..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:13
msgid "scenario name^A Crisis of Leadership"
msgstr "A Crise de Liderado"

#. [side]: type={TYPE}, id={ID}
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:44
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:68
msgid "Clan Whitefang"
msgstr "Clan Colmillo Branco"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:50
msgid "Chief Khargol"
msgstr "Chefe Khargol"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:51
msgid "Ga-har"
msgstr "Gah-har"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:52
msgid "Aharb"
msgstr "Aharb"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:53
msgid "Arshag"
msgstr "Arshag"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:54
msgid "Rizgab"
msgstr "Rizgab"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:57
msgid "Muk-har"
msgstr "Muk-har"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:153
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:164
msgid "25 gold"
msgstr "25 ouro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:154
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:155
msgid "50 gold"
msgstr "50 ouro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:156
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:158
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:160
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:208
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:209
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:210
msgid "100 gold"
msgstr "100 ouro"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:157
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:159
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:161
msgid "200 gold"
msgstr "200 ouro"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:324
msgid ""
"I have the scheming orc locked up, Konrad. My soldiers and I will guard the "
"camp to make sure he doesn’t escape until you safely return."
msgstr ""
"Teño encerrado ao orco intrigante, Konrad. Os meus soldados e eu gardaremos "
"o campamento para asegurarnos de que non escape ata que volvas san e salvo."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:330
msgid ""
"Yeah yeah, nice cage. Now, prince — recruit three of your best fighters, and "
"my followers’ wagons will sneak you four into the camp."
msgstr ""
"Sí, sí, boja gaiola. Agora, príncipe, recluta tres dos teus mellores "
"loitadores, e os carros dos meus seguidores faranche entrar catro no "
"campamento de forma encuberta."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:336
msgid ""
"You haven’t seen our camp before, but as long as you stay hidden in my "
"wagons you should be able to freely explore. Once you find the chief, kill "
"him!"
msgstr ""
"Non viches o noso campamento antes, pero mentres te manteñas agochado nos "
"meus vagóns poderás exploralo libremente. Cando atopes ao xefe, mátao!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:344
msgid "Recruit three units to help Konrad infiltrate the orcish camp"
msgstr ""
"Recruta tres unidades para axudar a Konrad a infiltrarse no campamento orco"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:351
msgid "Find and defeat the Orcish Sovereign"
msgstr "Atopa e derrota ao Soberano Orco"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:362
msgid ""
"Konrad can only recruit or recall during this scenario’s first turn. Next "
"turn, Fagh-mok will sneak all your units into the center of the orcish camp."
msgstr ""
"Konrad só pode recrutar ou chamar durante o primeiro turno deste escenario. "
"No seguinte turno, Fagh-mok levará furtivamente todas as túas unidades ao "
"centro do campamento orco."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:368
msgid ""
"Konrad’s soldiers are disguised. They will be permanently revealed after any "
"soldier moves adjacent to an enemy."
msgstr ""
"Os soldados de Konrad están disfrazados. Revelaranse permanentemente despois "
"de que calquera soldado se mova xunto a un inimigo."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:396
msgid ""
"Just you? You’re going alone? ...fine, pick a wagon, get in, and hide under "
"the hay. My goblins will sneak you inside."
msgstr ""
"Só ti? Vas só? ...ben, escolle unha carreta, métete e escóndete debaixo do "
"palla. Os meus trasnos meterante dentro ás agachadas."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:405
msgid ""
"Ready? Pick a wagon, get in, and hide under the hay. Harness your animals to "
"the front. My goblins will sneak you all inside."
msgstr ""
"Preparado/a? Escolle unha carreta, métete dentro e escóndete debaixo do feo. "
"Agarra os teus animais para ir diante. Os meus trasnos meteránvos dentro ás "
"agachadas."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:415
msgid ""
"Ready? Pick a wagon, get in, and hide under the hay. Yes, even that big rock "
"thing. My goblins will sneak you all inside."
msgstr ""
"Preparado/a? Escolle unha carreta, métete e escóndete debaixo do palla. Si, "
"mesmo esa gran cousa de pedra. Os meus trasnos meteránvos dentro ás "
"agachadas."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:425
msgid ""
"Ready? Pick a wagon, get in, and hide under the hay. Err... maybe we can "
"find something less flammable than hay to cover up that fire thing."
msgstr ""
"Preparado/a? Escolle unha carreta, métete dentro e escóndete debaixo do "
"feno. Eh... quizais poidamos atopar algo menos inflamable que o feno para "
"tapar esa cousa do lume."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:434
msgid ""
"Ready? Pick a wagon, get in, and hide under the hay. My goblins will sneak "
"you all inside."
msgstr ""
"Preparado/a? Escolle unha carreta, métete dentro e escóndete debaixo do feo. "
"Os meus trasnos meteránvos dentro ás agachadas."

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:512
msgid "Wagons at the gate!"
msgstr "Carros á porta!"

#. [message]: role=gate_speaker
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:517
msgid ""
"That you, Razgob? Glad to see you’re bringing pillage with you this time."
msgstr "Es ti, Razgob? Alégrome de ver que traes o botín contigo esta vez."

#. [message]: role=gate_speaker
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:522
msgid ""
"That you, Razgob? Big load of pillage you’ve brought with you this time."
msgstr ""
"Es ti, Razgob? Trouxeches contigo esta vez unha gran cantidade de botín."

#. [message]: role=wagon1
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:527
msgid "Wagon Driver"
msgstr "Condutor de carro"

#. [message]: role=wagon1
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:529
msgid "(shaking) *squeak*"
msgstr "(tremendo) *chíu*"

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:533
msgid ""
"Stupid runtling, quit trembling! What’re you so afraid of? Go on through and "
"get everything to the stockpiles."
msgstr ""
"Estúpido ruxido, deixa de tremer! De que tes tanto medo? Continúa e leva "
"todo ás reservas."

#. [hides]: id=disguised
#. ability given to a wagon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:563
msgid "disguised"
msgstr "disfrazado"

#. [hides]: id=disguised
#. ability given to a wagon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:565
msgid "This unit’s mundane exterior conceals assassins within."
msgstr "O exterior mundano desta unidade agocha asasin@s no seu interior."

#. [message]: speaker=$spotter_id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:618
msgid ""
"Hey, I think there’s someone hiding inside this wagon! Let’s chase away the "
"driver and break it apart!"
msgstr ""
"Ei, creo que hai alguén agochado dentro deste vagón! Imos escorrentar o "
"condutor e desfacelo!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#. this is the same orc who let Konrad's soldiers in
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:634
msgid "It’s a spy! Which one of you grunts let that worm into our camp?!"
msgstr ""
"É un espía! Cal de vós, gruñidores, deixou entrar ese verme no noso "
"campamento?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:638
msgid ""
"We’re under attack! Check the other wagons! Grab your swords and kill "
"anything that looks out of place!"
msgstr ""
"¡Estamos baixo ataque! Revisa os outros carros! Colle as túas espadas e mata "
"todo o que pareza fóra de lugar!"

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#. [event]
#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:649
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:949
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:954
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:990
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1005
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/bigmap.cfg:77
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/unified_characters.cfg:37
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/unified_characters.cfg:452
msgid "Konrad"
msgstr "Konrad"

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:651
msgid ""
"They’re getting ready for battle! We have to defeat the chief before we’re "
"overwhelmed."
msgstr ""
"Estánse preparando para a batalla! Temos que derrotar ao xefe antes de que "
"nos acurruren."

#. [message]: role=arshag_wolf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:780
msgid "Grrrr! Arf!"
msgstr "Grrrr! Arf!"

#. [message]: speaker=Arshag
#. Arshag is talking to his pet wolf, in the same way that a modern human might talk to a dog
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:785
msgid ""
"Who’s a good girl? Are you a good girl? Are you ready to feast on the bones "
"of our enemies?"
msgstr ""
"Quen é unha boa rapaza? Es ti unha boa rapaza? Estás preparada para festexar "
"cos ósos dos nosos inimigos?"

#. [message]: role=arshag_wolf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:789
msgid "Arf! Arf! Woof!"
msgstr "¡Arf! ¡Arf! ¡Buf!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader3b
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:804
msgid ""
"Hurry on past, goblin. I don’t want your stench in my nose while I’m trying "
"to eat."
msgstr ""
"Pasa de présa, trasno. Non quero o teu fedor no meu nariz mentres intento "
"comer."

#. [message]: role=nw_gold_guard
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:821
msgid ""
"That last raid was great! I can’t believe the queen is still finding rebel "
"villages for us to plunder!"
msgstr ""
"Esa última incursión foi xenial! Non podo crer que a raíña aínda estea "
"buscando aldeas rebeldes para que as saqueemos!"

#. [message]: role=nw_gold_guard
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:825
msgid ""
"Just look at this pile of gold I’ve pillaged! I hope nobody steals my loot "
"while I’m not looking..."
msgstr ""
"Mirade esta morea de ouro que saqueei! Espero que ninguén me roube o botín "
"mentres eu non estea mirando..."

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:841
msgid ""
"There are caged animals here, many bearing the brand of a chief. They don’t "
"look very well cared for."
msgstr ""
"Hai animais en gaiolas aquí, moitos levan a marca dun xefe. Non parecen "
"estar moi ben coidados."

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:845
msgid ""
"Let us lift the latch on their fence gate, then quietly leave before anybody "
"notices..."
msgstr ""
"Levantemos o pestillo da súa porta da cerca e marchemos tranquilamente antes "
"de que ninguén se decate..."

#. [message]: role=boar_speaker
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:863
msgid ""
"Chief! Chief! Someone opened the pasture gate! Your prize pigs are running "
"free!"
msgstr ""
"Xefe! Xefe! Alguén abriu a porta do pasto! Os teus porcos premiados corren "
"libres!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:867
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Imbiciles! You three, go guard the pen and find my pigs. When I find out "
#| "who was responsible..."
msgid ""
"Imbeciles! You three, go guard the pen and find my pigs. When I find out who "
"was responsible..."
msgstr ""
"Imbéciles! Vós tres, ide vixiar o curro e atopade os meus porcos. Cando "
"descubra quen foi o responsable..."

#. [message]: speaker=leader3
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:917
msgid ""
"Argh, this place is so boring! Why am I stuck guarding this dumb valley "
"instead of going out on raids? I wish something exciting would finally "
"happen..."
msgstr ""
"Argh, este lugar é tan aburrido! Por que estou atrapado vixilando este val "
"tolo en vez de saír de asaltos? Oxalá por fin aconteza algo emocionante..."

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:933
msgid "Hey, what’re you goblins doing back here? Get lost!"
msgstr "Ei, que facedes aquí atrás, trasnos? Despídevos!"

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:950
msgid "Look at all those weapons! This must be one of their armories."
msgstr "Mira todas esas armas! Debe ser un dos seus arsenais."

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:955
msgid ""
"If we can sabotage some without waking that goblin guard, we’ll make it "
"harder for their chief to recruit fighters and respond to our attack."
msgstr ""
"Se podemos sabotar a algúns sen espertar a ese garda trasno, "
"dificultarémoslle ao seu xefe recrutar guerreiros e responder ao noso ataque."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:965
msgid "The Orcish Sovereign’s gold has been reduced to 0."
msgstr "O ouro do soberano orco reduciuse a 0."

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:982
msgid ""
"Where’s that useless worm Fagh-Mok? He’s supposed to take orders from me! "
"But he’s been acting suspiciously lately, and now I can’t find him at all."
msgstr ""
"Onde está ese verme inútil, Fagh-Mok? ¡Debe recibir ordes de min! Pero "
"ultimamente anda a comportarse de xeito sospeitoso, e agora non o atopo en "
"ningún sitio."

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:986
msgid ""
"I’ll be watching him. He’d better not try anything funny or I’ll chop his "
"head off!"
msgstr ""
"Estarei vixiándoo. Será mellor que non intente nada raro ou lle cortarei a "
"cabeza!"

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:991
msgid "That must be the orcish chief. He’s the one we need to kill."
msgstr "Ese debe ser o xefe orco. É a el a quen temos que matar."

#. [message]: role=wagon1 {OR id=Konrad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1006
msgid ""
"We have reached an orcish keep, but our army is still outside. Any attempt "
"to bring them in would only give the orcs time to deploy more soldiers "
"against us."
msgstr ""
"Chegamos a un castelo orco, pero o noso exército aínda está fóra. Calquera "
"intento de traelos só lles daría tempo aos orcos para despregar máis "
"soldados contra nós."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1030
msgid ""
"You idiot! What’re you doing back here?! You’re supposed to be fighting the "
"chief!"
msgstr "Idiota! Que fas aquí atrás?! Debes estar loitando co xefe!"

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1036
msgid "Get back in there or our deal’s off!"
msgstr "Volta aí ou o noso trato cancelouse!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#. referring to the events from the final scenario of Asheviere's Dogs. Khargol wasn't a named character in that campaign, but perhaps he was one of the random grunts
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1052
msgid ""
"You! You’re that wizard from the battle at Dan’Tonk! The one who did the "
"storm and the lightning."
msgstr ""
"Ti! Ti es ese mago da batalla de Dan'Tonk! O que fixo a tormenta e o raio."

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#. Bazur is an orcish warrior, and the main character of Asheviere's Dogs.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1057
msgid ""
"Bazur always said he wanted a chance to kill you. Now I’ll do what he never "
"could!"
msgstr ""
"Bazur sempre dicía que quería ter unha oportunidade para matarte. Agora "
"farei o que el nunca puido!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1061
msgid ""
"Those were dark days. Today I end your rule as I shall one day end "
"Asheviere’s!"
msgstr ""
"Aqueles foron días escuros. Hoxe remato co teu reinado, así como un día "
"rematarei co de Asheviere!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1072
msgid ""
"Hey! Do you see that? That’s the thing the queen told us to watch out for!"
msgstr "Ei! Vés iso? Iso é o que a raíña nos dixo que tivésemos coidado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1076
msgid "The Sceptre of Fire! Get it!"
msgstr "O Cetro de Fogo! Consígueo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1087
msgid "Weakling invaders! I’ll kill you all!"
msgstr "Invadores frouxos! Matareivos a todos!"

#. [message]: role=arshag_wolf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1102
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "<i>whimper whimper whimper</i>"
msgid "whimper whimper whimper"
msgstr "<i>lamentación lamentación lamentación</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Arshag
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1106
#, fuzzy
msgid "You’ll pay for that!"
msgstr "Meus prisioneiros!! Pagarás por iso..."

#. [message]: speaker=Arshag
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1114
msgid "These foes are beyond my strength!"
msgstr "Estes inimigos están máis alá da miña forza!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader3
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1122
msgid "Filthy pinkskins!"
msgstr "Pieles rosas inmundas!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1130
msgid "Curse you all!"
msgstr "Maldición para todos vós!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader6
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1138
msgid "Gah!!"
msgstr "Gah!!"

#. [message]: speaker=Khargol
#. Konrad may not have struck the finishing blow, but it'll be either him or one of his soldiers
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1152
msgid ""
"Impossible! Arr, how shameful to die at the hands of some stupid assassins..."
msgstr "Imposible! Arr, que vergoñoso morrer a mans duns estúpidos asasinos..."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1162
msgid "Gado-har"
msgstr "Gado-har"

#. [message]: speaker=leader3
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1167
msgid "Khargol’s dead! The assassins killed our chief!"
msgstr "Khargol está morto! Os asasinos mataron o noso xefe!"

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1177
msgid ""
"Now is my chance! Set me free, girl, so I can take command of the horde!"
msgstr ""
"Agora é a miña oportunidade! Libérame, rapaza, para que poida tomar o mando "
"da horda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1181
msgid ""
"Set you free? Nice try. You’re not getting out of that cage until Konrad "
"returns."
msgstr "Liberarte? Bo intento. Non sairás desa gaiola ata que volva Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1187
msgid ""
"Stupid girl, you think the other orcs are just going to let him walk out? I "
"must take command. Set me free or your friends all die!"
msgstr ""
"Rapaza estúpida, cres que os outros orcos o van deixar marchar? Debo tomar o "
"mando. Libérame ou morren todos os teus amigos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1191
msgid "Rrr... insufferable. I don’t know how Mother stands working with orcs."
msgstr "Mrrr... insoportable. Non sei como soporta a nai traballar con orcos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1195
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Go. But don’t dare betray us, or I swear to personally find you and kill "
#| "you. If you know anything about me, you’ll know that’s a promise I can "
#| "keep."
msgid ""
"Go. But don’t you dare betray us, or I swear to personally find you and kill "
"you. If you know anything about me, you’ll know that’s a promise I can keep."
msgstr ""
"Vaite. Pero non te atrevas a traizoarnos, ou xuro que te atoparei "
"persoalmente e te matarei. Se sabes algo sobre min, saberás que é unha "
"promesa que podo cumprir."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1215
msgid "Assassins! I’ll get them!"
msgstr "Asasinos! Vou collelos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1220
msgid "You?! What??"
msgstr "Ti?! Que??"

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1226
msgid "Play dead, you idiot."
msgstr "Fai o morto, parvo."

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1245
msgid ""
"Look, everyone! I have slain the invaders and avenged the murder of our "
"chief!"
msgstr "Mirade todos! Matei os invasores e vinguei o asasinato do noso xefe!"

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1251
msgid ""
"As head of Khargol’s personal guard, is only right that I assume the late "
"chief’s duties! Long live chief Fagh-mok the Amazing!"
msgstr ""
"Como xefe da garda persoal de Khargol, é xusto que asuma as funcións do "
"defunto xefe! Longa vida ao xefe Fagh-mok o Incrible!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1259
msgid "Akhir"
msgstr "Akhir"

#. [message]: speaker=Arshag
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1264
msgid ""
"Fagh-mok? You?! You’re weak! You were nothing more than the chief’s sword-"
"carrier!"
msgstr "Fagh-mok? Ti?! Es débil! Non eras máis que o espadachín do xefe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Arshag
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1268
msgid ""
"No, I should be chief instead! Khargol respected me most of all! I followed "
"him from the beginning!"
msgstr ""
"Non, eu debería ser o xefe! Khargol respectábame por riba de todo! Seguino "
"dende o principio!"

#. [message]: speaker=leader3
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1273
msgid ""
"No, I should be chief! My warriors are the bravest, and I am the strongest "
"warrior of all!"
msgstr ""
"Non, eu debería ser o xefe! Os meus guerreiros son os máis valentes, e eu "
"son o guerreiro máis forte de todos!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1277
msgid "Bovrir"
msgstr "Bovrir"

#. [message]: speaker=leader4
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1282
msgid ""
"Strongest?! I could kill both you AND that ingrate Fagh-Mok, with one hand "
"tied behind my back!"
msgstr ""
"O máis forte?! Podería matarte a ti E a ese ingrato Fagh-Mok, cunha man "
"atada ás costas!"

#. [message]: speaker=faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1289
msgid "Oh yeah? Come here and try it, you worthless sack of slime!"
msgstr "Ah, si? Ven aquí e próbao, saco de lama sen valor!"

#. [message]: speaker=Arshag
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1293
msgid ""
"I say we kill all three of ’em! Warriors, fight to make me chief and I "
"promise to bathe you all in gold and blood!"
msgstr ""
"Digo que os matemos aos tres! Guerreiros, loitade para facerme xefe e "
"prometo bañarvos a todos en ouro e sangue!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1325
msgid "Hail, Li’sar! I return!"
msgstr "Saúdos, Li'sar! Volvín!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1329
msgid ""
"The orcich camp echoes with shouts and screams. I take it Fagh-Mok’s bid to "
"become chief has not gone according to plan?"
msgstr ""
"O campamento orco resoa con berros e alaridos. Supoño que a candidatura de "
"Fagh-Mok para converterse en xefe non foi segundo o planeado?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1333
msgid ""
"Not exactly, no. But at least he held up his end of the bargain, and we "
"ours. Chief Khargol is dead, and until the Whitefangs resolve their "
"succession crisis they’ll be of no aid to Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Non exactamente, non. Pero polo menos cumpriu a súa parte do trato, e nós a "
"nosa. O xefe Khargol está morto, e ata que os Dentes Brancos resolvan a súa "
"crise de sucesión non serán de axuda para Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/42_A_Crisis_of_Leadership.cfg:1337
msgid ""
"Then we’ve accomplished what we set out to do. Onwards to the next battle."
msgstr ""
"Entón cumprimos o que nos propuxemos facer. Adiante cara á próxima batalla."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:21
msgid "scenario name^Cliffs of Thoria"
msgstr "Penedos de Thoria"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:49
msgid "Drakes"
msgstr "Drakes"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:124
msgid "There is 80 gold lying in a cove at the bottom of this waterfall!"
msgstr "Hai 80 de ouro nunha cala ao pé desta fervenza!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:207
msgid ""
"All is quiet. Whatever fight was happening here, it ended before we could "
"intervene."
msgstr ""
"Todo está en silencio. Sexa cal for a pelexa que estivese a suceder aquí, "
"rematou antes de que puidésemos intervir."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:214
msgid ""
"And the outcome is no mystery — there is a small fleet of boats shattered "
"among the river islands! I shall send a scout to investigate."
msgstr ""
"E o resultado non é ningún misterio: hai unha pequena frota de barcos "
"esnaquizados entre as illas fluviais! Enviarei un explorador para investigar."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:228
msgid ""
"And the outcome is no mystery — there is a small fleet of boats shattered "
"among the river islands! I shall send my familiar to investigate."
msgstr ""
"E o resultado non é ningún misterio: hai unha pequena frota de barcos "
"esnaquizados entre as illas fluviais! Enviarei o meu familiar para "
"investigar."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:244
msgid ""
"Curious. The wrecks are not of proper ships, but of shallow-draft rafts "
"built only recently; much of their timber is green. Those that were not "
"capsized have been burned. And most curious of all — all flew the banner of "
"Wesnoth."
msgstr ""
"Curioso. Os restos non son de barcos de verdade, senón de balsas de pouco "
"calado construídas recentemente; gran parte da súa madeira é verde. As que "
"non viron foron queimadas. E o máis curioso de todo é que todas ondeaban o "
"estandarte de Wesnoth."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:248
msgid ""
"Wesnoth! There is only one army of Wesnoth in these lands, and it is the one "
"which I led here to fight you. These must be survivors from the volcano!"
msgstr ""
"Wesnoth! Só hai un exército de Wesnoth nestas terras, e é o que eu lideréi "
"ata aquí para loitar contra vós. Estes deben ser superviventes do volcán!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:252
msgid "I’m afraid they don’t seem to be survivors any longer, Li’sar."
msgstr "Temo que xa non parezan ser superviventes, Li’sar."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:261
msgid "Keh Ohn"
msgstr "Keh Ohn"

#. [message]: speaker=Keh Ohn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:269
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Interlopers from the Domain of Men!\n"
#| "Heed this warning for it is the last I shall offer your kind —\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Seek no further tresspass of our land across this river.\n"
#| "Lest you reach only that same end as they who did so before you."
msgid ""
"Interlopers from the Domain of Men!\n"
"Heed this warning for it is the last I shall offer your kind —\n"
"\n"
"Seek no further trespass of our land across this river.\n"
"Lest you reach only that same end as they who did so before you."
msgstr ""
"Intrusos do Dominio dos Homes!\n"
"Prestade atención a esta advertencia porque é a última que lles ofrecerei á "
"vosa especie.\n"
"\n"
"Non busquedes máis acceso á nosa terra a través deste río.\n"
"Para que non cheguedes só ao mesmo fin que aqueles que o fixeron antes de "
"vós."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:277
msgid ""
"A drake! So the winged figures we saw fighting were drakes. You are the ones "
"who destroyed this flotilla?"
msgstr ""
"Un dragón! Entón, as figuras aladas que vimos loitando eran dragóns. Vós "
"sodes os que destruístes esta flotilla?"

#. [message]: speaker=Keh Ohn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:281
msgid ""
"We are.\n"
"\n"
"For in violation of our Ways, they harvested game from our Domain.\n"
"Then... they took the eggs of drakes... our eggs... as prey.\n"
"\n"
"For such an act, I should grant no leniency.\n"
"Yet long ago, my ancestors once made similar transgressions against your "
"kind.\n"
"So I grant you, who were not directly responsible, your lives.\n"
"Now go."
msgstr ""
"Somos. Porque, en violación das nosas Leis, colleitaron presas no noso "
"Dominio. Logo... colleron os ovos dos drakes... os nosos ovos... como presa. "
"Por tal acto, non debería conceder ningunha clemencia. Con todo, hai moito "
"tempo, os meus antepasados cometeron transgresións semellantes contra a vosa "
"estirpe. Así que vos concedo, a vós que non estades directamente "
"responsables, as vosas vidas. Agora marchade."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:293
msgid ""
"The soldiers consumed drake eggs? I cannot imagine anyone would be fool "
"enough to do such a thing, unless unknowingly or in extreme starvation. I "
"fear this has been a terrible misunderstanding."
msgstr ""
"¿Consumiron os soldados ovos de pato macho? Non podo imaxinar a ninguén tan "
"tolo como para facer algo así, a non ser que o fixese sen sabelo ou nunha "
"fame extrema. Temo que isto foi un terrible malentendido."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:297
msgid ""
"The men I trained are skilled and tenacious. If it was possible to survive, "
"they will have. We will go, drake, but you will first turn over any "
"prisoners and allow us to search the river for survivors."
msgstr ""
"Os homes que adestrei son hábiles e tenaces. Se fose posible sobrevivir, "
"sobrevivirían. Iremos, Drake, pero primeiro entregarás os prisioneiros e "
"permitiranos buscar sobreviventes no río."

#. [message]: speaker=Keh Ohn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:301
msgid ""
"Their lives are forfeit.\n"
"All who have preyed upon our young, we shall destroy.\n"
"The matter is decided.\n"
"My decision, final."
msgstr ""
"As súas vidas están perdidas. A todos os que se alimentaron dos nosos mozos, "
"destruíremos. O asunto está decidido. A miña decisión é definitiva."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:308
msgid ""
"Foul dragon, the decision was never yours to make! If but one soldier of "
"Wesnoth has survived then I am coming to his rescue. Stand in my way only if "
"you seek to do battle."
msgstr ""
"Dragón malvado, a decisión nunca foi túa! Se un só soldado de Wesnoth "
"sobreviviu, entón vou ao seu rescate. Só te interpoñas no meu camiño se "
"queres loitar."

#. [message]: speaker=Keh Ohn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:312
msgid "So be it, fellow contender."
msgstr "Así sexa, compañeiro aspirante."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:322
msgid "Find the survivor near the southeast corner of the map."
msgstr "Atopa o sobrevivente preto da esquina sueste do mapa."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:329
msgid "Then, escort him towards the west edge of the map."
msgstr "Entón, escórtao cara ao bordo oeste do mapa."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:337
msgid "Reach Warven, then escort him towards the west edge of the map."
msgstr "Chega a Warven e escóltao cara ao extremo oeste do mapa."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:346
msgid "Escort Warven west to the marked hexes."
msgstr "Escolta a Warven cara ao oeste ata os hexágonos marcados."

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:353
msgid "Death of Warven"
msgstr "Morte de Warven"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:368
msgid ""
"Warven will remain under player control until the end of the scenario, but "
"will join Li’sar’s side in future scenarios."
msgstr ""
"Warven permanecerá baixo o control do xogador ata o final do escenario, pero "
"se unirá ao bando de Li'sar en futuros escenarios."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:383
msgid ""
"I don’t see any enemy keep on the river, but it’s littered with crude "
"dwellings. We should break down the drakish villages to stop them rallying "
"more fighters."
msgstr ""
"Non vexo ningún inimigo no río, pero está cheo de vivendas rudimentarias. "
"Deberíamos derrubar as aldeas dracas para evitar que reúnan máis combatentes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:403
msgid ""
"There is a cataract ahead. By the thunder of the water and the height of the "
"spume, it must drop several hundred feet at least! To try to sail past this "
"would be suicide."
msgstr ""
"Hai unha catarata por diante. Pola estrondo da auga e pola altura da escuma, "
"debe caer polo menos varios centos de pés! Intentar navegar máis aló sería "
"suicidio."

#. [message]: speaker=Keh Ohn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:417
msgid "GRRROOOOAAAAR!"
msgstr "GRRR ..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:423
msgid "Huzzah! We’ve killed their leader!"
msgstr "¡Hurra! Matamos ao seu líder!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:428
msgid ""
"Our dominant is slain!\n"
"Gliders, send word to the first intendant of his ascension by fate."
msgstr ""
"O noso dominante foi asasinado! Planadores, avisade ao primeiro intendente "
"da súa ascensión por destino."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:451
msgid ""
"We’ve slain one of the drakes! Their biology is... wow, incredibly strange — "
"yes, I think there must be some magic in them."
msgstr ""
"Matamos un dos dragóns! A súa bioloxía é... vaia, incriblemente estraña — "
"si, creo que debe haber algo de maxia neles."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:455
msgid ""
"With more specimens, I’m sure I could learn something practical. If you "
"could kill, say, err, thirty drakes — not including this one, that is — then "
"I’m sure their fire could show me how to improve my flashpowder."
msgstr ""
"Con máis especímenes, estou seguro de que podería aprender algo práctico. Se "
"puideses matar, digamos, eh, trinta drakes — non incluíndo este, é dicir — "
"entón estou seguro de que o seu lume podería amosarme como mellorar o meu "
"flashpowder."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:476
msgid ""
"That’s fifteen drakes you’ve defeated. I’m already learning so much from "
"dissecting the corpses! Fifteen more and I’m sure I’ll learn something "
"practical."
msgstr ""
"Son quince dragóns os que derrotaches. Xa estou aprendendo moito "
"diseccionando os cadáveres! Quince máis e seguro que aprenderei algo "
"práctico."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:486
msgid ""
"Oh, wow, you defeated all thirty drakes I asked for! These are just... "
"absolutely amazing! Such fascinating creatures! Did you know that each wing "
"contains upwards of seven major arteries?"
msgstr ""
"Vau, derrotaches os trinta dragóns que che pedín! Son simplemente... "
"absolutamente incribles! Unhas criaturas fascinantes! Sabías que cada á "
"contén máis de sete arterias principais?"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:490
msgid ""
"Err, and, well, of course I’ve extracted some particular reagents that could "
"be useful on the battlefield as well. As promised."
msgstr ""
"Eh, e, bueno, por suposto que extraín algúns reactivos concretos que tamén "
"poderían ser útiles no campo de batalla. Como prometín."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:522
msgid ""
"Good, we’ve destroyed one drake beacon. Each one we raze will make it more "
"difficult for them to rally their fighters."
msgstr ""
"Ben, destruímos un faro de dragóns. Cada un que arrasemos fará que sexa máis "
"difícil para eles reunir os seus guerreiros."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:591
msgid ""
"Look! I see someone at the top of the furthermost cliff! It’s a young human "
"officer, barely more than a boy. He appears badly hurt but still alive."
msgstr ""
"Mira! Vexo a alguén no cumio do cantil máis afastado! É un oficial humano "
"novo, pouco máis que un neno. Parece estar gravemente ferido, pero aínda "
"está vivo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:604
msgid ""
"I wonder why the drakes haven’t finished him by now? It is strange that "
"there are not any drakes in that area."
msgstr ""
"Pregúntome por que os dragóns aínda non o acabaron? É estraño que non haxa "
"ningún dragón nesa zona."

#. [message]: type=Water Serpent,Kraken
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:627
msgid "Grrroar"
msgstr "Grrroar"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:631
msgid "Well... that answers the question."
msgstr "Ben... iso responde á pregunta."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:636
msgid ""
"That young officer is Warven, one of my best lieutenants! He might well be "
"the only survivor of this battle! We must reach him and bring him to safety."
msgstr ""
"Ese mozo oficial é Warven, un dos meus mellores tenentes! Ben podería ser o "
"único sobrevivente desta batalla! Debemos alcanzalo e levalo a un lugar "
"seguro."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:639
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:640
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:641
msgid ""
"Must I remind you that he, like all the others who fought us underground, "
"once tried his utmost to kill us? Will he follow you, or will he choose to "
"betray us to Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Debo lembrarvos que el, como todos os demais que loitaron contra nós na "
"clandestinidade, unha vez fixo todo o posible por matarnos? Seguiravos ou "
"elixirá traizoarnos ante Asheviere?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:642
msgid ""
"I don’t mean to question your judgement, but wasn’t he trying to kill us not "
"so long ago? He’s one of Asheviere’s! Will he follow you, or will he choose "
"to betray us to the dark queen?"
msgstr ""
"Non quero cuestionar o teu xuízo, pero non estaba intentando matarnos hai "
"pouco? É un dos de Asheviere! Seguirate ou escollerá traizoarnos á raíña "
"escura?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:643
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Must I remind you that he, like all the others who fought us underground, "
#| "once tried his utmost to kill us? Will he follow you, or will he choose "
#| "to betray us to Asheviere?"
msgid ""
"What honor is there in the heart of a man who has served Asheviere; who "
"pursued us underground and fought to kill us? Will he follow you, or will he "
"choose to betray us to the dark queen?"
msgstr ""
"Debo lembrarvos que el, como todos os demais que loitaron contra nós na "
"clandestinidade, unha vez fixo todo o posible por matarnos? Seguiravos ou "
"elixirá traizoarnos ante Asheviere?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:644
msgid ""
"Not so long ago he was fightin’ underground and trying his best to kill "
"Konrad. How do you think he’s going to join our alliance now? What if he "
"betrays us to the queen?"
msgstr ""
"Non hai moito tempo loitaba na clandestinidade e facía todo o posible por "
"matar a Konrad. Como cres que se vai unir á nosa alianza agora? E se nos "
"traizoa ante a raíña?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:645
msgid ""
"Forget not that he, like the others who fought us underground, came north "
"with you to kill Konrad. If rescued shall he join our alliance, or shall he "
"betray us to Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Non esquezades que el, coma os outros que loitaron contra nós na "
"clandestinidade, veu ao norte convosco para matar a Konrad. Se o rescatan, "
"unirase á nosa alianza ou traizoaranos a Asheviere?"

#. [companion_message]
#. reference to this fable: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Scorpion_and_the_Frog
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:647
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aye, so said the scorpion to the frog! Dinnae forget, that ninnyhammerin’ "
#| "cad tried to kill Konrad not so long ago, same as all them other chuckle-"
#| "heads who fought us underground! He’ll betray us to Asheveire quick as a "
#| "wink."
msgid ""
"Aye, so said the scorpion to the frog! Dinnae forget, that ninnyhammerin’ "
"cad tried to kill Konrad not so long ago, same as all them other chuckle-"
"heads who fought us underground! He’ll betray us to Asheviere quick as a "
"wink."
msgstr ""
"Si, iso díxolle o escorpión á ra! Non esquezas que ese parvo intentou matar "
"a Konrad non hai moito, igual que todos eses outros parvos que loitaron "
"contra nós na clandestinidade! Traizoaranos a Asheveire nun abrir e pechar "
"de ollos."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:648
msgid ""
"It’s good to save a life and all, of course. But, err, well, you know, "
"wasn’t he fighting underground trying to kill Konrad not too long ago? Is he "
"going to join our alliance? What if he betrays us to Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Está ben salvar unha vida e todo iso, por suposto. Pero, eh, bueno, xa "
"sabes, non estaba loitando na clandestinidade intentando matar a Konrad non "
"hai moito? Unirase á nosa alianza? E se nos traizoa con Asheviere?"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:649
msgid ""
"Dosh don’t think dat be so smart. He was unnerground tryin’ to kill Konrad "
"not too long ago, wasn’t he? Now we want to help him? Dosh thinks he’ll run "
"quick as a wink back to dat queen, an’ we’ll be all da worse for it."
msgstr ""
"Non lle parece tan listo. Estaba na clandestinidade intentando matar a "
"Konrad non hai moito, non si? Agora queremos axudalo? Cre que correrá coma "
"un guiño de volta onde está a raíña, e que seremos todos peores por iso."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:650
msgid ""
"Do not forget that he, like all the others who fought us underground, once "
"tried his utmost to kill me. Will he follow you, or will he choose to betray "
"us to Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Non esquezas que el, como todos os demais que loitaron contra nós na "
"clandestinidade, unha vez fixo todo o posible por matarme. Seguirache ou "
"elixirá traizoarnos ante Asheviere?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#. "you people" refers to the last speaker - one of Konrad's many possible companions. Kalenz, Chantal, Haldiel, Elrian, Seimus, Harper, Moremirmu, Ulfdain, Jeniver, or Dosh.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:658
msgid ""
"Perhaps he did come to kill you, but he’s loyal to me and did so only at my "
"orders. I don’t question you people who Konrad chooses to put his trust in — "
"please don’t question mine."
msgstr ""
"Se cadra veu a matarte, pero é leal a min e só o fixo por orde miña. Non "
"cuestiono en quen Konrad decide confiar; por favor, non cuestionedes a miña."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:664
msgid ""
"Perhaps he did come to kill you, but he’s loyal to me and did so only at my "
"orders. You can trust him."
msgstr ""
"Se cadra veu para matarte, pero é leal a min e só o fixo por orde miña. "
"Podes confiar nel."

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:685
msgid "Who... who are you? A friend or a foe?"
msgstr "Quen... quen es ti? Un amigo ou un inimigo?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:689
msgid ""
"We are friends. Don’t worry about it and don’t try to fight us — you are in "
"no condition to fight."
msgstr ""
"Somos amigos. Non te preocupes por iso e non intentes loitar contra nós — "
"non estás en condicións de loitar."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:693
msgid ""
"Welcome back to the fold, young lieutenant. Let’s get you to the healers."
msgstr "Benvido de novo ao grupo, xove tenente. Imos levarte aos curadores."

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:697
msgid ""
"General Li’sar — here? Praise Haldric, you’re alive! But... what you doing "
"in league with the false prince?"
msgstr ""
"Xeneral Li’sar... aquí? Alabado sexa Haldric, estás vivo! Pero... que fas "
"aliado co falso príncipe?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:701
msgid "Call it a change of heart. You swore an oath to me. Will you follow us?"
msgstr "Chámalle un cambio de opinión. Xurachesme un xuramento. Seguirásnos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:705
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Your Highness ...Highnesses, I am yours to command."
msgid "Your Highness... Highnesses, I am yours to command."
msgstr "Vosa Altura... Vossas Alturas, estou ao voso mando."

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:732
msgid ""
"General... Thank you for rescuing me, but the others are in need of help too."
msgstr "Xeneral... Grazas por rescatarme, pero os demais tamén precisan axuda."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:736
msgid "Others? There are more survivors!?"
msgstr "Outros? Hai máis superviventes!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:740
msgid ""
"Yes, Your Highness! We were only the scouts — trying to find a way back "
"home. If I survive this battle, I can lead you upriver to our camp. They’ll "
"be elated to see that you’ve survived."
msgstr ""
"Si, Alteza! Só eramos os exploradores — tentando atopar o camiño de volta a "
"casa. Se sobrevivo a esta batalla, podo guiarche río arriba ata o noso "
"campamento. Estarán encantados de ver que sobreviviches."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:761
msgid ""
"Our foe flees.\n"
"We are victorious."
msgstr ""
"O noso inimigo foxe.\n"
"Somos vitoriosos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:767
msgid "Warven’s made it to safety! Time to leave, everyone."
msgstr "Warven chegou a salvo! É hora de marchar, todos."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:785
msgid ""
"No! Without him we will never find the other survivors. I’ve failed my duty "
"as commander."
msgstr ""
"Non! Sen el nunca atoparemos os outros superviventes. Fallei co meu deber "
"como comandante."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:803
msgid ""
"Even the best healing we can administer is no substitute for rest. We must "
"get Warven to safety before his wounds become too much to bear."
msgstr ""
"Nin sequera a mellor cura que poidamos administrar substitúe o descanso. "
"Debemos levar a Warven a salvo antes de que as súas feridas sexan "
"insoportables."

#. [message]: speaker=Warven
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:810
msgid "Argh... I... can’t—"
msgstr "Argh... eu... non podo—"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/43_Cliffs_of_Thoria.cfg:815
msgid ""
"No! Without him we will never find the other survivors. I’ve failed my men."
msgstr ""
"Non! Sen el nunca atoparemos os outros superviventes. Fallei aos meus homes."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:20
msgid "scenario name^Underground Channels"
msgstr "Canles Subterráneas"

#. [side]: id=leader3, type=Saurian Javelineer
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:117
msgid "Saurians"
msgstr "saurios"

#. [side]: id=Haralamdum, type=Ancient Wose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:166
msgid "Woses"
msgstr "Arboreáns"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:239
msgid ""
"Here we are! Whatever evil lurks within these caves, we shall put an end to "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Aquí estamos! Sexa cal sexa o mal que se agoche nestas covas, acabarémolo."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:251
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:252
msgid "Konrad, do you hear that sound? Look to the north. I wonder if—"
msgstr "Konrad, escoitas ese son? Mira cara ao norte. Pregúntome se..."

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:253
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Whoah, did you hear that? Look north! The trees are moving!"
msgid "Konrad, listen. Do you hear that? The trees are moving in the north!"
msgstr "Uau, escoitaches iso? Mira cara ao norte! As árbores están a moverse!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:254
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Delfador, do you hear that? Look to the north. Woses!"
msgid "Konrad, listen. Do you hear that? Look to the north. Woses!"
msgstr "Delfador, escoitas iso? Mira cara ao norte. Woses!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:255
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:256
msgid "Whoah, did you hear that? Look north! The trees are moving!"
msgstr "Uau, escoitaches iso? Mira cara ao norte! As árbores están a moverse!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:257
msgid "Hark to the north, Konrad! There is movement among the trees!"
msgstr "Escoita cara ao norte, Konrad! Hai movemento entre as árbores!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:258
msgid "Hey, do you hear that? Look north! Th’ trees are moving!"
msgstr "Ei, escoitas iso? Mira cara ao norte! As árbores están a moverse!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:259
msgid "Do you hear that? Is — yes! Yes, look! A wose!"
msgstr "Escoitas iso? É — si! Si, mira! Un wose!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:260
msgid "Hey, Konrad, did you hear dat? I tink dem trees are moving!"
msgstr "Ei, Konrad, escoitáchelo? Creo que as árbores se están movendo!"

#. [companion_message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:261
msgid "Delfador, do you hear that? Look to the north. Woses!"
msgstr "Delfador, escoitas iso? Mira cara ao norte. Woses!"

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. Well, I say. Is that young Master Delfador?
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:272
msgid "Well, I say ... hmm dum har ... young Master Delfador?"
msgstr "Ben, eu digo... hmm dum har... mozo señor Delfador?"

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. So it is! How is the ambassador? He was here just the other day.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:277
msgid ""
"Harum-alam-alam. So it is! Hmm hmm alam ... how is ... hum ... the "
"ambassador? He was here ... hmm ... just the other day."
msgstr ""
"Harum-alam-alam. Así é! Hmm hmm alam... como está... hm... o embaixador? "
"Estivo aquí... hmm... o outro día."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:281
msgid ""
"That was many years ago, I’m afraid. You are the woses who once resided at "
"the Grey Grove? I see you have learned the language of men."
msgstr ""
"Iso foi hai moitos anos, temo. Sodes os woses que outrora residiron no "
"Arboreto Gris? Vexo que aprendistes a lingua dos homes."

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. Hmm, yes. A very useful language. Now these undead... very troubling.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:286
msgid ""
"Hmm ... yes ... alam ... alam dum ... very useful ... language ... yes ... "
"hum ... now these undead ... harum ... very troubling."
msgstr ""
"Hmm... si... alam... alam dum... moi útil... linguaxe... si... hum... agora "
"estes mortos viventes... harum... moi preocupantes."

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. I am sure you could help rid us of these infernal undead. Afterwards, we could perhaps help you too.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:291
msgid ""
"I am sure ... dum hum ... you could help rid us of these ... alam hurum ... "
"infernal undead ... yes, harum-alam-alam. Afterwards, we could perhaps... "
"hmm ... help you too. Har alam dum."
msgstr ""
"Estou seguro... dum hum... poderías axudarnos a librarnos destes... alam "
"hurum... infernais mortos viventes... si, harum-alam-alam. Despois, quizais "
"poidamos... hmm... axudarte tamén. Har alam dum."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:299
msgid "Defeat the undead leader"
msgstr "Derrota o líder non morto"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:304
msgid "Death of Haralamdum"
msgstr "Morte de Haralamdum"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:325
msgid ""
"Konrad, this entrance is nearly flooded, and is too narrow for both our "
"armies to enter. My soldiers and I will search for another way in."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, esta entrada está case inundada e é demasiado estreita para que "
"entren os nosos dous exércitos. Os meus soldados e eu buscaremos outra "
"maneira de entrar."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:339
msgid ""
"It’s so exciting to finally see woses up close! I hear they have a "
"spectacular resistance to poison! Wose sap... curing — yes, if I could just "
"extract a bucket of wose sap I’m certain I could learn their secrets."
msgstr ""
"É tan emocionante ver por fin os woses de preto! Din que teñen unha "
"resistencia espectacular ao veleno! Saiba de wose... curando... si, se tan "
"só puidese extraer un balde de saiba de wose, estou segura de que podería "
"aprender os seus segredos."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:343
msgid ""
"Now, err, well, of course sap extraction would be problematic from a live "
"specimen, them being our allies and all. But, ah, we are on a battlefield. "
"<b><i>We</i></b> don’t have to be the ones doing the cutting."
msgstr ""
"Agora, eh, bueno, por suposto que a extracción de seiva sería problemática "
"dun exemplar vivo, xa que son os nosos aliados e todo iso. Pero, ah, estamos "
"nun campo de batalla. Non <b><i>temos</i></b> que ser nós os que fagamos as "
"podas."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:347
msgid ""
"You’re asking me to help you rob the dead. Don’t you think that’s a bit "
"ghoulish, Jeniver?"
msgstr ""
"Pidesme que te axude a roubar aos mortos. Non cres que iso sexa un pouco "
"macabro, Jeniver?"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:351
msgid ""
"But just imagine the possibilities! I ask you to help me stand next to a "
"wose when it dies. If I can, I’m sure — yes I’m sure I can gather enough sap "
"to begin curing poisons."
msgstr ""
"Pero imaxina as posibilidades! Pídoche que me axudes a estar ao carón dun "
"wose cando morra. Se podo, estou seguro... si, estou seguro de que podo "
"recoller abondo saiba para comezar a curar velenos."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:360
msgid "It’s falling over! Oh, now’s my chance to collect some sap!"
msgstr ""
"Está caendo! Oh, agora é a miña oportunidade de recoller algo de seiva!"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:376
msgid "Antivenom"
msgstr "Antivenom"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:377
msgid "Jeniver has gained the “<i>cures</i>” ability!"
msgstr "Jeniver gañou a habilidade de \" <i>curar</i> \"!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:381
msgid ""
"It works! It works! Oh, I knew it! Now, err, I suppose I’d better quickly "
"get back to the battle before the woses wonder what I was doing with their "
"friend."
msgstr ""
"Funciona! Funciona! Oh, xa o sabía! Agora, eh, supoño que mellor que volva "
"rápido á batalla antes de que os woses se pregunten que estaba facendo co "
"seu amigo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:403
msgid ""
"Everyone ready? Good. Now that Konrad has distracted them from the west, "
"we’ll push in from the east."
msgstr ""
"Todos preparados? Ben. Agora que Konrad os distraeu do oeste, avanzaremos "
"polo leste."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:426
msgid ""
"The river is clean and fresh in this direction. There are no undead to hunt "
"this way."
msgstr ""
"O río está limpo e fresco nesta dirección. Non hai mortos viventes para "
"cazar por este camiño."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:452
msgid "Look, saurians! What business do you have in these caves?"
msgstr "Mirade, saurios! Que tedes nestas covas?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:456
msgid "Fssssh! Ssslay you! Ssslay you all!"
msgstr "Fssssh! Ssslay you! Ssslay you all!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:460
msgid "I don’t think diplomacy will get us far with these ones."
msgstr "Non creo que a diplomacia nos leve lonxe con estes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:475
msgid ""
"The aggressive saurians are vanquished, but the undead are the greater evil "
"here. We must not waver!"
msgstr ""
"Os saurios agresivos están derrotados, pero os mortos viventes son o mal "
"maior aquí. Non debemos vacilar!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:487
msgid "Master. Is away. I guard. I will fight. Until Iliah. Malal returns."
msgstr "Mestre. Está fóra. Eu gardo. Loitarei. Ata que Iliah. Malal volva."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:491
msgid ""
"Your master Malal is gone, you undead fool! Go back to your eternal rest."
msgstr ""
"O teu amo Malal desapareceu, tolo non morto! Volve ao teu descanso eterno."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:495
msgid ""
"Iliah-Malal? That is the lich we fought in the swamp. What would one of his "
"minions be doing here? And why is it so powerful!?"
msgstr ""
"Iliah-Malal? Ese é o lich co que loitamos no pantano. Que estaría facendo "
"aquí un dos seus lacaios? E por que é tan poderoso!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. reference to Eastern Invasion's "Dark Sanctuary" scenario
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:500
msgid ""
"It speaks of guarding — perhaps Malal has a sanctuary hidden somewhere else "
"in these hills. I do not think we have time to search for it, though. "
"Perhaps a task for another hero, another time."
msgstr ""
"Fala de gardar... quizais Malal teña un santuario agochado noutro lugar "
"destas montañas. Non creo que teñamos tempo de buscalo, porén. Quizais sexa "
"unha tarefa para outro heroe, noutro momento."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:518
msgid ""
"There is an old book here, labeled <i>“Isaac Mallat — Journal.”</i> The "
"running water has washed away most of the ink, but one passage is still "
"readable..."
msgstr ""
"Hai aquí un libro vello etiquetado <i>como \"Isaac Mallat — Diario.\"</i> A "
"auga corrente levou a maior parte da tinta, pero aínda se pode ler un "
"pasaxe..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:523
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>—died in my arms. My own brother! He could have been saved!! This "
#| "imbicile king’s quarantine will be the end of us all.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I’m sure I’m not contagious. I’m sure there’s some way to cure it. If I "
#| "sneak out of the village and make my way north to—</i>"
msgid ""
"—died in my arms. My own brother! He could have been saved!! This imbecile "
"king’s quarantine will be the end of us all."
msgstr ""
"<i>—morreu nos meus brazos. O meu propio irmán! Poderíase salvar!! A "
"corentena deste rei imbécil será o fin de todos nós. Estou segura de que non "
"son contaxiosa. Estou segura de que hai algún xeito de curala. Se me "
"escabullo da aldea e vou cara ao norte cara a...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:525
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<i>—died in my arms. My own brother! He could have been saved!! This "
#| "imbicile king’s quarantine will be the end of us all.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I’m sure I’m not contagious. I’m sure there’s some way to cure it. If I "
#| "sneak out of the village and make my way north to—</i>"
msgid ""
"I’m sure I’m not contagious. I’m sure there’s some way to cure it. If I "
"sneak out of the village and make my way north to—"
msgstr ""
"<i>—morreu nos meus brazos. O meu propio irmán! Poderíase salvar!! A "
"corentena deste rei imbécil será o fin de todos nós. Estou segura de que non "
"son contaxiosa. Estou segura de que hai algún xeito de curala. Se me "
"escabullo da aldea e vou cara ao norte cara a...</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. Well done. Very good.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:545
msgid "Har hum har ... hmm ... well ... har alam dum ... good."
msgstr "Har hum har ... hmm ... ben ... har alam dum ... bo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:549
msgid ""
"Those undead will bother you no more, Sir Wose. Will you join us? We march "
"towards Weldyn, to depose the dark queen Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Eses mortos viventes non volverán molestarte, Sir Wose. Uniraste a nós? "
"Marcharemos cara a Weldyn para depoñer á escura raíña Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. March? So hasty. No, we are not soldiers, not at all. And we are not many.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:554
msgid ""
"March? So hasty. Harum-alam-alam ... no, we are not soldiers ... harum ... "
"not at all. And we are not ... hum ... not many."
msgstr ""
"Marzo? Tan apresurado. Harum-alam-alam... non, non somos soldados... "
"harum... en absoluto. E non somos... hum... non moitos."

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:558
msgid "Hmm ... but there was something ... something to help ..."
msgstr "Hmm ... pero había algo ... algo para axudar ..."

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. Oh, yes. The dust.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:564
msgid "Har dum ... oh, yes, the dust."
msgstr "Har dum... oh, si, o po."

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#. Dust carried by a skeleton. Something magical. I put it— where did I put it...
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:569
msgid ""
"Dust carried ... har alam dum ... by a skeleton. Something magical. I put "
"it ... harum ... where did I put it..."
msgstr ""
"Po levado... har alam dum... por un esqueleto. Algo máxico. Puxeno... "
"harum... onde o puxen..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:576
msgid ""
"I see it — a pouch of powdered sapphire! A valuable component for all kinds "
"of spells. I used the last of my supply in the defense of Elensefar, and "
"have sorely missed it since. Thank you for your gift, Haralamdum."
msgstr ""
"Xa o vexo: unha bolsa de zafiro en po! Un compoñente valioso para todo tipo "
"de feitizos. Usei o último das miñas provisións na defensa de Elensefar e, "
"desde entón, bótoo moito de menos. Grazas polo teu agasallo, Haralamdum."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:580
msgid ""
"Konrad, with this I can conjure up powerful earthen elementals. Malal must "
"have stashed it away here. Now it is ours."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, con isto podo conxurar poderosos elementais terrosos. Malal debeu "
"telo agochado aquí. Agora é noso."

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:586
msgid "Delfador can now recruit Granite Golems!"
msgstr "Delfador agora pode reclutar Gólemes de Granito!"

#. [message]: speaker=Haralamdum
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:606
msgid "Harum ... huff ..."
msgstr "Harum... buf..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:612
msgid "The woses have been defeated! The undead have won."
msgstr "Os arboans foron derrotados! Os non mortos venceron."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:627
msgid ""
"We should hurry, Konrad. There are storm clouds on the horizon. If we take "
"too long to finish our battle and it starts to rain, this entire cave system "
"might flood."
msgstr ""
"Deberíamos apurarnos, Konrad. Hai nubes de tormenta no horizonte. Se "
"tardamos demasiado en rematar a nosa batalla e comeza a chover, todo este "
"sistema de covas podería inundarse."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:638
msgid ""
"It’s starting to rain, and these caves are about to flood! The undead can "
"survive underwater, but I can’t. Even the merfolk must surface often for "
"air! We’ll have to break off the attack."
msgstr ""
"Está empezando a chover e estas covas están a piques de inundarse! Os mortos "
"viventes poden sobrevivir baixo a auga, pero eu non. Mesmo as sereas teñen "
"que saír á superficie a miúdo para coller aire! Teremos que interromper o "
"ataque."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/44_Underground_Channels.cfg:643
msgid ""
"It’s starting to rain, and these caves are about to flood! The undead can "
"survive underwater, but I can’t. We’ll have to break off the attack."
msgstr ""
"Está empezando a chover e estas covas están a piques de inundarse! Os mortos "
"viventes poden sobrevivir baixo a auga, pero eu non. Teremos que interromper "
"o ataque."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:8
msgid "scenario name^Test of the Clans"
msgstr "Proba dos Cláns"

#. [side]: type=Grand Knight, id={ID}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:41
msgid "Plainsmen"
msgstr "Homes da chaira"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:203
msgid ""
"The clans are rich and powerful, even under my mother, and their lands are "
"overflowing with stockpiled supplies. We’ll make better use of it than they "
"would."
msgstr ""
"Os clans son ricos e poderosos, mesmo baixo o mando da miña nai, e as súas "
"terras están cheas de subministracións acumuladas. Nós faremos un mellor uso "
"diso que eles."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:258
msgid "Hail, men of the plains! I greet you with a proposal."
msgstr "Saúdo, homes das chairas! Saúdovos cunha proposta."

#. [message]: speaker=Daryn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:262
msgid ""
"What do these intruders want? We did not invite them here, that is certain."
msgstr "Que queren estes intrusos? Non os convidamos aquí, iso é certo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:266
msgid ""
"You know that my late uncle, King Garard II, was a friend of the clans. Your "
"knights made up the cream of his army, and were venerated for their service. "
"What prestige do you plainsmen hold under Asheviere, queen of the cities and "
"employer of orcs?"
msgstr ""
"Sabes que o meu tío finado, o rei Garard II, era amigo dos clans. Os teus "
"cabaleiros formaban a crema do seu exército e eran venerados polo seu "
"servizo. Que prestixio tedes vós, xente das chairas, baixo Asheviere, raíña "
"das cidades e empregadora de orcos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:270
msgid ""
"Join us to overthrow the evil queen, and I will see the clans restored to "
"prominence within the courts of Weldyn. Oppose us, and I will strip you of "
"your power once the throne is rightfully reclaimed."
msgstr ""
"Únete a nós para derrocar á malvada raíña e verei como os clans volven "
"cobrar protagonismo nas cortes de Weldyn. Opóñete a nós e despoxareivos do "
"voso poder unha vez que o trono sexa lexitimamente reclamado."

#. [message]: speaker=Alric
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:276
msgid ""
"Hah! You think you can seize the throne? You who are led by these youths and "
"this old man?"
msgstr ""
"Ha! Cres que podes facerte co trono? Ti, que estás liderado por estes mozos "
"e este vello?"

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:280
msgid ""
"He will confront Asheviere, as he claims. Then he will die. And if we have "
"lent our support it will be all the worse for us."
msgstr ""
"Enfrontarase a Asheviere, como afirma. Despois morrerá. E se lle prestamos o "
"noso apoio, será moito peor para nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:284
msgid ""
"“These youths”, you dare call us? Don’t think me so weak that I cannot prove "
"my worth in pitched battle."
msgstr ""
"«Estes mozos», atreveste a chamarnos? Non me penses tan débil como para non "
"poder demostrar o meu valor nunha batalla campal."

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:288
msgid ""
"Hah! You would challenge us? I accept. Rout our clansmen and we will "
"repudiate the queen. Or otherwise leave now and never return!"
msgstr ""
"Ha! ¿Nos desafiarías? Acepto. Derrotade os nosos membros do clan e "
"repudiaremos á raíña. Ou se non, marchade agora e non volvedes nunca máis!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:292
msgid ""
"If you will not listen to reason, then so be it. Ready your lances, men of "
"the plains!"
msgstr ""
"Se non escoitades a razón, que así sexa. Preparade as vosas lanzas, homes "
"das chairas!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ruga
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:298
msgid "Fools! We will run you down like dogs!"
msgstr "Parvos! Atropelarémosvos coma cans!"

#. [message]: speaker=Daryn
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:302
msgid "There is no turning back for you now. You will not break us!"
msgstr "Agora non hai volta atrás para ti. Non nos romperás!"

