#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:407
msgid ""
"This is sheer madness. We cannot afford to wage war against these clansmen "
"when we should be marching against the Queen..."
msgstr ""
"Isto é pura tolemia. Non podemos permitirnos librar unha guerra contra estes "
"membros dos cláns cando deberiamos marchar contra a Raíña..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:412
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2045
msgid "Lord Bayar, halt this folly! I challenge you to a personal combat."
msgstr "Señor Bayar, detén esta loucura! Desafíote a un combate persoal."

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:416
msgid "Ho! You have amused me, young heir. Ho, ho, challenge indeed."
msgstr "¡Oh! Divertíchesme, mozo herdeiro. ¡Oh, oh, un verdadeiro desafío."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:420
msgid "Young heir? Then you assent to my claim?"
msgstr "Xove herdeiro? Entón asentes á miña pretensión?"

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:424
msgid ""
"Impudence. Bah! Do you see orcs on our plains? Did we not grant you a test "
"of your strength?"
msgstr ""
"Impudencia. Bah! Vedes orcos nas nosas chairas? Non vos concedemos unha "
"proba da vosa forza?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:428
msgid ""
"This is hardly a test. Our battle serves only to spill needless blood and "
"weaken us both."
msgstr ""
"Isto non é nin de lonxe unha proba. A nosa batalla serve só para verter "
"sangue innecesario e debilitarnos a ambos."

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:432
msgid "No, whelp. You may be weakened, but the horse clans are eternal."
msgstr ""
"Non, rapaz. Pode que esteas debilitado, pero os clans dos cabalos son "
"eternos."

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:434
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "No, whelp. You may be weakened, but the horse clans are eternal.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I will promise you this, however. If your forces can defeat me "
#| "personally, I myself will join your cause."
msgid ""
"I will promise you this, however. If your forces can defeat me personally, I "
"myself will join your cause."
msgstr ""
"Non, caramba. Pode que esteas debilitado, pero os clans de cabalos son "
"eternos.\n"
"\n"
"Porén, prométoche isto. Se as túas forzas poden derrotarme persoalmente, eu "
"mesmo unireime á túa causa."

#. [message]: speaker=Ruga
#. [message]: speaker=Daryn
#. [message]: speaker=Alric
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:440
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:444
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:450
msgid "Aye."
msgstr "Si."

#. [message]: id=Haldiel,Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:480
msgid ""
"This is my home, Konrad, and Simyr’s too. Although we were barely men when "
"we left, their Horsemen will still recognize us as kin."
msgstr ""
"Este é o meu fogar, Konrad, e tamén o de Simyr. Aínda que eramos pouco máis "
"ca mozos cando marchamos, os seus Xinetes recoñecerannos como parentes."

#. [message]: id=Haldiel,Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:486
msgid ""
"This is my home, Konrad. Although I was barely a man when I left, their "
"Horsemen will still recognize me as kin."
msgstr ""
"Este é o meu fogar, Konrad. Aínda que era pouco máis ca un mozo cando "
"marchei, os seus Xinetes recoñeceranme como parente."

#. [message]: id=Haldiel,Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:492
msgid ""
"Now that their leaders have offered to join our cause, I believe I can "
"convince their fighters as well. Help me defeat Cavalrymen and Horsemen in "
"combat, and I believe I can persuade them to follow their leaders and join "
"you."
msgstr ""
"Agora que os seus líderes ofreceron unirse á nosa causa, creo que poderei "
"convencer tamén aos seus loitadores. Axúdame a derrotar Cabaleiros e Xinetes "
"en combate, e penso que poderei persuadilos para que sigan aos seus líderes "
"e se unan a ti."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#. said by either Haldiel or Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:521
msgid "I have persuaded this one to join us in the next battle, Konrad."
msgstr "Convencín a este para que se una a nós na próxima batalla, Konrad."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#. said by either Haldiel or Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:529
msgid ""
"This fighter is injured now, but he is willing to join us for our next "
"battle."
msgstr ""
"Este loitador está ferido, pero está disposto a unirse a nós na seguinte "
"batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#. said by either Haldiel or Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:537
msgid "Konrad, I have convinced this fighter to join us in our next battle."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, convencín a este loitador para que se una a nós na próxima batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#. said by either Haldiel or Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:545
msgid ""
"I have spoken with this one, Konrad. He will join us in the next battle."
msgstr "Falei con este, Konrad. Unirase a nós na seguinte batalla."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:609
msgid ""
"How can this be?! You have bested me in combat! Impossible... but true. I "
"will honor my pledge to join your army."
msgstr ""
"Como pode ser isto?! Vencéchesme en combate! Imposible... pero certo. "
"Cumprirei a miña promesa de unirme ao teu exército."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:610
msgid ""
"I cannot believe this! You have defeated me, despite everything. I pledge my "
"lance into your service, young ones."
msgstr ""
"Non podo crer isto! Derrotástesme, a pesar de todo. Comprométovos a miña "
"lanza ao voso servizo, rapaces."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:611
msgid ""
"A heroic battle! Yet in the end I am bested — incredible. I will join you, "
"Konrad and Li’sar."
msgstr ""
"Unha batalla heroica! Porén, ao final son derrotado... incrible. Unireime a "
"vós, Konrad e Li'sar."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:612
msgid ""
"Bah, a humiliating defeat! But a defeat nonetheless. Let it not be said that "
"Sir Rugan is without honor — as agreed, I will join your army."
msgstr ""
"Vaia, unha derrota humillante! Pero unha derrota ao fin e ao cabo. Que non "
"se diga que Sir Rugan carece de honra... como acordamos, unireime ao voso "
"exército."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:648
msgid ""
"We have defeated many foes — the plainsmen’s resolve is shaken! Only a few "
"more and they will surely break."
msgstr ""
"Derrotamos a moitos inimigos — a resolución dos homes das chairas está "
"abalada! Só uns poucos máis e romperán sen dúbida."

#. [message]: role=clanboss
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:665
msgid "Stop! Stop! Our armies can bear this no longer."
msgstr "Para! Para! Os nosos exércitos non poden soportar isto máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:669
msgid "So you admit defeat! You assent to my claim and repudiate Asheviere?"
msgstr ""
"Entón admites a derrota! Aceptas a miña reclamación e repudias a Asheviere?"

#. [message]: role=clanboss
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:673
msgid ""
"Indeed — you have humbled us, bearers of the Sceptre. His and Her Royal "
"Highnesses fighting in tandem... perhaps you truly do have a chance at "
"defeating the great queen."
msgstr ""
"De certo, humillástesnos, portadores do Cetro. Súas Altezas Reais loitando "
"en tándem... quizais teñades de verdade unha oportunidade de derrotar á gran "
"raíña."

#. [message]: role=clanboss
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:677
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The Clans cannot risk all by joining you in your attack on Weldyn, but "
#| "you have proven yourself — neither shall we join Asheviere in "
#| "opposition.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "And as a gesture of goodwill, I instead offer you our warchest; a vast "
#| "reserve of supplies and coin to sustain you on your crusade."
msgid ""
"The Clans cannot risk all by joining you in your attack on Weldyn, but you "
"have proven yourself — neither shall we join Asheviere in opposition."
msgstr ""
"Os clans non poden arriscar todo uníndose a vós no voso ataque a Weldyn, "
"pero xa demostrastes o voso valor; tampouco nós nos uniremos a Asheviere na "
"oposición.\n"
"\n"
"E como xesto de boa vontade, ofrézovos o noso cofre de guerra; unha vasta "
"reserva de subministracións e moedas para sustentarvos na vosa cruzada."

#. [message]: role=clanboss
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:679
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The Clans cannot risk all by joining you in your attack on Weldyn, but "
#| "you have proven yourself — neither shall we join Asheviere in "
#| "opposition.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "And as a gesture of goodwill, I instead offer you our warchest; a vast "
#| "reserve of supplies and coin to sustain you on your crusade."
msgid ""
"And as a gesture of goodwill, I instead offer you our warchest; a vast "
"reserve of supplies and coin to sustain you on your crusade."
msgstr ""
"Os clans non poden arriscar todo uníndose a vós no voso ataque a Weldyn, "
"pero xa demostrastes o voso valor; tampouco nós nos uniremos a Asheviere na "
"oposición.\n"
"\n"
"E como xesto de boa vontade, ofrézovos o noso cofre de guerra; unha vasta "
"reserva de subministracións e moedas para sustentarvos na vosa cruzada."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:684
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Konrad and Lisar have each gained 300 gold!"
msgid "Konrad and Li’sar have each gained 300 gold!"
msgstr "Konrad e Lisar gañaron 300 de ouro cada un!"

#. [message]: role=clanboss
#. "Her" refers to Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:694
msgid ""
"Now go from this place, and fight with courage. Fight Her as ferociously as "
"you have fought us."
msgstr ""
"Agora sae deste lugar e loita con coraxe. Loita contra ela tan ferozmente "
"como loitaches contra nós."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/47_Test_of_the_Clans.cfg:715
msgid ""
"Bah, the Sceptre is but a magic staff. Steel is the true test of a ruler."
msgstr ""
"Bah, o Cetro non é máis ca un bastón máxico. O aceiro é a verdadeira proba "
"dun gobernante."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:10
msgid "scenario name^Dan’Tonk"
msgstr "Dan'Tonk"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:289
msgid ""
"Hello, Isolde. I see my mother’s appointed you regent in Dan’Tonk — "
"congratulations. We were comrades, once. I’m sorry we now find ourselves on "
"opposing sides."
msgstr ""
"Ola, Isolde. Vexo que miña nai te nomeou rexente en Dan'Tonk. Parabéns. "
"Fomos camaradas, unha vez. Síntoo que agora nos atopemos en bandos opostos."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:293
msgid ""
"Hello, Li’sar. I’m sorry too. I never saw you as one to turn against your "
"sovereign; your own kin. ...I suppose it runs in the family."
msgstr ""
"Ola, Li’sar. Eu tamén o sinto. Nunca te vin como alguén que se volva contra "
"o teu soberano; contra a túa propia familia... Supoño que é algo de familia."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:297
msgid ""
"You are bold to march out from behind your walls and meet us on the open "
"plain. Are you not worried we will defeat you?"
msgstr ""
"Es atrevido ao saír das túas murallas e enfrontarnos no campo aberto. Non "
"che preocupa que che derrotemos?"

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:301
msgid ""
"Hmph. My whole life, I’ve wanted to live a peaceful life. But there’s always "
"someone causing problems. First it was Garard, then the baron. Outlaws on "
"the isles, elves in the Aethenwood. Always one more thing."
msgstr ""
"Hmph. Toda a miña vida quixen vivir unha vida pacífica. Pero sempre hai "
"alguén causando problemas. Primeiro foi Garard, despois o barón. Foraxidos "
"nas illas, elfos no Bosque de Aethen. Sempre unha cousa máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:305
msgid ""
"And now it’s you three. At least you had the courtesy to come to my city — "
"your queen’s city — in person. I can vanquish you and your armies all at "
"once."
msgstr ""
"E agora sodes vós tres. Polo menos tivestes a cortesía de vir á miña cidade —"
"a cidade da vosa raíña— en persoa. Podo vencervos a vós e aos vosos "
"exércitos á vez."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:335
msgid "Defeat Isolde"
msgstr "Derrota a Isolde"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:349
msgid ""
"Gryphons will appear periodically near the northwest corner of the map. They "
"aren’t your allies, but will prefer to attack Isolde’s soldiers when given "
"the choice."
msgstr ""
"Os grifos aparecerán periodicamente preto da esquina noroeste do mapa. Non "
"son os teus aliados, pero preferirán atacar os soldados de Isolda cando se "
"lles dea a opción."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:368
msgid "Kraww!!"
msgstr "Que rico!!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:372
msgid "Look, gryphons are attacking soldiers inside the city walls!"
msgstr ""
"Mirade, os grifóns están atacando os soldados dentro das murallas da cidade!"

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:376
msgid "These vermin again. What did that dwarf do to rile them up so badly?!"
msgstr "Estes vermes outra vez. Que fixo ese anano para enfurecelos tanto?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:380
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I suspect they have a particular grudge against the soldiers of Dan’Tonk, "
#| "but we should still do our best to stay our of their way — they remain "
#| "wild animals."
msgid ""
"I suspect they have a particular grudge against the soldiers of Dan’Tonk, "
"but we should still do our best to stay out of their way — they remain wild "
"animals."
msgstr ""
"Sospeito que gardan un rencor particular contra os soldados de Dan'Tonk, "
"pero aínda así deberiamos facer todo o posible por manternos lonxe deles; "
"seguen sendo animais salvaxes."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:420
msgid ""
"Li’sar, as a general of Wesnoth you were surely familiar with Dan’Tonk’s "
"defenses. Do you have any insight into its weaknesses? Is there anything we "
"can use against the general?"
msgstr ""
"Li’sar, como xeneral de Wesnoth seguramente coñecías as defensas de "
"Dan’Tonk. Tes algunha idea das súas debilidades? Hai algo que poidamos usar "
"contra o xeneral?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#. reference to Asheviere's Dogs
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:425
msgid ""
"There was a hidden tunnel, once, but I had it collapsed some years ago. "
"Sorry."
msgstr "Houbo un túnel oculto, pero fíxeno colapsar hai uns anos. Sinto."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:453
msgid "Argh! This is going terribly. Retreat! Retreat!"
msgstr "Argh! Isto vai terriblemente mal. Retirada! Retirada!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:478
msgid ""
"Victory is won. As we expected, Isolde has taken refuge behind the city "
"walls. Her army is defeated, but not broken. We lack the supplies or time to "
"besiege the city proper."
msgstr ""
"A vitoria está gañada. Como agardábamos, Isolde refuxiouse tras as murallas "
"da cidade. O seu exército está derrotado, pero non aniquilado. Non temos "
"abastecementos nin tempo para sitiar a cidade propiamente dita."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:482
msgid ""
"Maybe we don’t need to, Delfador. Power is a fragile thing, and we’ve shown "
"this entire city — a city that once fought against Asheviere — that the "
"queen is not so unbeatable as she once seemed. I do not think Isolde will be "
"able to leave Dan’Tonk again without risking its revolt."
msgstr ""
"Se cadra non precisamos, Delfador. O poder é algo fráxil, e demostrámoslle a "
"toda esta cidade (unha cidade que outrora loitou contra Asheviere) que a "
"raíña non é tan imbatible como parecía antes. Non creo que Isolde poida "
"deixar Dan'Tonk de novo sen arriscarse á súa revolta."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:486
msgid ""
"That, and also I’ll leave a few of my men behind to destroy the roads and "
"harass any sorties. Dan’Tonk won’t pose any problem when we attack Weldyn."
msgstr ""
"Iso, e tamén deixarei algúns dos meus homes atrás para destruír as estradas "
"e acosar calquera incursión. Dan'Tonk non supoñerá ningún problema cando "
"ataquemos Weldyn."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:502
msgid ""
"We’re doing well. If we can keep up the fight for a little longer, I suspect "
"Isolde will be forced to give up the fight."
msgstr ""
"Estamos ben. Se podemos manter a loita un pouco máis, sospeito que Isolde se "
"verá obrigada a darse por vencida."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:509
msgid ""
"You are a more skilled fighter than you look, Konrad. I don’t believe I can "
"defeat you today. It’s time to cut our losses and retreat."
msgstr ""
"Es un loitador máis habilidoso do que aparentas, Konrad. Non creo que poida "
"derrotarte hoxe. É hora de recortar as nosas perdas e retirarnos."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/48_Dan_Tonk.cfg:514
msgid ""
"That’s a poor choice, soldiers. I hope you weren’t planning on ever seeing "
"retirement."
msgstr ""
"Esa é unha mala elección, soldados. Espero que non pensásedes en xubilarvos "
"algún día."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:11
msgid "scenario name^The Battle for Wesnoth"
msgstr "A Batalla polo Noroeste"

