#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1305
msgid "Ack!"
msgstr "Ai!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1311
msgid ""
"That guard was carrying some kind of strange device! Whatever it was, we "
"slew him with such a mighty blow that he had not the chance to use it."
msgstr ""
"Ese garda levaba algún tipo de estraño dispositivo! Fose o que fose, "
"matámolo cun golpe tan poderoso que non tivo a oportunidade de usalo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1316
msgid ""
"Well done! We slew this guard with such a mighty blow that he had not a "
"chance to destroy his bridge."
msgstr ""
"Ben feito! Derrotamos a este garda cun golpe tan poderoso que non tivo "
"ningunha oportunidade de destruír a súa ponte."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1335
msgid "The fire is getting to the explosive powder! Your Majesty—"
msgstr "O lume está a chegar á pólvora explosiva! Maxestade..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1344
msgid "Argh! Your Majesty... it doesn’t even need to walk..."
msgstr "Argh! Maxestade... nin sequera precisa camiñar..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1349
msgid "Argh! Your Majesty... the plan..."
msgstr "Argh! Vosa Maxestade... o plan..."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1354
msgid "Carry out your orders. Do not disappoint me."
msgstr "Cumpre as túas ordes. Non me decepciones."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1435
msgid "So. After burning half my fields, these rebels come at last to face me."
msgstr ""
"Entón. Despois de queimar a metade dos meus campos, estes rebeldes veñen por "
"fin a enfrontarse a min."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1440
msgid "So, these rebels come at last to face me."
msgstr "Así que, estes rebeldes veñen por fin a enfrontarse a min."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1445
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Surrender, mother. The land’s blood is spent. I have come to take my "
#| "rightful place."
msgid ""
"Surrender, Mother. The land’s blood is spent. I have come to take my "
"rightful place."
msgstr ""
"Ríndete, nai. O sangue da terra está esgotado. Vin ocupar o meu lugar "
"lexítimo."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1449
msgid ""
"Ahh. My own daughter, a turncoat. Such treason my reign must endure! But "
"endure it will."
msgstr ""
"Ahh. A miña propia filla, unha traizón. O meu reinado debe soportar unha "
"traizón semellante! Pero soportaraa."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1453
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "For the walls of Weldyn are strong. And her allies are many! They will "
#| "arrive in days — and then you will die."
msgid ""
"The walls of Weldyn are strong. And her allies are many. They will arrive in "
"days — and then you will die."
msgstr ""
"Porque as murallas de Weldyn son fortes. E os seus aliados son moitos! "
"Chegarán en días, e entón morrerás."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1473
msgid ""
"Knights from the Horse Clans, footmen from Dan’Tonk, and orcish hordes from "
"the north now swollen even further with your mage Mirya’s new recruits. We "
"know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros dos Clans de Cabalos, soldados de infantería de Dan'Tonk e hordas "
"orcas do norte agora inchadas aínda máis cos novos recrutas da túa maga "
"Mirya. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1475
msgid ""
"Knights from the Horse Clans, footmen from Dan’Tonk, and orcish hordes from "
"the north. We know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros dos Clans de Cabalos, soldados de infantería de Dan'Tonk e hordas "
"orcas do norte. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1476
msgid ""
"Knights from the Horse Clans, footmen from Dan’Tonk, and your mage Mirya "
"with her newly-recruited grunts. We know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros dos Clans de Cabalos, soldados de infantería de Dan'Tonk e a vosa "
"maga Mirya cos seus gruñidos recentemente recrutados. Sabémolo e estamos "
"preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1477
msgid ""
"Footmen from Dan’Tonk, orcish hordes from the north, and your mage Mirya "
"with her newly-recruited grunts. We know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Infantes de Dan’Tonk, hordas orcas do norte e a vosa maga Mirya cos seus "
"gruñidos recentemente recrutados. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1478
msgid ""
"Knights from the Horse Clans and orcish hordes from the north, now swollen "
"even further with your mage Mirya’s new recruits. We know, and we are "
"prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros dos Clans de Cabalos e hordas orcas do norte, agora aínda máis "
"numerosas cos novos recrutas da túa maga Mirya. Sabémolo e estamos "
"preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1480
msgid ""
"Knights from the Horse Clans and footmen from Dan’Tonk. We know, and we are "
"prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros dos Clans de Cabalos e soldados de infantería de Dan'Tonk. "
"Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1481
msgid ""
"Footmen from Dan’Tonk and orcish hordes from the north. We know, and we are "
"prepared."
msgstr ""
"Infantes de Dan'Tonk e hordas orcas do norte. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1482
msgid ""
"Knights from Horse Clans and orcish hordes from the north. We know, and we "
"are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros de Clans de Cabalos e hordas orcas do norte. Sabémolo e estamos "
"preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1483
msgid ""
"Footmen from Dan’Tonk and your mage Mirya with her newly-recruited orcs. We "
"know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Infantes de Dan'Tonk e a vosa maga Mirya cos seus orcos recentemente "
"recrutados. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1484
msgid ""
"Knights from the Horse Clans and your mage Mirya with her newly-recruited "
"orcs. We know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Cabaleiros dos Clans dos Cabalos e a vosa maga Mirya cos seus orcos "
"recentemente recrutados. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1485
msgid ""
"Orcish hordes from the north, now swollen even further with your mage "
"Mirya’s new recruits. We know, and we are prepared."
msgstr ""
"Hordas orcas do norte, agora aínda máis numerosas cos novos recrutas da túa "
"maga Mirya. Sabémolo e estamos preparados."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1487
msgid ""
"Fewer than there might have been. Of all your allies, only your mage Mirya "
"and her newly-recruited orcs are still ready to aid you. We did not come "
"here unprepared."
msgstr ""
"Menos dos que poderían haber. De todos os teus aliados, só a túa maga Mirya "
"e os seus orcos recentemente recrutados aínda están listos para axudarte. "
"Non viñemos aquí sen preparación."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1488
msgid ""
"Fewer than there might have been. Of all your allies, only the orcish hordes "
"of the north still stand ready to aid you. We did not come here unprepared."
msgstr ""
"Menos dos que poderían haber. De todos os teus aliados, só as hordas orcas "
"do norte aínda están listas para axudarte. Non viñemos aquí sen preparación."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1489
msgid ""
"Fewer than there might have been. Of all your allies, only the Horse Clans "
"still stand ready to aid you. We did not come here unprepared."
msgstr ""
"Menos dos que poderían haber. De todos os teus aliados, só os Clans dos "
"Cabalos aínda están dispostos a axudarte. Non viñemos aquí sen preparación."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1490
msgid ""
"Fewer than there might have been. Of all your allies, only the footmen of "
"Dan’Tonk still stand ready to aid you. We did not come here unprepared."
msgstr ""
"Menos dos que poderían haber. De todos os teus aliados, só os soldados de "
"Dan'Tonk aínda están dispostos a axudarte. Non viñemos aquí sen preparación."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1492
msgid ""
"What allies, Your Grace? The Horse Clans have turned their backs; Dan’Tonk "
"is barricaded; the orcish clans are embroiled in civil war. Even your mage "
"Mirya is gone. You have nothing more than the forces arrayed before us here."
msgstr ""
"Que aliados, Vosa Graza? Os Cláns Ecuestres deron a espalda; Dan'Tonk está "
"barricado; os cláns orcos están inmersos nunha guerra civil. Ata a súa maga "
"Mirya desapareceu. Non tes nada máis que as forzas que están dispostas "
"diante de nós aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1499
msgid ""
"How long must the people endure your rule, woman? Give the throne to your "
"daughter. She is the rightful heir. We even hold the Sceptre to prove it!"
msgstr ""
"Canto tempo terá que soportar o pobo o teu goberno, muller? Dálle o trono á "
"túa filla. Ela é a lexítima herdeira. Incluso temos o cetro para demostralo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1503
msgid ""
"Delfador! My old tormentor! Treason! Men! Seize them! Kill them! Kill them "
"all!"
msgstr ""
"Delfador! Meu vello atormentador! Traizón! Homes! Atrapádeos! Matádeos! "
"Matádeos a todos!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1511
msgid "Defeat Asheviere"
msgstr "Derrota a Asheviere"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1530
msgid ""
"It’s you! The dwarf from Gryphon Mountain! I thought you were merely "
"delivering eggs to Asheviere, not fighting for her."
msgstr ""
"Es ti! O anano do Monte Grifón! Pensei que só lle estabas entregando ovos a "
"Asheviere, non loitando por ela."

#. [message]: speaker=Burlin
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1534
msgid "Well, you know what they say: money talks. It’s nothing personal."
msgstr "Ben, xa sabes o que din: o diñeiro fala. Non é nada persoal."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1569
msgid ""
"Their initial attack will be especially powerful, but they will continue "
"reinforcing Asheviere every day or two until she is defeated — or we are."
msgstr ""
"O seu ataque inicial será especialmente poderoso, pero seguirán reforzando a "
"Asheviere cada día ou cada dous días ata que ela sexa derrotada — ou nós o "
"sexamos."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mentoring}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1573
msgid ""
"Each wave of attackers will be ready to move and fight the instant they "
"arrive, so we should be careful not to leave our soldiers exposed near the "
"attackers’ entry points."
msgstr ""
"Cada onda de atacantes estará lista para moverse e loitar no instante en que "
"cheguen, polo que debemos ter coidado de non deixar os nosos soldados "
"expostos preto dos puntos de entrada dos atacantes."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1581
msgid ""
"Konrad, Asheviere’s allies have prepared a follow-up attack! This wave is "
"not especially powerful, but I suspect that each subsequent follow-up will "
"be more deadly than the last."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, os aliados de Asheviere prepararon un ataque de seguimento! Esta "
"onda non é especialmente poderosa, pero sospeito que cada onda posterior "
"será máis letal que a anterior."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1727
msgid ""
"Konrad, I sense a current of magic approaching along the north road. I "
"suspect we will soon encounter that teleporting mage of Asheviere’s, along "
"with her orcish allies and mage followers."
msgstr ""
"Konrad, sinto unha corrente de maxia que se achega polo camiño norte. "
"Sospeito que pronto nos atoparemos con esa maga teletransportadora de "
"Asheviere, xunto cos seus aliados orcos e seguidores magos."

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1744
msgid "Ah, we’ve arrived at the perfect time."
msgstr "Ah, chegamos no momento perfecto."

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1771
msgid ""
"Congratulations on your entry into the queen’s service, orcs. To earn your "
"first payment, bring me the heads of the rebel leaders."
msgstr ""
"Parabéns pola vosa entrada ao servizo da raíña, orcos. Para gañar o voso "
"primeiro pago, traédeme as cabezas dos líderes rebeldes."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1780
msgid "You’re a good mage, Mirya. It’s a shame you’re a bad person."
msgstr "Es unha boa maga, Mirya. É unha mágoa que sexas unha mala persoa."

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1788
msgid ""
"Ow! I think it’s time to take my leave. No point dying for the cause when I "
"could live for it instead."
msgstr ""
"Ai! Creo que é hora de marchar. Non ten sentido morrer pola causa cando podo "
"vivir por ela."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#. "Morium libre vintis" doesn't mean anything. It's just some gibberish that sounds like a magic spell.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1794
msgid "You will not leave. Morium libre vintis!"
msgstr "Non te marcharás. Morrerás libre aos vinte!"

#. [message]: speaker=Mirya
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1802
msgid "My spell is broken!"
msgstr "O meu conxuro está roto!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1829
msgid ""
"Look, to the west! There is a great plume of dust visible just over the "
"horizon."
msgstr ""
"Mira, cara ao oeste! Hai unha gran columna de po visible xusto sobre o "
"horizonte."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1834
msgid ""
"That road leads to Dan’Tonk — there must be a column of soldiers marching to "
"my mother’s aid. They’ll be here any moment."
msgstr ""
"Ese camiño leva a Dan’Tonk. Debe haber unha columna de soldados marchando en "
"axuda da miña nai. Estarán aquí en calquera momento."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1848
msgid ""
"Your Majesty! So Konrad has come, just as you said he would. My army will "
"make short work of him."
msgstr ""
"Vosa Maxestade! Así que Konrad chegou, xusto como vostede dixo que ía "
"chegar. O meu exército ocuparáse del axiña."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1881
msgid "I’m sorry it had to come to this, Isolde. I respected you."
msgstr "Síntoo moito ter que chegar a isto, Isolde. Respectábate."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1885
msgid "You picked the wrong side, princess. I’ll try to capture you alive."
msgstr "Escolliches o lado equivocado, princesa. Intentarei capturarche viva."

#. [message]: speaker=Isolde
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1893
msgid "Don’t surrender, my queen! Do not let my death be in vain!"
msgstr "Non te rindas, miña raíña! Non deixes que a miña morte sexa en van!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1912
msgid ""
"I hear the rhythmic beat of war-drums. There is a vast orcish host "
"approaching from the northeast, behind us! They must have come a long way to "
"make war."
msgstr ""
"Escoito o ritmo dos tambores de guerra. Hai unha vasta hoste orca que se "
"achega dende o nordeste, detrás de nós! Deben ter percorrido un longo camiño "
"para facer a guerra."

#. [message]: speaker=Faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1928
msgid ""
"Should’ve taken me up on my offer when you had the chance, Konrad. If I "
"can’t kill the chief, maybe I can still win his favor by killing you!"
msgstr ""
"Deberías ter aceptado a miña oferta cando tiveste a oportunidade, Konrad. Se "
"non podo matar o xefe, quizais aínda poida gañar o seu favor matándote a ti!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1958
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Coming here was a poor decision, orc. The dark queen’s reign is at an "
#| "end. You tie yourself to a sinking ship."
msgid ""
"Coming here was a poor decision, orc. The dark queen’s reign is at an end. "
"You lash yourself to a sinking ship."
msgstr ""
"Vir aquí foi unha mala decisión, orco. O reinado da raíña escura chegou ao "
"seu fin. Átaste a un barco que se afunde."

#. [message]: speaker=Faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1962
#, fuzzy
msgid "Yeah yeah. Let’s get on with the fighting!"
msgstr "Saiamos de aquí."

#. [message]: speaker=Faghmok
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1970
msgid "Arrrgh! What a waste..."
msgstr "Arrrgh! Que desperdicio..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:1989
msgid ""
"There is a thunder of approaching hooves in the south! The Horse Clans have "
"come."
msgstr ""
"Escoítase un trueno de cascos que se achegan polo sur! Chegaron os Cláns "
"Ecuestres."

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2007
msgid ""
"Hail, good Asheviere! We have taken the long road and come around by the "
"south to surprise the rebels!"
msgstr ""
"Salve, bo Asheviere! Tomamos o camiño longo e vimos polo sur para sorprender "
"os rebeldes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2011
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "More like you took the long road hoping to miss the worst of the "
#| "fighting. I expected better, Bayar. We will discuss this after the battle."
msgid ""
"More likely you took the long road hoping to miss the worst of the fighting. "
"I expected better, Bayar. We will discuss this after the battle."
msgstr ""
"Máis ben coma se fixeras o longo camiño coa esperanza de evitar o peor dos "
"combates. Esperaba algo mellor, Bayar. Falaremos disto despois da batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2049
msgid "Ignore him. Run them down like dogs."
msgstr "Ignórao. Persígueos coma se fosen cans."

#. [message]: speaker=Bayar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2057
msgid "No! I am beaten! Perhaps the dark queen truly can be bested..."
msgstr ""
"Non! Estou derrotado/a! Quizais a raíña escura sexa realmente superada..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2096
msgid "Mother, I swore to end your reign of evil, and now I shall."
msgstr "Nai, xurei acabar co teu reinado do mal, e agora o farei."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere {ASHEVIERE_VARIATION defeated}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2100
msgid "Daughter, I built this kingdom for you. It has all been for you!"
msgstr "Filla, eu construín este reino para ti. Todo foi para ti!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2104
msgid ""
"Even now, can you not tell the truth? Your greed has corrupted your soul. "
"You are a monster! A murderess! It pains me to kill you, Mother, but you "
"have chosen your own fate. For Wesnoth!"
msgstr ""
"Mesmo agora, non podes dicir a verdade? A túa cobiza corrompeu a túa alma. "
"Es un monstro! Unha asasina! Dóeme ter que matarte, Nai, pero escolliches o "
"teu propio destino. Para Wesnoth!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2122
msgid ""
"You have hunted me across the countryside, indeed across the years. Here I "
"am, Dark Queen."
msgstr ""
"Me cazaches por todo o campo, e mesmo ao longo dos anos. Aquí estou, Raíña "
"Escura."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere {ASHEVIERE_VARIATION defeated}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2126
msgid ""
"I was sure I had killed you, yet you haunt me still. Be gone, demon! I "
"banish you, ghost!"
msgstr ""
"Estaba segura de que te matara, pero aínda me persegues. Vaite, demo! "
"Destierrote, pantasma!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2130
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Oh, wretched lady, I am very real. The land has suffered from your greed "
#| "and ambition. You will now be held to account for your misdeeds. For the "
#| "young prince Konrad! For WESNOTH!"
msgid ""
"Oh, wretched lady, I am very real. The land has suffered from your greed and "
"ambition. You will now be held to account for your misdeeds. For the young "
"Prince Konrad! For WESNOTH!"
msgstr ""
"Oh, desgraciada, son moi real. A terra sufriu a túa cobiza e ambición. Agora "
"pagarás todas as túas débedas. Polo mozo príncipe Conrad! Polo NOROESTE!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2148
msgid "As I destroyed your son, I now destroy you."
msgstr "Do mesmo xeito que destruín o teu fillo, agora destrúote a ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere {ASHEVIERE_VARIATION defeated}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2152
msgid ""
"You were always defiant, wizard, and no one has thwarted my plans as "
"determinedly as you."
msgstr ""
"Ti sempre fuches desafiante, mago, e ninguén frustrou os meus plans con "
"tanta determinación coma ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2156
msgid ""
"I have always been a humble servant of the Crown, and remain such even now."
msgstr "Sempre fun un humilde servidor da Coroa, e sigo séndoo aínda agora."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere {ASHEVIERE_VARIATION defeated}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2160
msgid ""
"Delfador! You utterly disgust me, you sniveling worm. How dare you confront "
"me, your queen?"
msgstr ""
"Delfador! Dásme noxo, verme choramingante. Como te atreves a enfrontarte a "
"min, a túa raíña?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2164
msgid "How dare I? I, High Provost of the Council of Archmagi..."
msgstr "Como me atrevo? Eu, Alto Prebosto do Consello de Arquimeigos…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2166
msgid ""
"... bearer of the staff of An-Usrukhar, guardian of the book of Crelanu ..."
msgstr "… portador do bastón de An-Usrukhar, gardián do libro de Crelanu…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2168
msgid ""
"... Mage Protector of The Kingdom Of The Peoples Of The West-North, Chief "
"Advisor to the Crown..."
msgstr ""
"… Meigo Protector do Reino dos Pobos do Noroeste, Principal Conselleiro da "
"Coroa…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2170
msgid ""
"... and personal counselor to my King and my friend, Garard the Second, whom "
"you most foully betrayed..."
msgstr ""
"… e conselleiro persoal do meu rei e amigo, Garard o Segundo, a quen vós "
"traizoastes vilmente…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador {DELFADOR_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2172
msgid "I am Delfador the Great and TODAY YOU MEET YOUR ATONEMENT!"
msgstr "Son Delfador o Grande e HOXE ENFRONTADES A VOSA EXPIACIÓN!"

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere {ASHEVIERE_VARIATION defeated}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2203
msgid "Treason! The evil ones have slain me!"
msgstr "Traizón! Os malvados matáronme!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2208
msgid ""
"For too long has your darkness troubled the world, Asheviere. Your time has "
"come!"
msgstr ""
"Durante demasiado tempo a túa escuridade atormentou o mundo, Asheviere. "
"Chegou a túa hora!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2209
msgid "Vengeance for the fallen! Vengeance for Deoran!"
msgstr "Vinganza polos caídos! Vinganza por Deoran!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2210
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2211
msgid ""
"The hand of the Clans strikes you down, witch! Vengeance for my king! "
"Vengeance for Garard!"
msgstr ""
"A man dos Clans derrúbate, meiga! Vinganza polo meu rei! Vinganza por Garard!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2212
msgid ""
"Dark queen, your evil ends this day. In the name of the Light, I purge you "
"from this world!"
msgstr ""
"Raíña escura, a túa maldade remata hoxe. En nome da Luz, purgote deste mundo!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2213
msgid "Here’s for Baldras! Here’s for Delwyn and Dallben!"
msgstr "¡Viva Baldras! ¡Viva Delwyn e Dallben!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2214
msgid ""
"Dinnae recognize me, do ye? You sent me to the gibbet, ye milksop, ye "
"coward! Ah’ll cut that lubberworting head right off yer steamin’ corpse!"
msgstr ""
"Non me recoñeces, verdade? Enviáchesme á forca, molho, covarde! Vouche "
"cortar esa cabeza de lagarta do teu cadáver fumegante!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2215
msgid "Sorry about this! Oh, how did I get caught up in all this?"
msgstr "Desculpa por isto! Oh, como me vinchei en todo isto?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2216
msgid "For Alduin! For my friends, my apprentices, and my home! Now burn!"
msgstr ""
"Por Alduin! Polos meus amigos, os meus aprendices e o meu fogar! Agora "
"ardede!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2217
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "For Alduin! For my friends, my apprentices, and my home! Now burn!"
msgid "For Alduin! For my friends, my family, and my home! Now burn!"
msgstr ""
"Por Alduin! Polos meus amigos, os meus aprendices e o meu fogar! Agora "
"ardede!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2218
msgid "Dis not personal, queen. But Dosh gonna squash you like frog."
msgstr "Non é persoal, raíña. Pero o Señor vai esmagarte coma se fose unha ra."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere {ASHEVIERE_VARIATION defeated}
#. "struck by some lowborn grunt" hints to the player that there's messages if Konrad/Lisar/Delfador get the kill
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2223
msgid ""
"Oh, such indignity to have the final blow struck by some lowborn grunt..."
msgstr ""
"Oh, tanta indignidade recibir o golpe final dado por algún gruñido de baixa "
"cuna..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2231
msgid "And so passes Asheviere, queen of Wesnoth."
msgstr "<i>— Raíña Axevier, 503 D.N.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2235
msgid "We have won at last! Li’sar! You will be queen!"
msgstr "Por fin gañamos! Li'sar! Serás raíña!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar {LISAR_VARIATION glad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2239
msgid ""
"Yes, but I won’t ever forget what you have done for me, Konrad. And you, "
"Delfador."
msgstr ""
"Si, pero nunca esquecerei o que fixeches por min, Konrad. E ti, Delfador."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2244
msgid "So much blood. So much death. For what? A title?"
msgstr "Tanta sangue. Tanta morte. Para que? Un título?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2248
msgid ""
"For justice, Elf Lord. We fight because if we do not, evil would prevail. "
"But, I implore you to let the dead have their rest. We have taken victory. "
"Tomorrow is a new day, friends... let us build this kingdom anew."
msgstr ""
"Pola xustiza, Señor Elfo. Loitamos porque se non o facemos, o mal "
"prevalecerá. Pero implorovos que deixedes que os mortos descansen. Acadamos "
"a vitoria. Mañá é un novo día, amigos... construamos este reino de novo."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2253
msgid ""
"We have taken victory. Tomorrow is a new day, friends... let us build this "
"kingdom anew."
msgstr ""
"Tivemos a vitoria. Mañá é un novo día, amigos... reconstruyamos este reino."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2347
msgid "And so the Dark Queen’s reign was ended."
msgstr "E así rematou o reinado da Raíña Escura."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2351
msgid ""
"Li’sar, daughter of Garard II and Heir to the Throne of Wesnoth, was crowned "
"Queen and Bearer of the Sceptre of Fire, which she would pass on to all her "
"successors. Her reign was long, and she undid much of the evil deeds of her "
"mother."
msgstr ""
"Li’sar, filla de Garard II e herdeira ao trono de Wesnoth, foi coroada raíña "
"e portadora do cetro de lume, que transmitiría a todos os seus sucesores. O "
"seu reinado foi longo e desfixo moitas das malas accións da súa nai."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2353
msgid ""
"Delfador became Li’sar’s High Counselor, advising her in the most important "
"matters of state. He lived until a ripe old age and was granted a royal "
"funeral, after which he was buried in the Royal Crypt in Weldyn."
msgstr ""
"Delfador converteuse no Gran Conselleiro de Li’sar, asesorándoa nos asuntos "
"de estado máis importantes. Viviu ata unha idade avanzada e concedéuselle un "
"funeral real, tras o cal foi enterrado na Cripta Real en Weldyn."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2358
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Chantal ventured into the palace dungeons, where she found her great-"
#| "grandfather Kalenz among many other prisoners. Togther they returned to "
#| "their home in the north and never again came to the lands of men."
msgid ""
"Chantal ventured into the palace dungeons, where she found her great-"
"grandfather Kalenz among many other prisoners. Together they returned to "
"their home in the north and never again came to the lands of men."
msgstr ""
"Chantal aventurouse nos calabozos do palacio, onde atopou o seu bisavó "
"Kalenz entre moitos outros prisioneiros. Xuntos regresaron ao seu fogar no "
"norte e nunca máis volveron ás terras dos homes."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2359
msgid ""
"Kalenz and Chantal returned to their homes in the north, and never again "
"came to the lands of men."
msgstr ""
"Kalenz e Chantal volveron aos seus fogares no norte e nunca máis volveron ás "
"terras dos homes."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2360
msgid ""
"Kalenz returned to his home in the north and never again came to the lands "
"of men."
msgstr ""
"Kalenz volveu ao seu fogar no norte e nunca máis volveu ás terras dos homes."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2361
msgid ""
"Haldiel — and Kaylan — returned to the Horse Plains. With the queen defeated "
"and her supporters among the the Horse Lords disgraced, the returnees gained "
"much clout within the Horse Clans, and enacted reform."
msgstr ""
"Haldiel — e Kaylan — regresaron ás Chairas dos Cabalos. Coa raíña derrotada "
"e os seus partidarios entre os Señores dos Cabalos desprestixiados, os "
"retornados gañaron gran influencia nos Clans e impulsaron reformas."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2362
msgid ""
"Haldiel returned to the Horse Plains. The queen’s supporters were "
"embarrassed by her defeat, but Kaylan’s death left Konrad’s allies with no "
"one to rally behind. Change would be slow."
msgstr ""
"Haldiel regresou ás Chairas dos Cabalos. Os partidarios da raíña quedaron "
"avergoñados pola súa derrota, pero a morte de Kaylan deixou aos aliados de "
"Konrad sen ninguén arredor de quen unirse. O cambio sería lento."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2363
msgid ""
"Moremirmu lived the rest of his days as a wandering warrior, bringing light "
"and hope wherever he went. When at last he fell, he was buried with honors "
"and laid to rest among the other heroes of his order."
msgstr ""
"Moremirmu viviu o resto dos seus días como un guerreiro errante, levando luz "
"e esperanza alá onde ía. Cando finalmente caeu, foi enterrado con honras e "
"depositado entre os outros heroes da súa orde."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2364
msgid ""
"Harper returned to the Three Sisters, where she led her people back to the "
"mainland, to reclaim their ruined hometowns. Delwyn and Dallben were "
"rebuilt, and prospered."
msgstr ""
"Harper regresou ás Tres Irmás, onde levou ao seu pobo de volta ao continente "
"para recuperar as súas cidades natales en ruínas. Delwyn e Dallben foron "
"reconstruídas e prosperaron."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2365
msgid ""
"With Konrad’s blessing, Ulfdain rallied a company of soldiers — dwarves and "
"men both — and set out to fight for Knalga. They were never heard from again."
msgstr ""
"Coa bendición de Konrad, Ulfdain reuniu unha compañía de soldados — tanto "
"ananos como homes — e partiu para loitar por Knalga. Nunca máis se soubo "
"deles."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2366
msgid ""
"Jeniver swallowed her pride and traveled to Alduin. At Delfador’s insistence "
"she was awarded a professorship, and would go on to contribute greatly to "
"the advancement of alchemy and the training of young minds."
msgstr ""
"Jeniver tragou o seu orgullo e viaxou a Alduin. Por insistencia de Delfador, "
"outorgáronlle unha praza de profesora e contribuiría enormemente ao avance "
"da alquimia e á formación de mentes novas."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2367
msgid ""
"Seimus returned to Alduin, where he was hailed as a hero by many (and "
"reviled by a few). He presided over the academy for many years, where he was "
"often visited by his friend Delfador."
msgstr ""
"Seimus regresou a Alduin, onde foi aclamado como un heroe por moitos (e "
"vilipendiado por algúns). Presidiu a academia durante moitos anos, onde "
"recibía a visita do seu amigo Delfador."

#. [then]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2371
msgid "His grandparents’ loan was repaid in full, plus interest."
msgstr "A débeda dos seus avós foi saldada por completo, con xuros incluídos."

#. [then]
#. [else]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2371
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2374
msgid ""
"Inspired by Konrad’s leadership, Elrian forwent his study of magic and "
"instead devoted himself to the study of strategy. In time, he would become "
"one of the Crown’s top generals."
msgstr ""
"Inspirado polo liderado de Konrad, Elrian abandonou o estudo da maxia e "
"dedicouse á estratexia. Co tempo, converteríase nun dos mellores xenerais da "
"Coroa."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2377
msgid ""
"Dosh returned to the north, where stories of his battle-feats and "
"exceptional intelligence (for a troll) made him a figure of some renown. In "
"time he accrued enough followers to start his own clan, which he ruled "
"wisely as chief."
msgstr ""
"Dosh volveu ao norte, onde as historias das súas fazañas de batalla e a súa "
"intelixencia excepcional (para ser un trol) o converteron nunha figura de "
"certa sona. Co tempo, acumulou seguidores dabondo para fundar o seu propio "
"clan, que gobernou sabiamente como xefe."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2378
msgid ""
"Konrad kept his promise to Merle, channeling gold and attention towards the "
"Dulatus hills. That place became known as a home of great craftsmen."
msgstr ""
"Konrad cumpriu a súa promesa a Merle, canalizando o ouro e a atención cara "
"aos outeiros de Dulatus. Ese lugar converteuse nun fogar de grandes artesáns."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2379
msgid ""
"Jotha eventually returned to his home in the north, this time alongside many "
"other merfolk. The Bay of Jotha (so it came to be called) would grow into a "
"prosperous settlement; a rare jewel of civilization in the northern "
"wildlands."
msgstr ""
"Jotha finalmente regresou ao seu fogar no norte, esta vez xunto a moitos "
"outros sirénidos. A Baía de Jotha (así foi como se lle chamou) converteríase "
"nun próspero asentamento; unha xoia rara da civilización nas terras salvaxes "
"do norte."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2380
msgid ""
"Warven, now elevated to Grand Marshal, continued to serve Li’sar loyally for "
"many years. He would one day be crippled in battle, and would retire to "
"teach at Weldyn’s military academy."
msgstr ""
"Inspirado polo liderado de Konrad, Elrian abandonou o estudo da maxia e "
"dedicouse á estratexia. Co tempo, converteríase nun dos mellores xenerais da "
"Coroa."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2381
msgid ""
"Blackwing the raven, already advanced in age, passed away soon after "
"Asheviere’s demise. He was laid to rest at the Royal Library, in a glass "
"ossuary ornamented with all manner of trinkets and baubles."
msgstr ""
"Corvo Negro, xa de idade avanzada, morreu pouco despois da caída de "
"Asheviere. Foi enterrado na Biblioteca Real, nun osario de vidro adornado "
"con todo tipo de amuletos e baratezas."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2394
msgid ""
"The prisoners Asheviere had threatened were found and freed, none the worse "
"for their ordeal. Most returned to their homes, singing the new Queen’s "
"praises."
msgstr ""
"Os prisioneiros que Asheviere ameazara foron atopados e liberados, sen que "
"sufriran danos polo seu calvario. A maioría regresou ás súas casas, cantando "
"as loanzas da nova raíña."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2400
msgid ""
"The bones of the infant Prince Konrad were retrieved from the elves and "
"buried in the Royal Crypt in Weldyn, which our Konrad visited to pay homage "
"every week."
msgstr ""
"Os ósos do príncipe infante Konrad foron recuperados dos elfos e enterrados "
"na Cripta Real en Weldyn, que o noso Konrad visitaba para render homenaxe "
"cada semana."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2402
msgid ""
"And as for our Konrad himself... the foundling prince became a noble in "
"Li’sar’s court."
msgstr ""
"E en canto ao noso propio Konrad... o príncipe expósito converteuse nun "
"nobre na corte de Li’sar."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2409
msgid ""
"The prince and the queen’s mutual respect grew into friendship, trust, and "
"eventually something more. They were married, and together they had two sons "
"and a daughter."
msgstr ""
"O respecto mutuo entre o príncipe e a raíña converteuse en amizade, "
"confianza e, finalmente, en algo máis. Casaron e tiveron dous fillos e unha "
"filla."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2413
msgid ""
"They ruled wisely, but some wounds are slow to heal. The croplands "
"surrounding Weldyn would never entirely recover from their razing. The "
"people there grew hard and bitter; that land spawned many outlaws."
msgstr ""
"Reinaron con sabedoría, pero algunhas feridas tardan en curar. As terras de "
"cultivo arredor de Weldyn nunca se recuperarían completamente da súa "
"devastación. A xente alí fíxose dura e amarga; esa terra xerou moitos "
"proscritos."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2417
msgid "But such was the cost of victory, wasn’t it?"
msgstr "Claro que non fomos nós, verme!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2425
msgid ""
"The prince and the queen’s mutual respect grew into friendship, trust, and "
"eventually something more. They were married, and together they had two sons "
"and a daughter. The kingdom once more prospered under their rule."
msgstr ""
"O respecto mutuo entre o príncipe e a raíña converteuse en amizade, "
"confianza e, finalmente, en algo máis. Casaron e, xuntos, tiveron dous "
"fillos e unha filla. O reino prosperou unha vez máis baixo o seu goberno."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2429
msgid "All was well."
msgstr "Todo estaba ben."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50_The_Battle_for_Wesnoth.cfg:2438
msgid ""
"How unfortunate, for both you and your loved ones. I shall have to make an "
"example of you."
msgstr ""
"Que desafortunado, para ti e para os teus seres queridos. Terei que facer un "
"exemplo contigo."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:5
msgid "Overlook"
msgstr "Pasar por alto"

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Konrad’s once-ragged band of refugees had grown to a massive army. The young "
"prince strode among the ranks, visiting and encouraging soldiers: both his "
"and Li’sar’s."
msgstr ""
"O outrora esfarrapado grupo de refuxiados de Konrad convertérase nun "
"exército enorme. O mozo príncipe camiñaba entre as filas, visitando e "
"animando aos soldados: tanto os seus como os de Li'sar."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Many had left behind the safety and peace of their homes to make war — his "
"war. The weight of that thought bore on him. Much had changed since the "
"flight from the Aethenwood."
msgstr ""
"Moitos deixaran atrás a seguridade e a paz dos seus fogares para facer a "
"guerra, a súa guerra. O peso dese pensamento o agochaba. Moito cambiara "
"desde a fuxida de Aethenwood."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Although once mortal enemies, the prince and princess had forged an uneasy "
"alliance; perhaps even a friendship. But the question of succession "
"remained. Li’sar held the Sceptre, but Konrad’s claim was strong. The matter "
"could not lie unresolved; not so near to the throne."
msgstr ""
"Aínda que noutro tempo foran inimigos mortais, o príncipe e a princesa "
"forxaran unha alianza incómoda; quizais mesmo unha amizade. Pero a cuestión "
"da sucesión seguía adiante. Li'sar posuía o cetro, pero a pretensión de "
"Konrad era forte. O asunto non podía quedar sen resolver; non tan preto do "
"trono."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Although once mortal enemies, the prince and princess had forged an uneasy "
"alliance; perhaps even a friendship. But the question of succession "
"remained. Konrad held the Sceptre, but Li’sar’s claim was strong. The matter "
"could not lie unresolved; not so near to the throne."
msgstr ""
"Aínda que noutro tempo foran inimigos mortais, o príncipe e a princesa "
"forxaran unha alianza incómoda; quizais mesmo unha amizade. Pero a cuestión "
"da sucesión seguía adiante. Konrad posuía o cetro, pero a pretensión de "
"Li'sar era forte. O asunto non podía quedar sen resolver; non tan preto do "
"trono."

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:34
msgid ""
"At length, the rebel army came to the northern shore of the river Weldyn, "
"and paused there. To look at the city. To make plans for the battle, and to "
"talk."
msgstr ""
"Finalmente, o exército rebelde chegou á ribeira norte do río Weldyn e "
"detívose alí. Para observar a cidade. Para facer plans para a batalla e para "
"falar."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#. this is a lead-in to the main conversation, but also explains to the player why we start the battle next to the river, even though we approached from a different direction on the overworld.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:87
msgid ""
"—and the outskirts are barely a day’s march away. We should approach along "
"the river, to make use of our merfolk and to cover our flank. She’ll cut off "
"our supply chain if we give her the chance."
msgstr ""
"—e os arredores están a apenas un día de marcha. Deberíamos achegarnos ao "
"longo do río, para facer uso dos nosos sirenas e cubrir o noso flanco. "
"Cortará a nosa cadea de subministración se lle damos a oportunidade."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#. this is a lead-in to the main conversation, but also explains to the player why we start the battle next to the river, even though we approached from a different direction on the overworld.
#. out of character, we start next to the river so that the player has a chance to use their merfolk, if any
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:94
msgid ""
"—and the outskirts are barely a day’s march away. We should approach from "
"the northeast, using the river to cover our flank. She’ll cut off our supply "
"chain if we give her the chance."
msgstr ""
"—e as aforas están a apenas un día de marcha. Deberíamos achegarnos polo "
"nordeste, usando o río para cubrir o noso flanco. Cortará a nosa cadea de "
"subministración se lle damos a oportunidade."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:100
msgid ""
"The prisoners could be a problem, if she threatens them to try to force our "
"surrender. But I don’t think it will come to that. She knows we’re not so "
"foolish as to give in."
msgstr ""
"Os prisioneiros poderían ser un problema se ela os ameaza para tentar "
"obrigar a nosa rendición. Pero non creo que chegue a iso. Ela sabe que non "
"somos tan tolos como para rendernos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:112
msgid "Delfador, what do you think? You’ve been very quiet recently."
msgstr "Delfador, que che parece? Estives moi calado ultimamente."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:116
msgid ""
"Weldyn. The great city. The ancient city. The city of evil. The city of "
"good. The city of men."
msgstr ""
"Weldyn. A gran cidade. A antiga cidade. A cidade do mal. A cidade do ben. A "
"cidade dos homes."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:124
msgid ""
"I have not looked upon that city for seventeen years, Konrad. Seventeen "
"years ago, when I should have been at the height of my power. But my "
"strength failed me. I failed, and I cannot atone for it."
msgstr ""
"Non vin esa cidade dende hai dezasete anos, Konrad. Dezasete anos atrás, "
"cando debería estar no cumio do meu poder. Pero as forzas falláronme. "
"Fracasei e non podo expiar por iso."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:129
msgid ""
"You could not defeat Asheviere, I know. But you rescued me. That was no "
"failure."
msgstr ""
"Non puideches derrotar a Asheviere, sei. Pero me rescataches. Iso non foi un "
"fracaso."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:133
msgid "You do not understand."
msgstr "Non entendes."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:145
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The battle had been long and hard. We had been defeated. Eldred was "
#| "slain, but I knew that Asheviere’s wrath would be great. That many "
#| "innocents would be slain.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I had to save the monarchy. I had to save the princes. I made haste to "
#| "Weldyn, before the guards of Asheviere could get there, to carry out "
#| "their evil orders."
msgid ""
"The battle had been long and hard. We had been defeated. Eldred was slain, "
"but I knew that Asheviere’s wrath would be great. That many innocents would "
"be slain."
msgstr ""
"A batalla fora longa e dura. Foramos derrotados. Eldred fora asasinado, pero "
"eu sabía que a ira de Asheviere sería grande. Que moitos inocentes serían "
"asasinados.\n"
"\n"
"Tiña que salvar a monarquía. Tiña que salvar os príncipes. Apresureime a "
"Weldyn, antes de que os gardas de Asheviere puidesen chegar alí, para "
"cumprir as súas ordes malvadas."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:147
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The battle had been long and hard. We had been defeated. Eldred was "
#| "slain, but I knew that Asheviere’s wrath would be great. That many "
#| "innocents would be slain.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I had to save the monarchy. I had to save the princes. I made haste to "
#| "Weldyn, before the guards of Asheviere could get there, to carry out "
#| "their evil orders."
msgid ""
"I had to save the monarchy. I had to save the princes. I made haste to "
"Weldyn, before the guards of Asheviere could get there, to carry out their "
"evil orders."
msgstr ""
"A batalla fora longa e dura. Foramos derrotados. Eldred fora asasinado, pero "
"eu sabía que a ira de Asheviere sería grande. Que moitos inocentes serían "
"asasinados.\n"
"\n"
"Tiña que salvar a monarquía. Tiña que salvar os príncipes. Apresureime a "
"Weldyn, antes de que os gardas de Asheviere puidesen chegar alí, para "
"cumprir as súas ordes malvadas."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:151
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But I failed. I was too late. I entered the chambers of the youngest "
#| "prince, Prince Konrad, just as one of the evil ones ran him through.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "All was lost. The heirs were slain. Only Asheviere and her daughter had "
#| "any claim to the throne."
msgid ""
"But I failed. I was too late. I entered the chambers of the youngest prince, "
"Prince Konrad, just as one of the evil ones ran him through."
msgstr ""
"Pero fallei. Cheguei tarde de máis. Entrei nos apousentos do máis novo dos "
"príncipes, o príncipe Conrad, a tempo de contemplar como un deses malvados "
"se abalanzaba sobre el. Todo estaba perdido. Os herdeiros foran asasinados. "
"Só Axevier e a súa filla poderían reclamar o trono."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:153
msgid ""
"All was lost. The heirs were slain. Only Asheviere and her daughter had any "
"claim to the throne."
msgstr ""
"Todo estaba perdido. Os herdeiros foron asasinados. Só Asheviere e a súa "
"filla tiñan dereito ao trono."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION concerned}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:157
msgid "I am not dead, Delfador. What is this you’re saying!?"
msgstr "Non estou morto, Delfador. Que estás dicindo!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Of course, you are surprised by this, but it is the truth. In haste, I "
"vanquished the evil ones who had committed this foul deed. Then I took the "
"little prince’s broken body, and away I rode. Far away, to the land of the "
"elves."
msgstr ""
"Por suposto, isto sorprendeche, pero é a verdade. Apresuradamente, derrotei "
"os malvados que cometeran este acto repugnante. Despois collín o corpo "
"esnaquizado do pequeno príncipe e marchei cabalgando. Lonxe, á terra dos "
"elfos."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:165
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "By strange and mysterious fortune, the Elf Lady Parandra had come across "
#| "a human child. She knew not where he had come from, only that the orcs "
#| "would have eaten him if it weren’t for her intervention.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "The elves felt that great fortune smiled upon this nameless child. "
#| "Perhaps that is why this most truthful of peoples agreed to my plan."
msgid ""
"By strange and mysterious fortune, the Elf Lady Parandra had come across a "
"human child. She knew not where he had come from, only that the orcs would "
"have eaten him if it weren’t for her intervention."
msgstr ""
"Por estraña e misteriosa fortuna, a dama elfa Parandra atopouse cun neno "
"humano. Non sabía de onde viña, só que os orcos o terían comido se non fose "
"pola súa intervención.\n"
"\n"
"Os elfos sentiron que unha gran fortuna lle caía a este neno sen nome. "
"Quizais sexa por iso que este pobo, o máis sincero dos pobos, aceptou o meu "
"plan."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:167
msgid ""
"The elves felt that great fortune smiled upon this nameless child. Perhaps "
"that is why this most truthful of peoples agreed to my plan."
msgstr ""
"Os elfos creron que unha gran fortuna sorría a este neno sen nome. Quizais "
"por iso este pobo tan veraz aceptou o meu plan."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:171
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "After burying the little prince, we agreed never to speak of him again. "
#| "Instead, this orphan child we would call Konrad, and he would be brought "
#| "up to be king.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I would say that I had slain the guards before they had carried out their "
#| "evil deed, instead of after. No one would ever have to know. And no one "
#| "did know for certain, until now."
msgid ""
"After burying the little prince, we agreed never to speak of him again. "
"Instead, this orphan child we would call Konrad, and he would be brought up "
"to be king."
msgstr ""
"Despois de enterrar o principiño, acordamos non volver falar del nunca máis. "
"En vez diso, a este neno orfo chamaríamolo Konrad, e sería educado para ser "
"rei.\n"
"\n"
"Eu diría que matei os gardas antes de que levasen a cabo a súa mala acción, "
"en vez de despois. Ninguén tería que sabelo nunca. E ninguén o soubo con "
"certeza, ata agora."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:173
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "After burying the little prince, we agreed never to speak of him again. "
#| "Instead, this orphan child we would call Konrad, and he would be brought "
#| "up to be king.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "I would say that I had slain the guards before they had carried out their "
#| "evil deed, instead of after. No one would ever have to know. And no one "
#| "did know for certain, until now."
msgid ""
"I would say that I had slain the guards before they had carried out their "
"evil deed, instead of after. No one would ever have to know. And no one did "
"know for certain, until now."
msgstr ""
"Despois de enterrar o principiño, acordamos non volver falar del nunca máis. "
"En vez diso, a este neno orfo chamaríamolo Konrad, e sería educado para ser "
"rei.\n"
"\n"
"Eu diría que matei os gardas antes de que levasen a cabo a súa mala acción, "
"en vez de despois. Ninguén tería que sabelo nunca. E ninguén o soubo con "
"certeza, ata agora."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:183
msgid ""
"I had thought that we could one day make you king, Konrad. But now I see "
"that fate has made a different choice. That despite all of Asheviere’s evil, "
"this Li’sar is fit for the throne."
msgstr ""
"Pensei que algún día poderiamos facerte rei, Konrad. Pero agora vexo que o "
"destino tomou unha decisión diferente. Que a pesar de toda a maldade de "
"Asheviere, este Li'sar é apto para o trono."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:188
msgid ""
"Parandra was right. Li’sar... Li’sar is the rightful queen. From a long line "
"of kings, stretching all the way back to the seafarers of old from the west."
msgstr ""
"Parandra tiña razón. Li’sar... Li’sar é a raíña lexítima. Dunha longa liñaxe "
"de reis, que se remonta aos antigos mariñeiros do oeste."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:193
msgid ""
"Li’sar... Li’sar is the rightful queen. From a long line of kings, "
"stretching all the way back to the seafarers of old from the west."
msgstr ""
"Li’sar... Li’sar é a raíña lexítima. Dunha longa liñaxe de reis, que se "
"remonta aos antigos mariñeiros do oeste."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:199
msgid "Li’sar... The rightful queen..."
msgstr "Li'sar... A raíña lexítima..."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:203
msgid ""
"Delfador, I am honored. And Konrad... I’m just as surprised by this "
"revelation as are you. In truth, you’d nearly had me convinced we were of "
"one blood. I can’t call you my cousin any more, now."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, síntome honrado. E Konrad... Estou tan sorprendido por esta "
"revelación coma ti. A verdade é que case me convencías de que eramos do "
"mesmo sangue. Xa non te podo chamar meu primo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:211
msgid ""
"Then call me a friend. I was ready to be king. But in our time together I "
"have come to agree with Delfador — you will make a good queen."
msgstr ""
"Entón chámaime amigo. Eu estaba preparado para ser rei. Pero no tempo que "
"pasamos xuntos cheguei a coincidir con Delfador: serás unha boa raíña."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:215
msgid "It is decided."
msgstr "Está decidido."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/scenarios/50x_Overlook.cfg:220
msgid ""
"Now, let us not tarry here any longer! The dawn breaks! The time has come "
"for the heir to the throne to claim it!"
msgstr ""
"Agora, non nos demoremos máis aquí! Amenece! Chegou a hora de que o herdeiro "
"ao trono o reclame!"

#. [terrain_type]: id=impassable_fence
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/terrain.cfg:7
msgid "Impassable Fence"
msgstr "Cerca intransitable"

#. [terrain_type]: id=web
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/terrain.cfg:16
msgid "Spiderweb"
msgstr "Tea de araña"

#. [terrain_type]: id=dummy_obstacle
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/terrain.cfg:27
msgid "Point of Interest"
msgstr "Punto de interese"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dwarvish Bloodaxe, race=dwarf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Dwarvish_Bloodaxe.cfg:18
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "According to legend, the mystical bloodaxes were forged at the dawn of "
#| "time in the great stone-fires of Dhur Darihm, when all Irdya was still "
#| "drowned in flame and soot. It is with them that the first dwarves made "
#| "war against the troll-mother, laying low her people and forevermore "
#| "claiming dominion in the underearth.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "While the truth of this legend is a matter of debate, battlefield reports "
#| "leave no doubt that such weapons exist, and that they confer great "
#| "resilience upon their wielder. The dwarves’ few remaining bloodaxes are "
#| "jealously guarded, passed down from father to son and reclaimed from the "
#| "fallen even at great cost."
msgid ""
"According to legend, the mystical bloodaxes were forged at the dawn of time "
"in the great stone-fires of Dhur Darihm, when all Irdya was still drowned in "
"flame and soot. It is with them that the first dwarves made war against the "
"troll-mother, laying low her people and forevermore claiming dominion in the "
"underearth."
msgstr ""
"Segundo a lenda, as místicas machadas de sangue foron forxadas nos albores "
"dos tempos nos grandes fogueiras de pedra de Dhur Darihm, cando toda Irdya "
"aínda estaba afogada en chamas e hollín. Foi con elas que os primeiros "
"ananos fixeron a guerra contra a nai trol, derrotando ao seu pobo e "
"reclamando para sempre o dominio no subsolo.\n"
"\n"
"Aínda que a verdade desta lenda é motivo de debate, os informes dos campos "
"de batalla non deixan dúbida de que tales armas existen e de que confiren "
"unha gran resistencia ao seu portador. As poucas machadas de sangue que "
"quedan dos ananos son celosamente gardadas, transmitidas de pais a fillos e "
"recuperadas dos caídos mesmo a un gran custo."

#. [unit_type]: id=Dwarvish Bloodaxe, race=dwarf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Dwarvish_Bloodaxe.cfg:20
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "According to legend, the mystical bloodaxes were forged at the dawn of "
#| "time in the great stone-fires of Dhur Darihm, when all Irdya was still "
#| "drowned in flame and soot. It is with them that the first dwarves made "
#| "war against the troll-mother, laying low her people and forevermore "
#| "claiming dominion in the underearth.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "While the truth of this legend is a matter of debate, battlefield reports "
#| "leave no doubt that such weapons exist, and that they confer great "
#| "resilience upon their wielder. The dwarves’ few remaining bloodaxes are "
#| "jealously guarded, passed down from father to son and reclaimed from the "
#| "fallen even at great cost."
msgid ""
"While the truth of this legend is a matter of debate, battlefield reports "
"leave no doubt that such weapons exist, and that they confer great "
"resilience upon their wielder. The dwarves’ few remaining bloodaxes are "
"jealously guarded, passed down from father to son and reclaimed from the "
"fallen even at great cost."
msgstr ""
"Segundo a lenda, as místicas machadas de sangue foron forxadas nos albores "
"dos tempos nos grandes fogueiras de pedra de Dhur Darihm, cando toda Irdya "
"aínda estaba afogada en chamas e hollín. Foi con elas que os primeiros "
"ananos fixeron a guerra contra a nai trol, derrotando ao seu pobo e "
"reclamando para sempre o dominio no subsolo.\n"
"\n"
"Aínda que a verdade desta lenda é motivo de debate, os informes dos campos "
"de batalla non deixan dúbida de que tales armas existen e de que confiren "
"unha gran resistencia ao seu portador. As poucas machadas de sangue que "
"quedan dos ananos son celosamente gardadas, transmitidas de pais a fillos e "
"recuperadas dos caídos mesmo a un gran custo."

#. [attack]: type=blade
#. [object]: id=bloodaxe
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Dwarvish_Bloodaxe.cfg:32
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:365
msgid "bloodaxe"
msgstr "machada de sangue"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dwarvish Witness, race=dwarf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Dwarvish_Witness.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Witness"
msgstr "Testemuña anana"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dwarvish Witness, race=dwarf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Dwarvish_Witness.cfg:20
msgid ""
"A Witness functions as the eyes of the dwarves’ history, a deep lore that "
"they never share with outsiders. The presence of a Witness instils dwarvish "
"warriors with the knowledge that their deeds (and their deaths) will not go "
"unrecorded, inspiring them to daunting deeds and great heroics. The person "
"of a Witness is considered sacred, and Witnesses are often used as envoys "
"between dwarvish clans."
msgstr ""
"Os observadores son os ollos da historia dos ananos, un profundo coñecemento "
"que nunca comparten con estraños. A presenza dun observador incita aos "
"ananos guerreiros co coñecemento de que as súas fazañas (e mailas súas "
"mortes) non pasarán desapercibidas, inspirándoos a realizar fazañas "
"desalentadoras e grandes accións heroicas. . Os observadores son "
"considerados sagrados, e a miúdo son usados coma embaixadores entre clans de "
"ananos."

#. [dummy]: id=march
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Elite_Units.cfg:12
msgid "march"
msgstr "Marzo"

#. [dummy]: id=march
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Elite_Units.cfg:13
msgid ""
"This unit has improved movement on forest, cave, hill, mountain, frozen, and "
"water terrain."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidade ten un movemento mellorado en terreos de bosque, cova, colina, "
"montaña, xeado e auga."

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Civilian, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Elvish_Civilian.cfg:4
msgid "Elvish Civilian"
msgstr "Civil Elfo"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Civilian, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Elvish_Civilian.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Although elves are not warlike by nature, their natural grace ensures that "
"even untrained they have talent for swords and bows. However, if you are "
"hurling civilians at your foes, you’re clearly out of superior forces."
msgstr ""
"Aínda que os elfos non son guerreiros por natureza, a súa graza natural "
"garante que mesmo sen adestramento teñan talento para as espadas e os arcos. "
"Non obstante, se estás lanzando civís contra os teus inimigos, está claro "
"que estás sen forzas superiores."

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Elvish_Civilian.cfg:22
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_Warrior_of_Light.cfg:32
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_White_Warrior.cfg:30
