#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Mage_Shackled.cfg:15
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "These mages have bound wrists, and cannot use their magic."
msgid ""
"These mages have heavy manacles on their wrists and ankles, slowing their "
"movement and restricting their magic."
msgstr "Estes magos teñen as muñecas atadas e non poden usar a súa maxia."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Mage_Shackled.cfg:26
msgid "kick"
msgstr "chute"

#. [female]: gender=female
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Mage_Shackled.cfg:35
msgid "female^Shackled Mage"
msgstr "Maga encadeada"

#. [unit_type]: id=Warrior of Light, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_Warrior_of_Light.cfg:4
msgid "Warrior of Light"
msgstr "Guerreiro da luz"

#. [unit_type]: id=Warrior of Light, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_Warrior_of_Light.cfg:21
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "After years of experience, the most devout of warriors develop vast "
#| "spiritual powers. By strict devotion to the path of the light, they can "
#| "call upon its aid to chase away the shadows of the night.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "No matter how foul the pit from whence darkness crawls, there too will "
#| "you find these champions of light working tirelessly to cleanse evil from "
#| "the troubled world in which they live."
msgid ""
"After years of experience, the most devout of warriors develop vast "
"spiritual powers. By strict devotion to the path of the light, they can call "
"upon its aid to chase away the shadows of the night."
msgstr ""
"Tras anos de experiencia, os guerreiros máis devotos desenvolven vastos "
"poderes espirituais. Mediante unha estrita devoción ao camiño da luz, poden "
"invocar a súa axuda para espantar as sombras da noite.\n"
"\n"
"Non importa o fétido que sexa o pozo do que sae a escuridade, alí tamén "
"atoparás estes campións da luz traballando incansablemente para limpar o mal "
"do mundo problemático no que viven."

#. [unit_type]: id=Warrior of Light, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_Warrior_of_Light.cfg:23
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "After years of experience, the most devout of warriors develop vast "
#| "spiritual powers. By strict devotion to the path of the light, they can "
#| "call upon its aid to chase away the shadows of the night.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "No matter how foul the pit from whence darkness crawls, there too will "
#| "you find these champions of light working tirelessly to cleanse evil from "
#| "the troubled world in which they live."
msgid ""
"No matter how foul the pit from whence darkness crawls, there too will you "
"find these champions of light working tirelessly to cleanse evil from the "
"troubled world in which they live."
msgstr ""
"Tras anos de experiencia, os guerreiros máis devotos desenvolven vastos "
"poderes espirituais. Mediante unha estrita devoción ao camiño da luz, poden "
"invocar a súa axuda para espantar as sombras da noite.\n"
"\n"
"Non importa o fétido que sexa o pozo do que sae a escuridade, alí tamén "
"atoparás estes campións da luz traballando incansablemente para limpar o mal "
"do mundo problemático no que viven."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_Warrior_of_Light.cfg:44
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_White_Warrior.cfg:42
msgid "lightbeam"
msgstr "raio de luz"

#. [unit_type]: id=White Warrior, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_White_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "White Warrior"
msgstr "Guerreiro branco"

#. [unit_type]: id=White Warrior, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_White_Warrior.cfg:20
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Not every white mage is content to merely wander the world, ministering "
#| "to sickness and injury. Magi of a more martial bent are often driven to "
#| "seek out villainy wherever it lies, delving into dark places and "
#| "cleansing them of evil.\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Armed with a blessed sword and channeling their light towards the mending "
#| "of their own wounds, such a warrior proves a potent ally against all "
#| "things unnatural."
msgid ""
"Not every white mage is content to merely wander the world, ministering to "
"sickness and injury. Magi of a more martial bent are often driven to seek "
"out villainy wherever it lies, delving into dark places and cleansing them "
"of evil."
msgstr ""
"Non todos os magos brancos se conforman con simplemente vagar polo mundo, "
"atendendo enfermidades e feridas. Os magos cunha inclinación máis marcial "
"adoitan ser impulsados a buscar a vileza onde queira que estea, afondando en "
"lugares escuros e limpándoos do mal.\n"
"\n"
"Armado cunha espada bendita e canalizando a súa luz cara á curación das súas "
"propias feridas, un guerreiro así demostra ser un potente aliado contra todo "
"o antinatural."

#. [unit_type]: id=White Warrior, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Human_Moremirmu_White_Warrior.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Armed with a blessed sword and channeling their light towards the mending of "
"their own wounds, such a warrior proves a potent ally against all things "
"unnatural."
msgstr ""
"Armado cunha espada bendicida e canalizando a súa luz para curar as súas "
"propias feridas, este guerreiro resulta un aliado poderoso contra todo o "
"antinatural."

#. [unit_type]: id=Caravan, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Caravan.cfg:5
msgid "Caravan"
msgstr "Caravana"

#. [unit_type]: id=Caravan, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Caravan.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Caravans are used to carry gold or supplies across long distances. Because "
"of the immense weight of the cargo this caravan carries, it is not nimble, "
"but the driver can still try to drive off attackers with his whip."
msgstr ""
"As caravanas úsanse para transportar ouro ou subministracións a longas "
"distancias. Debido ao inmenso peso da carga que transporta esta caravana, "
"non é áxil, pero o condutor aínda pode intentar repeler os atacantes co seu "
"látego."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Caravan.cfg:29
msgid "whip"
msgstr "látego"

#. [unit_type]: id=Granite Golem, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Golem.cfg:4
msgid "Granite Golem"
msgstr "Gólem de granito"

#. [unit_type]: id=Granite Golem, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Golem.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Towering over the battlefield, these enormous earthen constructs represent "
"the pinnacle of elemental magic. Though painfully clumsy and impossible to "
"transport across long distances, their vast bulk renders them nigh-immune to "
"most forms of damage."
msgstr ""
"Erguéndose sobre o campo de batalla, estas enormes construcións de terra "
"representan o cume da maxia elemental. Aínda que son dolorosamente torpes e "
"imposíbeis de transportar a grandes distancias, a súa enorme masa fainos "
"case inmunes á maioría das formas de dano."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Golem.cfg:65
msgid "fist"
msgstr "puño"

#. [unit_type]: id=Quintain, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Quintain.cfg:4
msgid "Quintain"
msgstr "Estafermo"

#. [unit_type]: id=Quintain, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Quintain.cfg:15
msgid "Quintains are used to practice swordplay and jousting on."
msgstr "Os quintainas úsanse para practicar o manexo da espada e o lanzamento."

#. [unit_type]: id=Wagon, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Wagon.cfg:5
msgid "Wagon"
msgstr ""
"A remota propiedade franca de Maghre, nos confines occidentais do Reino do "
"Noroeste, foi noutro tempo un lugar pacífico, cuxos habitantes descoñecían "
"en gran medida as idas e vindas do resto do mundo. As guerras nin o rumor de "
"guerras os afectaban. Nin sequera os mercadores eran vistos raramente, aínda "
"que as caravanas entre Aldril e Dan'Tonk podían enviar unha carreta cando as "
"chamaba a torre do faro."

#. [unit_type]: id=Wagon, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Wagon.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Caravans are used to carry gold or supplies across long distances. This one "
"is laden only lightly with hay, instead concealing Konrad and his soldiers."
msgstr ""
"As caravanas úsanse para transportar ouro ou subministracións a través de "
"longas distancias. Esta está cargada só lixeiramente con feno, polo que "
"agocha a Konrad e os seus soldados."

#. [unit_type]: id=Cave Wall, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Wall.cfg:5
msgid "Cave Wall"
msgstr "Parede da cova"

#. [unit_type]: id=Cave Wall, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Mechanical_Wall.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A crudely hewn cave wall, weakened by recent cave-ins. Experience gathered "
"from mining is of little use on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"Unha parede de cova toscamente labrada, debilitada por derrubamentos "
"recentes. A experiencia adquirida na minería é de pouca utilidade no campo "
"de batalla."

#. [unit_type]: id=Gryphlet, race=gryphon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Monster_Gryphlet.cfg:4
msgid "Gryphlet"
msgstr "Gryphlet"

#. [unit_type]: id=Gryphlet, race=gryphon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Monster_Gryphlet.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Juvenile gryphon are covered with white and gray feathers, softer and more "
"luxurious than those of their adult relatives. By the time they learn to "
"fly, most have already grown larger than a wolf, and are more than capable "
"of defending their nests from intruders."
msgstr ""
"Os grifos novos están cubertos de plumas brancas e grises, máis suaves e "
"luxosas que as dos seus parentes adultos. Cando aprenden a voar, a maioría "
"xa medraron máis ca un lobo e son máis que capaces de defender os seus niños "
"dos intrusos."

#. [unit_type]: id=Sleeping Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Monster_Sleeping_Gryphon.cfg:4
msgid "Sleeping Gryphon"
msgstr "Grifo durmido"

#. [unit_type]: id=Sleeping Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Monster_Sleeping_Gryphon.cfg:20
msgid "Shhhh! The gryphon is sleeping! You’d better not wake it up!"
msgstr ""
"Garda silencio! O grifón anda a durmir, será mellor que non o espertes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Barrow Wight, race=undead
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Undead_Horse_Barrow_Wight.cfg:4
msgid "Barrow Wight"
msgstr "Espectro da mámoa"

#. [unit_type]: id=Barrow Wight, race=undead
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Undead_Horse_Barrow_Wight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Perpetually haunted by the fading memory of its former life, a Barrow Wight "
"wanders aimlessly in a delirium of darkness and despair. Their chill essence "
"is shrouded behind cloak and bone, shielding them from most magic."
msgstr ""
"Perpetuamente perseguido pola esvaecida memoria da súa antiga vida, un "
"Barrow Wight deambula sen rumbo nun delirio de escuridade e desesperación. A "
"súa esencia fría está envolta detrás da capa e dos ósos, protegiéndoos da "
"maioría da maxia."

#. [resistance]: id=shroud
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Undead_Horse_Barrow_Wight.cfg:33
msgid "shroud"
msgstr "sudario"

#. [resistance]: id=shroud
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Undead_Horse_Barrow_Wight.cfg:34
msgid "While defending, this unit has 50% fire and arcane resistance."
msgstr ""
"Mentres se defende, esta unidade ten un 50% de resistencia ao lume e aos "
"arcanos."

#. [unit_type]: id=Vampire Lady, gender=female, race=undead, description=
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Undead_Vampire_Lady.cfg:4
msgid "female^Vampire Lady"
msgstr "vampiresa"

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/units/Undead_Vampire_Lady.cfg:27
msgid "blood kiss"
msgstr "bico de sangue"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/bigmap.cfg:22
msgid "It is spring; the next scenario will have normal days and nights."
msgstr "É primavera; o seguinte escenario terá días e noites normais."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/bigmap.cfg:28
msgid "It is summer; the next scenario will have unusually long days."
msgstr "É verán; o seguinte escenario terá días inusualmente longos."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/bigmap.cfg:34
msgid "It is autumn; the next scenario will have normal days and nights."
msgstr "É outono; o seguinte escenario terá días e noites normais."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/bigmap.cfg:40
msgid "It is winter; the next scenario will have unusually short days."
msgstr "É inverno; o seguinte escenario terá días inusualmente curtos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/bigmap.cfg:67
msgid ""
"This port has many small boats for us to use! I won’t be able to travel "
"through deep water, but I can certainly reach the coastal islands and reef."
msgstr ""
"Este porto ten moitas barquiños pequenos para que os usemos! Non poderei "
"viaxar por augas profundas, pero sen dúbida poderei chegar ás illas "
"costeiras e ao arrecife."

#. [time]: id=spring{NOWEATHER}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/schedule.cfg:176
msgid "Spring"
msgstr "Primavera"

#. [time]: id=summer{NOWEATHER}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/schedule.cfg:188
msgid "Summer"
msgstr "Verán"

#. [time]: id=autumn{NOWEATHER}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/schedule.cfg:200
msgid "Autumn"
msgstr "Outono"

#. [time]: id=winter{NOWEATHER}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/schedule.cfg:212
msgid "Winter"
msgstr "Inverno"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:50
msgid ""
"I hope Delfador is well. We could have used his help in this battle, but I "
"know what he’s doing is important."
msgstr ""
"Espero que Delfador estea ben. Poderiamos ter necesitado a súa axuda nesta "
"batalla, pero sei que o que está a facer é importante."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:54
msgid ""
"The attack on the Aethenwood was bad enough. Elensefar must surely be even "
"more fierce..."
msgstr ""
"O ataque ao Bosque de Aethen xa era bastante malo. Elensefar debe ser aínda "
"máis feroz..."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:71
msgid ""
"I hope our rewards from this battle are worth the time we’re spending to "
"fight it. We may have plenty of time to roam the Great Continent right now, "
"but we won’t always. We should make every battle count."
msgstr ""
"Espero que as recompensas desta batalla paguen o tempo que dedicamos a "
"loitala. Pode que teñamos tempo de sobra para percorrer o Gran Continente "
"agora mesmo, pero non sempre o teremos. Deberíamos aproveitar cada batalla."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:86
msgid "My hand tingles with power... Burn in the name of the kings of Wesnoth!"
msgstr "A miña man formiguea de poder... Arde en nome dos reis de Wesnoth!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:102
msgid ""
"I am glad to see that you have been taking good care of my familiar, Konrad. "
"Blackwing and I have been through many trials together."
msgstr ""
"Alégrome de ver que coidastes ben do meu familiar, Konrad. Blackwing e eu "
"pasamos por moitas probas xuntos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:106
msgid ""
"Thank you for entrusting me with him! He has become a valuable member of our "
"team."
msgstr ""
"Grazas por confialo en min! Converteuse nun membro valioso do noso equipo."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:119
msgid ""
"Seimus, I am glad that you still stand with us. I fear you would have gone "
"down a dark path had Konrad and I not come to Alduin that day."
msgstr ""
"Seimus, alégrome de que aínda esteas con nós. Temo que terías seguido un "
"camiño escuro se Konrad e eu non viñésemos a Alduin ese día."

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:123
msgid ""
"Oh yes, don’t remind me. I’m trying not to think too much about all that."
msgstr ""
"Ah, si, non mo lembres. Estou a tentar non pensar demasiado en todo iso."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:141
msgid "Fool girl! You shall meet the same fate as did your brother!"
msgstr "Rapaza tola! Correrás o mesmo destino que o teu irmán!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:162
msgid ""
"Lord Kalenz, I am grateful for your help. But when you made your journey to "
"come join me, could you not have brought an elvish army along with you? I "
"know you’re a powerful lord and greatly loved by your people."
msgstr ""
"Señor Kalenz, agradezo a túa axuda. Pero cando fixeches a túa viaxe para vir "
"comigo, non poderías ter traído un exército élfico contigo? Sei que es un "
"señor poderoso e moi querido polo teu pobo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:166
msgid ""
"Even only a few elvish warriors could have made a great difference in our "
"quest! Your kin are many, and I know firsthand their great skill at sword "
"and bow."
msgstr ""
"Incluso uns poucos guerreiros élficos poderían ter marcado unha gran "
"diferenza na nosa misión! Os vosos parentes son moitos, e coñezo de primeira "
"man a súa gran habilidade coa espada e o arco."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:170
msgid ""
"Not so many as we once were, Konrad. And one elf alone can quietly travel "
"through human lands far easier than can an army or war-band."
msgstr ""
"Non tantos como antes, Konrad. E un só elfo pode viaxar tranquilamente polas "
"terras humanas moito máis facilmente que un exército ou unha banda de guerra."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. this is a hint that there's a special reward if you bringing Kalenz to Lintanir forest
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:175
msgid ""
"But should we ever make our way east back to my home in the Lintanir, my "
"subjects will certainly be ready to offer gold and supplies. Especially "
"after Asheviere’s crimes in the Aethenwood. A victory for you is a victory "
"for all elves."
msgstr ""
"Pero se algunha vez volvemos cara ao leste, ao meu fogar no Lintanir, os "
"meus súbditos estarán dispostos a ofrecerme ouro e provisións. Especialmente "
"despois dos crimes de Asheviere no Bosque de Aethen. Unha vitoria para ti é "
"unha vitoria para todos os elfos."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:189
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Kalenz, did you ever know my father? Delfador has told me many things "
#| "about the Prince Arand, and Delfador’s regrets regarding him. I feel I "
#| "would very much have liked to have met him."
msgid ""
"Kalenz, did you ever know my father? Delfador has told me many things about "
"Prince Arand, and Delfador’s regrets regarding him. I feel I would very much "
"have liked to have met him."
msgstr ""
"Kalenz, coñeceches algunha vez ao meu pai? Delfador contoume moitas cousas "
"sobre o príncipe Arand e os arrepentimentos de Delfador con respecto a el. "
"Sinto que me gustaría moito coñecelo."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz knows that Arand is not Konrad's father. Konrad does not. Technically, everything Kalenz says here is true.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:194
msgid ""
"Your father? No, I did not know your father, nor any of your family. "
"Delfador and I have spoken about your parentage, and there is nothing for me "
"to add."
msgstr ""
"O teu pai? Non, non coñecía ao teu pai, nin a ningún membro da túa familia. "
"Delfador e eu falamos sobre a túa estirpe, e non teño nada máis que engadir."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:213
msgid ""
"It is sad to see what Wesnoth has fallen to, Konrad. Do not make the same "
"mistakes as did my people."
msgstr ""
"É triste ver o que causou Wesnoth, Konrad. Non cometas os mesmos erros que "
"fixo a miña xente."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. Konrad speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:218
msgid ""
"I know something of the history of the elves. Delfador says that you once "
"lived as if in a dream, untroubled by even the rumor of strife. That sounds "
"an envious life."
msgstr ""
"Sei algo da historia dos elfos. Delfador di que outrora viviches coma nun "
"soño, sen que che perturbasen nin sequera o rumor de conflitos. Parece unha "
"vida envexosa."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:224
msgid ""
"Indeed. But then man came. And with man came the orcs, chasing after the "
"very sceptre that your cousin now holds."
msgstr ""
"De feito. Pero entón chegou o home. E co home viñeron os orcos, perseguindo "
"o mesmo cetro que agora ostenta o teu curmán."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:230
msgid ""
"Indeed. But then man came. And with man came the orcs, chasing after that "
"very sceptre you now hold."
msgstr ""
"De feito. Pero entón chegou o home. E co home viñeron os orcos, perseguindo "
"ese mesmo cetro que agora tes."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:236
msgid ""
"In those days we fought battles great and terrible. Armies of elves marched "
"across the open plain to make war, first against the orcs, then against each "
"other. Now so few of us remain."
msgstr ""
"Naqueles tempos librabamos batallas grandes e terribles. Exércitos de elfos "
"marchaban pola chaira aberta para facer a guerra, primeiro contra os orcos, "
"despois entre si. Agora quedan tan poucos de nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:242
msgid ""
"The Aethenwood is younger; I am glad that many of their number walk with "
"you, Konrad. But some scars do not heal. I hope your civil war will end "
"better than did mine."
msgstr ""
"O Bosque de Aethen é máis novo; alégrome de que moitos deles camiñen "
"contigo, Konrad. Pero algunhas cicatrices non curan. Espero que a túa guerra "
"civil remate mellor que a miña."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. Kalenz speaks about the events of LoW
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:248
msgid ""
"The Aethenwood is younger; I am glad that you were raised among them, "
"Konrad. But some scars do not heal. I hope your civil war will end better "
"than did mine."
msgstr ""
"O Bosque de Aethen é máis novo; alégrome de que te criaran entre eles, "
"Konrad. Pero algunhas cicatrices non curan. Espero que a túa guerra civil "
"remate mellor que a miña."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. Delfador and Chantal first met in The Deceiver's Gambit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:266
msgid ""
"Chantal, it has been a long time since we first met in the Lintanir. I have "
"grown old. You are as young as ever."
msgstr ""
"Chantal, pasou moito tempo dende que nos coñecemos no Lintanir. Envellecín. "
"Ti es tan nova coma sempre."

#. [message]: speaker=Chantal
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:270
msgid ""
"I am young in body, at least. Do I detect a hint of jealousy in the voice of "
"Delfador the Great? Hah — I am glad to have your company once again."
msgstr ""
"Son novo de corpo, polo menos. Detecto algún indicio de celos na voz de "
"Delfador o Grande? Ha... Alégrome de ter a túa compañía unha vez máis."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:274
msgid ""
"Jealousy? Banish the thought. It is good to travel with you as well. I am "
"sure you will enjoy getting to know our lively band of warriors."
msgstr ""
"Celos? Desbota ese pensamento. Tamén é bo viaxar contigo. Seguro que gozarás "
"coñecendo á nosa animada banda de guerreiros."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:290
msgid ""
"Haldiel, you fought in Garard’s war against the orcs. Did you know my father?"
msgstr ""
"Haldiel, loitaches na guerra de Garard contra os orcos. Coñeciches ao meu "
"pai?"

#. [message]: speaker=Haldiel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:294
msgid "Prince Arand? No, I was a member of King Garard’s Royal Cavalry."
msgstr "O príncipe Arand? Non, eu era membro da Cabalería Real do rei Garard."

#. [message]: speaker=Haldiel
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:298
msgid ""
"I was but a young man when your father fell, barely come of age. Garard "
"bestowed much favor upon the Horse Clans, but only so long as we trained "
"ever-greater numbers of young men for his cavalry."
msgstr ""
"Era pouco máis ca un mozo cando o teu pai morreu. Garard favoreceu moito aos "
"Clans dos Cabalos, pero só mentres adestrabamos cada vez máis mozos para a "
"súa cabalería."

#. [message]: id=Haldiel,Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:317
msgid "Sir Kaylan sends his regards, Lords of the Clans."
msgstr "Sir Kaylan envía os seus saúdos, Señores dos Clans."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:321
msgid ""
"We do not send ours. Kaylan defies the will of the Horse Clans by supporting "
"the upstart prince. What of his duty to his kin?"
msgstr ""
"Nós non enviamos os nosos. Kaylan desafía a vontade dos Clans dos Cabalos ao "
"apoiar ao príncipe usurpador. Que hai do seu deber coa súa xente?"

#. [message]: id=Haldiel,Simyr
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:325
msgid ""
"What of justice for Garard? What of our honor? Once, the Clans stood for "
"those ideals. How far you have fallen."
msgstr ""
"E que hai da xustiza para Garard? E da nosa honra? Houbo un tempo no que os "
"Clans defendían eses ideais. Canto caestes."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:329
msgid "Bah! Impudence! We have nothing more to speak about."
msgstr "Bah! Insolencia! Non temos nada máis que falar."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:349
msgid ""
"I’m grateful for your commitment, Elrian. Few are accepted into Alduin, and "
"even fewer choose to leave it. You gave up everything to fight alongside me."
msgstr ""
"Estou agradecido polo teu compromiso, Elrian. Poucos son aceptados en "
"Alduin, e aínda menos deciden abandonalo. Renunciaches a todo para loitar ao "
"meu lado."

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#. this is a hint that there's a special event if Konrad brings Elrian to Tath
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:357
msgid ""
"To be honest, studying magic was more my family’s dream than mine. My "
"grandparents are “new money”; wealthy merchants from the east side of Tath. "
"(As an aside — we should visit them if we’re ever in the area.)"
msgstr ""
"Para ser sincero, estudar maxia era máis o soño da miña familia ca o meu. Os "
"meus avós son “novos ricos”; comerciantes acomodados da parte leste de Tath. "
"(Por certo — deberiamos visitalos se algunha vez pasamos por alí.)"

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:363
msgid ""
"To be honest, studying magic was more my family’s dream than mine. My "
"grandparents are “new money”; wealthy merchants from the east side of Tath. "
"You’ve already been there and met them."
msgstr ""
"Para ser sincero, estudar maxia era máis o soño da miña familia ca o meu. Os "
"meus avós son “novos ricos”; comerciantes acomodados da parte leste de Tath. "
"Xa estiveches alí e coñecíchos."

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:369
msgid ""
"They sent their eldest grandson — me — to Alduin in the hopes of building "
"connections and making inroads with Wesnoth’s more established elites. I "
"suppose that hasn’t really worked out, seeing as I’m now a rebel and all."
msgstr ""
"Enviaron ao seu neto maior — a min — a Alduin coa esperanza de establecer "
"contactos e gañar influencia entre as elites máis consolidadas do Noroeste. "
"Supoño que iso non saíu moi ben, tendo en conta que agora son un rebelde."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:386
msgid ""
"That “Provost Seimus” we fought at Alduin seemed like a powerful mage. It’s "
"a shame he decided to side with Asheviere instead of joining us as you did, "
"Elrian."
msgstr ""
"Ese “Preboste Seimus” contra o que loitamos en Alduin parecía un mago "
"poderoso. É unha mágoa que decidise poñerse do lado de Asheviere en vez de "
"unirse a nós, como fixeches ti, Elrian."

#. [message]: speaker=Elrian
#. this is a hint that Konrad can recruit Seimus if he brings Delfador to speak with him. That can't happen in this playthrough anymore; only on a future playthrough.
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:391
msgid ""
"I think Seimus is a good man, deep down. But he’s convinced himself that the "
"only way Alduin can survive is by bending the knee. It would probably take a "
"talking-to from Delfador himself to convince him otherwise..."
msgstr ""
"Creo que Seimus é boa persoa, no fondo. Pero convenceuse de que a única "
"forma de que Alduin sobreviva é someterse. Probablemente só Delfador podería "
"facelo cambiar de idea…"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:407
msgid ""
"Hello Seimus, my old master. I’ll bet you regret expelling me now, don’t you!"
msgstr ""
"Ola Seimus, meu vello mestre. Seguro que agora te arrepentirás de "
"expulsarme, non si?"

#. [message]: speaker=Seimus
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:411
msgid ""
"Err, are you— who are you again? Many aspire to join the ranks of the magi, "
"but few have the skill."
msgstr ""
"Eh, es ti... quen es ti outra vez? Moitos aspiran a unirse ás filas dos "
"magos, pero poucos teñen a habilidade."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:434
msgid ""
"Moremirmu, I’ve met White Mages before, but never someone quite like you. "
"Where do you hail from?"
msgstr ""
"Moremirmu, xa coñecín Magos Brancos antes, pero nunca a alguén coma ti. De "
"onde es?"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#. this is a hint that there's a special event for bringing Moremirmu to the monastery in the Gryphon Mountains
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:439
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "From the great monastery of the seal, good Konrad! It is by the grace of "
#| "the Light that I was rescued and raised there, high in the Gryphon "
#| "Mountains."
msgid ""
"From the great monastery of the seal, good Konrad! It is by the grace of the "
"Light that I was rescued and raised there, high in the Gryphon Mountains. We "
"ought to visit there someday."
msgstr ""
"Do gran mosteiro do selo, bo Konrad! É pola graza da Luz que fun rescatado e "
"criado alí, no alto das Montañas Grifón."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:443
msgid ""
"Now, I have taken up the sword and ventured forth in search of evil to "
"smite. And lo! You and I united, and lo! Now we quest together against the "
"evils of Asheviere."
msgstr ""
"Agora, empuñei a espada e aventureime na procura do mal que castigar. E "
"velaquí! Ti e eu unímonos, e velaquí! Agora loitamos xuntos contra os males "
"de Asheviere."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:456
msgid ""
"What strange magic you wield, Kalenz. It is light, yet it is not of the "
"Light! What manner of unhallowed spells do you weave?"
msgstr ""
"Que estraña maxia manexas, Kalenz. É luz, pero non é da Luz! Que clase de "
"conxuros profanos teces?"

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:460
msgid ""
"This is magic of the faerie. It is similar in some ways to your Light, but "
"it is natural to the elves. Few are the male elves permitted to learn it. "
"And no outsiders, for it is an art inherited only by my kind."
msgstr ""
"Esta é a maxia das fadas. É semellante en certos aspectos á túa Luz, pero é "
"natural para os elfos. Poucos son os elfos masculinos aos que se lles "
"permite aprendela. E ningún forasteiro, pois é unha arte herdada só polo meu "
"pobo."

#. [message]: speaker=Kalenz
#. this is a reference to the events of LoW, where Kalenz gained his magic after drinking an invisibility potion brewed by Crelanu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:465
msgid ""
"Although I gained my magic in a different manner than do most of my kind, it "
"is now as much a part of me as is my blood."
msgstr ""
"Aínda que obtiven a miña maxia dun xeito diferente ao da maioría da miña "
"especie, agora forma parte de min tanto como o meu sangue."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:478
msgid ""
"You wield your lightning with a nigh-supernatural skill, Delfador. Truly you "
"have been blessed by the Light."
msgstr ""
"Empuñas o teu raio cunha habilidade case sobrenatural, Delfador. De verdade "
"fuches bendicido pola Luz."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:482
msgid ""
"But what of your skill with the sword? Our foes are not content to loiter at "
"a distance and await their destruction. Enemies of evil must stand ready to "
"fight with steel!"
msgstr ""
"Pero que hai da túa habilidade coa espada? Os nosos inimigos non se "
"contentan con vagar á distancia e agardar a súa destrución. Os inimigos do "
"mal deben estar preparados para loitar co aceiro!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:487
msgid ""
"I need little strength of body, Moremirmu, for I wield the magical flaming "
"sword of the Lintanir. A mighty boon, and one I am well grateful for."
msgstr ""
"Necesito pouca forza corporal, Moremirmu, porque empuño a espada máxica e "
"flamexante do Lintanir. Unha gran bendición, e pola que estou moi agradecido."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:492
msgid ""
"I am an old man, Moremirmu. My magic serves me where my body has failed. I "
"shall trust in you, Konrad, and our allies to carry the steel."
msgstr ""
"Son un home vello, Moremirmu. A miña maxia sérveme onde o meu corpo fallou. "
"Confiarei en ti, Konrad, e nos nosos aliados para levar o aceiro."

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:511
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Acceede not your souls to the unclean, my fellow warriors! We shall "
#| "cleanse these dead in holy fire!"
msgid ""
"Accede not your souls to the unclean, my fellow warriors! We shall cleanse "
"these dead in holy fire!"
msgstr ""
"Non entreguedes as vosas almas aos impuros, meus compañeiros guerreiros! "
"Purgaremos estes mortos en lume sagrado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Moremirmu
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:530
msgid ""
"You have turned from the Light, men of Wesnoth! Hark to my words! Atone for "
"your crimes! Return to the Light, or soon shall come the black soot over "
"Weldyn and the death of all men!"
msgstr ""
"Abandonastes a Luz, homes de Wesnoth! Escoitade as miñas palabras! Reparade "
"polos vosos crimes! Volved á Luz, ou pronto chegará o negro follín sobre "
"Weldyn e a morte de todos os homes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#. Harper and Konrad discuss the events of Liberty
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:549
msgid ""
"Konrad, how come you never asked me just how we all came to live on the "
"Three Sisters? It be a powerful story, an’ one that matters for how you’re "
"fightin’ Asheviere too! I’ve been excited to tell you!"
msgstr ""
"Konrad, por que non me preguntaches como chegamos a vivir nas Tres Irmás? É "
"unha historia poderosa, e unha que tamén importa para como loitas contra "
"Asheviere! Tiña moitas ganas de contarcho!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#. Harper and Konrad discuss the events of Liberty
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:554
msgid ""
"Oh, the others already explained it to me! Asheviere took over, you ran from "
"your homes, destroyed Halstead, and ended up on the islands. Just like that, "
"right?"
msgstr ""
"Ah, os outros xa mo explicaron! Asheviere tomou o control, fuxistes das "
"vosas casas, destruístes Halstead e acabastes nas illas. Así, sen máis, non "
"si?"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:558
msgid ""
"... err, but you can still tell me again. Your parts especially, Harper! I’d "
"always be happy to listen."
msgstr ""
"... eh, pero aínda podes repetir. Os teus papeis, especialmente, Harper! "
"Sempre estaría encantado de escoitarte."

#. [message]: speaker=Somf
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:571
msgid ""
"You ne’er seemed one for princes or kings, Harper. We fought pretty hard t’ "
"get away from th’ queen. Why’re you fightin’ for this “Konrad” now, an’ "
"draggin’ me into it too?"
msgstr ""
"Nunca che parecías un tipo de príncipes ou reis, Harper. Luitamos moi duro "
"para afastarnos da raíña. Por que agora estás loitando por este \"Konrad\" e "
"me arrastras a min tamén?"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:575
msgid ""
"We never fought just to get away. Baldras fought fer a better life fer all "
"of us, an’ fer everyone!"
msgstr ""
"Nunca loitamos só para fuxir. Baldras loitou por unha vida mellor para todos "
"nós e para todos!"

#. [message]: speaker=Harper
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:579
msgid ""
"Konrad’s a good person. He wants what’s best fer everyone too. And he saved "
"my life from a lich! That’s gotta be worth somethin’."
msgstr ""
"Konrad é unha boa persoa. Tamén quere o mellor para todos. E salvoume a vida "
"dun lich! Iso ten que valer algo."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. stay in your graves, you rotting heaps of bones
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:600
msgid "Stay in yer graves, ye rottin’ heaps o’ bones!"
msgstr "Quédate nas vosas tumbas, moreas de ósos podres!"

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. ah, insulting these dead ones is just no fun. They can't understand me...
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:607
msgid ""
"Ah, insultin’ these dead’uns is jus’ no fun. They cannae understand me..."
msgstr "Ah, insulinar a estes mortos non ten graza. Non me poden entender..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. And stay down!
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:626
msgid "An’ stay down!"
msgstr "E queda aí!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:638
msgid ""
"Ulfdain, how did you find yourself in Wesnoth? Delfador always told me that "
"the dwarves preferred to keep their own company in Knalga, except for their "
"human friends at the Doors."
msgstr ""
"Ulfdain, como te atopaches en Wesnoth? Delfador sempre me dicía que os "
"ananos preferían manter a súa propia compañía en Knalga, agás cos seus "
"amigos humanos nas Portas."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:642
msgid ""
"Aye, tha’s true. Not the most outgoin’ o’ folks, we dwarves ain’t. Heads "
"harder than a’ troll’s half th’ time, and more stubborn too! But t’ tell ye "
"the truth, there ain’t much hope left in Knalga, least not that I’ve heard "
"about."
msgstr ""
"Si, iso é certo. Non somos os máis extrovertidos da xente, non si? Teñen a "
"cabeza máis dura que a dun trol a metade das veces, e son máis teimudos "
"tamén! Pero, a verdade, non queda moita esperanza en Knalga, polo menos que "
"eu teña oído falar."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:646
msgid ""
"Ah’m ashamed to admit it, Konrad, but I left. An Ulfserker ain’t afeared o’ "
"no troll or orc, but watchin’ my home slowly fall to pieces around me? My "
"friends dyin’ one by one? I fled our dyin’ home in search o’ a better life "
"elsewhere."
msgstr ""
"Dáme vergoña recoñecelo, Konrad, pero marchei. Un Ulfserker non lle teme a "
"ningún trol nin a ningún orco, pero ver como a miña casa se esfarela "
"lentamente ao meu redor? Os meus amigos morrendo un por un? Fuxín da nosa "
"casa moribunda na procura dunha vida mellor noutro lugar."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:650
msgid ""
"An ye see how that ended up. A great galumphing gallow-fool I’ve been. If ye "
"hadn’t helped me miners and I when ye did..."
msgstr ""
"E xa vedes como acabou iso. Fun un gran parvo e tolo. Se non me axudaras a "
"min, os mineiros, e a min cando o fixeches..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:663
msgid ""
"This fight’s good an’ all, but when’re we getting t’ Weldyn? Ah cannae wait "
"to show tha’ dew-beatin’ gobermouch excuse for a queen exactly what I think "
"o’ her!"
msgstr ""
"Esta loita está ben e tal, pero cando chegaremos a Weldyn? Non podo esperar "
"para amosar a esa desculpa de raíña charra e que non serve de nada polo que "
"penso dela!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:668
msgid ""
"We shall find ourselves in Weldyn sooner rather than later, I suspect. We "
"have come a long way together since you first joined us, Ulfdain — now even "
"the princess is on our side!"
msgstr ""
"Supoño que nos atoparemos en Weldyn máis cedo que tarde. Xa percorrimos un "
"longo camiño xuntos desde que te uniches a nós por primeira vez, Ulfdain — "
"agora mesmo ata a princesa está do noso lado!"

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:673
msgid ""
"I appreciate the enthusiasm, but we’re in no state to confront Asheviere "
"anytime soon! For now we should focus on surviving and building up our "
"strength."
msgstr ""
"Aprecio o entusiasmo, pero non estamos en condicións de enfrontarnos a "
"Asheviere en breve! Por agora deberiamos centrarnos en sobrevivir e en "
"reforzar as nosas forzas."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:690
msgid ""
"You are an alchemist, Jeniver? That is a brave choice, for your craft is not "
"looked kindly upon by Alduin. There are some who think it hogwash and "
"superstition."
msgstr ""
"¿Es alquimista, Jeniver? Iso é unha elección valente, pois o teu oficio non "
"goza de boa fama ante Alduin. Hai quen o considera parvada e superstición."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:694
msgid ""
"Superstition?! No, no, no! That’s a common misconception, born of— of— dumb "
"ignorance! Alchemy is just— it’s the future! There’s so much for us to "
"learn, it’s—"
msgstr ""
"Superstición?! Non, non, non! É unha idea errónea moi común, nacida de... "
"de... estupida ignorancia! A alquimia é simplemente... é o futuro! Temos "
"tanto que aprender, é..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:698
msgid ""
"No offense meant, my lady. Perhaps we can discuss your studies in more depth "
"at another time."
msgstr ""
"Sen intención de ofender, miña señora. Quizais poidamos falar dos seus "
"estudos con máis profundidade noutro momento."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:728
msgid ""
"Oh! Is that another giant spider? I could use some more spider poison, err, "
"venom — I suppose it’s not really poison — for my blowdarts. Can you kill "
"one for me?"
msgstr ""
"Ah! É outra araña xigante? Poderíame vir ben un pouco máis de veleno de "
"araña, eh, veleno (supoño que en realidade non é veleno) para os meus "
"dardos. Podes matarme unha?"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:736
msgid "Wonderful, the spider is dead! Just, ah, just give me a moment here..."
msgstr "Marabilloso, a araña está morta! Só, eh, só déixame un momento aquí..."

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:818
msgid "Improved Blowgun"
msgstr "Flauta de vento mellorada"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:819
msgid "Jeniver’s “<i>blowgun</i>” attack can now be used twice each turn!"
msgstr ""
"O ataque de \" <i>cerbatana</i> \" de Jeniver agora pódese usar dúas veces "
"por quenda!"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:839
msgid "Improved Flashpowder"
msgstr "Flashpowder mellorado"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:840
msgid "Jeniver’s “<i>flashpowder</i>” attack can now be used twice each turn!"
msgstr ""
"O ataque \" <i>pólvora</i> \" de Jeniver agora pódese usar dúas veces por "
"quenda!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:857
msgid ""
"Konrad, I had no idea you had a troll with you! What was his name? Dosh? "
"Dosh, CAN. YOU. UNDERSTAND. ME?"
msgstr ""
"Konrad, non tiña nin idea de que levabas un trol contigo! Como se chamaba? "
"Dosh? Dosh, PODES. ENTENDER. MIN?"

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:861
msgid "Dere sometin’ wrong wit’ your head, girl? You talkin’ real funny."
msgstr "Tes algo mal na cabeza, rapaza? Estás falando moi raro."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:865
msgid ""
"Oh! Oh, well then, Dosh, can I trouble you for a few pieces of your flesh? "
"It’ll grow back, I’m sure. I have this, err, theory I want to try with "
"regeneration, you see..."
msgstr ""
"Oh! Oh, pois entón, Dosh, podo molestarte para conseguir uns anacos da túa "
"carne? Seguro que volverá crecer. Teño esta, eh, teoría que quero probar coa "
"rexeneración, xa ves..."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:869
msgid ""
"You want some pieces of Dosh? Dere definitely sometin’ wrong wit’ your head. "
"But okay. Here you go."
msgstr ""
"Queres algúns anacos de Dosh? Sen dúbida hai algo mal na túa cabeza. Pero "
"vale. Aquí os tes."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:893
msgid ""
"Oh, a troll! Err, Konrad, you know, they say trolls have amazing powers of "
"regeneration... in fact, I have something of a theory about the curative "
"properties of troll-flesh..."
msgstr ""
"Oh, un trol! Eh, Konrad, sabes? Din que os trols teñen un poder de "
"rexeneración incrible... de feito, teño unha especie de teoría sobre as "
"propiedades curativas da carne de trol..."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:904
msgid ""
"The troll’s dead? Oh, wonderful— yes, yes there’s something I’ve been "
"meaning to try with regeneration..."
msgstr ""
"O trol está morto? Oh, marabilloso—si, si, hai algo que tiña pensado probar "
"coa rexeneración..."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:919
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<span size='x-small'>Mix with one vial of frostbone... infusion of "
#| "boar... heat over an open flame...</span>"
msgid ""
"Mix with one vial of frostbone... infusion of boar... heat over an open "
"flame..."
msgstr ""
"<span size='x-small'>Mesturar cun vial de óso de xeada... infusión de "
"xabaril... quentar sobre unha chama aberta...</span>"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:932
msgid "Oh! Oh Light, that’s foul! That stings! It blew up in my face!"
msgstr "Oh! Oh Luz, que noxo! Iso pica! Estoupoume na cara!"

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:936
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I was— well, I was <b><i>trying</i></b> to unlock the secrets of the "
#| "rapid curation of venoms; the curing of poison and bolstering of the body "
#| "and so-on. But trollish regeneration seems, err, well—  incompatible with "
#| "my methods."
msgid ""
"I was— well, I was <b><i>trying</i></b> to unlock the secrets of the rapid "
"curation of venoms; the curing of poison and bolstering of the body and so-"
"on. But trollish regeneration seems, err, well— incompatible with my methods."
msgstr ""
"Eu estaba... bueno, eu estaba a <b><i>tentar</i></b> desentrañar os segredos "
"da rápida curación dos velenos; a curación do veleno e o fortalecemento do "
"corpo e demais. Pero a rexeneración trol parece, eh, bueno... incompatible "
"cos meus métodos."

#. [message]: speaker=Jeniver
#. this is a hint that Jeniver will get a bonus if you bring her to Underground Channels (with Woses)
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:941
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Although, if you could someday find some other regenerating creature for "
#| "me to take a sample of..."
msgid ""
"Although, if you could someday find some other species of regenerating "
"creature for me to take a sample of..."
msgstr ""
"Aínda que, se algún día puideses atopar algunha outra criatura rexeneradora "
"da que eu poida coller unha mostra..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ulfdain
#. "from below" implying that dwarves believe that they end up in some underworld after death
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:971
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Ah can’t believe yer expecting me to fight side-by-side with some half-"
#| "wit, bog-handed, mumblecrest o’ a troll, Konrad. I kin feel my ancesters "
#| "laughin’ at me from below!"
msgid ""
"Ah can’t believe yer expecting me to fight side-by-side with some half-wit, "
"bog-handed, mumblecrest o’ a troll, Konrad. I kin feel my ancestors laughin’ "
"at me from below!"
msgstr ""
"Non podo crer que esperes que loite cóbado con cóbado cun trol parvo, de "
"mans pantanosas e con crista de burla, Konrad. Case sinto os meus "
"antepasados rindo de min dende abaixo!"

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:975
msgid ""
"Hey, who you calling... uhh... thing. Not like Dosh been killin’ hundred "
"dwarves or nothin’ like that."
msgstr ""
"Ei, a quen chamas... eh... cousa. Non é como se Dosh estivese matando cen "
"ananos nin nada diso."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:979
msgid ""
"Dosh only ever kill two, small ones, an’ dey not even fight back. Dwarves "
"not hard to kill. You probably not hard either."
msgstr ""
"Os ananos só matan dous, os pequenos, e nin sequera se defenden. Os ananos "
"non son difíciles de matar. Probablemente ti tampouco."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:983
msgid ""
"Enough, both of you! Behave, or you’ll find yourselves needing to fight me, "
"too."
msgstr ""
"Xa abonda, os dous! Compórtense ben, ou vós tamén teredes que loitar comigo."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:996
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am not well-accustomed to fighting alongside trolls, Dosh. In the past "
#| "I have fought against your kind instead. I hope there will be no tension "
#| "betwewen us."
msgid ""
"I am not well-accustomed to fighting alongside trolls, Dosh. In the past I "
"have fought against your kind instead. I hope there will be no tension "
"between us."
msgstr ""
"Non estou moi afeito a loitar xunto a trolls, Dosh. No pasado loitei contra "
"a túa especie. Espero que non haxa tensión entre nós."

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1000
msgid ""
"Nah, Dosh excited to be fightin’ with Delfador. Da orcs and trolls all be "
"telling stories about all da big battles you fought back when. Now soon dey "
"telling stories about Dosh too!"
msgstr ""
"Non, Dosh está emocionado de loitar con Delfador. Os orcos e os troles "
"estarán contando historias sobre as grandes batallas que libraches antes. "
"Agora pronto tamén contarán historias sobre Dosh!"

#. [message]: speaker=Dosh
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1015
msgid "You bad troll, bad! Bad trolls be getting hit with big sticks!"
msgstr "Ti, troll malvado, malo!   Aos trolls malos bótanlles paus grandes!"

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1032
msgid ""
"I never thought I’d be fighting alongside the very wizard who killed my "
"brother. I never had a chance to meet him. Thanks to you."
msgstr ""
"Nunca pensei que estaría loitando xunto ao mesmo mago que matou ao meu "
"irmán. Nunca tiven a oportunidade de coñecelo. Grazas a ti."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1036
msgid ""
"You never had a chance to meet your father, either. I think Garard would be "
"proud of you. You have his skill with the sword."
msgstr ""
"Tampouco tivo ocasión de coñecer ao teu pai. Creo que Garard estaría "
"orgulloso de ti. Tes a súa habilidade coa espada."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1040
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "But as for your brother... I have no doubt that Asheviere puffed Eldred "
#| "up with flattery and lies, but it was his hand and his hand alone that "
#| "slew the old king. Your brother sealed his own fate that day, Lisar."
msgid ""
"But as for your brother... I have no doubt that Asheviere puffed Eldred up "
"with flattery and lies, but it was his hand and his hand alone that slew the "
"old king. Your brother sealed his own fate that day, Li’sar."
msgstr ""
"Pero en canto ao teu irmán... Non teño dúbida de que Asheviere inchou a "
"Eldred con adulacións e mentiras, pero foi a súa man, e só a súa man, a que "
"matou o vello rei. O teu irmán selou o seu propio destino aquel día, Lisar."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1044
msgid ""
"Save your breath. You’re not making this any easier. Let’s just do what "
"needs to be done."
msgstr ""
"Garda o alento. Non o vas poñer máis doado. Fagamos o que hai que facer."

#. [message]: speaker=Lisar
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1059
msgid "A powerful magic awakens in my hands. Behold the Sceptre of Fire!"
msgstr "Unha maxia poderosa esperta nas miñas mans. Velaquí o Cetro de Lume!"

#. [message]: id=$defector1.id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1174
msgid "Is that... the Sceptre of Fire?! Ye gods, it’s real!"
msgstr "É iso... o Cetro de Lume?! Oh, deuses, é real!"

#. [then]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1181
msgid "The legends are true! The true queen has come!"
msgstr "As lendas son certas! A verdadeira raíña chegou!"

#. [then]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1182
msgid "Spare me, madam, and I will pledge myself into your service!"
msgstr "Perdóame, señora, e xurarei servirte!"

#. [then]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1184
msgid "The legends are true! The true king has come!"
msgstr "As lendas son certas! O verdadeiro rei chegou!"

#. [then]
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1185
msgid "Spare me, sir, and I will pledge myself into your service!"
msgstr "Perdóame, señor, e xurarei servirte!"

#. [message]: id=$defector2.id
#. [message]: id=$defector1.id
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1203
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/smalltalk.cfg:1208
msgid "And I!"
msgstr "E eu!"

#. [dummy]: id=exacting
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:9
msgid "exacting"
msgstr "esixente"

#. [dummy]: id=exacting
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:10
msgid ""
"Li’sar has drilled her infantry to perfection. Though few in number, each of "
"her soldiers possesses skills not usually seen on others of their type."
msgstr ""
"Li’sar adestrou a súa infantaría á perfección. Aínda que poucos en número, "
"cada un dos seus soldados posúe habilidades que non se adoitan ver noutros "
"do seu tipo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:62
msgid ""
"I studied Li’sar back in the Aethenwood. Though her personal company is not "
"large in number, they are exactingly trained — each of them possesses one "
"ability not usually seen on others of their type."
msgstr ""
"Estudei a Li’sar alá no Bosque de Aethen. Aínda que a súa compañía persoal "
"non é numerosa, están adestrados con esixencia; cada un deles posúe unha "
"habilidade que non se adoita ver noutros do seu tipo."

#. [message]: speaker=Konrad {KONRAD_VARIATION mad}
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:77
msgid ""
"Look there: one of Li’sar’s personal company! I studied them back in the "
"Aethenwood. Though not large in number, they are exactingly trained — each "
"of them possesses one ability not usually seen on others of their type."
msgstr ""
"Mirade alí: un dos compañeiros persoais de Li’sar! Estudeinos no Bosque de "
"Aethen. Aínda que non son moitos en número, están adestrados con esixencia; "
"cada un deles posúe unha habilidade que non se adoita ver noutros do seu "
"tipo."

#. [dummy]: id=rejuvenate
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:92
msgid "rejuvenates"
msgstr "rexuvenece"

#. [dummy]: id=rejuvenate
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:93
msgid ""
"This unit will heal itself and adjacent allied units for 4 HP each turn. "
"This ability cannot cure poison, however, only delay its effect."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidade curará a si mesma e ás unidades aliadas adxacentes con 4 PV "
"cada turno. Esta habilidade non pode curar o veleno, senón só atrasar o seu "
"efecto."

#. [dummy]: id=smite
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:160
msgid "smite"
msgstr "ferir"

#. [dummy]: id=smite
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Each time this unit strikes a finishing blow, it deals 30 arcane damage to "
"adjacent enemies."
msgstr ""
"Cada vez que esta unidade dá un golpe final, inflixe 30 puntos de dano "
"arcano aos inimigos adxacentes."

#. [object]: id=sceptre_of_fire, type=fire, type=fire, type=fire, type=fire
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:197
msgid ""
"Forged by the dwarves of Knalga at the behest of King Haldric II, the magic "
"at the heart of this sceptre dates as far back as the mysterious Old "
"Continent. Among its many powers is the ability to hurl fireballs of great "
"size."
msgstr ""
"Forxado polos ananos de Knalga por orde do rei Haldric II, a maxia que se "
"agocha no corazón deste cetro remóntase ao misterioso Vello Continente. "
"Entre os seus moitos poderes está a capacidade de lanzar bólas de lume de "
"gran tamaño."

#. [object]: id=sceptre_of_fire, type=fire, type=fire, type=fire, type=fire
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:202
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:216
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:230
#: data/campaigns/Heir_To_The_Throne/utils/specials_and_abilities.cfg:244
msgid "sceptre of fire"
msgstr "cetro de lume"

